<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><gpx xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:groundspeak="http://www.groundspeak.com/cache/1/0/1" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" version="1.0" creator="Groundspeak, Inc.All Rights Reserved.http://www.groundspeak.com" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.topografix.com/GPX/1/0 http://www.topografix.com/GPX/1/0/gpx.xsd http://www.groundspeak.com/cache/1/0/1 http://www.groundspeak.com/cache/1/0/1/cache.xsd" xmlns="http://www.topografix.com/GPX/1/0"><name>Cache Listing Generated from Geocaching.com</name><desc>This is an individual cache generated from Geocaching.com</desc><email>contact@geocaching.com</email><url>http://www.geocaching.com</url><urlname>Geocaching - High Tech Treasure Hunting</urlname><time>2026-06-02T21:35:40.1117629Z</time><keywords>cache, geocache</keywords><wpt lat="60.108383" lon="19.899383"><time>2003-08-01T00:00:00</time><name>GCGW3M</name><desc>Aland by Estonian team MTNM, adopted by Annams</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCGW3M</url><urlname>Aland</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="91596" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Aland</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Estonian team MTNM, adopted by Annams</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="3917656">Annams</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Åland Islands</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>[EST] 1.08.03 peitsid 4 Eesti rattamatkajat ehk võistkond MTNM aarde Ahvenamaale ehk Alandile. [ENG] 4 Estonian hikers with bike hid a cache to Aland in 01.08.2003.
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The first geocache on the Aland Islands, placed 1st August 2003.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="UserSuppliedContent" style="text-align:left;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Since Feb 2016 adopted by user Loranga.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="UserSuppliedContent" style="text-align:left;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Since Jan 2019 adopted by user Annams.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>In a low place near a very high place.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364949942"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-02T13:43:09</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="27856066">st_ranger</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Nachdem das primäre Ziel der Reise, der Match Stash in Schweden gefunden war, waren noch weitere Ziele an der Reihe. Um auch mal alle Anrainer-Staaten der Ostsee besucht zu haben, fiel die Wahl auf die nahe gelegenen Åland-Inseln. Eine prima Entscheidung, denn hier gibt es auch gute Verstecke.
So kam ich auch zu diesem Cache GCGW3M Aland und konnte die Aufgabe erledigen. Vielen Dank an Estonian team MTNM, adopted by Annams für dieses Versteck.

Efter att resans huvudmål, Match Stash i Sverige, hade hittats var det dags för ytterligare mål. För att ha besökt alla länder som gränsar till Östersjön föll valet på de närbelägna Ålandöarna. Ett utmärkt val, eftersom det finns bra gömställen även här.
Så kom jag också till denna cache GCGW3M Aland och kunde slutföra uppgiften. Stort tack till Estonian team MTNM, adopted by Annams för detta gömställe.
Här var jag glad över att ha hittat burken till öns äldsta cache. Därefter njöt jag av utsikten från tornet i strålande väder.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1365010343"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-02T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4711882">ij_</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">tftc</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364827266"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T17:38:59</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="55417172">Släpvagn</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Bra gömd </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364791197"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T13:20:10</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4772667">jodeponken</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Kanske inte det stabilaste av torn, men finfin utsikt. Gott om små slemma fästingar här. Tftc</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362941961"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-23T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="9869635">birchtar</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Ute på tur med proppan. Är på Åland några dagar. Kul att få logga Ålands äldsta cache, blev min cache 8000. Fin utsikt från fågeltornet.
Tftc.  23 maj 2026 19:36</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="42.399917" lon="19.657717"><time>2007-08-08T00:00:00</time><name>GC17X8V</name><desc>Shqiperia Earthcache #1 - Former river-channel by Saman </desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC17X8V</url><urlname>Shqiperia Earthcache #1 - Former river-channel</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Earthcache</type><groundspeak:cache id="748120" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Shqiperia Earthcache #1 - Former river-channel</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Saman </groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="169532">Saman</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Earthcache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Not chosen</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>2.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Albania</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>&lt;b&gt;This earthcache will take you to the beautiful valley near the Boga village in georgeous Albanian Alps. You will find a very interesting object, which was created by water erosion in the former river-channel from the pudding stone.&lt;/b&gt;
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;i&gt;&lt;b&gt;Pudding stone&lt;/b&gt; is a conglomerate rock made up of a mixture of different, irregular sized grains and pebbles held together by a finer matrix, usually formed from quartz sand. The sedimentary rock is formed in river channels and may contain various minerals such as chromite, corundum, platinum, diamond, gold, sapphire, and zircon. Its name is said to derive from a resemblance to Christmas pudding.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Erosion&lt;/b&gt; is the detachment of earth material from the surface. Once detached, agents like water or wind transport the material to a new location where it is deposited. The most ubiquitous form of erosion is that done by water.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;The water erotion&lt;/b&gt; is the breakdown of solid rock into smaller particles and its removal by water.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;There are three classes of erosion by water:&lt;br /&gt;
(a) splash erosion occurs when raindrops strike bare soil, causing it to splash, as mud, to flow into spaces in the soil and to turn the upper layer of soil into a structureless, compacted mass that dries with a hard, largely impermeable crust;&lt;br /&gt;
(b) surface flow occurs when soil is removed with surface run-off during heavy rain&lt;br /&gt;
(c) channelised flow occurs when a flowing mixture of water and soil cuts a channel, which is then deepened by further scouring. A minor erosion channel is called a rill, a larger channel a gully.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;If you want to log this cache, you have to complete two tasks:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
1) how big is (approximately) the highest tower of the object?&lt;br /&gt;
2) take a picture of you in front of the object and upload the image to your log.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;There is a shop and pub in the village, and if you will kindly ask the friendly owner, you can sleep in your tent in his garden (experience from 2007). V roce 2007 jsme spali ve stanu na zahrade majitele mistniho obchodu a hospody, je mozne, ze vam to umozni v pripade potreby i ted, kdyz tak napiste nejake zkusenosti, jak to tam dnes vypada se sluzbama. Hezky vylet po krasne Albanii :)&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;center&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/cb6900b9-fb26-4180-96ea-ce2029944fa6.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/center&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1362794428"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-23T11:30:07</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3484410">5h</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Gevonden op onze Balkantrip.  Dank.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1361258247"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-16T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2852634">Rumtreiber67</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Auf kleiner Tour diesen schönen EC besucht und natürlich die Aufgabe gelöst und dem Owner zugeschickt. Vielen Dank und herzliche Grüße vom Rumtreiber aus Braunschweig, Deutschland.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1359750156"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-06T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="23708326">RalleMucke</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Auf unserer Fahrt von Albanien nach Montenegro hatten wir die Möglichkeit, auch diesen Cache zu besuchen. Das war sehr beeindruckend, wobei es immer total schwierig ist Gröẞenbeschreibungen vorzunehmen.
Die Antwort wurde an den Owner gesendet


Liebe Grüße an Saman, verbunden mit großem Dank für den Cache senden 

RalleMucke

