🇪🇹 Ethiopie</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1269380730"><groundspeak:date>2024-11-03T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2893186">Joskaranch</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Our first geocache in Ethiopia on an amazing trip through the Afar region. The volcano and Danakil Depression were the absolute highlight. TFTC!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="-52.1394" lon="-60.59615"><time>2007-11-14T00:00:00</time><name>GC17CXT</name><desc>Falkland Islands 2nd Albermarle Harbour by tacanman</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC17CXT</url><urlname>Falkland Islands 2nd Albermarle Harbour</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="733363" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Falkland Islands 2nd Albermarle Harbour</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>tacanman</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="456972">tacanman</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="0">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="56" inc="1">Medium hike (1 km–10 km)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="10" inc="1">Difficult climb</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="43" inc="1">Livestock nearby</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Falkland Islands</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Warning This cache is remote even by Falklands Standards.  Approach with care after first obtaining a weather forcast and infoming someone where you are going.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>This cache is located in the hills surrounding Albermarle Harbour.  It is the 2nd cache in the Falklands and the first on West Falkland.
Albermarle is one of the southern most places on the islands and commands fantastic scenery towards the coast.  This cache overlooks the harbour where it is possible to see Seals, Ducks, Geese and occasional penguins.  Fishing here is fantastic with large mullett available.
The cache is located just below the saddle hidden in a large clump of rocks.</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>In Rock Crevise</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1335751340"><groundspeak:date>2025-11-23T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6140848">hausche05</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Hier will ich schon immer mal hin, vielleicht klappt es ja irgendwann einmal.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1218004746"><groundspeak:date>2024-02-25T20:23:28</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="26379968">G14Classified</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">A glorious day today and although we had to get the ferry we thought we had enough time to get and boy was a good decision. TFTC. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1077385449"><groundspeak:date>2022-02-04T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3301615">Bob_Sharon</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Out for an early morning run from Alice.  A quick find and not been found for 4 years.  Everything good at the location and the cache is in the good condition.  TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="768477259"><groundspeak:date>2018-05-17T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4085211">landyliam</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">My first find on the Falklands with muggles Ian and Charlie after a hike down the hill (suppose its not really a 5 if you approach from above:-) ) a little snow at the top and lovely dry conditions made up for the cold (0 degrees) the silence at the GZ was deafening, I don’t think I’ve ever heard such quiet, or maybe my hearing has gone since the chopper ride! Cache is in excellent condition. TFTC.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="757272197"><groundspeak:date>2018-04-06T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="22855047">Geo_Voss</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Hola</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="62.0074" lon="-6.7628"><time>2005-02-05T00:00:00</time><name>GCMPFC</name><desc>Skansin by Matfus</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCMPFC</url><urlname>Skansin</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="206319" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Skansin</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Matfus</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="221425">Matfus</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="30" inc="1">Picnic tables nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="26" inc="1">Public transportation nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="38" inc="0">Campfires</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Faroe Islands</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Denne cache er placeret ved en gammel fæstning i Tórshavn. Den ligger tæt på færgehavn, og lufthavnsbussens holdeplads. This cache is placed by an old (small) fortress in Tórshavn. It is placed near the ferry, so it is fine to find, while waiting for the ferrys.
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;På en god sommerdag - DE FINDES!- kan der være mange mennesker i området.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Cachen er en klar plasticboks ca. 15x10x15 cm. Indeholder: FFC, logbog, blyant, &amp;quot;cachekort&amp;quot;, 2 balloner, en bil, en snurretop, perler, 2 færøske flag, TB Lunde. I foråret 2008 forsvandt cachen, men blev i juni 2008 genetableret af okvalle. Tak for det :-) I efteråret 2012 forsvandt cachen igen, og endnu en gang redede Okvalle situationen. Tak igen :) Først på sommeren 2014 forsvandt den så igen igen - Denne gang var det Holger_Danske der reddede os og lagde en ny cache. Tak for det. Her i august 2014 forsvandt den s¨for foreløbigt sidste gang - Afventer lige og ser hvad vi finder på ;/ Igen fik vi hjælp fra en geocaher vi ikke kendte i forvejen. Tak til zweirad for at genplacere cachen. Thanks to zweirad for replacing the cache :) Igen var den forsvundet . Tak til Roddaren for at erstatte den. &lt;strong&gt;Igen i 2022 forsvandt den, og denne gang var det en lokal gammel kollega der redede den, tak til johnmilling.&lt;/strong&gt; Dette er den næstældste cache på Færøerne og den ældste aktive - og dog, for her kommer en lille hemmelighed: Foggy Sheeptrack er den første cache placeret på Færøerne, og selv om den er arkiveret kan den faktisk stadig findes. Den blev placeret af nogle helt nystartede tyske geocachere, Barbara og Eberhard Giese - som desværre trods deres store erfaring med at finde EN cache ikke fik noteret koordinaterne helt rigtigt :( De har faktisk ikke geocachet siden..... I 2005 fandt vi den og fik lagt en ny cache på positionen, som også blev opdateret på GC. Cachen kan findes her: https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCG9D1_foggy-sheeptrack Foggy Sheeptrack er som sådan forældreløs - men vi føler lidt det er vores fjerne nevø, så pas godt på den ;)&lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Ca. 0,5 m over jorden, bag en løs sten
Aprox. 0,5 m over the ground, behind a loose stone</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364962096"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-02T13:31:43</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="14866753">Marvanw</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Easy find!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364701008"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-31T19:59:57</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="55526636">turiind</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Preatty easy its fun😋</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364698589"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-31T19:51:54</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="55526635">djurhuus17</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Very easy and great find:) </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364224264"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T19:40:43</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5237906">Luna Express</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Easy first find in the Faroe Islands! Cache and log are in good shape. Thanks for the lovely views! </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364048539"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-28T17:29:32</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2429796">Jeandix</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">After we went to Nølsoy for the day we ended this day with finding this geocache. Nice to find such an oldie on a neat place. 

MPLC </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="-17.76556666666667" lon="177.20645"><time>2002-07-20T00:00:00</time><name>GC7590</name><desc>Malololailai by Spudgun &amp; Pam</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC7590</url><urlname>Malololailai</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="30096" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Malololailai</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Spudgun &amp; Pam</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="38290">spudgun2020</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="42" inc="1">Needs maintenance</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Fiji</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>A Cache in Paradise</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>Malololailai is a small island in the Mamanuca group. You can get to it by plane (10 mins) or ferry (40 mins).

You can walk to the cache in less than an hour from the airfield or marina but allow 3hrs return. The snorkling at this spot is spectacular so pack a lunch and take your swimwear.

http://www.musketcovefiji.com/

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>The cache is concealed on a very large rock under a bush</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364671176"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-28T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8405181">kimbathelion</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Out on a snorkeling trip. Gorgeous spot.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1359401868"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-06T09:35:42</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="18925548">Wandering_Wagners</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">What a gorgeous day!!! The water was so incredibly clear! Thank you!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1345181709"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-16T17:40:22</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="53127168">SnipsOrElse</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We forgot a pen but hopefully this photo my mum took of my holding the log is enough! 

We asked the lovely man from our resort to take us here! Got a little lost along the way (mum was navigating 😂) 

Also had fun sea-glass hunting here and we saw an eel which my brother was very pleased with! 

TFTC! 💖🇦🇺🦘</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1345707639"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-15T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2195479">Snips and Co</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thanks, Spudgun &amp; Pam, for the cache and the adventure.

I use the excuse of snorkelling on the outer reef to get the kids in the speedboat, then I show our captain where I really want to go. He asks me to navigate (bad idea), and of course, we take the ‘scenic route’. 

Once there, our captain became my caching partner, eager to find what I was looking for. He is surprised. I tell him it’s been here since 2002, and as he is from a local village, he is shocked, “It’s been here since I was three”, he says incredulously. Fun, fun.

Our joy is slightly marred by the lack of a pen until we burn some wood to make a charcoal writing implement. Seriously, only I would go all this way without a pen. Once all was done, we picked up the rubbish on this tiny beach and took the direct route to the outer reef for that well-deserved snorkel.

*On a family mini break (is one week a mini break? It feels like it) in Fiji to slow down, soak up the sun, and find some remote caches. We are staying at Castaway Island, enjoying doing very little in the balmy weather. Our activities include snorkelling, a game or two of Bananagram (well, probably more accurately described as a ferociously fought competition for the title of Big Banana), and relaxing in hammocks.*</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1343329738"><groundspeak:date>2026-01-30T20:45:25</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="51470980">skilleranton123</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thanks for hidding it </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="60.367983" lon="25.136433"><time>2000-09-30T00:00:00</time><name>GC72</name><desc>Sun Gear by Kalle Reunanen</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC72</url><urlname>Sun Gear</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="114" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Sun Gear</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Kalle Reunanen</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="257">kalle</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="0">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Finland</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Uusimaa</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Location: About 4 km south of Kerava quite near Keinukallio Ski centre.&lt;br /&gt;
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;h1&gt;Presumably the first stash in Finland !&lt;/H1&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks to SlashDot that I found this very interesting site / sport.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The stash is located under the root of a fallen tree in woods bit over 1 km south from Keinukallio ski centre. It should be quite easy (2/2) to find with picture clues and co-ordinates. There is path passing about 50 m from the stash. Stash is marked with blue paper ribbon attached in nearby small tree. See pictures for more clues.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Stash contains:&lt;br /&gt;
* Letter in Finnish and English&lt;br /&gt;
* Sunglasses&lt;br /&gt;
* 1 key ring&lt;br /&gt;
* 1 bag of xylitol chewing gum&lt;br /&gt;
* 1 box of freshing mints&lt;br /&gt;
* Logbook and pen&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Position information should be very good. My Garmin III+ claims averaged position accuracy to be 3.2m ( see photo below). I would be happy to hear from you if you find the stash.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Stash is now easy to access but when the snow comes, I would guess that it will be very difficult to access during January-March depending how much snow there will be on the top of the cliff I put the stash.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Happy Hunting.&lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1365031296"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-02T22:58:30</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="7576543">Dunaghiri</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found while on a business trip in Finland.
After visiting our customers in Seinäjoki and Ruovesi, we made a detour back to Helsinki via this old cache

Bedankt!
