S und U von
Die c-SaU Bande 👩🏼‍🤝‍👨🏻</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360098293"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-09T20:14:50</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="18168712">misssab</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">[Message et photo envoyés à l'owner]
Depart de Papeete pour un tour de Tahiti la grande île,  on profite de faire un crochet  sur la route pour valider cette virtuelle qui nous permet de découvrir ce coin. Nous n'aurons malheureusement pas le temps de visiter mais le jardin est accessible et je profite pour demander tout de même la validation avec une belle pièce de collection historique visible et qu'on a trouvé tres bien conservée. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1359643425"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-07T08:50:20</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="300257">nordjas</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Driving around the island today and made a stop, TFTC!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1353673570"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="24153335">lometogo</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This morning we went out snorkling, so now its time for some geocaching.
We waited for the bus about 30 min and when arriving it was quit full, but we managed to get space for standing - spoke to others whom didnt get on the earlier one as it was FULL. After about 30 min we got of at the petrol station and walked down to the museum, what a nice surprise. Beautiful building and really nice objects inside. On the way back we stopped at the coordinates and took a picture too.
Thank you for keeping this oldie a live.
Greetiings from 🇲🇾🇩🇰</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1351215606"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-25T17:01:39</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3346571">Roller57</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Wonderful informative location. Learned a lot about Polynisia. TFTC!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="42.4679166666667" lon="44.4873333333333"><time>2006-03-27T00:00:00</time><name>GCV3AH</name><desc>Georgia on my mind by GPearl</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCV3AH</url><urlname>Georgia on my mind</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="366656" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Georgia on my mind</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>GPearl</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="162314">GPearl</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Georgia</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Georgia's first geocache! Hidden at the skiing-resort and
heliski-base of Gudauri in the Caucasus.
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>     &lt;div align="center"&gt;&lt;img src=
     "http://img.groundspeak.com/cache/8aefee5e-10cd-46ce-b34c-6d3df4f623c9.jpg"&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Georgia's first geocache was placed by an Austrian team while
doing heliskiing in the area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The cache - a small Tupper box with a blue lid - is hidden at
2110m at the foot of a big rock, which is slightly overhanging,
hence protecting the cache from the elements. The rock is some
metres to the east of the first ski lift in-between the pylons no.
9 and 10 but cannot be seen from the lift.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please close and hide the cache well again!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Gaumardjos!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size="1"&gt;Small note on cache maintenance: The Austrian
heli-guides who spend 9 weeks each year at Gudauri promised me to
look after the cache.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;div align="center"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Bitte den Cache wieder sorgfältig
verstecken!&lt;/b&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;font color="#8F8F8F"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Please hide the cache thoroughly
again!&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;div align="center"&gt;&lt;a href=
"http://www.keenpeople.com/geocaching/cacherate/articol.php?id=GCV3AH"
   target="_blank"&gt;&lt;img src=
   "http://www.keenpeople.com/components/counter2.php3?ID=GCV3AH&amp;amp;bgcol=FFFFFF&amp;amp;fgcol=000000"
     border="0"&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Click To Rate This Cache&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1362696131"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-22T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6656479">Topta</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Dneska jsme s Bary10, xai a tomrachunek vyrazili na sever Gruzie až téměř k ruským hranicím.
Podařilo se nám odlovit i tuto kešku.
Počasí nakonec nebylo tak špatné, občas pršelo a občas i sluníčko vysvitlo. Cesta na sever nám zabrala téměř 4 hodiny, ty kolony tady jsou neuvěřitelné.

Díky za kešku.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362618751"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-22T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8284991">tomrachunek</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Odloveno během návštěvy Gruzie. Více později</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363434893"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-18T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2063573">Die drei Landeier</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We spent 10 days traveling through beautiful Georgia and had the opportunity to get to know the country and its people. Whenever a geocache was along our route, we visited it. Many thanks to the owners for hiding them. 
Of course, we also visited the oldest cache in Georgia.

Danke fürs verstecken sagen

Die drei Landeier       </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362597803"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-13T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="22896733">montik1</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Nejstarší kešku jsem musela ukecat mudly, aby mi počkali ji odlovit.  Odlov byl z kopve do kopce, ale nakonec se povedl. Na silnici přes Kavkaz do Ruska byl provoz, co nikdo nechce. My ale jedeme naštěstí naopak zpět do Tbilisi, takže relativně frčíme.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364949820"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-12T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="790955">ollilein</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">While traveling through the Caucasus with sozioma, AmoebeST and Keen Barete, we came across this cache. 😊

Our journey through Georgia, Armenia and Azerbaijan was full of amazing landscapes, friendly people, cultural highlights and plenty of adventures. 🏔️🌄🚙 This cache was another nice stop along the way and a great reason to explore the area a little more. 😎

Thanks for placing and maintaining the cache! 👍 TFTC! 😊
Greetings,
ollilein</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="50.20635" lon="7.3335"><time>2001-02-11T00:00:00</time><name>GC26C</name><desc>Medieval View by The Rhine Knight</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC26C</url><urlname>Medieval View</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="620" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Medieval View</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>The Rhine Knight</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="2937">RhineKnight</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="42" inc="1">Needs maintenance</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Germany</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Rheinland-Pfalz</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>For the most rewarding hike start off at a parking lot (N50-12.098 E07-21.326), from there its a pleasant and rewarding 2km or so walk
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>The stash is near the Elz Castle, one of the most beautiful German medieval buildings. It's worth a visit any time. The area around the castle lends itself for extensive hikes etc. Please bear in mind the castle is open to visitors only from March 31 to October 31.
&lt;p&gt;The stash container is a RubberMaid type box, which is inside a blue plastic bag.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The cache is buried under some rocks and covered with moss but is not too difficult to find. Since this area attracts a lot of visitors please make sure to properly cover the stash after your visit. Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Recently (Apr.2017) I've been asked to change the Terrain Rating from 1.5 up to 3 to accommodate the mollycoddled German geocacher. I think 2.5 should suffice.&lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364873991"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T20:49:19</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="49846465">MikroLei</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Heute waren wir bei der Burg Eltz und haben viele Geocaches gesucht. 🏰😃

Die Waldgeister fanden wir besonders cool. 🌲👻 Außerdem durften wir die Burg von innen anschauen und haben viel Spannendes gelernt.

Am Ende hatten wir 17 Geocaches und 2 Adventure Labs gefunden. 💚🦎

Und das Beste: Trotz fast 20.000 Schritten haben wir alles geschafft! 💪😊🍀🦎</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364877877"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T15:01:39</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="9232751">Frau_KreiBi</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">10222

Der erste Urlaub mit dem Dachzelt…
Heute ging es den Moselsteig entlang zur Burg Eltz. 
Der älteste Cache Deutschlands steht nun auch in meiner Liste. 

Herzliche Grüße und vielen Dank für diesen Cache
sagt Frau_KreiBi 🙋🏼 mit Cachedog Boneco 🐕 aus Kulmbach in Oberfranken </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364830724"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T12:53:02</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="19564183">Leichtis</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">17 Geocaches und 2 Adventure Labs rund um die Burg Eltz standen heute auf unserem Programm. 😃🏰
Natürlich durfte dabei auch der älteste aktive Geocache Deutschlands nicht fehlen. 💚
Ein echtes Highlight war die Führung durch die Burg Eltz. Dabei konnten wir einen spannenden Blick in die Geschichte der Burg werfen und verstehen, warum sie zu den schönsten Burgen Deutschlands zählt. 🏰✨
Besonders begeistert haben uns außerdem die liebevoll gestalteten Waldgeister-Caches. 🌲👻 Die kreativen Figuren und die aufwendige Gestaltung zeigen, wie viel Herzblut hier investiert wurde. Solche Dosen bleiben einfach in Erinnerung.
Unterwegs konnten wir auch einige Caches entlang des Traumpfads einsammeln. Die Kombination aus tollen Wegen, dichter Natur, beeindruckenden Ausblicken und schönen Verstecken hat den Tag zu einem echten Erlebnis gemacht. 🌳🥾
Was wir anfangs etwas unterschätzt haben: Meine Uhr zeigte am Ende fast 20.000 Schritte an. 😱🫣 Die letzten Kilometer waren dann doch ein harter Ritt, besonders für die Kinder. Aber sie haben tapfer durchgehalten und alle geplanten Ziele mit erreicht. 💪😊
Am Ende standen 17 Geocaches, 2 Adventure Labs, jede Menge neue Eindrücke, viele schöne Erinnerungen und einige zusätzliche Smileys auf der Karte. 😃🦎
Vielen Dank an alle Owner fürs Legen und Pflegen der Caches und für diesen abwechslungsreichen Tag rund um die Burg Eltz! 🍀💚🦎</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364924417"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4836446">steff0070</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Ein Besuch der Burg Eltz stand schon lange auf der ToDo-Liste von Frau steff und in dem diesjährigen Pfingsturlaub hat es eeennndddlich geklappt. Vom angegebenen Parkplatz machten wir uns auf den Weg und erst nach der letzten Wegbiegung konnten wir dieses beeindruckende Bauwerk erblicken. Natürlich wollten wir die Burg von innen besichtigen und wir hatten das Glück an eine der ersten Führungen des Tages teilnehmen zu dürfen - sehr informativ und die Burg einfach ein Traum. Im Anschluß haben wir dann noch den ältesten aktiven Geocache in Deutschland besucht. Das Döschen hat sich einen wirklich schönen Ort ausgesucht.

Danke für den Oldie sagen steff0070</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364403995"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2562804">Muller&amp;Thurgau</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">A je to tady. Dlouho plánovaná velká expedice v sestavě happy.ov, Lo36, Müller&amp;Thurgau a taxoft vyrazila napříč Evropou. A cestou jsme navštívili i tuto krabičku.
Díky za keš. 

Die lange geplante große Expedition mit happy.ov, Lo36, Müller&amp;Thurgau und taxoft startete quer durch Europa. Unterwegs besuchten wir diesen Cache.
Vielen Dank für den Cache!

The long-planned big expedition with happy.ov, Lo36, Müller&amp;Thurgau and taxoft set off across Europe. On the way we visited this cache.
Thanks for the cache.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="6.081233" lon="0.050083"><time>2003-11-09T00:00:00</time><name>GCH6Z7</name><desc>Baboon Country by Ghana Mountaineers</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCH6Z7</url><urlname>Baboon Country</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="102030" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Baboon Country</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Ghana Mountaineers</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="156161">bushratgh</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>3</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>4.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Ghana</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Find the cross, look to your right. And please be careful on the last meters .....</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>Park your car at N 06 05.513 / E 000 03.186. The first part is obvious from there.

06/11/2011

Have replaced the cache six weeks ago. It is now a tupperware box in a plastic bag. In the box is the log book.

Good luck.</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1346533856"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-27T15:17:48</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6451067">GëoRebel</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">tftc</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1176381046"><groundspeak:date>2023-06-24T19:46:07</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="46216596">Radvilas1</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">h</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1155013404"><groundspeak:date>2023-03-24T17:56:21</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="44901309">thehoppster24</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Nice</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1137566025"><groundspeak:date>2022-11-13T18:03:29</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="43732833">Dergeo_cacher</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Top</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="783097664"><groundspeak:date>2018-07-12T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="23716497">MajorobaTeam</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">&gt; Vielen Dank an den Owner für das Legen und Pflegen von diesem Cache!

[:)] 
**Trade In:** niets ✓
**Trade Uit:** niets ✓
Thanks for the cache.
&gt; Majoroba Team</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="36.1341" lon="-5.348517"><time>2002-10-28T00:00:00</time><name>GCA227</name><desc>1st Gibraltar by mafra</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCA227</url><urlname>1st Gibraltar</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="41511" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>1st Gibraltar</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>mafra</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="68108">mafra</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="42" inc="1">Needs maintenance</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Gibraltar</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>2. Edition</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>On the Gibraltar rock</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364588928"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-31T14:57:21</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5848977">Criks</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Hard walk up and down…
TFTC
Criks</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364146025"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T12:17:26</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8439955">Drdg</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thanks! </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363596222"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-15T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="10106772">jirca76</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">&gt;TFTC

------

We visited this place during our holiday. Thank you for showing a very nice place.
Greetings from CZ.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1361225824"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-14T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="18083834">FrauBrömmel</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Today GrafZahl66 and I walked the nature park and of course we also found some caches. Thank you for the cache.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1361111478"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-14T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1190348">ostmacht</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Unser diesjähriger Ausflug als Team SBC09 führte uns nach Gibraltar.  Dabei besuchten wir auch diesen Ort. 

Danke und viele Grüße aus Deutschland sagt ostmacht</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="37.058083" lon="25.510083"><time>2001-08-18T00:00:00</time><name>GC1B5B</name><desc>Agia Irene by J. Kotsos and T. Kotsos</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC1B5B</url><urlname>Agia Irene</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="7003" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Agia Irene</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>J. Kotsos and T. Kotsos</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="22457">jkotsos</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Greece</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>The first Cache in Greece! On the Aegean Island of Naxos on the road just outside Apiranthos (about 25km from Chora). Hang on... these coordinates are not possible!! Or are they. BACK IN ITS PLACE AS OF 16/8/2021!
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>Find the little Saint! The cache is OUTSIDE the church. It is in line with the roof in the SE corner. You will find a tupper-ware container covered by several stones. This cache was placed by myself and Tania Kotsos. Please hide the cache properly once you have found it. Also please KEEP OFF the roof of the church. Enjoy the view! Don't forget to see Apiranthos ... a magic village.
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Dont confuse St Irene with St John.... Find the steps and go down the side of the cliff....</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364977739"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-02T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8414048">BiSiLu</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Wir verbringen 14 Tage in Athen, Syros, Naxos und Milos. Und selbstverständlich werden wir immer wieder mal auch einige Caches loggen. Wir danken allen Ownern fürs Auslegen und senden herzliche Grüsse, BiSiLu😎 aus 🇨🇭

Heute besuchten wir die wunderschönen Bergdörfer Aperathos und Filoti. Es war schlicht traumhaft. Dieser Cache bietet eine sensationelle Aussicht! Dass das Logbuch etwas nass ist, ist in Anbetracht des Alters dieses Caches eine Nebensächlichkeit 😉. Erster Cache von Griechenland - wow!!!! 😀
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364558484"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-31T14:05:49</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="40203138">finding_janka</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">A day trip with the car across the island of Naxos. 
Besides exploring the island I also wanted to see if I can find the oldest cache in Greece 🇬🇷 after visiting 2 mountain villages the location was on my way to Aperathos. I found the little church and also the hiding spot of the tupper container! Very happy to have a 25 year old cache in my hands! 😇😃

Thanks a lot for hiding and maintaining the cache over all the years. ✨</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364287256"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="16637518">geomike49</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found it.  More to follow.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362533285"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-21T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="13272924">gubo66</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Kalimera! 🇬🇷

​As part of our 14-day island hopping trip through Greece, we were lucky enough to spend 4 wonderful days here as well. We explored the area in glorious sunshine. The paths were sporty and steep (we certainly could skip the gym!), and there were plenty of interesting sights to take in, but of course, our caching senses stayed sharp. And lo and behold: found and successfully logged! 📝

​A big thank you to the owner for hiding this cache in such a great location.

​Warm regards from the Münsterland (Germany) from gubo66! 🙌



Discover: CEBKVZ
                  CETFBC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1344526123"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-07T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="7605948">Uli001</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Hallo J. Kotsos and T. Kotsos

dieses Jahr verschlug es mich mit meinem Kind 2 Y007 für eine Woche nach Grichenland. Von Berlin ging es nach dem Chaos mit Blitzeis über Athen nach Naxos zum ältesten Cache von Grichenland. Naxos ist eine schöne kleine Inselwelt mit versteckten Badebuchten. Eine nutzten wir um uns Wasser zu springen. Die einheimischen belächelt uns dafür. Hej, 21 Grad sind genügend zum Baden. Ok, dass Wasser hatte nur 5cm aber angenehm war es trotzdem. 

Nach drei Tagen ging es zurück nach Athen um die Stadt unsicher zu machen. Hier verbrachten wir ebenfalls drei Tage und besichtigen die üblichen Stationen. Anschließend ging es zurück nach Berlin. 

Thanks to the CO for your Cache and showing us this place
Greetings from Germany/Sachsen/Leipzig
Uli</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="76.5756166666667" lon="-67.9115"><time>2002-08-11T00:00:00</time><name>GC8074</name><desc>El Conquistador's Treasure by Viperwolf1</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC8074</url><urlname>El Conquistador's Treasure</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="32884" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>El Conquistador's Treasure</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Viperwolf1</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="28956">Viperwolf1</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>4</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>4.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Greenland</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Greenland's first cache. The cache is located on top a moraine just south of the end of the Harald Moltke Glacier near Thule Air Base.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>Bring small items to trade because of the small box. Do not hike in this area alone. Plan your trip ahead and let a responsible person know when you should be back. This is a long, strenuous hike and chance of injury is high.
This cache is best accessed from the road leading East, just past Storm Shelter 11 at N76 33.6804 / W68 16.0086. Take the dirt road all the way to the end near the ice cap at N76 32.5740 / W68 6.1128. From there travel on foot in a NW direction across very rocky terrain for about 2.8 miles. Once you reach N76 34.2102 / W67 58.3056, you will have a terrific view of the Wolstenholme Fjord and the glacier. The descent down the mountain toward the glacier is very steep, nearly 45 degrees with about a 1400 foot elevation drop. Be extremely cautious of loose rocks. Once at the foot of the mountain, climb up the moraine adjacent to the glacier. You will find a rock cairn with the cache inside.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;font color="red"&gt;
&lt;small&gt;Admin note: cache placed on vacation, geocacher unaware of prohibition against placing caches that can't be maintained. There are no local geocachers in this area at this time. If there is one later who could adopt the cache it would be appreciated. If the cache is found to be in poor condition by a finder please remove it and ask the cache owner to archive it. Thanks. &lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
Tahu Nuva - The Nordic &amp; Baltic Countries Cache Reviewer&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/font&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Bring a camera for some incredible pictures of icebergs calving from the glacier.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1250474173"><groundspeak:date>2024-08-02T13:56:15</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4419499">Team Lillie</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">O</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1179380857"><groundspeak:date>2023-07-08T19:46:39</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="46393467">aghahw</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">A</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1156679580"><groundspeak:date>2023-04-03T10:32:06</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="40303538">irissarsfield</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found it </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1103644029"><groundspeak:date>2022-06-12T21:04:53</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="41313475">scottiec123</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We have a good time to do with you guys too much and I will miss it you guys will get a great weekend love </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="974243408"><groundspeak:date>2020-10-26T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="29885668">17rabbits21</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">More one💪</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="12.096133" lon="-61.696783"><time>2003-07-23T00:00:00</time><name>GCGGQX</name><desc>What a Hole by Ryan Colley</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCGGQX</url><urlname>What a Hole</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Virtual Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="81653" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>What a Hole</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Ryan Colley</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="23889">geekyink</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Virtual Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Virtual</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Grenada</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>This is a virtual cache of the beautiful volcano lake on the Island of Grenada.
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>This is a virtual cache of one of the most beautiful sights on the Island of Grenada. The coordinates are for the "wood structure with the best view!". If you have a picture from your visit, feel free to upload it!
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1361508480"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-16T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2355922">pheenyx</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Nice lake, but no swimming 🤔</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1359349616"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-05T12:15:27</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1397372">The Gator Bait Four</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We started our daily adventure here. Came out to the lake and took a picture. Hid up the hills looking for the monkeys. But did not find them. Beautiful rainforest area. Thanks.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1359211449"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-15T08:52:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="594365">Barbie&amp;Bruettler</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Auf unserer 4-wöchigen Reise von der Karibik über Mittelamerika ins Mittelmeer auf der "Mein Schiff 1" haben wir 15 Länder bereist und natürlich auch in jedem Land zumindest einen Cache gefunden.

During our 4-week trip from the Caribbean via Central America to the Mediterranean on the "Mein Schiff 1" we visited 15 countries and of course found at least one cache in every country.

On the way to our hike to the jungle we stopped here. 
Thanks for showing this amazing place!

Greetings from Germany, 
Barbie&amp;Bruettler
Thanks to geekyink

*13141*</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1354942446"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-12T17:44:51</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2063565">nosdos89</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We drove across the island today and, of course, had to stop at this crater lake. It rained quite a bit but we managed to use the rain-free period.

Thanks for placing this Virtual here.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362103291"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-08T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4816482">8-Rollen</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">With Freddylog on a cruise trip - we visited the caribbean islands.
Today we are on a Walk through the rainforest of Grenada.
At the visitor Center of the national park we visited the crater.
Nice view.
Thanks for the VC.
8-Rollen</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="16.244033" lon="-61.175117"><time>2005-11-06T00:00:00</time><name>GCR847</name><desc>Castle cache by pgremion</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCR847</url><urlname>Castle cache</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="311683" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Castle cache</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>pgremion</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="490867">pg971</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="0">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="0">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="0">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="14" inc="0">Recommended at night</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="30" inc="1">Picnic tables nearby</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Guadeloupe</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>La vue sur la Désirade et la croix du morne Pavillon est agréable.
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>Croix de la Pointe des Châteaux Monument - Saint-François Particulièrement visité, le bélvédère du Morne Pavillon, arbore fièrement sa croix. On accède à la croix depuis le parking situé au pied du morne Petite saline. Un sentier escarpé serpentant au travers de plantes arbustives aux longues racines, aux feuilles épaisses et vernissées conduit à la croix. 10 m de haut pour un poids de 9 tonnes, elle fut érigée en célébration du centenaire du diocèse à l’initiative du curé de Saint-François, le père Jean-Baptiste de Lahondèses et de l’évêque de Guadeloupe, Monseigneur Gay (1946). 

Une nouvelle croix a été placée en 2002. Tout près sont disposées deux tables d’orientation. Très beau point de vue. Dans l’axe de la Pointe des Colibris, le plateau dyssimétrique et tabulaire de La Désirade, plus au sud, les îles de Petite Terre. 
Vers le nord-est on découvre la succession de paysages jusqu’aux plateaux de l’est Grande Terre et en bas, l’anse des Châteaux et sa mer agitée, réputée dangereuse pour ses courants. 

Source de l'information: https://fr.guadeloupe-tourisme.com/28/croix-de-la-pointe-des-chateaux-saintfrancois/ Cross of the Pointe des Châteaux Monument - 

Saint-François particularly visited, the belvedere of the Morne Pavillon, proudly displays its cross. 
You reach the cross from the parking lot at the foot of the dreary Petite Saline. A steep path winding through shrubby plants with long roots, thick and glazed leaves leads to the cross. 10 m high for a weight of 9 tons, it was erected as a celebration of the centenary of the diocese on the initiative of the parish priest of St. Francis, Father Jean-Baptiste de Lahondèses and the Bishop of Guadeloupe, Monsignor Gay (1946 ). 
A new cross was placed in 2002. Nearby are two orientation tables. Very nice view. In the axis of the Pointe des Colibris, the dyssimetric and tabular plateau of La Désirade, further south, the islands of Petite Terre. Towards the northeast we discover the succession of landscapes to the plateaux of the east Grande Terre and below, the cove of the castles and its agitated sea, known as dangerous for its currents. 

Source of information: https://fr.guadeloupe-tourisme.com/28/croix-de-la-pointe-des-chateaux-saintfrancois/ 


</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Au pied d'un petit buisson, cachée sous des pierres.

At the foot of a small bush, hidden under stones.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1362144414"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-19T10:59:48</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3737840">coca57</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Trouvée à 10h57.
Merci pour ces magnifiques paysages.
Ça nous change complètement de la Moselle. Mais vive Kanfen. 
Quel beau département 
Mplc</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362060830"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-18T19:56:27</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2758778">RetiredGuy</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I did a day trip over from Saint Martin to get to this oldie. What a fun short hike to this and the cross. Favorite point!

Oldest cache in country #100!
www.RetiredGuy.com</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1359336888"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-05T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="14838090">Arralla</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Quelle vue et le vent fait du bien. Dépôt de tb</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1358982417"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-02T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4662839">CaMap</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">An der Pointe des Chateaux haben Fischibo und ich auf dem bisher höchsten Korallenriff gestanden. Hier einen Cache zu finden, war mir ein besonderes Anliegen.
TFTC.


À la Pointe des Châteaux, Fischibo et moi nous sommes tenus sur ce qui était, jusqu'alors, le plus haut récif corallien que nous ayons jamais vu. Trouver une géocache à cet endroit était particulièrement important pour moi.
MPLC.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1355760702"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-18T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8116474">sylmas</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Trouvée entre amis lors d'une belle journée rando. MPLC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="13.534967" lon="144.802733"><time>2002-01-26T00:00:00</time><name>GC357C</name><desc>Two Lovers Point by MNMartian (adopted by VeteranTributes)</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC357C</url><urlname>Two Lovers Point</urlname><sym>Geocache Found</sym><type>Geocache|Virtual Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="13692" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Two Lovers Point</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>MNMartian (adopted by VeteranTributes)</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="8897214">VeteranTributes</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Virtual Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Virtual</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="1">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="0">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="2" inc="1">Access/parking fee</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="52" inc="0">Night cache</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="14" inc="0">Recommended at night</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="64" inc="0">Tree climbing required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="10" inc="0">Difficult climb</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="17" inc="0">Poisonous plants</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Guam</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Two Lovers Point is located down a side road off Marine Drive across from the Micronesia Mall. Parking is available at no charge as are the main areas of the park, although to enter the lookout area of the park there is a $3 admission fee.
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;The Legend of Two Lovers Point tells of two young lovers who, forbidden from being together in life, leaped to their deaths from the cliffside so they could be together in eternity.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Guam is a tropical island with many things to do and see. You&amp;#39;ll either find you&amp;#39;re here because of the military (which as a reservist is how I made it here) or you just decided to come for a vacation. Either way - get out and enjoy the island and all it has to offer, like scuba diving and snorkling the beautiful coral reefs (please use the buddy-system), shopping at the duty free stores at the Micronesia Mall or the Guam Premium Outlet (GPO), or going on a Boonie Stomp (hiking trip) to many interesting places on the island like caves, historic battlefields and hidden waterfalls. Don&amp;#39;t forget to head on down to the Chamorro Village on Wednesday nights (which is the best time to go because they also have crafters selling their goods) and try the local food!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color:#c0392b;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Note: On May 24, 2023, Typhoon Mawar damaged the Two Lovers Statue at Two Lovers Point. It is currently being repaired and will go back on display at a future date. Until that time, a photo taken with yourself or your group anywhere on the grounds with Two Lovers Point in the background will be your logging task.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364911830"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T09:58:02</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5135925">ZacharyKZH</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">3-10

Well, it would be strange if I came all the way to Guam and not visit one of her iconic landmarks. So, here I am. I got here just as the gates opened, so, there were no crowds — just a few other early (love?)birds. 

Walked around, drank in the view, took a few photos and that’s that. It’s a shame the famous sculpture has probably been brought down again by another Typhoon — they really can’t catch a break, huh? Anyway, thanks for the virtual cache!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1359674831"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-08T11:24:25</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="47846063">Alquaiel</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">What a Great place to visit!!!  </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1356377852"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-21T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="44672992">mendiGUAM65</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Visited Two Lovers’ Point a week after Sinlaku’s landfall in the Marianas.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1354086202"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-09T17:27:43</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="54551143">jaecabrera11</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">TFTC!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1351500202"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-27T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6696085">LuckyL10n</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">#27859: Day 4 of the Geocaching Without Borders (or GWB as we will be signing logs on this visit) Asia Mission. Our team comprises myself (LuckyL10n), Sol de lune, McLookers, gmj3191, PamJ and Earthbound Chief.  After arriving in Guam late last night, we set off on our first mission of the visit this morning.  Arrived at GZ and after enjoying the great views and grabbing a snap or two, an earthcache and a DNF on a nearby trad, we were on our way again.  TFTC VeteranTributes [:)]</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="576363093"><groundspeak:date>2016-02-27T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2089726">travelingGeek</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found on my birthday during an extended layover on the way home from Macau.  Very pretty sure and well worthy the entry fee to go up top.  It was early and I had the place to myself. I'll post a cool rainbow pic when I get home. 

Thanks for the hide!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="17.227167" lon="-89.62615"><time>2001-11-27T00:00:00</time><name>GC2A86</name><desc>Hot Jungle (Tikal) by buda</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC2A86</url><urlname>Hot Jungle (Tikal)</urlname><sym>Geocache Found</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="10886" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Hot Jungle (Tikal)</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>buda</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="27716">buda</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="0">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="2" inc="1">Access/parking fee</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="56" inc="1">Medium hike (1 km–10 km)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="27" inc="0">Drinking water nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Guatemala</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Placed in 2001 and the first physical physical cache in the country! Going to Guatemala, bring your GPS. This was the first one in Guatemala, but not the last I hope. You get to see some of the most impressive Maya-sites if you take this cache. There might be a small entrance fee.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:24px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;(Flores / Tikal)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
This cache was placed in the stone age of geocaching and well before the rule of vacation/maintained caches. &lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
HELPING out would render a gold star, a thought in the GC-heaven, a mention and a cold beer in Sweden if you ever go hunting there! MANY thanks in advance /buda&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;em&gt;&lt;u&gt;Original listing:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/em&gt; &amp;quot;This is our first cache (and also the first physical one in the country) in Guatemala. Visiting the beautiful city of Flores is a dream. You will probably make a trip to the &amp;quot;ruins&amp;quot; one of your days here? Bring your GPS then and take the canopy tour on your own :)&lt;br /&gt;
For nice lodging in Flores, try the upper new rooms at the Villa De Lago, a bargain for 150 Q with TV, air-con and nice view of the lake (2001).&lt;br /&gt;
We had too little time to spend here, sad to say, we “must” move on to Belize tomorrow and then in a couple of weeks go back to Sweden, Europe.&amp;quot; &lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The original cache canister is (from 2001) a small tupperware containing a logbook pen and some other items.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BRING LOOOOOOOTS OF WATER!!! This might be a H-O-T place!!!!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;* * PLEASE REHIDE IN A WAY THAT PROTECTS THE CACHE FROM BEING MUGGLED BY THE COATIS&lt;/strong&gt; (raccon animal) * *&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Please help me MAINTAIN this very &lt;strong&gt;old cache, the only physical (2001) in Guatemala&lt;/strong&gt;. IF you have the chance of helping me out in the area you will become my new HERO!!!&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Updated 2012: &amp;quot;GPSMartyx&amp;quot; helped me to restore this one. Now its a container again. The original hiding place was a large tree. But now it&amp;#39;s over TEN years ago I was there so the tree might be fallen down... ;)&lt;br /&gt;
THANKS to: G-O-CACHERS and then NLT for helping out&lt;br /&gt;
Update June 2014: Cacher &amp;quot;dillemarco&amp;quot; reports updates of the cache as of today, I changed the ratings accordingly to 2/2,5. &lt;br /&gt;
Update May 2015: Thanks to cacher &amp;quot;cacheditin&amp;quot; the cache is still alive! I feel so happy for that. Many thanks!&lt;br /&gt;
Update mid 2017: Cacher ´&amp;quot;oranje.cph&amp;quot; helped out with a box big as a lunchbox. Many thanks!&lt;br /&gt;
Update Feb 2018: Cacher &amp;quot;Highlands_Guy&amp;quot; put a new shiny brown box at the location. Many thanks!&lt;br /&gt;
Update Nov 2018: Cacher &amp;quot;Saarfuchs&amp;quot; kindly put a new canister in place!&lt;br /&gt;
Update Jan 2019: Cacher &amp;quot;WFoxnTIG&amp;quot; fixed this one, many thanks!&lt;br /&gt;
Update Nov 2019: Cacher &amp;quot;chrini1&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;NBILLI78&amp;quot; restored, many thanks!!! (new hint)&lt;br /&gt;
Update April 2023: Still here as the oldest i Guatemala&lt;br /&gt;
Update Dec 2023: Changed back the name to the original (Hot Jungle) after GC for some strange reason changed it to Tikal only&lt;br /&gt;
 &lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>”Breast height” (as of  May 2022) Rehidden</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1359540376"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-06T17:04:27</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="12069368">mašla</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">TFTC. Nalezena společně s kamarády při návštěvě Tikalu

</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360648921"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-06T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3102281">raa.radim</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Hot Jungle (Tikal)  GC2A86  buda  2.0 2.5   Malá 6. května 2026   10:50  středa

CZ
Navštíveno s Romanem (pantok), Honzou s Klárkou (consolador), Karlem (pixkarel), Martinem (Pernak1) a Alenou (mašla) vod camcaď po camcaď při potulce po světě cestou do Mexika a Střední Ameriky: Belize a Guatamely.

Den čtrnáctý: 
na jeden den do Guatemaly na Tikal

Dnes jsme s místní cestovkou, která vše perfektně zařídila, vyzazili do Tikalu, nejrozlehlejších ruin starověkého mayského města s nejdelším trvaním. Výlet se velmi vydařil a až na to 42°C vedro to bylo fajn. Krom návštěvy tohohle archeologického unikátu jsme si připsali i tři body za nejstarší guatemalskou keš, event a earthku a zhlédli i velmi zajímavou faunu a flóru.

Taky samosebou jsme brali, co nám přišlo do cesty a zapadne to i do nějakých těch matrixů, výzev, kalendářů, opasků, badgenů, puclíků, pokladů a dalších prapodivných statistik a tak jsme na zpáteční cestě navštívili i pár zajímavých keší v dočasném bydlišti San Ignacio, na které už včera nezbyl čas.

Tak i tady to byl rychlý a pohodový nález skrýše a pak i samotné zalogování první a zároveň nejstarší guatemalské keše. 

Díky za zajímavou keš na parádním místě. +FP

Pro větší počet slov do dalšího diamantu (no je to zatím v nedohlednu) více pozdějc, snad i nejen za dlouhých zimních večerů.


ESP
Visité con Roman (pantok), Honza con Klárka (consolador), Karel (pixkarel), Martin (Pernak1) y Alena (mašla) de camcaď a camcaď mientras viajaba por el mundo camino a México y Centroamérica: Belice y Guatemala.

Día catorce: 
Un día en Guatemala, Tikal 

Hoy, con un guía local que lo organizó todo a la perfección, fuimos a Tikal, las ruinas más grandes de la antigua ciudad maya, con la visita más larga. El viaje fue todo un éxito y, salvo por el calor de 42 °C, estuvo bien. Además de visitar este sitio arqueológico único, también conseguimos tres puntos por el tesoro más antiguo de Guatemala, un evento y cerámica, y observamos una fauna y flora muy interesantes.

También dábamos por sentado lo que encontrábamos y que encajaría en alguna de esas matrices, desafíos, calendarios, cinturones, insignias, botones, tesoros y otras estadísticas extrañas, así que de regreso visitamos algunos geocachés interesantes en la residencia temporal de San Ignacio, para los que no tuvimos tiempo ayer. 

Así que aquí también fue fácil y rápido encontrar el tesoro y luego registrar el primer y más antiguo geocaché guatemalteco. 

Gracias por el interesante geocaché en un lugar estupendo. +FP

Para más información sobre el próximo diamante (bueno, aún no está a la vista), más adelante, quizás no solo durante las largas noches de invierno.


EN
Visited with Roman (pantok), Honza with Klárka (consolador), Karel (pixkarel), Martin (Pernak1) and Alena (mašla) from camcaď to camcaď while wandering around the world on the way to Mexico and Central America: Belize and Guatemala. 

Day fourteen: 
for one day in Guatemala to Tikal 

Today, with a local tour guide who arranged everything perfectly, we went to Tikal, the largest ruins of the ancient Mayan city with the longest duration. The trip was very successful and except for the 42°C heat, it was fine. In addition to visiting this archaeological unique, we also scored three points for the oldest Guatemalan cache, event and earthenware and saw very interesting fauna and flora. 

We also took for granted what came our way and it would fit into some of those matrices, challenges, calendars, belts, badges, buttons, treasures and other strange statistics, so on the way back we visited a few interesting caches in the temporary residence of San Ignacio, which we didn't have time for yesterday. 

So here too, it was a quick and easy find of the stash and then the logging of the first and oldest Guatemalan cache itself. 

Thanks for the interesting cache in a great place. +FP  

For more words for the next diamond (well, it's not in sight yet) more later, perhaps not only during long winter evenings.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1359549887"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-06T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2878257">pantok</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Posbírána třináctý to den cesty do Mexika a Belize a Guatemaly, spolu s Consolador, raa.radim, mašla, pixkarel a Pernak1. Domluvili jsme výlet do Tikalu, významného naleziště mayské civilizace, ukryté v džungli severní Guatemaly. Byla to nejen archeologicky, ale i přírodovědně zajímavá podívaná, viděli jsme nosály, chápány a vřešťany. 
_____________
Greetings from Brno the Czech Republic. 
T F T C! 🦎 🇨🇿 🧑‍🔬 🦠
_____________
✏ Geocache: Hot Jungle (Tikal)
🙎 By: buda
📏 Size: Malá
🧠 D 2.0 / 🏔 T 2.5. 
Keš nalezena dne 📅 6. května 2026 v ⌚ 10:52 hod.
🏆 This is my found log no. 17496.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1359546441"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-06T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="15542427">pixkarel</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">6. května 2026 10:48
Navštíveno společně s kamarády při naší cestě do Mexika, Belize a Guatemaly. Třináctý den byla v plánu výlet na mayské památky do Tikalu v Guatemale.  Diky za pozvání na zajímavé místo a keš. 🇨🇿
Moje první Guatemalská keš 🙂</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1359538368"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-06T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="17092668">Pernak1</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">6. května 2026 - Gracias por la cache. Registrado en el viaje de aventura de Cancún a Tikal, donde la costa caribeña se transforma en selva maya.

🇨🇿🇸🇰🇵🇱🇦🇹🇵🇹🇪🇦🇬🇮🇲🇦🇭🇺🇧🇬🇩🇪🇹🇷🇲🇽🇧🇿🇬🇹</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="907797916"><groundspeak:date>2020-02-08T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2089726">travelingGeek</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Man we walked a lot in this park!   Had a great time seeing all of the Mayan ruins, animals, and sights!

This is the 7th country I have found the oldest active cache int!

Log and container are in great shape.  Thanks to all that keep this cache alive!
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="49.435183" lon="-2.6722"><time>2002-01-13T00:00:00</time><name>GC3209</name><desc>View.1 by tc</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC3209</url><urlname>View.1</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="12809" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>View.1</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>tc</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="35533">tc</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="42" inc="1">Needs maintenance</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Guernsey</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Not hard to get to, but you will have to walk the last bit, finding it may be a little harder.
