</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Nice view from here, but you are looking the wrong way!</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1354924925"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-12T21:04:27</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5397332">Southerntrekker</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Hi There

As the owner has not responded to either my log or my colleague's previous log requesting that they check this cache I am archiving it. 

Please note that once the cache has been archived, this can not be undone. This is explained in the Help Center - http://support.groundspeak.com//index.php?pg=kb.page&amp;id=70

You will need to create a new listing, put it back in for review and as long as it meets today's guidelines and no other caches have been published in the area causing a proximity problem, then it will be published.

Regards

Southerntrekker
Volunteer UK Reviewer North Wales, London and Isle of Man - http://www.geocaching.com 
UK Geocaching Wiki - https://wiki.groundspeak.com/display/GEO/United+Kingdom
Geocaching.com Help Center - http://support.groundspeak.com//index.php
UK Geocaching Information and Resource site - http://www.follow-the-arrow.co.uk</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1348340995"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-09T21:55:12</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Unknown</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5397332">Southerntrekker</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Hi There

This cache has been flagged by Geocaching HQ or through a Needs Archive Log as one that may need attention. I notice that no action has been taken by the owner, to correct the issue. Please, could the owner please check this cache and give an indication of when it may be sorted out. If there is no response to this log after 30 days I will archive the cache. In the meantime I am disabling it.

Guidelines:

* You are responsible for occasional visits to your cache to ensure it is in proper working order, especially when someone reports a problem with the cache (missing, damaged, wet, etc.) or posts a Needs Maintenance log. Temporarily disable your cache to let others know not to search for it until you have addressed the problem.
You are permitted a reasonable amount of time --generally, up to 4 weeks – in which to check on your cache. If a cache is not being maintained, or has been temporarily disabled for an unreasonable length of time, we may archive the listing.

Could the cache owner please place a note on the cache page so that other cachers and I can see what your intentions are? 

Please do not e-mail me with the update. It may be one of my colleagues who checks your cache again and they won't know you contacted me. It's a good idea with a cache you've disabled and which may take a while to sort out to post a note once a month so people (and reviewers!) know you are still dealing with it. This will also prevent us from chasing you up and sending more e-mails!

Regards

[Southerntrekker](http://www.geocaching.com/profile/?u=southerntrekker) - Volunteer UK Reviewer North Wales, London and Isle of Man [www.geocaching.com](http://www.geocaching.com)  
[UK Geocaching Policies Wiki](https://wiki.groundspeak.com/display/GEO/United+Kingdom)  
[Geocaching Help Center](http://support.groundspeak.com//index.php)
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1343959406"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-05T13:03:35</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Unknown</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2327319">NlLS</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">🇬🇧 He's definitely gone. Now we really need to ask the owner.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1343982385"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-05T12:16:41</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Didn't find it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5532832">Samlucky67</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Leider nicht gefunden </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1343959283"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-05T12:15:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Didn't find it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2327319">NlLS</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">🇬🇧 Despite an intensive search, we couldn't find anything here. Either we were simply too blind, or the cache is no longer there. We'll come back if our path takes us this way again.
🇩🇪 Hier haben wir trotz intensiver Suche nichts gefunden. Entweder waren wir einfach zu blind, oder der Cache ist nicht mehr vorhanden. Wir kommen wieder, sollte uns unser Weg hier nochmals vorbeiführen.
12:15</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="10.030733" lon="-12.884467"><time>2013-07-27T00:00:00</time><name>GC4H7R6</name><desc>The first cache in Guinee: Le Dauphin by Effe kijke</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC4H7R6</url><urlname>The first cache in Guinee: Le Dauphin</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="3796888" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>The first cache in Guinee: Le Dauphin</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Effe kijke</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="5314100">dommer2</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Micro</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="0">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="27" inc="1">Drinking water nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="29" inc="1">Telephone nearby</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Guinea</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>&lt;p&gt;GB: "Le Dauphin" in Kindia, primary school in the third world.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;FR: école primaire&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NL: basisschool&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;De allereerste cache in Guinee!! Deze basisschool is in 2004 opgezet door het NL-Guinees echtpaar Folmer-Sow, in de wijk Ferefou te Kindia.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The very first Cache in Guinee!! This primary school was founded in 2004 by the Dutch-Guineas couple Folmer-Sow, at Kindia.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Le premier cache en Guinee!! Cette école primaire etait fondée par le couple Guinéen-Hollandais Sow-Folmer à Kindia.&lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>NL : Indien de cache niet te vinden is, bent u van harte welkom op het kantoor van de school, daar is een reserve logboekje beschikbaar. Bezoekers altijd welkom.

GB: In case you can not find the cache, please feel welcome at the office of the school, a spare logrol is available. Feel free for a visit.

FR: En cas le cache nést pas la, vous êtes bienvenue au bureau de l'école, un log reserve est la.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364799104"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T04:30:23</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5314100">dommer2</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">The first cache in Guinee: Le Dauphin was transferred from Effe kijke to user dommer2</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1345989672"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-19T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1108150">kkmk</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We've been coming to Guinea for 3 years teaching English in the capital.  This weekend was our first excursion away from the capital, so we were excited to see something new.  We made a quick stop here to find this cache.  The first people we talked to didn't know anything about it, but they took us to the right people and we were able to sign the log.  TFTC!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1346089146"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-16T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="11608678">Frodosi</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">First time in Western Africa and wow. This was an amazing experience. We have been some days at the school we support through KiK (Kids in Kindia) and were lucky that one of the few Guinean caches was here. Tftc!  </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1344255744"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-08T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1351184">SeekerSupreme</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">It was Saturday. School was closed and padlocked. A local guy went with us to help find the school guard. We went to his other workplace, we went to his home and spoke with his wife, but the school guard with the key was not to be found anywhere.

I initially logged this as a DNF.  After I wrote this log, the CO contacted me and kindly offered that, since I was there and just had the misfortune of the school being closed, I would be allowed to log this as a find.  So I changed my DNF to a Find.  Thank you so much.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1350266505"><groundspeak:date>2025-12-31T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="42639719">Seattlehunter</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found this container on a world tour from 2022 to 2025. I think it was the best experience of my life doing this trip. Could see a lot.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="19.78625" lon="-72.247317"><time>2001-05-01T00:00:00</time><name>GC8D0</name><desc>Cruise Cache - Labadee Beach by Todd &amp; Tracy</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC8D0</url><urlname>Cruise Cache - Labadee Beach</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="2256" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cruise Cache - Labadee Beach</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Todd &amp; Tracy</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="3067">Todd &amp; Tracy</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="42" inc="1">Needs maintenance</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="55" inc="1">Short hike (&lt;1 km)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="40" inc="1">Stealth required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="30" inc="1">Picnic tables nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="59" inc="1">Food nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="27" inc="1">Drinking water nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="4" inc="1">Boat required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="64" inc="0">Tree climbing required</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>3</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Haiti</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>First cache in Haiti!! This is a small cache on Labadee Beach in Haiti near Cap Haitien. This is a semi private part of the area and it is closed to the public when the cruise ships come in, but may be accessible during other periods. The cache is located under part of the wall of a footpath that goes to one of the highest points in this area. Average altitude measured was 23 feet. Please read the update on location in the Long Description!
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>Because of the sharp rocks in the area, it has been placed so you will not need to leave the path. It is relatively easy to find, but hard to get to unless you make the right travel arrangements! I tried to hide it well in a crevice so that it would not be discovered accidentally. The box is a small 8”x5”x2” clear plastic container with a beige top. Initial contents include the logbook, geocache instructions in English, French, German, Italian, Spanish and Portuguese, a pencil, a pen and a pair of sunglasses. It's doubtful that we'll ever be able to maintain this one, so please bring some spare baggies &amp;amp; a pencil to leave just in case. Please read the logs to note that the location has changed since 9 years ago when placed. Best bet is: this one: N 19 47.166 and W 072 14.834. It is hidden under a few rocks within reach of the standing on the path. I needed about 3-4 minutes to let the signal settle down. I believe the trees were causing a little bit of interference. If you look at my log entry I included a picture of the spot
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Corner of the wall facing south.
Approximately 10 feet from a tree to the Northeast and 10 feet from a tree to the Northwest.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1349556546"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-28T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4837511">Cachehunter49gy</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Together with supertwinfan, we visited Labadee Beach. Along the rocky coastline and on the sandy beach, you can clearly see the traces of erosion and sediment deposits, which stand as silent witnesses to the past. Unfortunately we didn’t spot a Travel Bug. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1349350275"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-28T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="17210926">supertwinfan</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">A wonderful visit to Labadee Beach! The coastal rocks and sandy shoreline clearly show the effects of erosion and sediment deposition over time. Great pölace to be.  Sorry - no TB seen.

</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1344219237"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-07T16:27:06</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="48952538">Simeon0_0</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">To anyone who finds this cache and is heading south, please take pengu (the travel bug) with you! As he is trying to get to the continent of the South pole!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1336350930"><groundspeak:date>2025-11-29T20:14:38</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="7846286">Dirk De Baene</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Favo ! Nice place</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1331173869"><groundspeak:date>2025-10-14T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5206691">TEAM_GDY</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">searched for 40 minutes finally found
