Too bad the owner hasn't been on for a long time.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="377400558"><groundspeak:date>2014-01-18T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3886115">Frado:</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Pretty sure that it is a fake log. It should be deleted!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="22.2542" lon="113.905117"><time>2001-10-21T00:00:00</time><name>GC251B</name><desc>Lantau by Team Dragon</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC251B</url><urlname>Lantau</urlname><sym>Geocache Found</sym><type>Geocache|Virtual Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="9499" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Lantau</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Team Dragon</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="18400">Team Dragon</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Virtual Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Virtual</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Hong Kong</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>A virtual cache in the middle of Lantau Island. The coordinates
aren't easy to get to, it will be a long climb if you are out of
shape. You'll know the reason for the cache once you're close.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>Lantau island is the big island between Chek Lap Kok Airport and
Hong Kong Island. From Central, you can take the subway (HK$23 pp
each way) or you can take the bus. In order to get to the cache,
you will need to take the #23 bus from the subway station. Fare is
HK$16 pp each way every day except Sunday when it is HK$25. Make
sure you have exact change and there is a 7-11 nearby if you need
to make change. 
&lt;p&gt;The web page of the new cable car can be found at
http://www.np360.com.hk/&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It doesn't cost anything to get to the cache and this is a
location that won't take you long to see, I spent about 2 hours
here.&lt;/p&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Look up</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364812344"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T21:04:59</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="28918198">Mrs_OzKEG</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Visiting the Budda with Oz KEG</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362855770"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-23T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="43748430">Aezelys</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">First Time in Hong Kong !

A bit cloudy today 😅

Tftc !
                              
_____________________
The Earth

Look again at that dot. That's here. That's home. That's us. On it everyone you love, everyone you know, everyone you ever heard of, every human being who ever was, lived out their lives. The aggregate of our joy and suffering, thousands of confident religions, ideologies, and economic doctrines, every hunter and forager, every hero and coward, every creator and destroyer of civilization, every king and peasant, every young couple in love, every mother and father, hopeful child, inventor and explorer, every teacher of morals, every corrupt politician, every “superstar,” every “supreme leader,” every saint and sinner in the history of our species, lived there—on a mote of dust suspended in a sunbeam.

Carl Sagan</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1361203884"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-09T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="26940951">Le20</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I really enjoyed an amazing (geocache) week in Hong Kong! During my trip I searched for and found several caches across the city and surrounding areas. The warm and humid weather made some walks quite challenging, but that was all part of the experience. Along the way I was rewarded with beautiful views, interesting places, and surprisingly peaceful spots of nature in the middle of the busy city. From modern urban districts to green hills and waterfronts, every cache showed me a different side of Hong Kong. Thanks for placing and maintaining these caches. They made my week here even more enjoyable and memorable! </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363070474"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-08T12:52:23</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="24692740">Alex4493</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Cache trouvée au détour d'une balade pour faire jaunir la carte. 
