This is a GRANDFATHER CACHE. It was within guidelines when placed and published. IT IS ALLOWED  and is only available to MILITARY PERSONNEL . </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1336550166"><groundspeak:date>2025-12-01T16:18:11</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Needs Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="14214008">b2nuts</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I can't get into the military base. I'm denied access because I'm not a member of the military. How is it possible that this kind of cache was allowed to be placed here?

I paid for a taxi to get here, and I'm not allowed in. 
This is unacceptable.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1323953575"><groundspeak:date>2025-09-13T18:18:08</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="53880694">GARYthyMIGHTY</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thanks for my first find! </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="20.32895" lon="100.095917"><time>2002-12-22T00:00:00</time><name>GCB8F7</name><desc>Snake Medicine by Barnyard Dawg &amp; Butane</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCB8F7</url><urlname>Snake Medicine</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Virtual Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="47351" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Snake Medicine</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Barnyard Dawg &amp; Butane</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="6504205">Barnyard Dawg</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Virtual Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Virtual</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="0">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="0">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="4" inc="1">Boat required</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Laos</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>For over two decades, Snake Medicine, Laos's oldest and only classic Virtual Cache, has been a beacon for many visiting geocachers, eager to learn more about this mysterious concoction.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;This is an easy adventure, but it will cost you a short boat ride from the Imperial Golden Triangle Resort, a popular tourist hotel in Thailand's tri-border area, across the Mekong River. This is a safe location, frequented by tourists. If you get as far as the Golden Triangle Resort, you need to go the extra mile just to say you did it. Bring your passport! &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;

The Lao beer is pretty good, but if you want a real treat, try the rice whiskey with the pickled cobra, or there is even something worse.  You'll have to see for yourself. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="http://geocaching.nouveaustere.com/GCB8F7/snake_medicine_whiskey.jpg" width="600" height="338" alt="Snake medicine at a Laos nightmarket" /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Snake medicine at a Laos nightmarket. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How to claim this Virtual Cache? &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;IMPORTANT NOTE!  As of 10th November 2023, the original logging task has been replaced! &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;While the idea of sending a postcard as proof of your visit is wonderful and rather unique, sharing an address online clashes with current privacy concerns, and is no longer a preferred option. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strike&gt;Mail a postcard from the site. &lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;NEW logging task;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take two photos; 1) take a selfie (optional) and/or a photo of a thumbs-up, peace-symbol (V) or personal item with "snake medicine" clearly showing in the photo, and 2) a photo at the Done Xao market area. And if anyway possible, do not log with a boring "TFTC", you can do better ;-)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
These photos are a simple requirement, please do not give me a reason to delete your log. You can find "snake medicine" for sale near the waypoint provided. &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Postcard previously mentioned as part of the listing can be found in the following notes &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GL1B7X6TA"&gt;Postcards part 1&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GL1B7X628"&gt;postcards part 2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1354153994"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-09T21:40:41</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1419589">Orchidee_Jena</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thank you for this nice cache.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1353919586"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-08T17:40:22</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3006333">Arthur 2010</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thanks for the nice geocache </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1345197305"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-16T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2186529">Flep98</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Visited Dongxao Island by boat from Thailand today to get the country point for Laos, a really odd place, but did find the Snake Medicine. Thanks for the cache!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1344045126"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="9330776">Cuxine</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Zusammen mit meinem lieben Tooltime bin ich gerade auf eine Reise um die ganze Welt gestartet und eines unserer ersten Ziele hier in Thailand ist Chiang Rai. Heute stand ein Tagesausflug nach Laos in die Sonderwirtschaftszone an. Mit dem Langboot ging es über den Mekong und auf die andere Seite - nachdem wir brav unser "Eintrittsgeld" bezahlt hatten, liefen wir ein bisschen herum und ich muss sagen: ziemlich künstlich ist hier mittlerweile die Welt geworden - und so ganz anders, als ich es erwartet hatte... Doch plötzlich fanden sich dann doch ein paar der "alten Traditionen" hier in der künstlich erschaffenen Zone... Interessant... 
Herzlichen Dank an Barnyard Dawg  fürs Herlocken an diesen Ort und natürlich auch fürs Ausarbeiten des Virtuals  "Snake Medicine" hier in Laos! Ohne Geocaching wären wir hier sicher nie hergefahren! 
Liebe Grüße von der Nordsee aus Deutschland von Cuxine 🌊🌊🌊☀️
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1344042427"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5231988">Tooltime_2011</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Meine liebe Cuxine und ich sind für einige Zeit auf einer Reise um die Welt und inzwischen sind wir in Chiang Rai angekommen. Von hier aus unternahmen wir einen Ausflug nach Laos. Ein gechartertes Longboat brachte uns für 500 Baht über den Mekong. In der chinesischen Sonderwirtschaftszone angekommen, mussten wir erstmal 50 Baht Eintritt pro Person bezahlen 😮
Danach machten wir einen Schnelldurchlauf durch die SoWiZo um alle Caches inklusive eines Events  machen zu können.
Vielen Dank für diesen Virtual Cache und schöne Grüße aus Wünsdorf bei Berlin.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="33.89565" lon="35.639066666666665"><time>2002-04-29T00:00:00</time><name>GC5344</name><desc>Lebanon's First Cache by PumpMe &amp; Arakie </desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC5344</url><urlname>Lebanon's First Cache</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="21316" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Lebanon's First Cache</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>PumpMe &amp; Arakie </groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="43094">PumpMe</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Lebanon</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>The cache is located on the hill of the Mar Chaaya Monastery in Brumana</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>Cache contains lots of valuable items but we forgot 2 put a log book. So please bring a log book with u in case u get there b4 i get the chance 2 go back myself. 
&lt;P&gt;
One valuable advice: WEAR LONG PANTS WHEN GOING 2 LOOK 4 THIS CACHE. Lots of thorny bushes &amp; jagged rocks. </groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>From the lower car park, walk towards the large radio antenna. Follow the path behind the antenna about 350 meters to a nice clearing. Look for a large rock with a wooden stick. From this rock walk about 100m WSW thru heavy bushes; u'll get 2 a large outcrop of rocks with a 360 view of Beirut. On these rocks look for 2 red painted spots one of which is a circle. The cache is well hidden between these spots.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1238729287"><groundspeak:date>2024-06-06T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="617338">Mimring</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">What an adventure to get to this one. The lower parking is not accessible so we parked on the road up and found a trail that took us to the antenna. We followed directions on a nice road through a bee farm and down to the clearing, which was where the road doubled back. We didn't find the stick in the rock but followed the arrow which led us to a trail marked with black tape and shotgun cartridges. 60 feet short of GZ we found a rock outcrop with a big red circle ⭕ so we started our search. Bad idea. After 15 minutes we respected the GPS and bushwhacked to another outcrop. This was definitely the one.  Here we saw a red dot and a circle and between them a perfect hiding place for a cache.  Alas, we found nothing. After the hike, I was full on drenched with sweat so we watched the sun descend. And then I hid a small replacement blue bison tube. It is hidden in a small crevice 15vm above the red dot on the rocks furthest from the view, covered by another rock.  Not ideal, but I wanted to claim this find. All our colleagues waiting for us for dinner were now worried, so we hiked back to the car as fast as my old legs would carry me.

Memorable view and a memorable hike. Fave point. TFT oldest in Lebanon C</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1233227442"><groundspeak:date>2024-05-11T16:10:29</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="13828223">kimbaraka</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Beautiful spot, geocache might need a bit of maintenance though. Thank you for the cache!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1178629119"><groundspeak:date>2023-07-02T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="15377839">coolekuh</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">

Ich bin für 4 Tage mit 22 anderen Geocachern in den Libanon gereist.
Neben den Caches wollten wir mehr von Land und Leuten erfahren.
Und? Ja genau man weis eigentlich nichts über dieses Land.
Die Explosion im Hafen von Beirut 2020, die Kriege 1982 und 2006, ja das sind Tatsachen die bekannt sind, aber die schönen Seiten dieses tollen Landes sind nicht wirklich bekannt, oder?
Ich habe mich jedenfalls absolut sicher gefühlt und die Zeit genossen.
Ob es beim Abendessen in der Zaitunay Bay, oder der Besichtigung der unfassbar schönen Jeita Grotte, der Statue Lady of Lebanon in Harissa, oder der Stadt Byblos war.
Auch bei der Bustour durch Beirut, vorbei an vielen Sehenswürdigkeiten, oder alleine in der Stadt, hatte ich nie ein schlechtes Gefühl.

Am besten gefallen hat mir der vorletzte Tag den ich nie vergessen werde. Beim Stop am Pigeon Rock, zog uns in eine direkt an der Klippe gelegene Location. Hier haben wir bei einigen Bier und einer Wasserpfeife Ideen für die nächsten Reisen gesammelt.

Die krönung des Tages, war dann eine unterhaltsame Taxifahrt zum ältesten Cache im Libanon. Der Taxifahrer ahnte sicher nicht, worauf er sich da eigenlassen hatte. Nach und nach fand er aber sichtlich gefallen an unser wilden Navigation um einen geeigneten Weg zum Cache zu finden. Aber der Erfolg zählt, wir stehen im Logbuch.

Danke Libanon, du hast uns willkommen geheißen und uns deine Einzigartigkeit und deine Kultur und Geschichte gezeigt. Wir wünschen Dir und Deinen Bewohnern das Beste für die Zukunft.

Danke sagt Coolekuh

I went to Lebanon for 4 days with 22 other geocachers.
In addition to the caches, we wanted to learn more about the country and its people.
And? Yes, you actually know nothing about this country.
The explosion in the port of Beirut in 2020, the wars in 1982 and 2006, yes, these are facts that are well known, but the beautiful sides of this great country are not really known, are they?
In any case, I felt absolutely safe and enjoyed the time.
Whether it was dining at Zaitunay Bay, or visiting the impossibly beautiful Jeita Grotto, the Lady of Lebanon statue in Harissa, or the city of Byblos.
Even on the bus tour through Beirut, past many sights, or alone in the city, I never had a bad feeling.

I liked the penultimate day the best, which I will never forget. At the stop at Pigeon Rock, pulled us into a location right on the cliff. Here we collected ideas for the next trips over a few beers and a water pipe.

The highlight of the day was an entertaining taxi ride to the oldest cache in Lebanon. The taxi driver certainly had no idea what he had let himself in for. Gradually, however, he visibly liked our wild navigation to find a suitable way to the cache. But success counts, we are in the log book.

Thank you Lebanon, you welcomed us and showed us your uniqueness and your culture and history. We wish you and your residents the best for the future.

Thanks says Coolekuh</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1361902874"><groundspeak:date>2023-07-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="43288136">Frau_Löffelchen</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Unsere Gruppe aus Germany war zu Besuch im Libanon. Wir hatten uns einen Bus gemietet und sind alle Caches abgefahren. Geloggt haben wir als CRBEIRUT2023 um Platz zu sparen. Wir hatten alle viel Spaß und der Fahrer hat was zu erzählen. 
TftC Gruß Frau_Löffelchen</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1305974281"><groundspeak:date>2023-07-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8141941">lacori</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Auf unserer Gacherreise in den Libanon, dürften wir die Stadt Beirut besuchen, was eindrücklich war anstatt nur aus den Medien zu hören und sehen. Um das Logbuch zu schonen haben wir CRBeirut2023 unterzeichnet.
Sorry für den spaten Eintrag, habe bei der Kontrolle dies erst jetzt bemerkt.

Gruss Lacori  Schweiz</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="-29.5234666666667" lon="29.19935"><time>2004-12-18T00:00:00</time><name>GCMA6A</name><desc>Black Mountain  by Durbs</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCMA6A</url><urlname>Black Mountain </urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="194506" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Black Mountain </groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Durbs</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="231849">Durbs</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>4</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Lesotho</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Enjoy the views of Lesotho, from the old road.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>We placed a small canister under a few rocks next to the road. Due the location, there are local herds men watching, your every move. Enjoy the view from the old road. The road is only suitable for a 4X4 but you can walk there, as the cache is near the main road.
 
NB Please be prepare for cold weather. At 3244M the weather can change radically. </groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1362946499"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-22T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="29045327">Hunger_Cat</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Yay!!!! I did it. We did it. Geo-Igel and I. Wht a great day. This is my highest Log. Tftc.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362722529"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-22T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="7081170">Geo-Igel</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Sani Pass from South Africa to Lesotho and a little further to Black Mountain. Incredibly beautiful view, just amazing. The cache was found quickly. On the short hike up to the location, breathing became a little heavier here at an altitude of 3260 meters. Thanks for this nice cache.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364123567"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-03T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="7680062">Matisons!</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Stopped at this cache while visiting **Lesotho**! [^]
**My #171st visited Geocaching country!**

---
This cache was easily found and the logbook was signed.
One more smiley face for me in the GEO map.[;)]
Everything was in good condition!
Happy to find the oldest cache in the country.
Thank you for hiding this cache and showing me this place! [;)]

