</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362133560"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-21T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6756354">Eifelfindus</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Nach unseren ursprünglichen Reiseplänen sollte es eigentlich nach Vietnam gehen – doch der Nahost-Konflikt machte uns kurzfristig einen Strich durch die Rechnung. Also entschieden wir uns spontan für Südafrika … und rückblickend war das definitiv eine richtig gute Entscheidung!

Unsere Reise startete in Johannesburg und führte uns innerhalb von 3,5 Wochen auf knapp 5000 km quer durch den Nordosten Südafrikas. Zu den Highlights unserer Rundreise gehörten unter anderem der beeindruckende Kruger Nationalpark, das wunderschöne Eswatini, die Küstenregion am Indischen Ozean, Lesotho sowie die spektakulären Drakensberge.
Während der gesamten Reise hatten wir unglaublich viele schöne Eindrücke, tolle Begegnungen und unvergessliche Landschaften erleben dürfen. Natürlich durfte auch das Geocaching nicht fehlen, wodurch wir zusätzlich viele interessante Orte entdeckt haben, die wir ohne dieses Hobby vermutlich nie gesehen hätten.

Es ist der älteste Cache des Landes! Was für eine Ehre.

Vielen Dank an alle Owner, die mit ihren Dosen dazu beitragen, Reisenden solche besonderen Plätze zu zeigen und die Reise noch ein Stück abwechslungsreicher zu machen.

Viele Grüße aus Deutschland — und vielleicht führt dich ja auch irgendwann einmal ganz spontan ein Flug zu uns, schließlich wartet hier bald ein großes Mega-Event auf Besucher aus aller Welt! 😊
GCBAWVP - MEGA EVENT - AUGUSTA TREVERORUM - 08.08.2026
[MEGA GERMANY GEOCACHING WEBSITE](https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCBAWVP_project-augusta-treverorum)

Und wer es noch nicht gesehen hat, der sollte sich flott anmelden:
**-&gt; [PROJECT AUGUSTA TREVERORUM - HIER KLICKEN](https://coord.info/GCBAWVP)**
-&gt; MEGA EVENT TRIER
-&gt; 07.-09. August 2026 
-&gt; Zurück in die Zeit - Auf den Spuren der Römer</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1338250286"><groundspeak:date>2025-12-18T10:01:43</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5094801">ctulhu</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Wet logbook. So,  fotolog instead.
But what am amazing view! 

Tftc</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="25.522133" lon="10.600783"><time>2008-01-14T00:00:00</time><name>GC18KWH</name><desc>Acacus - First Earthcache in Libya by Sir Hugo und Tarnmuggel</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC18KWH</url><urlname>Acacus - First Earthcache in Libya</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Earthcache</type><groundspeak:cache id="769842" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Acacus - First Earthcache in Libya</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Sir Hugo und Tarnmuggel</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="451170">Sir Hugo und Tarnmuggel</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Earthcache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Other</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="0">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="27" inc="0">Drinking water nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="33" inc="1">Motorcycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="34" inc="1">Quads</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="35" inc="1">Off-road vehicles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="31" inc="1">Camping nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="38" inc="1">Campfires</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="23" inc="1">Dangerous area</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="18" inc="1">Dangerous animals</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>4.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Libya</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Tadrart Acacus is a desert area in western Libya and is part of the Sahara. It has a large variation of landscapes, from differently coloured sanddunes to arches, gorges, rocks and mountains.
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>Some geoarchaeological characteristics of the Tadrart Acacus:&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Travertine:&lt;/b&gt; Travertine deposits have been found in numerous caves and rock shelters within the Tadrart Acacus, developed in fractures and in the joins between strata. The formation of travertine requires a higher availability of water than is at present the case. A research of an Italian-Libyan Archaeological Mission involved the uranium/thorium dating of these deposits, and the definition of the isotopic composition of stable isotopes of oxygen and carbon. Dates range from 14.000 to 10.000 years B.C., and the samples show isotopic depletion. It can be said, that they were formed by meteoric water, indicating intense monsoon rains in the central Sahara at the beginning of the Holocene.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Rock varnish:&lt;/b&gt; Rock varnish is a fine film rich in manganese which covers the surface of sandstone exposed to the atmosphere. Its origins are generally attributed to microbial activity under humid conditions in the past. The Italian-Libyan team obtained some consistent radiocarbon datings for this substance (spanning the Early and Middle Holocene); however, it is not entirely clear what part of the varnish has been dated. The rock varnish in the Messak Settafet, as shown by microscopy, is composed of three microlayers of different composition, belonging to three different phases of the Holocene.The innermost layer is rich in alluvial clay, indicating humid conditions (Wet Holocene); the presence of P205 indicates biological activity during deposition. The second microlayer is rich in manganese, and is of bacterial origin; the outer layer is made up of aeolian quartz dust, and was formed during the Late Holocene desertification. Lake Deposits: Lake sediments found in the interdune corridors indicate the presence of palaeolakes in the ergs, the result of higher levels of rainfall. During the Holocene intense precipitation caused the oversaturation of the dunes and consequently a rise in the water table. Radiocarbon dating indicates the presence of lakes between 8.400 and 4.600 years B.C. The sedimentary facies, composed of peat, carbonated mud, and then a gypsum crust, shows the gradual rise in water levels in the lake, and the subsequent drying up of the basin. The molluscs present in the sediment and the fragments of ostrich eggs near the deposits represent a register of the isotopic composition of the waters of the lakes, and of the rates of precipitation in surrounding areas.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;How to get there:&lt;/b&gt; The asphalt roads end in Awaynat. (N25°47.165 E010°34.510) To enter the desert, you need a permission of the Libyan authorities and a 4x4. You must be accompanied by an official represetative of the tourism police as well.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;How to log this cache:&lt;/b&gt; On the given coordinates, you find the rock formation that you see on the picture. In English, it is called “The thumb”.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;1.&lt;/b&gt; What`s the Tuareg name of it? Send an email to xxxx-in-libya@web.de, and replace the xxxx by the Tuareg name of the “thumb”. (4 letters). &lt;i&gt;Notice: There might be two different spellings. We look for the one, that ends with a “d”.&lt;/i&gt; You get an autoreply, when your answer is correct. It is recommended to write at least one or two sentences in your mail, otherwise it might be concidered as spam, and the autoresponder does not work.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;2.&lt;/b&gt; Post a photo showing you with your GPSr in front of the "thumb"-rock.
&lt;center&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/log/a11bef20-a37e-43bf-a16f-1b783253642b.jpg" border="0" /&gt;&lt;/center&gt;
&lt;center&gt;&lt;a href="http://s05.flagcounter.com/more/SR3"&gt;&lt;img src="http://s05.flagcounter.com/count/SR3/bg=FFFFFF/txt=000000/border=CCCCCC/columns=2/maxflags=12/viewers=0/labels=0/" alt="free counters" border="0" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/center&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1180585156"><groundspeak:date>2023-07-14T17:16:41</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="46513041">Dadaa11</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found it</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1146005285"><groundspeak:date>2023-01-22T20:23:48</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="40390275">SilasandGavin</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Y</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="746428669"><groundspeak:date>2018-02-13T16:49:14</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="10036910">viperbruno</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I send throw message the answer, the mail isn't working for me.
TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="548701948"><groundspeak:date>2015-10-12T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4133568">Claudan35</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Je viens d'envoyer le mail avec demande d'accusé de réception, c'est bon, j'ai reçu l'accusé de réception:
Final-Recipient: rfc822; xxxd-in-libya@web.de
Original-Recipient: rfc822;xxxd-in-libya@web.de
Action: relayed
Status: 2.0.0

Je joins une photo ou l'on voit la que la personne qui tient le livre est à la fois sur la couverture du livre et sur la photo grandeur nature ( c'est comme sur la boîte de vache qui rit).
J'envoie aussi trois autres photos, dont le "doigt".
Merci pour cette earth-cache.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="489067570"><groundspeak:date>2015-03-27T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6531814">Fam_Marple</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Diese Tour kam uns irgendwie kurzfristig dazwischen. Eigentlich wollten wir eher nicht in die Region reisen, da es in der gesamten Region teilweise sehr unsicher geworden ist. Aber das Team hat sich durchgesetzt und so konnten wir einen kulturell geschichtlichen Ausflug starten. Die Tage durch die ungewohnte Umgebung war sehr interessant. Und am Ende kamen wir auch wieder Sicher nach Hause.
Fotos waren leider nicht gestattet, aber die Eindrücke die wir gesammelt hatten waren viel wertvoller als irgend eine Fotografie. 



This entry was edited by Mr. &amp; Mrs. Marple on Tuesday, 07 April 2015 at 07:53:34 UTC.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="47.1429" lon="9.545633333333333"><time>2003-01-12T00:00:00</time><name>GCC2F4</name><desc>Liechtenstein's First by Heinz-Achmed</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCC2F4</url><urlname>Liechtenstein's First</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="49908" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Liechtenstein's First</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Heinz-Achmed</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="85064">Heinz-Achmed</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="42" inc="1">Needs maintenance</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Liechtenstein</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Beinahe ein drive-by Cache. Nearly a drive-by cache.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>Das gibt es noch mitten in Europa: Ein "unbeflecktes" Land. Auch hier einmal der Erste zu sein, wird wohl immer schwieriger ...

Dies ist ein Cache auf über 1500 m Höhe - dementsprechend ist die Anfahrt. Wir empfehlen den Weg am Schloss des Fürsten entlang. Von hier hat man schon mal einen Vorgeschmack auf die Aussicht von oben. 

In Triesenberg dann Richtung Malbun / Gaflei weiterfahren. Der Cache befindet sich ca. 30 Höhenmeter über dem Parkplatz (N 47°08.552; E 009°32.675) am Hotel in Gaflei. Es geht über die Wiese hoch (keine 5 Minuten).

Alternativ bietet sich auch eine Wanderung von Feldkirch oder Amerlügen über die "Drei Schwestern" und den "Fürstensteig" an. Diese Tour dauert (ab Amerlügen) ca. 6 Stunden. Dann mit dem Bus zurück.

IN:
- Flaschenöffner aus Alu mit Sockel aus Holz
- Ansteckpin vom BMW Werk in München
- Mini-Puzzle
- Gummi-Tausendfüsler (leuchtet im Dunkeln!)
- Sonnen-Amulett
- Duftöl
- Olivin in Lava-Asche aus Lanzarote (Direktimport!)
- 2 Murmeln

--------------------------
Still possible in Europe: a country without cache. Nice to be the first to place one in a country ...

This is at about 1500 m height - with the respective way thereto. We recommend the way passing the castle of the Principal of Liechtenstein. Here you get a first foretaste for the view from up there.

In Triesenberg drive on in direction of Malbun / Gaflei. The cache is ca. 30 meter above the parking site (N 47°08.552; E 009°32.675) at the hotel in Gaflei. Just uphill over the green.

Alternativeley you can hike from Feldkirch or Amerlügen over the "Drei Schwestern" and the "Fürstensteig". This tour takes about 6 hours from Amerlügen. Then back by bus.

IN:
- bottle opener (alu) with base (wood)
- pin from BMW plant in München
- mini puzzle
- plastic millipede (glowing in the dark!)
- sun amulett (brass)
- fragrance oil
- Olivin stone in lava ash from Lanzarote (direct import!)
- 2 marbles



</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Der Cache befindet sich unter Wurzeln, aber nicht unter einem lebenden Baum.
The cache is situated under roots but not under a living tree.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1365011625"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-02T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4516421">cachesurfer2011</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Heute fuhren womochri und ich nach Liechtenstein, um in jedem Bezirk Caches zu besuchen und natürlich auch jede Menge Challenges. Der älteste Cache darf dann auch nicht fehlen. Er ist in einem sehr guten Zustand und gut zu finden. TB in. Vielen lieben Dank für diesen Oldie.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1365011310"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-02T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5603627">womochri</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Am Dienstag vor einer Woche starteten cachesurfer2011 und ich unsere Tour zum MegaEvent in Italien. Nach Zwischenstopps in Villach, Bergamo und Cazarrate machen wir nun Halt in Vorarlberg.
Der heutige Tag war Caches in und um Liechtenstein gewidmet.
Gleich am Morgen starteten wir mit diesem netten Landesoldie!
Der Ausblick hat mir hier gut gefallen!

Danke für das Herlocken und den Geocache! - 🇬🇧 Thanks for the cache (English) - 🇮🇹 Grazie per questo cache (say) – 🇮🇪 Go raibh maith agat as an taisce (Gaeilge) - 🇭🇺 Köszönöm a geoláda (Magyar) - 🇸🇰 Ďakujem za kešku (Slovensky) - 🇨🇿 Díky za keš Čeština) - 🇭🇷 Hvala cache (Hrvatski) - 🇫🇷 Merci pour la cache (Français) - 🇵🇱 Dzięki za kesza (Polski) - 🇪🇸 Gracias por el cache (Español) – 🇵🇹 Obrigado por isso cache (ar ) – 🇳🇱 Bedankt voor de cache (Nederlands) - 🇸🇪 Tack för att cache (Svenska) – 🇳🇴 Takk for at cache (Norsk) - 🇮🇸 Takk fyrir skyndiminnið (Íslenska) - 🇹🇷 Önbellek için teşekkürler (Türkçe) - 🇷🇺 Спасибо за кеш (рус.) - 🇨🇳 感谢您的缓存 (中文) - 🇯🇵 キャッシュありがとうございます (日本語)</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364387434"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T17:44:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2372188">Thoby</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Hr 17.44  
Found it with hathneit on the way back to Denmark, after attending the first MEGA in Italy.  
TFTC Heinz-Achmed  
Cache #41.947  
        
    
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364387099"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T17:42:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5136895">hathneit</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">On our way home to Denmark from Italy, we took the small detour for this cache.    
What a view</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364781698"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T14:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="24985544">Tillba</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Heute ging es für uns zum ersten Mal nach Lichtenstein. Wir hatten eine kleine Tour zusammengestellt um schöne Orte und Caches zu besuchen. Wir haben viel gesehen und erlebt. 
Der Ort ist definitiv eine weitere Reise wert, da es noch viel zu entdecken gibt.
Dieser Cache war natürlich ganz oben auf unserer Liste. Schön ist es hier oben. 
Danke für den Oldie in so einer tollen Umgebung.🤗</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="55.782967" lon="23.891383"><time>2003-05-12T00:00:00</time><name>GCGCMZ</name><desc>Tulip time by Sandrius</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCGCMZ</url><urlname>Tulip time</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="77718" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Tulip time</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Sandrius</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="713200">Sandrius</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="42" inc="1">Needs maintenance</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="0">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="0">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="2" inc="1">Access/parking fee</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="0">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="55" inc="1">Short hike (&lt;1 km)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="38" inc="0">Campfires</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="0">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="64" inc="0">Tree climbing required</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Lithuania</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>You should buy ticket to go to the cache. &lt;br /&gt;
Museum workers is not happy if you go around fences.&lt;br /&gt;
There is Adventure Lab too.&lt;br /&gt;
First cache placed by Edvinas 76&lt;br /&gt;
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>Description from 2003:&lt;br /&gt;
Lt: &lt;b&gt;Burbiškio dvaro istorijos ekspozicija&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Informacija lankytojui: Darbo laikas&lt;br /&gt;
Balandžio 1 d. – spalio 31 d.:&lt;br /&gt;
antradieniais – sekmadieniais 9–17 val.&lt;br /&gt;
Bilieto kaina:&lt;br /&gt;
suaugusiesiems – 6 Lt;&lt;br /&gt;
moksleiviams, studentams, II ir III grupes neigaliesiems – 3 Lt;&lt;br /&gt;
ikimokyklinio amžiaus vaikams, I grupes neigaliesiems – nemokamai.&lt;br /&gt;
Ekspozicija&lt;br /&gt;
Burbiškio dvaro istorijos ekspozicija ikurta sename Baženskiu dvare, kuris istoriniuose šaltiniuose minimas nuo XVII a. Peizažinio tipo dvaro parkas, užimantis 28 ha pasižymi ispudingais tvenkiniais, kuriuose yra 15 salu. Dvaro pastatai suformuoti taip, kad sudaro dideli uždara kiema, todel primena tvirtove. Atstatytame rumu sveciu korpuse rengiami sveciu namai, rumu verandoje irengta dvaro istorijos ekspozicija. Parke gausu skulptoriaus Kazimiero Uliansko darbu: poeto Adomo Mickeviciaus paminklas (pastatytas 1911 m.), Lietuvos Didžiojo kunigaikšcio Vytauto paminklas (pastatytas 1912 m.), Šv. M. Marijos skulptura, didingi parko vartai, liutu tiltas. Parke irengti takai, tvenkiniu salos sujungtos 12 tilteliu. Parko geliu daigyne auga ivairiu augalu kolekcijos. Dvare vyksta restauravimo darbai.Burbiškio dvaro skulpturos&lt;br /&gt;
Lietuvos didžiojo kunigaikšcio Vytauto paminklas;&lt;br /&gt;
Poeto Adomo Mickeviciaus paminklas;&lt;br /&gt;
Dievo Motinos skulptura „Nekalto prasidejimo Marija“;&lt;br /&gt;
Liutu skulpturos;&lt;br /&gt;
Fauno skulptura „Velniukas“;&lt;br /&gt;
Nimfos skulptura, undine;&lt;br /&gt;
Baženskiu šeimos biustai;&lt;br /&gt;
Baženskiu šeimos herbai;&lt;br /&gt;
Bareljefai;&lt;br /&gt;
Dvaro svirno skulptura.&lt;br /&gt;
Iš visu Radviliškio rajone esanciu dvaru Burbiškio dvare XX a. pr. buvo sukaupta bene daugiausia meno vertybiu. Burbiškio dvaras pasižymejo senosios bajoriškos dvaru kulturos puoselejimu. Dvaro savininkai Baženskiai kure dideli ir puošnu parka, jame stat paminklus, skulpturas, kaupe archyva ir biblioteka. Dauguma meno vertybiu dvarininko Mykolo Baženskio užsakymu sukure skulptorius Kazimieras Ulianskis (1878–1914). M. Baženskis dvara paveldejo 1903 m. po tevo Mykolo-Ignoto Baženskio mirties (mire 1902 m.). Dvarininkas M. Baženskis jaunysteje mokesi Rygoje, veliau buvo išsiustas mokytis I Galicija, po to studijavo agronomijos mokslus Leipcige. Pasižymejo romantiškomis aspiracijomis, dievino kompozitoriu Štrausa ir labai mego skaityti poeto Adomo Mickeviciaus poemas. O jose buvo placiai aprašyta Lietuvos praeitis, lietuviu kovos su kryžiuociais. Garsaus ir mylimo poeto kuryba pažadino domejimasi istorija, Lietuvos praeitimi ir senove. Dar tebesimokydamas toli nuo teviškes M. Baženskis svajojo, kaip papuošti Burbiškio dvaro parka gražiais meno kuriniais. Baiges mokslus Vokietijoje jis sugrižo i Burbiškio dvara ir pats emesi tvarkyti uki. Cia gyvendamas neatsisake savo sumanymo skulpturomis išgražinti tevo irengta parka. Ieškojo gabaus menininko, galincio ta jo sumanyma igyvendinti. 1910 m. M. Baženskis susipažino su jaunu ir gabiu skulptoriumi K. Ulianskiu. Dailininkas 1907 m. buvo baiges skulpturos mokslus Lenkijoje. Mokesi Varšuvoje pas skulptoriu H. Marcevski, o Krokuvos dailes akademijoje pas skulptoriu Konstantina Lašcka. K. Ulianskis, baiges mokslus, gyveno Panevežyje ir dirbo ivairius skulpturos darbus bažnycioms. M. Baženskiui skulptoriu, atrodo, bus rekomendaves dvarininkas Karpis. Nors galejo ši pažintis užsimegzti ir per Petra Vileiši. K. Ulianskis buvo žinomas kaip gabus, darbštus ir kuklus menininkas. Kaip tik tokios savybes labai patiko M. Baženskiui. Šis, kaip ir dera turtingam dvarininkui, tapo mecenatu – pasieme skulptoriu i kelione po Italija. Buvo aplankytos ir kitos Europos šalys. Šios keliones metu, besilankant žymiausiuose meno centruose, matyt, atsirado susitarimas tarp dvarininko mecenato ir skulptoriaus. Tuomet galejo buti aptarti ir numatyti ateities darbai, suplanuota skulpturu išdestymo parke tvarka, nes 1911 m. Burbiškio dvaro parke jau pastatomas pirmasis paminklas, kuriamos kitos skulpturos.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
En: EXPOSITION ON HISTORY OF THE BURBISKIS MANOR&lt;br /&gt;
Working time From April 1 to October 31. On Tuesdays - Sundays from 9.00 to 17.00. Ticket price - 6Lt&lt;br /&gt;
The exposition is displayed in the old manor of Bazenskiai mentioned in historical sources since the 17th century. The park of manor is of landscape-type. It occupies 28 ha of area and is famous for impressive ponds containing 15 islets. The buildings of manor form a big close yard and remind of a fortress. The restored part of palace will house guests’ rooms and the terrace - an exposition on history of manor, which is already equipped. Works of art by Kazimieras Ulianskas, the sculptor, abound in the park: the monument for poet Adomas Mickevicius (built in 1911), the monument for Vytautas, the Great Duke of Lithuania (built in 1912), the sculpture of Holy Maiden Mary, the grandiose gate of park, the bridge ornamented by sculptures of lions. The park is traversed by many pathways. 12 small bridges connect the islets.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;a href="http://s05.flagcounter.com/more/UGE"&gt;&lt;img src="http://s05.flagcounter.com/count/UGE/bg=FFFFFF/txt=000000/border=CCCCCC/columns=8/maxflags=248/viewers=0/labels=1/pageviews=1/" alt="free counters" border="0" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>tree</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364329080"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-26T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4826042">4Hippies</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Today our journey takes us from Latvia to Lithuania. Our main destination is Šiauliai, where we'll spend the night. We want to visit the Hill of Crosses and find the oldest geocache, Tulip Time. 
Of course, we paid the entrance fee; the workers need to be paid, and the garden and buildings need to be maintained. The garden was even open until 6:00 PM, so we unexpectedly had a little more time to admire the tulips. Some were already past their bloom, but others were still very beautiful. We quickly found the geocache and signed the logbook. 
Many thanks for preserving this old treasure! 💙
TFTC and best regards from the 4Hippies 👋</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362890585"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-23T18:33:43</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8264741">Stieb05</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Yes.... zusammen mit Stieb01 &amp; Co. für ein Wochenende in Riga. Heute Morgen ging es früh mit dem Lux-Express-Bus los, um den Länderpunkt für Litauen 🇱🇹 zu cachen. Nach der Ankunft am Busbahnhof ging es mit Bolt weiter und dann noch etwas zu Fuß…dieser älteste Cache konnte prima gefunden werden und wir stehen nun im Logbuch…danach wurden noch die Tulpen bewundert, bevor es mit Bolt zurück in die Stadt zum cachen ging.
Für den Oldie und Länderpunkt bleibt natürlich ein FP zurück….

Vielen Dank an Sandrius für das Legen und Pflegen der Dose sowie für den neuen Smiley auf der Karte

DFDC sagt Stieb05 

</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362882703"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-23T18:07:31</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4841656">Ruebe71</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Heute haben wir mit dem Lux Expressbus einen Ausflug von Riga nach Panevezys gemacht. 
Wir konnten den ältesten Cache und einige weitere Caches besuchen.

Zum ältesten Cache sind wir mit dem Bolt Taxi gefahren. 
Mit 5 € Eintritt konnten wir in den schönen Tulpenpark. 

Den Cache konnten wir fix finden und uns ins Logbuch eintragen. Toll, dass dieser alte Cache noch besteht. 

Vielen Dank für den Cache. FP bleibt da.

LG Ruebe71


</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362983792"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-23T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8297463">Stieb01</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Für den Oldtimer lasse ich gerne ein blaues FP-Schleifchen zurück....
Gemeinsam mit Stieb05 und Co ging es heute auf kleine Cachertour.  Mit dem Fernbus fuhren wir von Lettland nach Litauen um hier ein paar neue Icons und Caches zu ergattern.
Dabei konnte der ein oder andere interessante Cache besucht und das Logbuch erfolgreich signiert werden. Dieser interessante Traditional-Cache konnte nach dem Umstieg zum Bolt-Taxi separat angefahren werden und grüßt nun als neuer Smiley auf unserer Cacherkarte. 
Schönes Museum und interessante Blumenzucht.
Viele Grüße von Stieb01 aus RLP und unserem schönen Naheland in Deutschland. Den besten Dank an Sandrius fürs Legen, Hegen und Pflegen dieses Caches.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364851040"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-22T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="15322489">mattia_p</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">{FTF}
Irish are on the road again.
Group of 7 (signing logs as Baltic Bashers); myself, Icklelego, Lulybelle, Greenbug, BigMcKs, MacAroni Senior, theswerve, took off from Dublin with a plan to visit Tallin, Helsinki, Riga,  Panevėžys (here for caches as well as 5km Park Run) and everything in between.
We had fabulous time meeeting local cachers, sampling local food and beer, visiting amazing places and having tones of laughs. We got over 150+ caches across 4 countries. Renting cars was essential to move around freely to get what we could in 6 days of travels. FP distributed accordingly. 
Thank you to all CO for placing and manatining all the caches.

TFTC! 😁</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="49.75" lon="6"><time>2002-04-02T00:00:00</time><name>GC4871</name><desc>Grand Luxembourg Quest I (virtual part) by enduromaniac (adopted by snoopy-doopy)</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC4871</url><urlname>Grand Luxembourg Quest I (virtual part)</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Virtual Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="18545" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Grand Luxembourg Quest I (virtual part)</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>enduromaniac (adopted by snoopy-doopy)</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="220451">snoopy-doopy</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Virtual Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Virtual</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="0">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>3</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Luxembourg</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>&lt;b&gt;Team BUDA adopted this cache in april 05, since this is a very
ancient cache we'd like to keep it going on. Please mail us for any
comments. Thanks.&lt;/b&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;After 'Team BUDA adopted this cache in april 05',
'snoopy-doopy' adopted this cache on the 08.11.2006 ('
snoopy-doopy's ' birthday) to let it going on .&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>This tour leads you all around the beautiful country of Luxembourg.
You will be given five pictures (see below) of different objects.
Your task is to find these objects in the country. 
&lt;p&gt;Well, Luxembourg is a small country, but to find an object in it
is still a hard task, therefore I give you five starting
coordinates. Each object is to be found within the circumference of
max. 700 m around a starting coordinate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The starting coordinates:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div style="margin-left: 2em"&gt;Echternach: N49°48,804'
E6°25,255'&lt;br&gt;
Schengen: N49°28,319' E6°21,960'&lt;br&gt;
Rodange: N49°32,046' E5°51,768'&lt;br&gt;
Perlé: N49°48,563' E5°45,900'&lt;br&gt;
Weiswampach: N50°08,311' E6°04,573' 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Take your digital camera and log this cache by submitting a
picture of you (NOT ONLY YOUR HAND!!!) standing at the 5 given
objects. Be smart and combine your odyssee with other caches in
Luxembourg&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364021817"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-28T15:38:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="7881502">EllyNilsson</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Vor einigen Jahren war es mein Ziel, alle virtuellen Caches von Luxemburg zu machen. Dieser hier blieb bis heute leider offen, aber inzwischen gibt es ja genügend neue Geister. Dabei war ich damals so happy bis auf diesen her sonst alle gemacht zu haben. 

Ganz einfach ist dieser hier wirklich nicht. Allein die Fahrerei. Dabei denkt man ja, Luxemburg sei gar nicht so groß . 

Nun ist das Werk endlich vollendet, und ich bin froh, dass er mich ab sofort nur noch als Smiley von der Karte angrinst. 
 
Herzlichen Dank snoopy-doopy für das Herführen.

Ein frischer Wind, neue Ideen, immer vorwärts führt der Weg.
So führte mich der heutige Weg zum letzten Standort des 👻 von Grand Luxembourg Quest I (virtual part) den ich nun am 28. Mai 2026 um 15:38 Uhr erfolgreich loggen konnte.

Viele Grüße sendet Elly Nilsson aus dem schönen Weinort Nittel.

www.Fewo-Nittel.de</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363837066"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-27T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2562804">Muller&amp;Thurgau</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">A je to tady. Dlouho plánovaná velká expedice v sestavě happy.ov, Lo36, Müller&amp;Thurgau a taxoft vyrazila napříč Evropou. A cestou jsme navštívili i tuto virtuálku.
Díky za keš. 

Die lange geplante große Expedition mit happy.ov, Lo36, Müller&amp;Thurgau und taxoft startete quer durch Europa. Unterwegs besuchten wir diese Cache.
Vielen Dank für den Cache!

The long-planned big expedition with happy.ov, Lo36, Müller&amp;Thurgau and taxoft set off across Europe. On the way we visited this cache.
Thanks for the cache.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363831241"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-27T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1570773">taxoft</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">1/?/? Day 5. Visited on a journey with friends. More info later.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363830024"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-27T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1570773">taxoft</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Fifth stage</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363830837"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-26T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1570773">taxoft</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Fourth stage</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="22.123883" lon="113.564083"><time>2003-03-11T00:00:00</time><name>GCE6DB</name><desc>Macau's Second - Coloane's Highest (China) by ooga booga</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCE6DB</url><urlname>Macau's Second - Coloane's Highest (China)</urlname><sym>Geocache Found</sym><type>Geocache|Virtual Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="59099" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Macau's Second - Coloane's Highest (China)</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>ooga booga</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="68818">ooga booga</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Virtual Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Virtual</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Macao</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>A virtual cache on Macau's Coloane Island that offers some nice vistas.
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PLEASE NOTE THAT YOU MUST PHYSICALLY VISIT THE COORDINATES LISTED IN THIS VIRTUAL CACHE IN ORDER TO LOG THIS CACHE.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition to the mainland peninsula of Macau, the former Portuguese colony and current SAR (Special Administrative Region) of China also consists of two islands, Taipa and Coloane. Taipa is rapidly becoming a boring Hong Kong-style conglomeration of apartment towers, but Coloane is still largely rural and mountainous, quite a contrast from the densely urban Macau mainland. With small villages, temples, and beaches, it's a great place to come spend an afternoon exploring.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This cache is a nice hike up Alto de Coloane, in the heart of the island. The city bus system is fast, extensive, and efficient, and there are a number of buses you can take from Macau to get out here. I used #26, but I believe 21/21A, 25/25A, and 26A will also work. There's bilingual schedules and route descriptions at almost every stop - basically any bus that has Coloane listed on its route will work. A good place to catch island-bound buses is near the Casino Lisboa, and fares should be less than MOP5.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Once you come across the causeway from Taipa to Coloane, start looking on your left for a children's theme park. Once you pass the main gate for this, hit the button to indicate you want the next stop, and you should be let off at a large grey entranceway, next to a &lt;s&gt;Mobil&lt;/s&gt;[UPDATE 4/5/04 - apparently it's now an Esso] station. These two are hard to miss, so if you don't see the theme park just hit the 'next stop' button at these and walk a few hundred meters back.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;From the entryway, it's about a 45-minute walk up Alto de Coloane - you'll pass an arboretum, several parks, and a creepy set of buildings that looked to me like an abandoned Portuguese military barracks. At the top, you'll see the reason for your hike (in addition to the views), and a tri-lingual plaque at the posted coordinates. I originally came up here intending to place a physical cache, but there wasn't really any place to hide one, so I just scoped out this virtual cache instead. At the end of the text is a date - for confirmation of your visit, email me that date. Don't post your answer in your log, even if encrypted.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(p.s. Freeewilly's cache notwithstanding, this is actually the highest place in all of Macau. However, his cache is certainly near the highest point in Macau proper. Also, if you're pressed for time or don't feel up to the walk, it's possible to take a taxi to here, which would make it about a 1/1.5 - but if you're going to take the easy way out, I'll leave it up to you to figure out how to get all the way to the cache!)&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Other Chinese caches by ooga booga Haerbin, Stalin Style A-maze-ing Old Summer Palace West Lake - Three Pagodas West Lake - Mid Lake Pavilion It's a Bird! It's a Plane! Hsien Ku Fung (Hong Kong) Mad Dogs and Englishmen (Hong Kong) Macau's Second - Coloane's Highest (Macau) Green Lotus Peak, Yangshuo&lt;br /&gt;
 &lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1362248046"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-10T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="38568466">DDThee</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">A member of our team is on vacation in Hong Kong and make a trip to Macao to visit this virtual cache too get a nice smiley on the card.

DDThee say thanks to the Cache Owner for placing the cache and making our worldwide hobby possible.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1361202964"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-10T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="26940951">Le20</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Today I made a trip to Macau! I took the ferry from Hong Kong early in the day, which already made the adventure feel special. Once I arrived, I continued my journey by bus across the island, using public transport to reach different cache locations efficiently and explore more of the area. Along the way, I enjoyed a beautiful walk through a mix of urban streets, nature, historic areas, and more peaceful spots. Each cache brought me to a new place and gave me a great impression of the city’s unique blend of cultures and scenery. A really enjoyable day of caching, travelling, and exploring. Thanks to all COs for placing and maintaining the caches!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1359148112"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-04T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="47925774">sansan_</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">坐上轻轨才发现今天周一没有接驳车上山顶好崩溃 五点冒着小雨我们还是决定上山了 一路上爬得死去活来 不过即使是搭大巴最后的一百米也需要徒步上去见妈祖 入口处还有一棵斜着生长的树遮挡她的真容 希望妈祖娘娘保佑一切顺利 FP&amp;TFTC！</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1359114296"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-04T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="38784139">Nicky_goforit</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">we finally climb it up and make it through. TFTC
May 4, 2026 18:02
😃# 2211</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1359228228"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-04T03:26:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="47701209">Maaaxxxxx</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">看了大巴时间表很久，也以为能够赶上最后一班，谁曾想周一压根没有大巴，三人在山下犹豫了很久最后还是来都来了，一路上不知道喊了多少次快死了但最后还是没有后退任何一步，希望妈祖能看到我们的毅力并保佑我们吧🤗
FP&amp;TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="291376440"><groundspeak:date>2013-01-28T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2089726">travelingGeek</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">What a great adventure!  I'm about to head back to the US after many days and nights working in Macau and I was worried I wouldn't manage to get in a cache here.  

So...  This can be done by taxi.  I did it in exactly 1 hour from my hotel in the coti central complex.  I had a great taxi driver that spoke pretty good english which was a good thing.  I started with the hotel writing out where I wanted to go and giving me a tourist map.  The map came in handy after we went to far and went up the wrong mountain.

Got nearly there are realized I had to walk the last 2/10th mi nearly straight up.   The Taxi was still there when I got back and I was even greeted in English by another visitor coming down from the statute as I was huffing my way up.

It was a grand adventure for my first find in macau made extra special by it being the oldest cache in Macau.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="42.013283" lon="21.61295"><time>2002-12-23T00:00:00</time><name>GCB82C</name><desc>Tupolev 154 by Damyan The Bogdan &amp; Vinas Jr</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCB82C</url><urlname>Tupolev 154</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="47148" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Tupolev 154</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Damyan The Bogdan &amp; Vinas Jr</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="90510">thebogdan</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="0">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="0">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="1">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="9" inc="0">Significant hike</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="33" inc="1">Motorcycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="35" inc="1">Off-road vehicles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="37" inc="1">Horses</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="29" inc="0">Telephone nearby</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>3</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>North Macedonia</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Nice closelook to some airplanes.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>You can have nice view to the departing airplanes from Skopje International Airport - Alexander The Great. You can climb the small hill above the cache. The first airplane that flew above the cache was Tupolev 154B so we gave the cache that name.

If you go by car from Skopje, use the road via Ilinden, Marino, Bunardzik, Ajvatovci.</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Plastic cylindrical black container, hanging on a branch of tree at hight of human.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364921533"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5533004">Endzan</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">After spending two wonderful days exploring Skopje, it was finally time to start our road trip around North Macedonia. We decided to begin with a special cache – the oldest cache in the country.

We parked our car near the monastery and enjoyed the walk to the cache location. Upon arrival, we found that the container was lying on the ground. After signing the logbook, we placed it a bit higher in a fork of a branch to help keep it safer and more visible.

While we were here, two airplanes flew directly overhead, adding an unexpected touch to the experience and making the visit even more memorable.

Thank you for maintaining this historic cache and for bringing us to this location!

Greetings from Latvia. 🇱🇻</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364878045"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-24T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1177288">Kuchenmops</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">In Vorbereitung auf den Trip zu Pfingsten mit den Jungs habe ich meinen Blick über die Karte schweifen lassen um die möglichst interessanten Caches herauszufiltern. Das Alter ist so ein Kriterium, also ist dieser Ort mit dem Alleinstellungsmerkmal als ältestem Cache des Landes ein Muss. Wir fuhren nach dem Frühstück los und parkten am Kloster. Von dort war es dann nicht mehr weit zu Fuß bis zum Cache. Neben dem guten Ausblick, sofern er noch nicht zugewachsen war, blieb als kurze Schrecksekunde die am Cache auftauchende Horde Hunde im Gedächtnis. Diese trotteten dann langsam von dannen, etwas mulmig war mir aber schon zumute. Wie man beim Lesen dieser Zeilen sicher vermutet - der (Austausch)Behälter wurde gefunden und ich wurde nicht gefressen. Also alles gut, besonders die im Anschluss folgende Besichtigung der Klosteranlage war spannend. Danke für den Cache, möge er noch lange erhalten bleiben!


---


Подготвувајќи се за патувањето за Педесетница со момците, го оставив погледот да талка по мапата за да ги одредам најинтересните скриени наоѓалишта. Возраста е еден таков критериум, па затоа оваа локација - која се одликува со уникатниот статус на домаќин на најстарото скриено наоѓалиште во земјата - беше апсолутно задолжителна. Тргнавме по појадокот и паркиравме кај манастирот. Оттаму, до скриеното наоѓалиште беше само кратка прошетка. Освен прекрасниот поглед - под претпоставка дека сè уште не беше целосно обраснато - единствениот момент што ми остана во сеќавање беше краткиот страв предизвикан од глутница кучиња што одеднаш се појавија токму на местото на скриеното наоѓалиште. На крајот полека се оддалечија, иако јас се чувствував малку нелагодно. Како што сигурно заклучивте од читањето на овие редови: контејнерот (заменски) беше пронајден, а јас не бев изеден. Значи, сè е во ред - а последователната обиколка на манастирскиот имот беше особено фасцинантна. Ви благодарам за скриеното наоѓалиште; нека остане тука долго време!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363337763"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-24T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6516000">ebatt</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Pfingstzeit ist Balkanzeit. Dieses Jahr bin ich mit den Jungs zu einem Roadtrip von Sofia nach Skopje und zurück unterwegs.

An Tag zwei begann unser eigentlicher Roadtrip. Wir holten unseren Mietwagen ab und fuhren von Bulgarien ins Nachbarland Nordmazedonien. 

Heute begannen wir mit einem Abstecher zum ältesten Cache des Landes. Wir stellten das Auto am Kloster ab und wanderten durch die Zypressenhügel zur Dose. Dort warteten 5 Hunde auf uns, die zum Glück schnell das Weite suchten.
Die Minidose hatten wir schnell gefunden. So ein Oldie ist doch immer wieder nice. 

Vielen Dank fürs Legen. TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1359714576"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-08T13:17:54</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1285743">krtecci</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This is the original one and the oldest in North Macedonia, which makes it very special. The original container is long gone, only replaced by a small tic tac box. I parked at the monastery which I recommend, the view is great from here and the monastery itself is also cute. Thanks for the great oldie!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1359278402"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-04T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="7917486">SteinernerMann</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Der Balkan-Roadtrip führt DieMarion, Drumpldeer, Zamonien und mich durch 13 wunderschönen Länder, in viele sehenswerte Städte und zu tollen Geocaches. Wir haben teilweise mit unserem Teamnamen 4HB geloggt

Hier machten wir eine kleine Wanderung</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="-18.993317" lon="47.53105"><time>2006-12-19T00:00:00</time><name>GCZWRQ</name><desc>Exotic by kiostsang</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCZWRQ</url><urlname>Exotic</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="509324" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Exotic</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>kiostsang</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="886321">kiostsang</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="42" inc="1">Needs maintenance</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Madagascar</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>The cache is a traditional one which is well hidden and I have friends checking and maintaining it regularly for nice local gifts.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>The cache is originally hidden with 2 local coloured rocks, which of course you would like to collect as a cache present. It also contains a logbook, and a pen to register your visit. Hope you will enjoy it.</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Look for the wall, and go at the back of the garden.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1293015406"><groundspeak:date>2025-04-21T13:49:01</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="18990911">Knagur Green</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Due to no response from the CO after the request to maintain or replace the cache, I am archiving it to, stop it showing on the listings  and/or to create place for the geocaching community.

The [Geocache Maintenance guideline](http://www.geocaching.com/about/guidelines.aspx#cachemaintenance) explains a CO's responsibility towards checking and maintaining the cache when problems are reported. 

Please note that if geocaches are archived by a reviewer or Geocaching HQ for lack of maintenance, they are not eligible for unarchival. This is explained in the [Help Center](http://support.groundspeak.com//index.php?pg=kb.page&amp;id=70)

If the CO feels that this cache has been archived in error please feel free to contact me within 30 days,  via email or message via my profile ,quoting the GC number concerned

Thank you for understanding

Knagur Green
Groundspeak Volunteer Reviewer</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1282204621"><groundspeak:date>2025-02-23T00:43:38</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Unknown</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="18990911">Knagur Green</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Maintaining the listing is part of a CO's responsibility. There are numerous fake logs on here. The CO will need to check the log sheet against them and delete all fake logs

 The physical cache also seems to be missing , the CO will need to check to see if it has been moved or is missing and replace in the correct location 
 Normal 30 day warning as per guidelines applies after which the cache could be archived. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1280890099"><groundspeak:date>2025-02-12T10:11:52</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Needs Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="48687423">DMT_Germany</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Der Cache ist leider nicht mehr vorhanden. 
Das Gelände ist jetzt eine Druckerei.
Die Logs sind alle Fake. Bitte überprüfen sie die logeinträge. Ich habe den owner mehrfach angeschrieben. Keiner antwortet. 

</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1274253624"><groundspeak:date>2024-12-23T14:51:09</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="51482147">FamillePrudentBès</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">J’ai un 1️⃣ L de lait j’ai deux j’ai deux ans je </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1273378015"><groundspeak:date>2024-12-13T19:16:14</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="51751539">o70</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">W</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="3.156383" lon="101.712967"><time>2002-10-24T00:00:00</time><name>GC9FDB</name><desc>Welcome to KL by Barnyard Dawg &amp; TimBish</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC9FDB</url><urlname>Welcome to KL</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Virtual Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="40923" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Welcome to KL</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Barnyard Dawg &amp; TimBish</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="6504205">Barnyard Dawg</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Virtual Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Virtual</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="1">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="40" inc="0">Stealth required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="30" inc="1">Picnic tables nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="59" inc="1">Food nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="27" inc="1">Drinking water nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="64" inc="0">Tree climbing required</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Malaysia</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Welcome geocacher to Kuala Lumpur, colloquially referred to as "KL".
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to KL&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For over two decades, Welcome to KL, Malaysia's oldest and only classic Virtual Cache, has been a beacon for many visiting geocachers, eager to admire the famous Petronas Twin Towers and its surroundings.  The game we all love has changed significantly since the creation of this cache, and where once this cache was a rare loner, today it is surrounded by many more caches hidden in the most prominent locations.  Thank you for visiting, and happy geocaching! &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="http://geocaching.nouveaustere.com/GC9FDB/klcc_park.jpg" width="600" height="338" alt="KLCC Park, view toward the Petronas towers" /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
KLCC Park, view toward the Petronas towers. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Petronas Twin Towers&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Petronas Towers are a pair of 88-storey supertall skyscrapers in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia, standing at 451.9 metres (1,483 feet). From 1998 to 2004, they were officially designated as the tallest buildings in the world until they were surpassed by the completion of the Taipei 101 in 2004. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Petronas Towers remained the tallest buildings in Malaysia until 2019, when they were surpassed by The Exchange 106. The Petronas Towers are a major landmark of Kuala Lumpur, along with the nearby Kuala Lumpur Tower and &lt;a href="https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC892FW"&gt;Merdeka 118&lt;/a&gt;, and are visible in many places across the city.  To this day, they are still the world's tallest twin skyscrapers. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How to claim this Virtual Cache? &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Enter the park and take a selfie (optional) and/or a photo of a thumbs-up, peace-symbol (V) or personal item with the Petronas Twin Towers clearly showing in the back. Happy geocaching! 
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Don't forget the logging task!</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364190124"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="51426009">Biniballs</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thanks for the virtual cache. We were caught in a thunderstorm today. By the time it stopped we were wet and tired. Despite that we managed to see the Petronas towers and the fountains. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362388708"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-21T09:24:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="9822129">daanmari</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Voor de tweede keer in Kuala Lumpur en wat is er veel veranderd. Maar deze iconische gebouwen typeren KL. Alleen zijn ze nu omgeven door meerdere hoge gebouwen</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362309041"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-20T15:55:49</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="43615850">abw0815</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We're spending three days in Kuala Lumpur. Today we spent the whole day strolling through the city and visiting various geocaches. We also took a walk in the beautiful KLCC Park and take a picture for this Virtual Cache. It is a beautiful place here. Thank you so much for this cache. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1361153255"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-15T23:22:24</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8777394">barucci</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">And there it is, the iconic Petronas Twin Towers! Tftc!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1361083602"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-15T19:40:06</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="27785300">spezlekv</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Das erste Mal am Tower. Wow. Danke an den Owner für die Chance.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="3.886267" lon="72.817"><time>2002-12-14T00:00:00</time><name>GCD212</name><desc>Greetings from Paradise by DerMaus</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCD212</url><urlname>Greetings from Paradise</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Virtual Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="53778" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Greetings from Paradise</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>DerMaus</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="83077">DerMaus</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Virtual Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Virtual</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="0">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="0">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="59" inc="1">Food nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="27" inc="1">Drinking water nearby</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>4</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Maldives</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>If you´ve got the opportunity to get there, you should reward yourself by logging a cache. It's nearly impossible to get the correct answers via googleEarth.

Wer schon mal da ist, sollte sich zusätzlich belohnen, indem er einen Cache loggen kann. Es ist nahezu unmöglich, die richtige Lösung über googleEarth zu ermitteln.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>The requirement for logging this cache is to mail me the texture and length of where you're standing. Sorry to have hidden only a virtual cache, it's a little bit to far away from my home to place a real one there.

Die Bedingung zum Loggen besteht in der Aufgabe, mir eine Mail zu senden, in der der Untergrund, auf dem Du stehst, und seine Länge beschrieben ist. Leider ist es nur ein virtueller Cache, aber er ist doch etwas weit weg, um ihn zu pflegen.

Il requisito per abbattere questo nascondiglio è alla posta me il tessuto e la lunghezza di dove lei stanno in piedi. Dolente di avere nascosto soltanto un nascondiglio virtuale, è un po'a lontano dalla mia casa per collocare un reale un lí.</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Of course, you're not standing in the water!
Wer im Wasser steht, macht was falsch!
Certo, lei non stanno in piedi nell'acqua! 
</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1357529480"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-27T13:15:24</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6596893">pitfeder</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Ein weiterer TB sammelt Kilometer. 

Gruss Pitfeder 🇨🇭👍🏼🪶</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1357325560"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-26T22:17:51</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6596893">pitfeder</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Einem TB noch Kilometer geben. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1356493977"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-22T00:33:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6596893">pitfeder</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Mit meinem geliebten Bebbigirl bin ich hier eine Woche auf dieser schönen Insel. Meine Frau hat diese Destination gewählt, weil hier der älteste Cache der Malediven ist. 
Und wir wurden nicht enttäuscht. 
Super freundliche Begrüssung mit feinem Ananassaft und Tips. 
Geräumiges komfortables Wasserfront-Haus. 
Kulinarisch hervorragendes Essen. 
Natürlich bald mal zum Cachenullpunkt. 
Und und umgesehen. 
Meine Frau hat die Antwort geschickt und Minuten später haben wir die Logfreigabe bekommen. 
Beim Besuch des Virtuellen umrundete auch ein über 1m grosser (kleiner?) Riffhai das Objekt. 
Was für ein Erlebnis. 

Danke „DerMaus“ fürs Auslegen. 
Natürlich gibt es noch ein blaues Favoband an die nächste Palme gebunden. 

Wir freuen uns auf Erkunden der Unterwasserwelt mit Schnorchel und Taucherbrille. 

Gruss Pitfeder, Switzerland 🪶🇨🇭</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1356493745"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-21T19:19:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6603330">Bebbigirl</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Unsere Ferien nach dem ältesten Geocache der Malediven 🇲🇻 ausgesucht. Hier ist es wunderschön und man wird mit einem Lächeln und Winken begrüsst. 
Mein lieblings Ehemann „Pitfeder“ ist begeistert…
Zum Nullpunkt in Flip Flops ( Holz-Boden sehr heiss ) spaziert. Tja was sieht man hier? Viele Fische und auch Haie und viel sonstiges.

Danke für den tollen alten Cache

Grüessli us Basel (CH 🇨🇭)</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1341405839"><groundspeak:date>2026-01-09T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1119165">Powerful_Mind</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Freut mich sehr, dass ich diesen schönen Virtual nun in meine Sammlung aufnehmen kann. 🤗
Da ich die Malediven liebe, gibt's hier einen dicken, fetten FP. 💙
Vielen Dank! 🏖☀️🌴🥥</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="14.197133333333333" lon="-3.523433333333333"><time>2002-02-25T00:00:00</time><name>GCC082</name><desc>Afrika2001 by Greg and Chris</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCC082</url><urlname>Afrika2001</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="49282" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Afrika2001</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Greg and Chris</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="42866">chrisvdb</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>3</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Mali</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Nice cache in the magic Dogon area in Mali.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>See http://afrika2001.org !</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1208470781"><groundspeak:date>2023-12-14T10:10:35</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="45387002">BobroobTaggiasco</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thanks ✌️🙏🧭</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1207676487"><groundspeak:date>2023-12-03T23:42:59</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="41255511">KamTheCool</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Cgg</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1203679755"><groundspeak:date>2023-10-31T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="47785192">gigi010</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">trovato in poco tempo</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1106675573"><groundspeak:date>2022-06-27T16:26:51</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="41576813">MrAdromeda</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Ez</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="992070340"><groundspeak:date>2021-01-31T19:56:45</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="29689884">Vossykind</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Gut</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="35.852283" lon="14.397117"><time>2004-01-04T00:00:00</time><name>GCHEQ7</name><desc>The Ring of Clapham Junction by lucentio (Adopted by Gremxul)</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCHEQ7</url><urlname>The Ring of Clapham Junction</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="109501" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>The Ring of Clapham Junction</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>lucentio (Adopted by Gremxul)</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="1401481">Gremxul</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Micro</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Malta</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>&lt;b&gt;*THE OLDEST ACTIVE CACHE ON THE MALTESE ISLANDS*&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The cache is placed within the area of the world famous cart ruts in Malta, called Clapham Junction.
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>The cache consits of one small plastic box containing only the travel bug "The Master Ring".&lt;br /&gt;
You can reach the location very easy by car - there is a car park nearby - or by bus 81 from Valetta via Rabat to Dingli. Leave the bus at Buskett Gardens. From there on it is a nice walk. Just follow the signs "Clapham Junction" or "Cart Ruts".&lt;br /&gt;
It is better to wear good hiking boots!&lt;br /&gt;
Look out for a small cavern with a large bush. The cache is not in the cavern ...
&lt;p&gt;All the rocks and stones you seen in this area are of significant ecological value and shelter entire eco-systems beneath them.&lt;br /&gt;
PLEASE MAKE SURE TO REPLACE ALL ROCKS/STONES (GENTLY) EXACTLY AS YOU FOUND THEM!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Completing this cache entitles you to TWO Geotrophy Badges!!!&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Click on the badges below for more information:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.geotrophy.net/countries.php?stat=25"&gt;&lt;img src="http://www.geotrophy.net/content/kat1-1-25.png" /&gt; &lt;img src="http://www.geotrophy.net/content/kat2-1-25.png" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Facing the small 'arch', the cache is to your left, near the mouth of the arch. Hmm...what's that small pile of stones hiding??</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364138356"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="18357547">POKEMISTRZ</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">TFTC

+FAV</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363730795"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-26T17:41:02</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6043584">De Lampjes</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Vanmorgen zijn we gaan wandelen in de bossen (Buskett Gardens). We hebben via een aantal traditionels een mooie ronde gemaakt. Wat een bijzondere plek. TFTC </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362115432"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-19T13:53:22</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4551227">hopsl1</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">TFTC 

Hopsl1</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362115438"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-19T13:53:14</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5182029">hexe68</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Gefunden mit Hopsl 1 ! 💚TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1361952890"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-18T15:56:18</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="11730159">Team Valtho</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Today we continue geocaching in Malta. We are visiting archaeological sites in Rabat and Mdina. But also a fun challenge cache and the oldest cache in Malta. We found or visited this cache as well, thanks.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="7.199283" lon="171.0523"><time>2003-04-25T00:00:00</time><name>GCG0DN</name><desc>B-24J "Liberator" by MiketheFiddler</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCG0DN</url><urlname>B-24J "Liberator"</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Virtual Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="65960" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>B-24J "Liberator"</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>MiketheFiddler</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="70165">MiketheFiddler</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Virtual Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Virtual</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Marshall Islands</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>This virtual cache is the submerged wreck of U.S. B-24J "Liberator" bomber, which crash-landed on a reef in the Majuro atoll during WWII.
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;center&gt;&lt;img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/gs-geo-images/31518ea7-4130-469c-a053-8b694de702b6_l.jpg" alt="Geocache of the Week banner" /&gt;&lt;/center&gt;
&lt;center&gt;&lt;img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/gs-geo-images/bd9b401a-6bed-4a0b-9c26-63ce971018f6_l.jpg" alt="B-24 wing and engines" width="333" height="250" /&gt;&lt;/center&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This cache is the submerged wreck of U.S. B-24J "Liberator" bomber, which crash-landed on a reef in the Majuro atoll during WWII.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The difficulty ratings for finding this cache lie in the remoteness of the Marshall Islands, and the fact that the wreck is almost completely submerged, about 2.6 miles offshore.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Majuro atoll is a mere 4-5 hour flight southwest of Honolulu. The preferred way to get there is via the famous &lt;a href="https://hub.united.com/united-island-hopper-serves-lifeline-2417909306.html"&gt;"Island Hopper"&lt;/a&gt;, currently operated by United Airlines. The trip to Majuro is well worth it for the beaches and reefs alone. The water visibility is quite good and there are many beautiful beaches and coral reefs available for beachcombing, snorkeling and diving. The Marshallese are generally very hospitable, and the fresh sashimi is truly wonderful. Local handicrafters make beautiful baskets, necklaces and stick charts of local materials. The Marshallese are considered by some to have been the premier sailors and navigators of the ancient Pacific. To the eyes of Euro-centric sailors, the local sailing outriggers initially seem quite primitive. However, on second and third looks, some surprising and counterintuitive complexities are evident in these speedy and sophisticated little craft.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To reach the cache site, your choices are to wade out to the site at low tide, swim, or hire one of the local dive operators to take you out in a boat. If you are a strong swimmer and have snorkel gear, the swim out from Laura Beach is quite pleasant, and allows ample opportunities to view colorful corals, clams, and fish. In any event, you will need a mask, snorkel and underwater camera to log this cache.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On December 28, 1943, this particular bomber sustained significant damage due to intense fighter opposition over its target area of Taroa. It limped back toward its base in Tarawa on 2 engines, making it back as far as Majuro, where the pilot crash-landed on the reef. The crew were taken into custody by the Japanese, who then controlled Majuro. Their fate is not known conclusively, although local oral history states that they were beheaded by the Japanese. Execution was, alas, a common outcome for downed U.S. airmen in the Pacific, so this is very likely the fate of this aircrew.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For a much more detailed account of this plane and its history, please visit Dirk Spennemann's &lt;a href="http://micronesia.csu.edu.au/Marshalls/html/B24/B24_Majuro.html"&gt;excellent account online&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;center&gt;&lt;img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/gs-geo-images/42df3a67-a50b-4636-a451-a819a1b2ca93_l.jpg" alt width="250" height="313" name="MiketheSnorkler" /&gt;&lt;/center&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Depending on the stage of the tide when you reach this site, the plane may or may not be visible above the water. When I visited the wreck site at slack tide three days ago, the tips of the propellers were just visible above the waterline. I was able to walk along the top of the wing with my head well above the water. Most of the aluminum wing is still intact, with three engines still attached. Most of the fuselage has disappeared, probably due to wave and tidal action over the years. Several other fragments of the plane are still visible nearby, including a Sperry Ball turret, the belly machine gun unit with one barrel of the machine guns still visible. This fragment is located a few feet to the rear of wing, and slightly to the right of midline.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;center&gt;&lt;img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/gs-geo-images/0e85d1a3-b13e-41c0-bb39-c60f4581e625_l.jpg" alt="Belly machine gun" width="376" height="250" /&gt;&lt;/center&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To log this cache, you must do the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;On the remaining machine gun, just above the perforated and air-cooled section of the barrel, a single word is still visible cast into the metal. E-mail that word to me -- please do not post it on this site in your log. Corrosion or vandalism may eventually wipe this away. However, it remains so easily legible after 60 years in salt water that I suspect it will endure for at least another decade or so of geocaching.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Post an underwater picture of you in front of one of the remaining props of this plane. Also feel free to post any other pictures of the plane or Majuro, other than the word on the machine gun barrel. Obviously these must be pictures taken after finding this as a virtual cache - not previously taken vacation shots or internet downloads.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take a moment to reflect on the many brave people who died on both sides of WWII in the Pacific Theater, and what life must have been like in those days, navigating the endless blue Pacific without a GPS....&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Happy hunting!!&lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1348616076"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-07T05:33:56</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="90014">Landmaus</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We found this geocache on our world tour in 2025/26. 
The trip includes 22 countries and goes all around the world. 
Start was in Kanada, followed by Chile and 20 Pacific Islands till Mongolia.
All the time we enjoyed the landscape, the people and the geocaches.
Thanks to all owners for hiding and maintaining of their caches.
Best regards Landmaus

PS: Answers send by Trebbi </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1333274576"><groundspeak:date>2025-11-06T10:31:09</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="42471693">UnicornDonutz</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Wreck is intact, in very shallow water. Better snorkel than dive. Choppy day, loads of current, shallow reef that separates Laura side of lagoon from open ocean. Site highly tide and weather dependent. Strong recommendation to visit with local dive/snorkel crew operator (we went out with Hiro from RayCrew).

Remaining gun encrusted with corals, couldn't make out data. Visited 6 July 2025. Definitely worth the logistics getting out there and tons of pristine coral heads to explore out on that side of the lagoon.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1183352303"><groundspeak:date>2023-04-19T13:31:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2028113">Sirusc</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found around 9.50

Yesterday I spent a lot of time trying to find someone to sail me out here with a lot of help from Pacific International Inc (PII). We tried a lot of different options, which didn’t work out, but in the end they found someone. I believe I paied 450 USD for the boat trip.
I had a great time on the boat and here at the virtual. Thanks for showing the place :) 


About today:
This was a very long day for me. I started the day by waking up in Robert Reimers in Marshall Islands. Then I took a taxi to get to a boat I had managed to book yesterday. They sailed me out to the virtual. After a good time at the virtual, we attempted a traditional on the way back, but sadly with a dnf.
In the evening I took a flight to Hawaii, which landed around 1 in the night (still today, because it crossed the date line). I spent the night at the airport.
In the morning I found out how the buses work and found my hostel in Waikiki.
Then I took a short walk in the mountains and found a large.
Back down in Waikiki I found a challenge cache and a wherigo before attending an event that luckily another tourists had created. I wanted to create my own event, but time ran away from me.
At the event I met the locals Cat and Skot, who I spent a lot of time with during my week here, and they helped me a lot :) 
After the event I found a traditional together with the event hosts and a Letterbox alone and then back to my hostel.


About my time in Marshall Islands:
Country number 81 :) 
I was here for 2 days. I came in the evening, slept twice at Robert Reimers, and then left in the evening.
When I arrived at Robert Reimers in the evening, I found out that they had me in an expensive room, but luckily I was able to change it to a cheaper room.
I spent the first say trying to find someone to sail me out to the virtual. This was not easy, but ended up succeeding :) 
The 2nd day I sailed out to the virtual, and on the way back I attempted the traditional, but sadly with a dnf


About my vacation:
My first trip around the world :) 
On my way around the world I visited 9 countries, and 7 of them were new for me. This also brought me to Oceania for the first time.
After this vacation I’ve geocached in 81 countries and 5 continents :) 

I live in Denmark
The starting point for planning this vacation was Singapore, where I attended the World Sport Stacking Championships both as a stacker and a national coach (by the way I became world champion in 25+ timed 3-6-3 relay with a mixed danish and german team :)).
I wanted to do most of my travel after the world championships, so I was done with stacking and could focus on geocaching.
With Singapore as my starting point, I looked at my map of geocaching countries I haven’t been in yet and decided I wanted to make it a trip around the world.
So my plan ended up being:
Qatar - Sri Lanka - Singapore - Brunei - Philippines - Guam - Micronesia - Marshall Islands - Hawaii
Most of these places were only 1-2 days. Singapore was 5 days (but very little geocaching).
Hawaii had by far the most caches I wanted for my statistics, so I decided to spend a full week here. Which turned out to be a great decision I’m very happy about.
I also had short visits to Sweden at the start of the vacation and California and United Kingdom at the end of it.
At the places it was possible (so mostly in Hawaii), I focused on the different D/T matrices and calendars with project-gc BadgeGen addons. At the places where that wasn’t possible, I just got whichever caches were there

Thanks a lot to MiketheFiddler for this cache :) 
Simon from Denmark</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="838443592"><groundspeak:date>2019-03-26T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="13792192">HariSree</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">FITW FMZ
I still can't figure it out what's in me that drives me to do such crazy things. Being a very very bad swimmer, I still decided to do this and I believe it was a fantastic experience. Myself and FMZ had this in our must do list before flying from NZ, but were not sure how to organize someone to take us there. Luckily Hiro became our Hero.. LOL. With the help of Ray crew, FMZ and a life jacket, I did mange to snorkel around this beautiful spot. It was bit scary when the sea became bit rough and I couldn't manage to swim back to the boat and FMZ had to swim dragging me. but.. WOOOO-HOOO I did it. Thanks a lot Mike for placing a cache and bringing us here. 

Planning is already underway for a huge celebration of geocaching in New Zealand in 2020.
There is a lot to celebrate: 20 years of geocaching worldwide, and 20 years since the first geocache was hidden outside the US - you guessed it, in New Zealand!
So mark these dates in your calendar and make sure you're in Auckland for the 23rd to 26th October, 2020. Find more details on www.nzmega.com</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="836404441"><groundspeak:date>2019-03-26T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="673399">funkymunkyzone</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Wow, what a truly amazing spot to go geocaching.  Visited here with harisree with the aid of Raycrew dive shop located at the Marshall Islands Resort where we were staying.  While everything else we tried to organise at the MIR was a nightmare, this one was easy because we just went and dealt with Hiro (Raycrew) directly and despite him thinking we were a bit crazy, and laughing at/with us a lot, it was all good and we set the date and time to head off.  Incidentally, he is also one of few who are licenced to dive/snorkel around historical sites, so that's a bonus.

Woke up this morning to horrible weather - it had been raining heavily all night, and the wind was howling.  We ahd already been warned that if it was windy, there would not be sheltered there and might not be possible to snorkel there.  But then as we got ready and had breakfast first the wind dropped and then the skies began to clear a little.

So we decided it was a go.  Packed our gear into the boat and headed off.  Calm at first and then it got pretty rough as we crossed the atoll.  But when we got near to the wreck, even the sun came out (and got me pretty burnt) and the wind wasn't as bad anymore.  Still some decent waves coming across, but not like the near 2m swell out in the middle of the atoll.

I had my phone, which, while already waterproof, I had inside a waterproof bag, and took 100s of photos all around the wreck, and of the remaining gun.  It was difficult as the phone kept behaving weirdly under the water, and a lot of the photos are a bit fuzzy from being takign through plastic, but still good enough photos.

Such an awesome spot, so glad to be abel to come here and find this.  This is what geocaching is all about!  Thanks Mike for bringing us here!!!  I will add a FP and I know harisree will too, so we will bring it up to 75% (should be 100%!!!)

TFTC!!! [:D][:D][:D][:D][:D]

***[======== NZ Mega 2020 ========](http://nzmega.com)***

Planning for the [NZ Mega 2020](http://nzmega.com) event is well underway. It will be held in Auckland over Labour Weekend, 23 to 26 October 2020. It's going to be a massive celebration of geocaching:

* 20 years of geocaching worldwide.
* 20 years since New Zealand had the very first geocache hidden outside of USA.
* And it's 2020 - all the 20s!

Talk to your geo-friends and start planning to be part of [this event](http://nzmega.com) - you won't want to miss it!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="14.602516666666666" lon="-61.06876666666667"><time>2003-02-04T00:00:00</time><name>GCD469</name><desc>I can sea four miles by madmax</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCD469</url><urlname>I can sea four miles</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Virtual Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="54377" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>I can sea four miles</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>madmax</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="15178">madmax &amp; tweety</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Virtual Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Virtual</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="42" inc="1">Needs maintenance</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Martinique</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>The first Cache on Martinique</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>  This statue is in a park on the island of Martinique. It is within walking distance of both cruise ship docks.
To log this cache please include a photo with you and your GPS in front of the statue. Or send me the numbers on the NW side of the base.</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1363497887"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-25T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="12997539">isanaïs</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Premier jour en Martinique, en balade à Fort de France ! De l'animation au parc des savanes en ce lundi férié, malheureusement la statue a disparu 😉 Photo pour preuve avec le socle...vide ! 

MPLC !</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1357980962"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-29T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="14838090">Arralla</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Le socle est vide.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1357039617"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-25T09:39:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="15353317">Carlitofirst</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Merci pour la cache </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1356880791"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-24T13:20:45</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="31133416">Hamsterhannah</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found the location, but there is no more statue. Attached is a pic of me at the base where the statue once was. Visiting from Sebring, FL, USA on the Caribbean Princess cruise ship </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1356884135"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-24T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4543306">PghPowers</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I appreciate these virtuals especially while traveling on the Caribbean Princess. Unfortunately the statue and plaque are not longer there so the attached photo only shows the barren base. Thanks for the cache from Pennsylvania USA. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="-20.1102" lon="57.5784"><time>2003-09-22T00:00:00</time><name>GCH02Z</name><desc>Garden Treasure by Vagabund, supported by cachemates1</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCH02Z</url><urlname>Garden Treasure</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="95419" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Garden Treasure</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Vagabund, supported by cachemates1</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="96256">Vagabund</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="0">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="0">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="40" inc="1">Stealth required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="30" inc="1">Picnic tables nearby</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Mauritius</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>The cache is located in the beautiful public botanical Garden of Pamplemousses. You can park your car free at S 20° 06.279 E 057° 34.822.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Entrance fee is 200 Rupees for non Mauritians.&lt;/b&gt;
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>This Cache is hidden in a big stonewall near the ground. To find the right stonewall use the pictures as a hint.&lt;br /&gt;
The cache is covered by a bright stone.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Be aware of the muggles!
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Next to a stone park bench.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1318139624"><groundspeak:date>2025-08-16T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="36679925">Cavabara</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Dopo mesi e mesi di programmazione finalmente è arrivato il momento della vacanza estiva che quest'anno ricade sulla stupenda Mauritius; partenza da Malpensa e arrivo a Jeddah dove facciamo uno scalo di 10 ore e un giretto nella città prima di ripartire per la destinazione finale.
Ottavo giorno di vacanza e ci siamo spostati di appartamento a Grand Baie dove decidiamo di visitare la zona nord dell'isola; prima tappa di oggi sono i Giardini Botanici di Plamplemause!
Bellissima la flora che cresce in questo luogo, la parte più bella per noi sono stati i fiori di loto ma tutto il resto vale assolutamente la visita, super consigliato, una volta qui mi stacco per visitare il luogo di posizionamento della più vecchia cache di tutta l'isola, veramente un peccato non aver più una cache qui; spero di non fare dispiacere al proprietario loggando la cache con una foto, nel caso posso rimuovere tranquillamente il log.
Un grazie a Vagabund per la cache e per il luogo scelto.

After months and months of planning, the time has finally arrived for our summer vacation, which this year falls on the beautiful Mauritius. We departed from Malpensa and arrived in Jeddah, where we made a 10-hour layover and a quick tour of the city before heading back to our final destination.
On the eighth day of vacation, we moved to our apartment in Grand Baie, where we decided to visit the northern part of the island. Our first stop today was the Plamplemause Botanical Gardens!
The flora that grows here is beautiful. The highlight for us were the lotus flowers, but everything else is absolutely worth the visit. Highly recommended. Once here, I'll also visit the location of the oldest cache on the island. It's a real shame they no longer have a cache here. I hope I don't upset the owner by logging the cache with a photo; if that happens, I can easily remove the log.
Thanks to Vagabund for the cache and the location.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1189488383"><groundspeak:date>2023-08-20T12:29:23</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="96256">Vagabund</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Nearly 20 years ago the cache was hidden as one of the first caches in Mauritius. Now it´s time to archive this one. Thanks to all visitors, who helped maintaining the cache.

Vagabund</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1188933706"><groundspeak:date>2023-08-16T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="19419664">Team_Pandabeers</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Unfortunately no more box on site. Maybe a cacher can place a new one here? The spoiler image is very easy to find.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1186035537"><groundspeak:date>2023-08-06T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1639477">Snake's Sakes</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Needs maintenance, as the cache definitely is missing. (We could easily find the place thanks to the spoilers, but the hole is empty). Thanks for lookng after this one...</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1186035152"><groundspeak:date>2023-08-06T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Didn't find it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1639477">Snake's Sakes</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This cache is definitely missing or has been wrongly placed by someone. We could easily find the place, where it was hidden once, thanks to the spoiler pictures. The white stone is missing and the hole behind it is empty. Definitely needs maintenance... Thanks anyway and best regards from Switzerland, Pullmex and Snake's Sakes</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="29.116783333333334" lon="-114.03053333333334"><time>2001-04-12T00:00:00</time><name>GC6CB</name><desc>Viva Baja #2 by David K</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC6CB</url><urlname>Viva Baja #2</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="1739" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Viva Baja #2</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>David K</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="5040">David K</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Not chosen</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>3.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Mexico</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Located at long abandoned gold mine in Baja California.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>This cache is in a white lid Rubbermaid type box. From the ghost town ruins, walk up the hill behind. Be very carefull of the deep, open mine shafts you will pass nearby. The cache contains a logbook, pencil, 50 ft. rope, toy compass, play money, and water bottle. The site is less than 4 miles from a paved road, 4WD is not needed. Enjoy the history and search in this awesome area! Photos will be posted here or on my web page, soon.  </groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>To find the mine, go east on the road to Bahia de los Angeles, 7.3 miles from Highway #1. Turn north on the dirt road at a culvert pipe crossing. Go less than 4 miles, keeping to the left at both junctions along the way. Park on the north side of the road at the adobe mine building ruins. The cache is at the top of the small hill, at the base of a boojum (cirio) tree and elephant tree growing next to each other. Rocks are on top.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="732441477"><groundspeak:date>2017-11-07T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="21904316">El_Chavo_</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Comencé temprano mi día de aventuras. Este geocaché fue mi objetivo principal. No solo es viejo, sino que me parece muy interesante. Tomé un giro equivocado en mi primer intento de llegar a la ubicación, pero corregí mi curso rápidamente. Temía que mi vehículo no pudiera llevarme allí, pero lo hizo muy bien. Algunos de los ejes en esta área parecen ir para siempre. Quería explorarlos, pero como estaba solo pensé que no era una buena idea. Voy a esperar hasta que esté con amigos la próxima vez. Es notable para mí cómo estos contenedores permanecen en gran forma con el tiempo. Gracias por colocar este.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="673906863"><groundspeak:date>2017-04-01T01:55:56</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="7520632">Den Spuenier</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Aujourd'hui en famille comme il est d'habitude nous faisons une petite sortie avec notre soucoupe volante que nous avons acquise l'année passée.
Après quelques instants elle était prêt pour un petit voyage
Nous visiterons de belles régions et promettons de revenir avec un peut plus de temps 
Salutation et merci pour la pose des boites 
MPLC 👨‍👨‍👧‍👦</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="656665201"><groundspeak:date>2016-12-17T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2434432">Break-A-Way (BAW)</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found on our amazing way across Mexico... 
We found the box near the parking place.... but now the box is back on place.

T4TC, it was a pleasure...

The Break-A-Way's</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="580514284"><groundspeak:date>2016-03-13T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="14812982">Atlasxxx</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Grazie</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1228277437"><groundspeak:date>2014-02-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1516884">gonefishing2</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We are here for hubby’s birthday with a group of friends.  

Hubby wanted to go jeeping for his birthday so here we are. The other people in our group think we are crazy for doing this treasure hunting thing.  We even showed them how to do it but they still think we are crazy.  </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="6.8453333333333335" lon="158.29878333333335"><time>2002-12-16T00:00:00</time><name>GCB5B5</name><desc>Kepirohi Falls by MiketheFiddler</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCB5B5</url><urlname>Kepirohi Falls</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Virtual Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="46517" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Kepirohi Falls</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>MiketheFiddler</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="70165">MiketheFiddler</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Virtual Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Virtual</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Micronesia</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Kepirohi Falls on the Island of Pohnpei, Federated States of Micronesia.  Requires a 1/2 mile hike up a gently sloping trail, which gets rocky and slippery towards the end.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>The only significant difficulty in reaching this cache is getting to the Island of Pohnpei (in the Federated States of Micronesia) in the first place.   The cache site can be reached by a short hike (over a rocky and occasionally slippery 1/2 mile path) from the main road around the island.  

We came most of the way to the falls by boat, after a long day snorkeling, sea kayaking and visiting the nearby Nan Madol (5th - 12th century megalithic city) ruins.  A nice, cool, fresh water shower was just what we needed after a long day mostly spent immersed in salt water.  These falls are 70 feet in height, and are probably the most popular of the island's many waterfalls.  Be careful about ingesting the water, as there is a lamentably high prevalence of contaminated water on this beautiful island.

I visited the falls on April 21, 2002,  during a business trip to the FSM, and logged many other lovely virtual waypoints throughout the reefs and islands of Micronesia.

This is a virtual cache, so please validate your visit by posting a photo of you and your GPS in front of the falls.

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1359088539"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-04T17:26:47</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2822410">Glenturret</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">
🇬🇧🇬🇧🇬🇧
A grand cruise aboard the expedition ship ‘Inspiration’ through the South Seas, from Fiji to Taiwan.
This morning we arrive in Phonpei and immediately set off on a tour of the island.


This brings us to MiketheFiddler’s “Kepirohi Falls”.

Wow, we’re amazed by this fantastic waterfall, which truly lives up to its name. Usually, such “tourist waterfalls” are more like trickles.
But this one is really superb.
At times it’s pouring with rain, which only adds to the experience – we’re having a brilliant time.

12394 / 04.05.2026 
Many thanks to MiketheFiddler for showing us this lovely spot.
Glenturret and Schatz

🇩🇪🇩🇪🇩🇪
Grosse Schiffstour mit dem Expeditionsschiff „Inspiration“ durch die Südsee von Fiji bis Taiwan.
Heute morgen erreichen wir Phonpei und treten auch sofort die Rundfahrt über die Insel an.


So kommen wir auch zum „Kepirohi Falls“ von MiketheFiddler.

Whow, wir staunen über diesem tollen Wasserfall, der diesen Namen auch wirklich verdient. Normalerweise sind solche „Touristenwasserfälle“ eher Rinnsale.
Dieser ist aber wirklich super.
Zwischendurch giesst es in Strömen und das verstärkt das Feeling noch - es macht uns riesengrossen Spass.

12394 / 04.05.2026 
Vielen Dank an MiketheFiddler für's Zeigen des netten Platzes.
Glenturret und Schatz</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1348616106"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-10T23:34:15</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="90014">Landmaus</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We found this geocache on our world tour in 2025/26. 
The trip includes 22 countries and goes all around the world. 
Start was in Kanada, followed by Chile and 20 Pacific Islands till Mongolia.
All the time we enjoyed the landscape, the people and the geocaches.
Thanks to all owners for hiding and maintaining of their caches.
Best regards Landmaus

PS: Answers send by Trebbi </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1338275468"><groundspeak:date>2025-10-27T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5164078">FamWigaWahn</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">During our visiting to Macronesia, it was clear for us, that we have to visit this waterfall and to take a 📸 for this old 👻.
🙏for the Cache.
Regards from 2️⃣6️⃣1️⃣8️⃣0️⃣ Wahnbek in 🇩🇪</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1353330954"><groundspeak:date>2025-10-09T11:44:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="23867654">trocuit</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">merci pour cette cache 
nana</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1234790295"><groundspeak:date>2024-05-18T12:53:11</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="49596451">Yemama</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Gorgeous walk to waterfall!  Spectacular falls, especially after a heavy rain!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="47.014867" lon="28.812017"><time>2006-01-16T00:00:00</time><name>GCT1QN</name><desc>First Cache in Moldova by jeffkc (adopted by dR4GONdd)</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCT1QN</url><urlname>First Cache in Moldova</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="335350" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>First Cache in Moldova</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>jeffkc (adopted by dR4GONdd)</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="40238583">dR4GONdd</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Moldova</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>The cache is located in a park in Chisinau, near a lake. It is a popular walking place for local citizens. The site is located beneath thick forest cover, so honing in on the location in the summer can be difficult. Note carefully the clue; if you get the general area there is probably only one possible location.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;^ORIGINAL SHORT DESCRIPTION^&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The cache has been disturbed and removed several times, but now someone else (not jeffkc, the original cacher) has installed a cache on the same site which people are finding. I continue to be amazed and pleased that the cache is being maintained by unknown persons, 18 years after I placed it. Watching from my home in Seattle, thank you to whomever is doing the maintenance--it is clear that a lot of geocachers are getting enjoyment from finding it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;09/01/2025:&lt;br /&gt;
The cache was transferred from jeffkc to dR4GONdd.&lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Inside the tree, head level.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364343885"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="54104149">Kubelii</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Díky za kešku 😊♥️</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364339191"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1599854">MekekeKáji</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Nalezeno při návštěvě Kišiněva. Díky za kešku.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364337655"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2948665">cz-cacher</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found easily during our trip to Moldova🇦🇩 and Romania🇷🇴. Thanks for this nice hide. Hallo from the Czech Republic🇨🇿😜</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364337237"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="7467793">Výletníci ČB</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false"># 19. 929
Keška odlovena v pohodě. 😃 15:30 hod.
Nalezeno během geodovolené v Moldavsku 🇦🇩 a Rumunsku 🇷🇴.
Zdravíme z České Republiky. 🇨🇿
Díky za krabičku!

# 19. 929
Cache caught fine. 😃 15:30 am
Found during geocaching in Moldova 🇦🇩 and Romania 🇷🇴.
Greetings from the Czech Republic. 🇨🇿
Thanks for the box!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363976778"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-26T11:48:03</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="13308157">Lipsiatrucker1</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This actually was my first cache in Moldova. Before i arrived in thid country I fought it would only be dirt, rubble and brutalist apartment blocks. Far from it. This place is gorgeous. This one at the cache in particular. 
The city is lively and has a great vibe to it!
Will come back,
TFTC!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="47.347117" lon="91.954383"><time>2002-10-05T00:00:00</time><name>GC9734</name><desc>Blue Caves by Steve (Licorice)</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC9734</url><urlname>Blue Caves</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Virtual Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="38708" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Blue Caves</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Steve (Licorice)</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="28262">Licorice</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Virtual Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Virtual</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="0">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="56" inc="1">Medium hike (1 km–10 km)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="0">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="27" inc="0">Drinking water nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="35" inc="1">Off-road vehicles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="29" inc="0">Telephone nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="21" inc="1">Cliff/falling rocks</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Mongolia</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>The Blue Caves are located in western Mongolia and feature ancient cave art drawings
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;img src="http://www.geckobeach.com/GPS/licorice22.jpg" width="240" height="180" hspace="5" align="right" /&gt;Although this is a virtual cache, it won't be easy to get to. In fact, not much in Mongolia is easy to get to, hence the terrain rating for this cache.
&lt;p&gt;You'll need to drive about a day south of Khovd in western Mongolia to reach the Blue Caves site. There's no real road to the cave site from Khovd, so your GPS will definitely come in handy to find the site while following a coarse dirt track. There are two separate caves at this location and they are located a good hike above the dirt track.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The larger of the caves features some very impressive ancient drawings in a series of chambers within the cave (see picture); however the drawings have had some damage to them in recent years. The second, and smaller cave does not contain any drawings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Onto the virtual cache: to score a find for this cache, take your GPS as close to the entrance of the larger cave (without losing the signal) and have a friend take a picture of yourself with your GPS and with the cavern of the cave behind you and upload it with your find. Any additional pictures are also welcome of the drawings within the larger cave or of your adventures enroute to the cache site.&lt;br clear="all" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1326914765"><groundspeak:date>2025-09-29T09:43:48</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="11359459">clerixx</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Great area to go if there‘s time :)</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1324626023"><groundspeak:date>2025-08-18T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="42371951">Grinseäffchen</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">You've only really been where you've been on foot.
(Johann Wolfgang von Goethe)

-------
It's always a pleasure to be guided to such wonderful places. Thank you for the experience and this outdoor fun.

-----
-----
Nur wo du zu Fuß warst, bist du auch wirklich gewesen.
(Johann Wolfgang von Goethe)

-------
Immer wieder ein Genuss an so wunderbare Orte geführt zu werden. Danke für das Erlebnis und diesen Outdoor-Spaß.

------
Ich bin gern an der frischen Luft unterwegs. Die Suche nach dem einen oder anderen Cache macht mir Spaß. Danke für das Verstecken des Caches sage ich mit meinem Onlinelog. Sorry für den einheitlichen Log, ich bin lieber draußen, kein Freund von vielen Worten. Somit als Dank das TFTC.	</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1324562089"><groundspeak:date>2025-08-18T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2303839">AR-Team</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Visited Mongolia, an exciting country, and also found this cache. The nature and vastness of the country are impressive. Thanks to the owner for the cache in such a beautiful area.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1320772730"><groundspeak:date>2025-08-13T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5935575">cheetah2012</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Nachdem wir die Stan-Länder hinter uns haben sind wir durch Russland in die Mongolei eingereist. Wir haben uns selbstverständlich viel Natur,  historische Bauten so wie auch Städte in ihrer Vielfalt angeschaut. Unterschiedliche Kulturen und freundliche Menschen getroffen.
Nun kommen zu meiner Liste auch einige mongolische caches dazu.
Bis hierher wird man ganz schön durchgeschüttelt. 
Tftc</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1309988854"><groundspeak:date>2025-07-10T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3321448">2 Highmountains</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Das heutige Ziel war die Blue Caves, grandios. 
Dabei sollte auch dieser virtuelle Cache mit gemacht werden.
Wir sagen danke fürs Herlocken und TFTC.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="42.396132" lon="18.764198"><time>2007-01-04T00:00:00</time><name>GC1095F</name><desc>FORTRESSES OF MONTENEGRO - "FORT GORAZDA" by The Montenegro Geocachers</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC1095F</url><urlname>FORTRESSES OF MONTENEGRO - "FORT GORAZDA"</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="521220" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>FORTRESSES OF MONTENEGRO - "FORT GORAZDA"</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>The Montenegro Geocachers</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="134861">MontenegroGeocachers</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="42" inc="1">Needs maintenance</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="23" inc="1">Dangerous area</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Montenegro</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>&lt;p&gt;This is one of a group of six geocaches, the first to be placed since Montenegro gained its independence in 2006. All are located around the Bay of Kotor. It is a fine example of an Austro-Hungarian Fortress.&lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;USE GREAT CARE TO HIDE THIS CACHE WELL AND AVOID MUGGLES! Park car at - N42 23.746, E018 45.818 The fort is an amazing example of Austro-Hungarian military architecture dated 1886. Surrounded by a dry moat, it has an enormous steerable gun emplacement guided by lookouts in protected bunkers using speaking tubes to guide the gun aimers. The cache is hidden within the boundaries of the fortress which dominates the approaches to the Bay of Kotor. A torch will be required and some exploration first inside and then outside the fort will be needed. Take care and do not attempt to scale the broken spiral staircase to the turret operators' position which is particularly dangerous. Please support "CACHE IN - TRASH OUT" to make Montenegro a clean environment http://www.geocaching.com/cito/&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you want to learn more about these fortresses, check out &lt;b&gt;&lt;font color="#FF3300" size="3"&gt;"The Austro-Hungarian Fortresses of Montenegro - A Hikers Guide"&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt; This is available from Amazon Books, "So Bookstore" in Herceg Novi or the "Forza Souvenir Shop" by the main gate in Kotor.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;center&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color="#FF3300" size="3"&gt;If you already have a copy, please post a photo holding it near the fortress!&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/center&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Look near the minor observation cupolas. </groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1363430059"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-25T13:14:33</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="55481131">obugraavci</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Sakladığın yeri ararken tüm binayı gezdik çok eğlenceliydi. Bir sonraki gelecek arkadaş kalem getirebilirse çok iyi olur. 
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362588803"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-22T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="7394303">Xiefehl_en_Mozique</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We placed a new one in the small dome.

TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362687950"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-22T11:15:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="7394303">Xiefehl_en_Mozique</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Vanaf 7 mei reizen we door de Balkan. Deze vakantie staat in het teken van vieren, geocachen en genieten van al het moois dat de Balkan te bieden heeft.
**Dag 16** Vanwege wat knieproblemen van één van de teamleden deden we vandaag de caches die we alleen met de auto konden bereiken. We tankten de auto vol en gingen de bergen in! Wel 25 haarspeldbochten werden getrotseerd en hier en daar stopten we voor een cache/uitzicht. We vonden 2 van de 4 oudste caches op de route. Uiteindelijk reden we het nationaal park in en bezochten het mausoleum én de enige Wherigo hier in de buurt. Het was 29 graden, al voelde het hoog in de bergen niet zo heet. De perfecte dag dus.

Starting May 7, we will be traveling through the Balkans. This holiday is all about celebrating, geocaching, and enjoying all the beauty the Balkans have to offer.
**Day 16** Due to some knee problems with one of the team members, today we did the caches that could only be reached by car. We filled up the car and headed into the mountains! We braved no fewer than 25 hairpin bends and stopped here and there for a cache or view. We found 2 of the 4 oldest caches on the route. Eventually, we drove into the national park and visited the mausoleum as well as the only Wherigo in the area. It was 29 degrees, although it didn't feel that hot high in the mountains. It was a perfect day.

This one was missing... we knew and bought a little box as a replacement. It was a great adventure visiting the old fortress! FAVO for showing this nice place.

MontenegroGeocachers TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362205785"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-19T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="7394303">Xiefehl_en_Mozique</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We will be here this week. We can hide a new box if you want. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362514622"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-19T10:18:04</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Didn't find it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="31648920">MI_Cache_</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Unfortunately couldn't find the cache. However, enjoyed our visit to this place! Thank you for leading us here! </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="16.762383" lon="-62.223033"><time>2009-12-23T00:00:00</time><name>GC227YC</name><desc>Woodlands Beach Cache by Cape Spear</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC227YC</url><urlname>Woodlands Beach Cache</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="1503142" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Woodlands Beach Cache</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Cape Spear</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="2831819">Cape Spear</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Montserrat</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Cache is near Woodlands Beach. It's a great beach for swimming and snorkelling in Montserrat and has good facilities such as a freshwater shower, benches for a picnic and beautiful sand. Feel free to leave anything else that will fit.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;The cache will take you to one of my favourite beaches in
Montserrat called Woodlands Beach. The waves are plenty, and it is right
beside a large and beautiful cliff in a very lush environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a very easy cache to access, and you really only need a
decent pair of shoes (I wore sandals). You need to bring your
bathingsuit for the swim.&lt;/p&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>The entrance to the cache is on the corner just before you reach the parking lot at Woodlands Beach.  It is about 15 to 20 feet east of the road at the end of a rock wall.  The cache is in a rock cairn just in front of a large boulder (the only one in the area).

My GPS was reading an error of 8 m.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1350997874"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-23T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3042368">Joci</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found it on my way back from the beach. Thank you for the cache. Joci! and a friend. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1348643296"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-12T16:37:40</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1893908">Oak.Family</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Visited during our trip to Monserrat, thanks a lot for a nice cache!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1348643470"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-12T12:39:52</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2103299">Chalupáři z Čes.ráje</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thank you for this cache 😁</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1344374768"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-08T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1049026">merdian</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">
On 31.1.26 my cruise tour with Oosterdam (Holland America Line) ended in Buenos Aires. It started 22 days before in Santiago de Chile. We visited Chile, Argentina, Antartica, Falkland Islands and Uruguay. After visiting the Iguazú falls, I had flights to Asuncion/Paraguay, Cusco/Peru, Santa Cruz/Bolivia, Caracas/Venezuela, Curacao, Bonaire, St. Maarten, Antigua and then to Montserrat. 
This is my third attempt to find a cache here. In 2019 a helicopter flight was cancelled and then I was denied boarding a flight in Antigua to Montserrat (I had no entry stamp from Antigua in my passport because I arrived with a cruise ship). 
Today I had a three hour day trip from Antigua. Arriving in Montserrat I had a taxi to this cache. After some searching I found the box and could sign the logbook. 

Thanks for providing a real cache here and greetings from Germany, Peter M. 

PS: This is my ISO-3166/Geocaching country #227/249. 
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1337785881"><groundspeak:date>2025-12-13T11:39:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4530482">Vlastas11</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">#6794, 2025-12-13 at 11:39, 

Nalezeno během mé cesty po Karibiku. Tímto se moje nově navštívené země stávají:
65. Antigua a Barbuda 🇦🇬 66. Montserrat 🇲🇸 67. Sint Maarten 🇸🇽 68. Saint Barthélemy 🇧🇱 69. Anguilla 🇦🇮 70. Saint Kitts and Nevis 🇰🇳
Během pobytu jsem našel několik keší a tahle byla jednou z nich. Děkuji za další bod a za přivedení na zajímavé místo.
Zdravím z České republiky 🇨🇿

