&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size="1"&gt;Note on cache maintenance: The actual location is
over looking the Passu Glacier and the staff there will maintain
the site. Email is not yet available at the community but
telephones are and I can maintain the cache that way.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>109 steps and 4 posts
staff at Glacier Breeze Restaurant know</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1320789464"><groundspeak:date>2025-07-20T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3978079">Rosee&amp;Wrecje</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false"># 9 in Pakistan
The long-planned, and at the same time postponed, journey to Pakistan has finally come true. I gradually travelled across the whole country from south to north and back again: Karachi - Lahore - Islamabad - Margalla Hills - Fairy Meadows and Nanga Parbat B. C. - Gilgit - Rakaposhi B. C. - Hunza Valley (Karimabad, Attabad Lake, Gulmit, Passu) - Naltar Valley (Satrangi Lake) - Skardu (Marsur Rock, Barah Broq - Moses Peak) - Taxila - Makli and Thatta. I saw and visited many really interesting and beautiful places during the whole journey ;-)

While hiking around Passu, I also stopped at this place... personally, I don't like this kind of caches... searching for a box while there are many muggles sitting in the restaurant watching you is a bit uncomfortable.
Finally, I found the box thanks to the hint from the owner...
Thanks for the cache at this place ;-)</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1294937651"><groundspeak:date>2025-04-28T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="376924">ladyangie</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">On our bicycle tour on the KKH saw this cache back in NZ so put it on bucket list. Was a bit hard without cell reception but got there in the end</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1266857587"><groundspeak:date>2024-10-22T15:31:45</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="28935220">TheGoldenCamel</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">First cache in Pakistan!!!
The camel is waaaaay excited and to be around her double humped sisters 🐪🐫🇵🇰 TFTF </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1176479084"><groundspeak:date>2023-06-16T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="45183178">Vardag</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">My first find was the first cache in Pakistan! Long story how the stars aligned but I'm super grateful for this. A lifetime hobby gets a great start. Place has changed a lot since the original 2004 photos obviously. We were on our way to Khunjrab pass and stopped at the nearby Yak Cafe before coming to the cache. We tried the apricot cake recommended by Geodirect; it was a bit mid honestly, but the view and chai were great! The restaurant owner seemed quite pleased with us and wanted to take a picture, while stressing how we had to be super careful with the cache. It was a nice break from the long travel and a cool find!
In: A fountain pen 
Out: the screaming man figurine thingy and a coin</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1181505635"><groundspeak:date>2023-06-03T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5339528">Pauele&amp;Dancul</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Together with expeeert. It was nice to find geocache here... thank you.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="7.33955" lon="134.458533"><time>2007-03-06T00:00:00</time><name>GC119V6</name><desc>Rock Islands of Palau by SurrenderTheBooty</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC119V6</url><urlname>Rock Islands of Palau</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Earthcache</type><groundspeak:cache id="551653" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Rock Islands of Palau</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>SurrenderTheBooty</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="551761">SurrenderTheBooty</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Earthcache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Not chosen</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Palau</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/51593eb4-1854-4a31-9ceb-bb5736b052ee.jpg" /&gt;
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;The Rock Islands of Palau are pure limestone and are are the remains of ancient coral reefs which were lifted up out of the ocean millions of years ago by volcanic forces.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Palau rests on top of an undersea ridge of volcanic mountains, part of the "Pacific Ring of Fire" known for its undersea activity. One of the deepest trenches in the ocean is just east of Palau (Marianas Trench) which is about 27,000 feet deep.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Locally called "Chelbacheb", the magnificent Rock Islands and the scuba diving areas around them have made Palau famous throughout the world. The Rock Islands are spread out over more than 23 miles between the islands of Koror and Peleliu. The islands are heavily undercut, giving them the appearance of green mushrooms.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rainfall passes through leaves and humus, picking up acidity which accelerates the erosion of the island's structure. At water level, the undercutting nature of the sea's erosion is evident. It is easy to see how the combined erosive effects of sea, rain and acidity erode the soft limestone islands at sea level. Sea urchins and limpets are embedded into the rock, eating algae in slow, but constant process, adding to the erosion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;No need for a boat or special equipment to claim this cache. At ground zero you will be standing near the pictured rock island in the harbor of Koror.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To claim this cache you must complete the two following tasks:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1. Have your picture taken in front of the rock island nearest GZ and post it in your log.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;2. Estimate the amount of the undercut on the rock island at GZ and send your estimation to us via e-mail.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Don't wait to log your find, attach the picture to your log and send the e-mail. If there is a problem with your findings we will contact you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All logs without a posted picture or e-mail will be deleted to comply with the EarthCaching requirements.&lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1360654682"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-12T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="16492496">D W N M</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Yesterday we arrived in the bay off Palau aboard the cruise ship Hanseatic Inspiration. Today the ship docked in port to refuel. From there we walked to this place. Thanks to the owner for showing us this one. Greetings from Luxembourg /Europe</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360522134"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-12T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2822410">Glenturret</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">



🇬🇧🇬🇧🇬🇧

A grand cruise on the expedition ship ‘Inspiration’ through the South Pacific, from Fiji to Taiwan.
Yesterday morning we arrived in Palau🇵🇼🇵🇼.
We realise that a Palau souvenir has to be earned the hard way 🥵🥵.
The geocaches are all difficult to reach.
Today, the Inspiration is heading to Malakal to refuel, which gives me the chance to make a find.
It’s already 31°C in the morning and I walk the kilometre to the cache “Rock Islands of Palau” by SurrenderTheBooty.
Soaking wet, I take a look at the location, take the required photos and assess the scouring.

Then I hurry back to the ship, taking a short detour to the nearby traditional geocache.

12397 / 12 May 2026 
Many thanks to SurrenderTheBooty for the cache and for showing us this lovely spot.
Glenturret and Schatz


🇩🇪🇩🇪🇩🇪
Grosse Schiffstour mit dem Expeditionsschiff „Inspiration“ durch die Südsee von Fiji bis Taiwan.
Gestern am Morgen erreichen wir Palau🇵🇼🇵🇼.
Wir stellen fest, dass das Souvenir Palau erst hart verdient werden muss 🥵🥵.
Die Geocaches sind alle schwer erreichbar.
Heute fährt die Inspiration zum Bunkern nach Malakal, was mir die Chance auf einen Found bietet.
Schon am Morgen ist es 31° und ich laufe den Kilometer bis zum Cache  „Rock Islands of Palau“ von SurrenderTheBooty.
Klatschnass schaue ich mir die Location an und mache die geforderten Fotos und schätze die Unterspülung.

Dann rasch zurück zum Schiff mit einem kleinen Umweg zum nahen Traditional-Geocache.

12397 / 12.05.2026 
Vielen Dank an SurrenderTheBooty für den Cache und für's Zeigen des netten Platzes.
Glenturret und Schatz</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1354141386"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-09T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4838161">NamelessGuy</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This week I am traveling to Taiwan and Palau. Even though I didn't have much time in both locations, I still managed to find some caches around the touristic highlights.
Today I explored the island with a rental car.
This one is a great example for the rock islands. Estimation done on site and sent to the CO already.

TFTC
NamelessGuy from Germany

----------
&gt;Fbz rb ar vf n yv gg yr ph evb hf. Lb he cr ef vf gr ag ch mm yr fb yi vat qr fr ei rf n er jn eq. Ur er vf gur pb qr sbe zl pb va gb qv fp bi re: CP 2K MO - Frr lbh fb ba ba gur ge nvy!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1352270333"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-01T22:39:55</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="19770250">AddisonPascal</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Visiting Palau for just a few days, this is my last full day in the country before I begin my journey back home to Australia. 
I walked here from my hotel on Malakal Island. It’s incredible how many fish I can see swimming in the water right near the shore!

Answers sent via email and photo attached to my log.
Thanks for the EarthCache!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1352105825"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-31T19:32:27</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="52375">rhodesisland</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Hafa Adai from Guam, USA.

lilmsmuffet and I took a few minutes to grab this cache while on a errand run.
Great vacation so far in Palau!
TFTEC!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="9.554417" lon="-79.655583"><time>2002-06-15T00:00:00</time><name>GC6CD0</name><desc>Fort Portobelo  by -Team Family Affair</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC6CD0</url><urlname>Fort Portobelo </urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Virtual Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="27856" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Fort Portobelo </groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>-Team Family Affair</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="22241">Team Family Affair</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Virtual Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Virtual</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Panama</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is the 26&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; geocache from Team Family Affair. We created this cache while on tour visiting Panama. This virtual cache is located at Fort Portobelo, in the Portobelo National Park located along the Caribbean Sea coastline. This fort and market town was founded in the late 1500s. In the 1600s the fort and town was the site of much trading , pirate activity as well as a primary pathway for the transportation of Gold, silver and precious stones to Spain and Europe. For more information about this Fort and strong hold we suggest the web site- &lt;a href="http://www.serve.com/CZBrats/PanamaViejo/portobel.htm"&gt;http://www.serve.com/CZBrats/PanamaViejo/portobel.htm&lt;/a&gt;. Also interesting and worthy of exploring is the legend and story of the Black Christ (at the little church in this immediate area), as well as the Customs House (built in 1630) where gold and silver was protected and stored while awaiting shipment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;"&gt;To log this cache as a find you must:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Find the location and take a selfie picture of yourself and your team and post it to your “found log” on this geocache page. ,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;"&gt;We hope you enjoy this cache as much as we did creating it!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-Team Family Affair&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1362413759"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-22T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="7366439">Rezi73</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Im Team „Untappd-Reisen“ – bestehend aus coolekuh, jojo71_geo, jowo2003, Rezi73 und Virtualboy – führte uns unsere diesjährige Reise durch Zentralamerika. Dabei besuchten wir Panama, Costa Rica, Nicaragua, El Salvador, Guatemala, Honduras, Belize und Mexiko.

Neben zahlreichen Sehenswürdigkeiten und beeindruckenden Naturwundern konnten wir unterwegs auch einige Geocaches entdecken und loggen.

Ein herzliches Dankeschön an alle Cacheowner fürs Legen und Pflegen der Caches – ohne euren Einsatz wäre dieses schöne Hobby nicht möglich.

Viele Grüße aus dem schönen Sachsen in Deutschland!
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1358015025"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-22T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2552416">Virtualboy</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Unterwegs in Zentralamerika mit dem **Team Untappd**: coolekuh, jojo71_geo, jowo2003, Rezi73 &amp; Virtualboy

Auf unserer dreiwöchigen Tour durch Panama, Costa Rica, Nicaragua, El Salvador, Guatemala, Honduras, Belize und Mexico besuchten wir viele beeindruckende Orte, lernen neue Länder und Gebräuche kennen, testeten die lokale kulinarischen Köstlichkeiten und auch das einheimische Bier.

Natürlich habe wir auch etwas Geocaching betrieben und dadurch schöne Locations entdeckt.

Dieser Cache war auch dabei. 

Vielen Dank sagt Virtualboy

in: nichts
out: nichts

Danke für den Cache - Thanks for that Cache- Merci pour la. Cache - Dzięki za Cache - Grazie per questo Cache - Takk for cachen - Obrigado por isso Cache - Gracias por el Cache - Díky za keš - Ačiū už tą talpyklą - Paldies par šo Cache - Aitäh selle eest Cache - Спасибо за то кэш - Kiitos, että Cache - Tack för cachen - Tak for denne Cache - Hvala cache - Ευχαριστώ για τη μνήμη cache - 感謝您的高速緩存 - Önbellek için teşekkürler - Köszönjük, hogy a cache - Bedankt voor de cache - Graças para o cache - Dankon pro la kaŝmemoron</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1355001245"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-22T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="15377839">coolekuh</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Vor uns lagen 3 Wochen Mittelamerika!
Im erprobten Team:  jojo71_geo, jowo2003, Rezi73, Virtualboy und coolekuh waren die Ziele klar.
In 8 Ländern mindestens 1 Cache finden, möglichst viele Cachearten pro Land, die ältesten Caches wenn möglich, aber last but not least viele verschiedene Biere testen.
All dieses ist uns sehr gut gelungen und ich bin mit unserer Ausbeute sehr zufrieden.
Außerdem haben wir viel gesehen und ich bin überrascht wie unbesorgt und sicher ich mich in allen Ländern gefühlt habe.
Die 3 Wochen waren anstrengend, aber sehr sehr schön, mit vielen neuen Eindrücken im Gepäck und sehr glücklich blicke ich zufrieden zurück.
Allen Ownern ein herzliches Dankeschön. 
Wenn Bei Caches Antworten erforderlich sind, schickt immer einer aus unserer Gruppe diese.

¡Nos esperaban tres semanas en Centroamérica!

En nuestro equipo de confianza —jojo71_geo, jowo2003, Rezi73, Virtualboy y coolekuh— los objetivos eran claros: encontrar al menos un geocaché en cada uno de los ocho países, la mayor cantidad posible de geocachés de distintos tipos por país, los más antiguos si era posible y, por último, pero no menos importante, probar una gran variedad de cervezas.

Lo logramos con creces y estoy muy contento con los resultados.

También vimos mucho y me sorprendió lo despreocupado y seguro que me sentí en todos los países.

Las tres semanas fueron agotadoras pero increíblemente maravillosas, dejándome muchas nuevas impresiones, y las recuerdo con gran alegría y satisfacción.

Un sincero agradecimiento a todos los propietarios de los geocachés.

Si se necesitan respuestas para un geocaché, alguien de nuestro grupo siempre las envía.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1350685248"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-22T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3811039">jowo2003</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">\# **24387** \#

Heute mal wieder etwas, diesmal in dieser Gegend rumgeströpert. 
Dabei ein paar Events, Earthcaches, Virtuals besucht oder physische Dosen gesucht. 

**GC6CD0** gehörte auch dazu und nun ziert ein weiteres Smiley die Karte. 

**Danke für den kurzweiligen Spass den ich hatte!**

----
Danke und Gruss an **Team Family Affair** sagt **jowo2003**. 

Danke für den Cache - Thanks for that Cache- Merci pour la. Cache - Dzięki za Cache - Grazie per questo Cache - Takk for cachen - Obrigado por isso Cache - Gracias por el Cache - Díky za keš - Ačiū už tą talpyklą - Paldies par šo Cache - Aitäh selle eest Cache - Спасибо за то кэш - Kiitos, että Cache - Tack för cachen - Tak for denne Cache - Hvala cache - Ευχαριστώ για τη μνήμη cache - 感謝您的高速緩存 - Önbellek için teşekkürler - Köszönjük, hogy a cache - Bedankt voor de cache - Graças para o cache - Dankon pro la kaŝmemoron</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1354983130"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-21T16:10:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="15684140">jojo71_geo</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">team untappd: coolekuh, jojo71_geo, jowo2003, Rezi73 &amp; Virtualboy
 
diese reise wollte ich schon immer machen ... der wunsch, so viel wie möglich mit dem auto unterwegs zu sein, konnte auf vielen etappen realisiert werden ... am ende standen auf dem weg von panama city über costa rica, nicaragua, el salvador, guatemala, honduras, belize nach mexiko city mehr als 6000 kilometer auf der uhr ... neue eindrücke und viele erlebnisse prägten diesen trip quer durch zentralamerika

panama
panama city: man spürt diese besondere mischung aus pulsierender moderne und kolonialem charme, die historische altstadt ist sehenswert

gatún: hier wollten wir einen blick auf die einfahrt vom karibischen meer in die schleusen werfen, beeindruckend – riesige schiffe ziehen gemächlich an einem vorbei, millimeterarbeit

portobelo: üppiges grün, alte festungsanlagen, die salzige brise der karibik, hier scheint die zeit stillzustehen
 

costa rica
puerto limón/cahuita: karibikfeeling pur, bunte häuser, entspannte menschen, abends gechillt in der strandbar ... ein ganz besonderer stopp führte uns ins sloth sanctuary, die begegnung mit den faultieren war einfach unvergesslich – zu sehen, wie behutsam hier mit den tieren umgegangen wird, hat den besuch ganz besonders gemacht

san josé: zwischen lebhaften straßen, kleinen parks und historischen gebäuden verstecken sich immer wieder spannende ecken, die nur darauf warten, entdeckt zu werden

la fortuna: eine kulisse, die man so schnell nicht vergisst, der mächtige vulkan im hintergrund, umgeben von sattgrünem dschungel

mistico hängebrücken: der regenwald aus einer völlig neuen perspektive ... hoch über dem boden, zwischen den baumkronen, mitten im herzen der natur
 

nicaragua
san juan del sur: sonnenuntergang und meeresrauschen, kleine gassen, bunte häuser – bei entspannter surfer-stimmung und leckeren cocktails hatten wir hier eine gute zeit

vulkan masaya: nichts bereitet einen auf den moment vor, wenn man plötzlich am kraterrand steht und in die tiefe schaut – leider hatten wir nur den schwefelgeruch in der nase, konnten aber keinen blick auf brodelnde lava erhaschen

granada: koloniales flair und farbenfrohe straßen verzaubern einen vom ersten moment an, beeindruckende kirchen und raue see
 

el salvador
san salvador: hier waren wir mehr als überrascht, eine lebendige interessante stadt, ok in der altstadt war es uns ein bisschen zu quirlig – definitiv eine reise wert

devils gate: der abstecher hierher war ein highlight – zwischen den markanten felsformationen öffnet sich ein weiter blick über die umliegende landschaft

el tunco beach: die felsformationen am strand geben der küste ihren ganz besonderen charakter, surferstimmung, das rauschen des pazifiks: hier chillten wir ne weile bei leckeren cocktails

 
guatemala
antigua: wie ein spaziergang durch eine andere zeit, die kopfsteingepflasterten straßen, die farbenfrohen fassaden und die beeindruckenden ruinen erzählen überall ihre eigene geschichte, umrahmt von vulkanen wirkt die stadt fast wie ein lebendiges gemälde

flores: für uns das sprungbrett nach tikal:  tief im regenwald erheben sich die gewaltigen tempel, der sonnenuntergang in tikal war einer dieser momente, die man nie wieder vergisst

 
honduras
copan: honduras hat uns überrascht, copan empfängt einen entspannt und charmant – die ruinen sind beeindruckend, die anlage heimat vieler tiere, so nah war ich einem frei herumfliegenden papagei noch nie

 
belize
altun ha: zwischen überwucherten wegen und steinernen strukturen entfaltet sich eine atmosphäre, die ruhig und kraftvoll zugleich ist – sicher eine der unbekannteren maya-stätten, einen stopp wert

san ignacio: diese stadt hatte ich mir anders vorgestellt, der aufenthalt war aber auch nur kurz auf unserem weg nach belize city

belize city: direkt an der küste gelegen weht hier ständig eine warme meeresbrise durch die straßen – gegessen haben wir ja auf der tour oft sehr lecker, der abend in einem hervorragenden restaurant wird aber lange in erinnerung bleiben

 
mexiko
tulum: karibik trifft maya-geschichte ... für mich die schönste ruine, direkt am karibischen meer gelegen

chichén itzá: das disneyland unter den maya-ruinen – klar ist die große pyramide beeindruckend, aber mir hat die atmosphäre nicht gefallen

cancun: zwischen party und paradies – weißer sand, sanftes wellenrauschen, karibikblau – und halligalli in der stadt, dem wir bewusst aus dem weg gegangen sind und lieber am strand nen lecker cocktail genossen haben

mexiko city: beeindruckender abschluss dieser reise – laut, riesig, vielfältig und voller energie ... moderne skyline trifft auf jahrhundertealte geschichte, hektisches stadtleben auf ruhige, versteckte oasen ... dazu duftet es überall nach frisch zubereiteten tacos und würzigen salsas, ich mag diese kleinen straßenstände</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="-5.859417" lon="144.582033"><time>2006-07-24T00:00:00</time><name>GCXT03</name><desc>NUMBAWAN Kudjip Cache by bdbhaiti, PyePoud</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCXT03</url><urlname>NUMBAWAN Kudjip Cache</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="447056" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>NUMBAWAN Kudjip Cache</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>bdbhaiti, PyePoud</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="233392">bdbhaiti</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="56" inc="1">Medium hike (1 km–10 km)</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>4</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>4</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Papua New Guinea</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>A cache hidden beside a jungle waterfall about one mile in from the road at Kudjip, PNG.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>The description for this cache will be detailed as the main idea is to get to the waterfall and then log your find.

The container is a small clear tupperware square buried in the rocks to the right of the top waterfall. The land is owned by Andrew Kewa who has approved the placement of the cache. Andrew is kickstarting a Cultural Center at the waterfalls, and he will be happy to show you around. Since it is still under development, he may charge a small fee (10 Kina) to show you around, but it is well worth it. 

Most locals will know Andrew and the site for the Cultural Center, so asking questions will get you right to the cache. Finding Andrew to show you to the falls is the key to this cache. If not, here are detailed directions:

As you enter Kudjip turn right at the tea fields and turn right again at the Sidney and Wanda Knox Memorial (the Nazarene Clinic is on the left). Park your car there and walk N beside the tea fields. After a few hundred feet there is a car gate on your left. This is the starting point, the first gate.

Turn left at the gate onto the road and proceed down it until you come to a Catholic Church. Turn right down a dirt path after the church. After a short time the path will become a dirt road. Eventually you will cross a wide wooden-pole bridge. At .83 mi from the first gate you will come to a bamboo gate which you can step over. 

At 1.07 mi from the first gate, there is a WOODEN GATE to the left and a trade store on the right. The sign says not to enter. This is the Cultural Center. It is Andrew's property and he has given permission for Geocachers to enter. The coordinates for the Cultural Center are (S 05 51.059), (E 144 34.072).

Walk up to the thatch huts in the cultural center, and the pathway to the waterfalls is straight through the huts.

The Cache is in the large rocks to the right of the falls.

The directions are quite complicated but Andrew will probably be around to show you to the cache.</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1341999314"><groundspeak:date>2026-01-17T12:00:25</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="53176094">Kaydos2025</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Ok</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1350264425"><groundspeak:date>2025-12-31T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="42639719">Seattlehunter</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found this container on a world tour from 2022 to 2025. I think it was the best experience of my life doing this trip. Could see a lot.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1273411076"><groundspeak:date>2024-12-14T12:04:18</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="39159598">Samtheman0_BB</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Se</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1248193778"><groundspeak:date>2024-07-24T09:19:38</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="48517751">GrfSonDuo</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1247754462"><groundspeak:date>2024-07-22T08:52:36</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Didn't find it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="50529149">Parsan131</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">N</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="-27.134216666666667" lon="-55.70933333333333"><time>2003-12-20T00:00:00</time><name>GCHC29</name><desc>First Cache in Paraguay (El primero) by manpy57</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCHC29</url><urlname>First Cache in Paraguay (El primero)</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="106930" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>First Cache in Paraguay (El primero)</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>manpy57</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="181715">manpy57</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Not chosen</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Paraguay</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>In a Municipal Park , Altitude 89 mts no far from Jesuist Reduction of Santisima Trinidad del Parana.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>Cache of Plastic Bottle with 3 pins inside( Paraguayan flag,Argentinian flag and 50 $ ), a pencil and a notebook
Its  located at  8 mts. from the tree of the picture.
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1165952325"><groundspeak:date>2023-05-10T10:08:58</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="791612">Chuck Walla</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Hello manpy57,

I am regretfully archiving this cache since there's been no response from nor action by the cache owner as requested in the last note posted by a reviewer.

***Chuck Walla***
