This is an easy one, a nice place to see and experience.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>Well, It looks like somebody made a tropy of the plaque! Which is why I didn't place a cache here because I thought it would disappear. It is still a nice place to visit. Instead of sending the answer to the old question, send a picture of yourself with the lion, or of a picture of yourself (ID Card, etc.) placed beside the lion, that will count as a find.
This is the original message.
Near this Plaza is a statue of a Golden Lion Looking towards the Plaza. (See picture of the lion) The Plaque under the Lion has a small golden crest in the upper left corner. What is the largest letter in the center of the crest? E-mail me with the answer, please do not post your answer on the site.

I wanted to place a traditional cache, but the people make that impossible. People are everywhere, sleeping everywhere and always watching. I liked this place the first time I came through a year ago and again this time. I think anyone visiting will find this an interesting place to see also. The art row is nice to browse and the traders market was a great place to find some unique gifts for my family.</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Walking from the traders market, through the Artist rows, go until you come to the round-a-bout, or circle drive as some call it. The Lion is on the Left side, in front of the Dollar City gift shop.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="811991866"><groundspeak:date>2018-10-24T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="13099142">SamXXXX</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Today I went for a geocaching tour in Miraflores. It was quite busy. In the afternoon the sun finally won the fight againdt the fog at some spots. Unfortunately I didnt find all the caches but enyojed the day anyways. 
Thanks to all the owners for making this day a pleasure.

Cheers from a Swiss guy on travels.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="785185286"><groundspeak:date>2018-07-07T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3086573">arieltuc</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false"> #616
 
 Una pena que se haya archivado este virtual, el lugar sigue existiendo y no sobran virtuales... En fin.


--------

### El viaje de los 8 aviones ###

Primera y última vez que hacemos esta locura:

8 Aviones
7 Valijas
6 Países
5 Mishiguenes
4 Hoteles
3 Vehículos
2 Nueva York
UNO es el creador Barujú Baruj Shemó!

Tuvimos tres eventos: 
[Lima](https://coord.info/GC7RQ66); [Ciudad de México](https://coord.info/GC7RTA1) (que no se hizo [:(]) y [New York](https://coord.info/GC7T850).

Encontramos hermosos cachés en cada lugar que estuvimos: 

* En Perú dos del amigo [lito_v 1](https://coord.info/GC74XV7) [lito_v 2](https://coord.info/GC77D38) y [uno muy original](https://coord.info/GC1EY5P) que sugiero a cada geocacher copiar en su ciudad. 

* En la ciudad de México conocimos al [Dr. Abel Celis](https://coord.info/GC4H6CK) y en Teotihuacán encontramos un caché físico del a´ño [2001](https://coord.info/GC2C78), el original se conserva... otra antig¨üedad mas se suma a las pirámides[8D]. 

* En New Jersey encontramos mejores cachés que en New York, obviamente es más fácil de esconder en el *Estado jardín* que en la *Gran manzana* 

[XL](https://coord.info/GC44VVJ), un enorme caché lleno de tesoros, comparable con el que encontramos hace dos años en Florida(https://coord.info/GC15RQB), hoy archivado.

También un [mistery](https://coord.info/GC62G28) no sólo porque me hizo ver tres veces una misma película para resolverlo, si no porque el lugar dónde está escondido es muy buen escondite, también el recepiente que hace de caché está relacionado con dicha película.

Por último sumamos un extraño [webcam cache](https://coord.info/GCQ9KT).

* La vuelta fue lo más loco, ya que en un mismo día estuvimos en 4 países distintos, encontrando cachés en cada uno, destacándose la fugaz visita a [Bogotá](https://coord.info/GC1MPWJ)

Caché encontrado (o visitado) con  🇦🇷 **[Geocaching Argentina](https://www.geocaching.com.ar "Geocaching Argentina")** 🇦🇷. TFTC.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="771637741"><groundspeak:date>2018-05-09T14:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="10106772">jirca76</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">&gt;TFTC

---------

**(ES - traducción de Google)**
La gran gira por el sur de Perú y Bolivia con un grupo de amigos nos ha llevado a este hermoso lugar.
Pasamos 3 semanas llenas de hermosas experiencias, naturaleza y monumentos.
Muchas gracias y envía saludos desde la República Checa.

**(EN)**
The great tour of southern Peru and Bolivia with a bunch of friends has brought us to this beautiful place.
We spent 3 weeks full of beautiful experiences, nature and monuments.
Thank you very much and send greetings from the Czech Republic.

**(CZ)**
Velká cesta po jižní části Peru a Bolívii s partou kamarádů nás přivedla na toto krásné místo.
Strávili jsme zde 3 týdny plné krásných zážitku, přírody a památek.
Moc díky a posílám pozdrav z České republiky.


</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="770690508"><groundspeak:date>2018-05-09T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="7753987">omadlikovi</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Hola (traducción de Google),
encontramos este caché durante un viaje de 3 semanas por una parte del sur de Perú. Naturaleza hermosa, personas sonrientes, comida interesante y una emocionante experiencia de viaje: esto es lo que Perú nos ofrece y por qué estábamos tan satistificados. El geocaching aquí no es tan popular como en Europa o EE. UU., Pero gracias a este caché tuvimos la oportunidad de encontrarlo aquí. Y esto es más importante que los cachés en los países mencionados. Así que muchas gracias por hacer un caché aquí, es muy apreciado y GRACIAS ;-).
OMadlikovi sazavsti, República Checa, Europa

(EN) Hello, 
we found this cache during a 3 weeks trip around a southern part of Peru. Beautiful nature, smileys people, interesting food and exciting sigths - this is what Peru offer to us and why we was so satistified. The geocaching here is not so popular as in Europe or US, but thanks to this cache we had a chance to found it here. And this is more important then caches in mentioned countries. So thanks a lot for making a cache here, it's very appreciated and THANK YOU ;-).
OMadlikovi sazavsti, Czech republic, Europe

(CZ) Ahoj,
našli jsme tuto keš během 3 týdenního výletu za kešemi jižní částí Peru. Krásná příroda, usměvaví lidé, zajímavé jídlo a vzrušující cestování - to je to, co nám Peru nabízí a proč jsme byli tak ohromení. Geocaching zde není tak populární jako v Evropě nebo v USA, ale díky této kešce jsme měli možnost získat bodík právě zde. A to je vlastně důležitější než leckteré kešky v uvedených zemích. Takže díky moc ownerovi za to, že tady vytvořil keš, velmi si toho ceníme a DĚKUJEME ;-).
OMadlikovi sazavsti, Ceska republika, Evropa</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="770651195"><groundspeak:date>2018-05-09T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2028879">pig€ons</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">9. května 2018

Visité con un grupo de amigos en vacaciones en Perú.
Gracias muy buen lugar, Perú, gente agradable y caché.

Visited with a bunch of friends on holidays in Peru.
Thank you very nice place, Peru, nice people and cache.

Odloveno cestou po Peru. Díky za zajímavé pěkné místo a cache.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="11.980983333333333" lon="121.90888333333334"><time>2001-12-22T00:00:00</time><name>GC2E5F</name><desc>Baling Hai-- Philippines First Geocache!! by Chris Juricache</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC2E5F</url><urlname>Baling Hai-- Philippines First Geocache!!</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="11871" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Baling Hai-- Philippines First Geocache!!</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Chris Juricache</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="13805">Chris JuriCACHE</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="42" inc="1">Needs maintenance</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Philippines</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>You'll need both land and/or sea transportion to get here-- but the journey and final location are the prize!cr</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>What with typhoons, tidal changes, monsoons and lots of small kids who beachcomb or fish nearby, this cache is tucked safely away where water and wind won't bother it.
&lt;P&gt;
The island this cache is located upon can only be reached by banca with this lat/long being a good spot to start walking from (N 11° 58.860 E 121° 54.508)if you come by banca. For an additional clue as to what to tell the banca pilot, see the cryptoclue. Once you've arrived on the island, you could also reach the cache location via wheeled transport, and a general heading along the only main road would bring you to this spot (N 11° 58.862 E 121° 54.594)and then a short walk down the steps.
&lt;P&gt;
While the cache is accessible any time of the year, the best times would be November to May. Once you reach the final location of the cache, simply ask one of the people in the building (Gemma, Zenny, Otik, or Julia--anyone) and wave your GPS. They'll direct you to the cache's location!
&lt;P&gt;
Note that you're on private property here but the owners have given me permission to place this there and they expect/wonder if anyone will come to their beautiful resort seeking this geocache 'thing'.``</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>The cache is located in the main reception office of the Baling Hai Beach Resort on the island of Boracay. A beautiful place to stay-- either there or on any of the other beautiful resort hotels. If coming by banca (boat), ask the pilot to take you to Baling Hai beach. Preferably before you even left, you'd realize you'd need reservations to stay somewhere on the island, so why not Baling Hai! bb</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1143831585"><groundspeak:date>2023-01-06T06:56:48</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="115500">Crow T Robot</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">The owner of this cache is not able to maintain it and it appears that the cache is not in the approved location.  Please submit a new listing if this issue is resolved.  Thank you.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1143499077"><groundspeak:date>2023-01-03T21:29:44</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Needs Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="15176977">horfo21</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This geocacher reported that this geocache should be archived. A community volunteer reviewer has been notified.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1143499075"><groundspeak:date>2023-01-03T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="15176977">horfo21</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I have visit this geocache and I cant go inside because  its under construction and if I ask for go to inside 
They ask for a fee, it not follow the rules from geocaching.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1142644348"><groundspeak:date>2022-12-31T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="164089">jtee</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">im heading to boracay in jan just to do this cache so i hope it doesnt get archived..maybe the owner will be able to put it outside of the resort so there are no issues with it</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1142741058"><groundspeak:date>2022-12-31T11:04:13</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="12919409">rogernordin</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">How can anyone require the VERY FIRST GEOCACHE on the Philippines to be archived by a reviewer just because you don't feel like paying an entrance fee? Shame on you... and, for the rules you are referring to, this cache was placed before these rules were added so older caches can not be judged the same manner as new ones. A placed date of 2001 that can never ever be recreated by a newer cache, and you want to destroy it? What's wrong with people...
P.S. I reached out over Facebook and the people at the place were really polite and no fee was asked for. Perhaps it depends on how one asks?

Logged with [GCDroid](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.gcdroid).</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="52.249467" lon="20.994117"><time>2001-11-01T00:00:00</time><name>GC26A9</name><desc>Ndebele 1 by RadManZulu</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC26A9</url><urlname>Ndebele 1</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Virtual Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="9897" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Ndebele 1</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>RadManZulu</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="24478">RadManZulu</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Virtual Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Virtual</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Poland</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Mazowieckie</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Escape from the Holocaust</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>What was the only organization dedicated to helping Jews escape
from Nazi occupied Europe to be sponsored by it's own government in
exile.
&lt;p&gt;You are looking for something about the size of a large
suitcase. If you find this object, you will know the answer to this
question. It is located near to the Monument to the Heroes of the
Ghetto in Warsaw. This is not a cache, visiting Poland for the
first time, I didn't feel I understood the environment well enough
to establish a proper cache. This will however, be the first
Geocaching location in Poland so I claim a first. If you are
interested in the Second World War, or you are Jewish, this is an
important site to visit. The coordinates were captured with an
Etrex Vista, the terrain was open and the accuracy was good to
within 16 feet.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;FIRST EVER Geocache in Poland!!&lt;/p&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364941313"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-02T11:22:25</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6806186">EMACAL</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We thank RadManZulu for hiding Ndebele 1 and all owners
This is an important place for all germans, because this is the place where Willy Brandt fell on his knees.
TftC says emACal</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364819936"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="970311">wafot</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Wow, from 2001, this is great! Have a long time, little one 😊

TFTC,

Team WaFoT

Das war Nummer 2154</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364961187"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-31T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="18979531">OrienTheory</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">An interesting choice to visit the museum today, as it isn't something we'd normally be interested in. However the atrocities of WWII do make us curious, and hence the visit to the museum. A great introduction to the history of warsaw.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363852363"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-27T13:44:48</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="12870175">Sambataneli</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Interesting visit to the museum🤔</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363855253"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-24T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="25980459">daleileima</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thanks for the cache!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="38.733817" lon="-27.054733"><time>2001-05-15T00:00:00</time><name>GC8EF9</name><desc>Translant Chess Cache by Gummy(Az) Team</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC8EF9</url><urlname>Translant Chess Cache</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="36601" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Translant Chess Cache</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Gummy(Az) Team</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="5714950">Gummy(Az) Team</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Other</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="67" inc="1">GeoTour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="59" inc="1">Food nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="27" inc="1">Drinking water nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Portugal</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Arquipélago dos Açores</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/b0193e24-d8e9-4ba3-a54d-85c89a8aba81.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/fb400c73-8091-4e58-95ce-d93fad900bf4.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="height:501px;width:100%;"&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td rowspan="3"&gt; &lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td colspan="2"&gt;&lt;img height="38" src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/9db0d744-e12e-4bb3-ad84-5c100c5ed88c.jpg" width="44" /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td rowspan="3"&gt; &lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td colspan="2"&gt;
			&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:&amp;amp;quot;"&gt;Esta é a geocache mais antiga de Portugal!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:12px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:&amp;amp;quot;"&gt;A cache situa-se no Miradouro do Facho!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img height="175" src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/large/a0b66eb2-9897-46e5-bed0-30c1242e31fe.jpg" width="222" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:12px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:&amp;amp;quot;"&gt;O Miradouro do Facho localiza-se na serra do Facho, na cidade da Praia da Vitória, na ilha Terceira, Açores.&lt;br /&gt;
			&lt;br /&gt;
			O seu nome advém do fato de, primitivamente, neste ponto ter sido mantida uma fogueira acesa todas as noites, com a função de farol de aviso à navegação.&lt;br /&gt;
			&lt;br /&gt;
			Encontra-se assinalado como &amp;quot;11 Faxo&amp;quot; na &amp;quot;Planta da Bahia da Villa da Praia&amp;quot; (1805).&lt;br /&gt;
			&lt;br /&gt;
			Durante a Guerra Civil Portuguesa (1828-1834), aqui na Serra do Facho, como no Pico do Capitão, no Pico das Cruzes, no Pico das Contendas e no Monte Brasil, foi restabelecido pelos Liberais o antigo sistema de fachos (sinais de bandeiras em mastros em cruz), que foi evoluindo ao ponto de ser capaz de enviar mais de 60 mensagens diferentes em meados do século XIX.&lt;br /&gt;
			&lt;br /&gt;
			O miradouro abriga o Monumento do Imaculado Coração de Maria (Conhecida por Santa do Facho), padroeira da cidade, iniciado em 1983 e inaugurado em 31 de Dezembro de 1999.&lt;br /&gt;
			&lt;br /&gt;
			Acedido por uma escadaria na encosta pelo lado da cidade ou pela estrada, de seu alto descortina-se uma magnifica vista panorâmica sobre a cidade e seu entorno, desde a Serra do Cume até ao areal da baía da Praia da Vitória.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;&lt;img height="175" src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/73767642-2db6-4fcf-b65a-53945b92ddbc.jpg" width="222" /&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;img height="342" src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/09670800-ebd5-4d7b-862e-ba03fe3e3e03.jpg" width="222" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;&lt;img height="175" src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/f31f1d5a-1399-4708-af78-dec846868955.jpg" width="222" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img height="58" src="http://www.geocaching.com/images/WptTypes/traditional_72.gif" width="55" /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#0000ff;font-family:&amp;amp;quot;"&gt;Acerca da cache:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style="font-family:Arial Black;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;O logbook está dentro do container, que por sua vez está dentro de um tupperware para proteção. Há espaço para objetos de troca, trackables, geocoins, etc.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Como o próprio nome indica, seria interessante haver partilha de peças de xadrez.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style="font-size:12px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial;"&gt;(Fica ao critério de cada um)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ff0000;font-family:&amp;amp;quot;"&gt;POR FAVOR, AJUDEM ESTA CACHE A DURAR!&lt;br /&gt;
TENHAM MUITO CUIDADO COM OS MUGGLES!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ff0000;font-family:&amp;amp;quot;"&gt;CUIDADO COM O MANUSEAMENTO DO CONTAINER!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/fb400c73-8091-4e58-95ce-d93fad900bf4.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="height:501px;width:100%;"&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td rowspan="3"&gt; &lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td colspan="2"&gt;&lt;img height="38" src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/93a536bb-19be-482c-9c5e-a95b095707dd.jpg" width="44" /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td rowspan="3"&gt; &lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td colspan="2"&gt;
			&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:&amp;amp;quot;"&gt;This is the oldest geocache in Portugal!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:12px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:&amp;amp;quot;"&gt;The cache is located at the Miradouro do Facho!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img height="175" src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/large/a0b66eb2-9897-46e5-bed0-30c1242e31fe.jpg" width="222" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:12px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:&amp;amp;quot;"&gt;The Miradouro do Facho located on the serra do Facho, in city of Praia da Vitória, in Terceira Island, Azores.&lt;br /&gt;
			&lt;br /&gt;
			Its name comes from the fact, primitively, this point has been kept a fire lit every night, with the function of the navigation beacon warning.&lt;br /&gt;
			&lt;br /&gt;
			Is designated as &amp;quot;11 Faxo&amp;quot; in &amp;quot;Planta da Bahia da Villa da Praia&amp;quot; (1805).&lt;br /&gt;
			&lt;br /&gt;
			During the Portuguese Civil War (1828-1834), here in Serra do Facho, as in Pico do Capitão, in Pico das Cruzes, in Pico das Contendas and in Monte Brasil, was restored by Liberals the old system of beams (signal flags on masts cross), that has evolved to the point of being able to send over 60 different messages by mid-century XIX.&lt;br /&gt;
			&lt;br /&gt;
			The Miradouro houses the Monument of the Immaculate Heart of Mary (known for Santa do Facho), patron saint of the city, initiated on 1983 and opened in December 31 of 1999.&lt;br /&gt;
			&lt;br /&gt;
			Accessed by a staircase on the hillside by the side of town or by the road, its high opens up a magnificent panoramic view upon the city and its surroundings, from Serra do Cume to the sand of bay of Praia da Vitória.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;&lt;img height="175" src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/73767642-2db6-4fcf-b65a-53945b92ddbc.jpg" width="222" /&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;img height="342" src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/09670800-ebd5-4d7b-862e-ba03fe3e3e03.jpg" width="222" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;&lt;img height="175" src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/f31f1d5a-1399-4708-af78-dec846868955.jpg" width="222" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img height="58" src="http://www.geocaching.com/images/WptTypes/traditional_72.gif" width="55" /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#0000ff;font-family:&amp;amp;quot;"&gt;About the cache:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial Black;"&gt;The logbook is inside a container, which is placed inside a tupperware for protection. The tupperware also has room for trade items, trackables, geocoins, etc.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
As the name suggests, it would be interesting to share chess pieces.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style="font-size:12px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial;"&gt;(entirely up to each individual)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ff0000;font-family:&amp;amp;quot;"&gt;PLEASE,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="background-color:#ffffff;color:#ff0000;font-family:Arial Black;"&gt;HELP THIS CACHELAST&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ff0000;font-family:&amp;amp;quot;"&gt;!&lt;br /&gt;
HAVE VERY CAREFUL WITH THE MUGGLES!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ff0000;font-family:&amp;amp;quot;"&gt;BE CAREFUL WITH CONTAINER HANDLING!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/04a41b81-2fc0-4cd7-b05d-ad0bd61db500.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Na direção do poste de madeira. O tupperware é apenas para proteger o container. O logbook está dentro do container. // In the direction of the wooden pole. The tupperware is just there to protect the container. The logbook is inside the container.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364009183"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-28T12:15:07</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Didn't find it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="27617159">dKAPs13</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Area closed therefore no change of getting there. Also dangerous with the storm today </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1361944637"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-18T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4483603">Friedcacher</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Mission completed. The final location is in the restricted area. But who care?

The logbook is full, I left a small replacement.

One TB out, one TB in.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1361087172"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-15T11:52:13</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5925816">BaldasFamily</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Encontrada numa viagem, com um grupo de velhos Amigos, que resolveu marcar um jantar fora do continente 😀</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360313097"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-10T19:19:44</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="38861852">vvn12</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">TFTC❤️ 
Team MoriLola </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360232701"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-10T15:04:07</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="11470633">pikaju</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Por terras açorianas não podíamos deixar de fazer estas caches 
OPC 
LOGADA COMO APPT ( At1964, pikaju, pykii, Tarmikos) 
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="18.069467" lon="-66.219267"><time>2002-12-28T00:00:00</time><name>GCBADB</name><desc>El Jibaro by Harold Hernandez</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCBADB</url><urlname>El Jibaro</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="47835" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>El Jibaro</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Harold Hernandez</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="89441">Haroldo</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="0">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="0">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="40" inc="1">Stealth required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="0">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Puerto Rico</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Look for the statue on your way from San Juan to Ponce.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>This is the oldest CACHE in Puerto Rico, yes.... still alive.

You can only locate this cache if you are driving southbound. It is located at 1,512 feet of altitud.

The cache is a small container. It contain a log and a pencil.

This is the first cache that I place.

Will hunting for this cache go a visit:

Monumento al Jíbaro Puertorriqueño

The Monumento al Jíbaro Puertorriqueño (Monument to the Puerto Rican Countryman) is a monument built by the Government of Puerto Rico to honor the now disappeared Puerto Rican Jíbaro, in remembrance of Puerto Rico's humble roots. It was sculpted by Tomás Batista.
The "Jíbaro" is a Puerto Rican staple of times past, a humble, hardworking and wise man, but living in poverty and with little or no education. Jíbaros disappeared from the countryside as freeways and well-maintained roads allowed the countrymen to emigrate from the island's mountains to the coastal cities to acquire education, better work opportunities, or even emigrate to the US mainland. Today, most Puerto Ricans have readily access to education and work.
Recognizing the influence of the Jíbaro in the development of the Puerto Rican culture, the Government of Puerto Rico erected the monument by Autopista PR-52, close to the island's Central Range to remind the passerby's of our lost, but not forgotten heritage and roots.</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Some rocks are guarding look around the base of a lonely  tree.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1362213371"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-19T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3403497">Georick402</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Greetings from Germantown MD. On the island for 5 days with three goals. 1. Meet family. 2. Visit the highpoint. 3. Get the oldest geocache. Anything else is a bonus.

Stopped here on our way to the highest point in Puerto Rico. A nice trail from the parking lot brought us to a clearing then to gz.

Need to be careful around gz as to not trip on any rocks. We also had to Google the type of tree we were looking off.

No problem with the find. Removed 1 travel bug and dropped off about 25.

AIO TFTC FP FROM ME</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362150739"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-19T11:32:29</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="21607857">Shelleyhorn</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thtf </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1351921257"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-29T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5105270">Zascandiles</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Hacemos un alto en busca del primer caché de Puerto Rico 🤩 El área de descanso está cerrada. Paramos en la valla, saltamos la cerca y subimos a por el caché. ¡No podíamos irnos sin haberlo encontrado!

Aparece sin problemas y en buen estado. 

TB in

Muchas gracias Haroldo por el caché y por mostrarnos este lugar.

Puedes seguir nuestras aventuras en Instagram: @geozascandiles

https://www.instagram.com/geozascandiles?igsh=dzlxemZ1ZDZhN2d0</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1350938858"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-13T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="950446">JuanaCache</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">What a cool stop this was. It was an easy short walk down the easy dewy grass trail to this wonderous tree with big fruits. I had to use the google machine to find out more about them. A quick sign and then we were off south to the other side of the island for more adventures. The smile is appreciated, thanks!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1349115622"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-13T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="350523">bflentje</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Find #32,129. Enjoying exploring the entire island of Puerto Rico between heading off on a 7 day cruise with wifey and geo-sis. We always strive to find a state's or country's oldest and this appears to be the one for Puerto Rico. Nice hide under an odd kind of fruit tree. TFTC.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="25.2808" lon="51.53525"><time>2004-03-01T00:00:00</time><name>GCHTRV</name><desc>Not the Golden Arch! by The MoJos</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCHTRV</url><urlname>Not the Golden Arch!</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Virtual Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="120122" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Not the Golden Arch!</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>The MoJos</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="100933">TheMoJos</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Virtual Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Virtual</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Qatar</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>An easy virtual cache to add Qatar to the list of geocache nations!</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description> 
DO NOT ATTEMPT TO LOG THIS CACHE UNLESS YOU ACTUALLY GO TO IT!!!


This cache will take you to Doha, Qatar.  Near the center of town is a unique arch.  In order to log this cache, email me the number of granite plates that compose one corner of the base. To clarify, the base is made of 8 sides, four long ones and 4 short ones, that are on the corners. Each corner is composed of a number of slanted granite plates. As an alternate method, you can send a picture of your GPS in front of the arch.  This is a very simple cache, but be careful of other vehicles.  Please do not put descriptions/pictures in your logs.  The intent of this cache is for you to actually visit the area, not just research on the internet.  After all, the whole point of geocaching is to get you off the couch!  If I believe that you did not actually visit the cache, I will delete the log entry.

Special "Thanks" to Tapio Heiskanen for his additional research and allowing me to reopen this cache.</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1346531821"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-27T18:03:28</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="27509281">vaakalintu</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I spend a day and a half in Doha on an extended layover on my way from Helsinki to Thiruvananthapuram. Came here to snap a quick pic before heading to the airport. I send the pic to the CO via message center. Thanks for the virtual and greetings from Finland!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1346183095"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-24T15:52:29</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="980790">Roggenfeld</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thanks for setting up this cache and for leading us to this arch.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1345586118"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-19T11:11:24</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="26238549">Stellasuisse</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Favorite point🤩! 

Our adventure “A world tour in 4 and a half months,” organized to celebrate our 40th wedding anniversary, began on February 11, 2026.

Step 1: Zurich, 1 night
Step 2: Abu Dhabi, 5 nights, with a day trip to Dubai
Step 3: Doha, we arrived on February 17 for 5 nights.

We are living this great journey in discovery mode… and Geocaching makes us see the world in a different way. It adds that extra magic, full of surprises, unexpected encounters, and little sparks of joy 😁🤩🥰.

Today we visited two iconic places in Doha:

Souq Waqif: a lively traditional market, where we were amazed to see for the first time so many falcons, each wearing a funny little hood, waiting patiently.

Katara Cultural Village: a seaside site of incredible beauty… we had never seen anything so splendid!

A huge thank you to all the cache and Lab owners who turn our trip into a true worldwide treasure hunt.
You are the anonymous accomplices of our laughter, our improbable detours, and those extra steps not planned by our legs… But they never complain, so we just keep going.

Geo-friendly greetings from two Swiss in celebration 💕🙋🏻‍♂️🙋🏻‍♀️

************************

Notre aventure « Un tour du monde en 4 mois et demi », organisée pour célébrer nos 40 ans de mariage, a débuté le 11 février 2026.

Étape 1 : Zurich, 1 nuit
Étape 2 : Abu Dhabi, 5 nuits, avec une excursion à Dubaï
Étape 3 : Doha, arrivés le 17 février pour 5 nuits.

Nous vivons ce grand voyage en mode découverte… et le Géocaching nous fait voir le monde autrement. Il y ajoute cette magie supplémentaire, faite de surprises, de rencontres inattendues et de petits éclats de joie 😁🤩🥰.

Aujourd’hui, nous avons visité deux lieux emblématiques de Doha :

Souq Waqif : un marché traditionnel animé, où nous avons été émerveillés de voir pour la première fois autant de faucons, chacun coiffé d’un petit casque très rigolo, attendant sagement.

Katara Cultural Village : un site au bord de la mer, d’une beauté incroyable… nous n’avions jamais vu quelque chose d’aussi splendide !

Un immense merci à tous les propriétaires qui, grâce à leurs caches et Labs, transforment notre voyage en une véritable chasse au trésor mondiale.
Vous êtes les complices anonymes de nos fous rires, de nos détours improbables et de nos pas supplémentaires non prévus par nos mollets… Mais ils ne se plaignent jamais, alors on continue.

Géoamicales salutations de deux Suisses en fête 💕🙋🏻‍♂️🙋🏻‍♀️</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1344628313"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-11T17:01:40</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="20584184">veselacicz</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Many thanks</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1344156599"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-07T18:22:50</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8895614">Pootlepants</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Answers sent. Lovely day exploring the sound. TFTC! </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="-21.225333" lon="55.684633"><time>2009-05-22T00:00:00</time><name>GC1RNRX</name><desc>LA PITON DE LA FOURNAISE (LA REUNION) by broiler</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC1RNRX</url><urlname>LA PITON DE LA FOURNAISE (LA REUNION)</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Earthcache</type><groundspeak:cache id="1248338" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>LA PITON DE LA FOURNAISE (LA REUNION)</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>broiler</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="851509">broiler</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Earthcache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Other</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="0">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="56" inc="1">Medium hike (1 km–10 km)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="14" inc="0">Recommended at night</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="27" inc="0">Drinking water nearby</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Réunion</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>&lt;center&gt;&lt;img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/gs-geo-images/343835e7-cde7-4108-964e-8b0146de550e_l.png" /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
This cache is &lt;a href="https://www.geocaching.com/blog/2020/05/new-country-souvenir-reunion-with-geocache-of-the-week-la-piton-de-la-fournaise/"&gt;&lt;font color="#0000FF"&gt;geocache of the week - 20th of May 2020!&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/center&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;font color="#FF0000"&gt;&lt;b&gt;5.9.2009: Attention: The path is currently closed behind the Chapelle de Rosemont. See changed log conditions at the end of the listing!&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Approach:&lt;/b&gt; By Le Vingt-Septième (27km from St. Pierre; 34km from St. Benoit) take the RF5. Follow the high quality forestry road „La route du Volcan“ via Nez du Boeuf (view point into the 1200m deep gorge of the Rivière de Remparts), Commerson Crater and the lunar landscape Plaine de Sable till &lt;b&gt;Pas de Bellecombe&lt;/b&gt;, where a parking lot and a snack bar are available to visitors.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Attention:&lt;/b&gt; Visitors exploring the caldera should be in good physical condition, with hiking shoes and a supply of drinking water and food. They must be prepared to exercise caution, for the weather can change very quickly, moving from bright sunlight and heat (with risks of heatstroke) to dense fog with cold and rain. In dense fog, straying from paths is very risky. Visitors are advised to take the necessary precautions for sun, heat, cold and rain and not to stray from marked paths.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Trip advisor:&lt;/b&gt; The most tourist take the following trail: Pas de Bellecombe – Formica Leo – Chapelle de Rosemont - La Soufière – Cratère Dolomieu – Cratère Bory– Chapelle de Rosemont – Formica Leo – Pas de Bellecombe (Duration: about 5 hours, distance 12,25km, 680m differences in high). You can also do the trip counterclockwise, that doesn't matter.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Tip:&lt;/b&gt;If you got the opportunity than make a helicopter trip above the volcano or the whole island.&lt;br /&gt;
Near to Pas de Bellecombe is situated the Gîte du volcan (WP9). This is a little restaurant where you can stay there overnight.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;La Piton de la Fournaise&lt;/b&gt; is a shield volcano on the eastern side of Réunion island. It is currently one of the most active volcanoes in the world, with more than 150 recorded eruptions since the 17th century. The last eruption began at 15th of Deceber 2008 and lasted till the 4th of february 2009.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A table with the recent eruptions since 1977 of the Piton de la Fournaise and a webcam you will find &lt;a href="http://www.fournaise.info/eruptions_tableau.php"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
The summit of the volcano is 2631m high. High cliffs known as &lt;b&gt;remparts&lt;/b&gt; form the caldera's rim. The caldera is breached to the southeast into the sea. It is also unstable and in the initial stages of failure and will eventually collapse into the Indian Ocean. There is evidence on the submerged flanks and abyssal plain of earlier failures. The lower slopes are known as the &lt;b&gt;Grand Brûlé&lt;/b&gt; ("Great Burnt"). Most lava eruptions are confined to the caldera.&lt;br /&gt;
Inside the caldera is a 400 metre high lava shield . Atop the lava shield are &lt;b&gt;Cratére Bory&lt;/b&gt; and &lt;b&gt;Cratére Dolomieu&lt;/b&gt;, which is by far the wider of the two.&lt;br /&gt;
Many craters and spatter cones can be found inside the caldera and the outer flanks of the volcano. At the beginning of the path that leads to the summit, there lies a noticeable small crater known as &lt;b&gt;Formica leo&lt;/b&gt;, named for its similar shape to the pitfall built by the little insect antlion.&lt;br /&gt;
Some of the beaches there are of a greenish colour, because of the olivine sand resulting from picrite basalt lavas. The Grand Brûlé is formed from solidified lava flows accumulated over hundreds of thousands of years; the most recent ones are often the darkest and most vegetation-free, while older ones can be covered by dense wild vegetation. Iridium is being ejected through these vents.&lt;br /&gt;
The volcano is over 530,000 years old, and for most of its history, its flows have intermingled with those from Piton des Neiges, a larger, older and heavily eroded extinct volcano which forms the northwest two-thirds of Réunion Island. There were three episodes of caldera collapses 250,000, 65,000 and 5,000 years ago. The volcano was formed by the Réunion hotspot, which is believed to have been active for the past 65 million years. There is evidence for explosive eruptions in the past.&lt;br /&gt;
Most eruptions of Piton de la Fournaise are of the Hawaiian style: fluid basaltic lava flowing out with fire fountaining at the vent. Occasionally, phreatic eruptions (groundwater steam-generated eruptions) occur. Lava flows crossing the Grand Brûlé occasionally reach the sea, with spectacular results.&lt;br /&gt;
Eruptions within the caldera do not cause much devastation, because the caldera is uninhabited and little infrastructure exists apart from the highway.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;font color="#FF0000"&gt;Attention: Inform yourself if the path is open. Due to volcanic activity it might be closed for a while.&lt;/font&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Your trip:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Pas de Bellecombe:&lt;/b&gt; Form the Parking place leads a path to the Pas de Bellecombe (2357m) which is situated over the caldera rim cliffs and offers a good point of view over the northeast part of the caldera. A good stairway path (more than 600 steps) descends from the pass to the caldera floor, (&lt;b&gt;Enclos Fouqué&lt;/b&gt;). The stairway offers good views onto the Formica Leo&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Formica Leo&lt;/b&gt;: This reddish little crater was built 1753 by a cinder rain.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;La Chapelle de Rosemont&lt;/b&gt;: This natuaral grotto was formed by a emorme explosion of a gas bubble, which served alrady the first explorers Joseph Hubert &amp;amp; Patu de Rosemont 1791 and Bory de Saint-Vincent 1801 as safehouse and invites for a short break before ascending the volcan.&lt;br /&gt;
Shortly after the Chapelle de Rosemont the path divides. If the weather does not force you to a quick direct ascendent, take the less steep path to the left vers Soufrière.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;La Soufrière&lt;/b&gt;: This brimstone pit (2518m) lies on the north side of the Dolomieu Krater, is 185m deep and its borders are very slippery. This pit was build during the eruption in 1964/65 where a lake of lava appeared. After that a gap occurred and the lake bottomed out leaving sulfric fumaroles behind.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Cratère Dolomieu&lt;/b&gt;: About one kilometer long and 750m wide the Dolomieu Crater ist h biggest of the two high plateau volcanos. It is appeared in 1791 as a result of the collapse of a hugh magma chamber. It was named by Jean-Baptiste Bory de Saint-Vincent in 1801 which heard of the death of his professor Dèodat Gratet de Dolomieu (specialist of basalt). Till the eruption in the second half of 2006, which recovered all, streams of lava, spatter cones and lava tunnels covered the bottom of the Dolomieu crater, which had a deepness of 80m in the East and 150m in the West before the eruption. Since the extraordinary eruption in April 2007, which caused the lowering of the bottom for about 300m, the crater has regained deepness. At the same opportunity ist northside collapsed in a thickness of 10 meters.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Cratère Bory&lt;/b&gt;: The steep faced Crater Bory is the smaller one of the two high plateau volcanos, which was built in 1791 and still presents traces of an recent eruption. It is 350m long and 200m wide. You can see the numbers of monitor units in the pit before dismount to the Chapelle de Rosemont (hard but short right path; less rude via Soufrière).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;To log this Earthcache as a found, you have to contact me via geocaching, telling me, the awnsers to the following questions:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;1.) Waypoint 2: Stairs:&lt;/b&gt; Look at your GPSr before and after climbing down the stairs. Tell me the difference in high.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;2.)Waypoint 3: Formica Leo:&lt;/b&gt; Search for the enamelled tag „Formica Leo“. Which information about the high you can read there?&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;s&gt;&lt;b&gt;3.) Waypoint 4: Chapelle de Rosemont:&lt;/b&gt; Estimate the altitude of the entrance.&lt;/s&gt; not visible anylonger&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;4.) Waypoint 5: Soufrière:&lt;/b&gt; Which colour could you see often at the black lava?&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;5.) Waypoint 8: Cratère Bory:&lt;/b&gt; Take a picture of you in front of the crater (enamelled sign (see reference-photo)) and upload it to your log (re-allowed by GC since June 2019). If it's to risky to go to this point document your visit with a photo at another recognisable spot.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Logs without the required e-mail will be deleted without comment. Due to "administration" of the log-permissions it is nessecary that every team send an e-mail by itsself even if you were there together. Do not wait for log-permission, just log your found directly after sending the mail; we will contact you if there is something wrong.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;font color="#FF0000"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Changed log-conditions (5.9.2009) because the path is closed behind the Chapelle de Rosemont: Fulfill task 1.), 2.) and 3.) and upload a picture which shows you at the chapelle (optional since 1.1.2011)!&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1351601271"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-21T12:27:48</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8272056">choconaren</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thanks for the cache with meerblau. Pity we weren’t on the other side. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1351168376"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-21T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4508454">meerblau</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I have to admit that I knew little about Réunion before our cruise stop there and only learned a few days prior to arrival that one of its volcanoes had erupted. That's a downside of long cruises with packed itineraries. On the other hand, Réunion truly surprised me with its stunning beauty - and, of course, its active volcano, Piton de la Fournaise.
Thank you very much for having lured choconaren and me here. I think that only the people who came by helicopter, had better views. Great place for an earthcache!

🇩🇪 Germany | 🇵🇹 Portugal | 🇪🇸 Spain | 🇧🇧 Barbados | 🇱🇨 St. Lucia | 🇩🇲 Dominica | 🇲🇸 Montserrat | 🇰🇳 St. Kitts and Nevis | 🇯🇲 Jamaica | 🇲🇽 Mexico | 🇧🇿 Belize | 🇬🇹 Guatemala | 🇨🇴 Colombia | 🇨🇷 Costa Rica | 🇵🇦 Panama | 🇪🇨 Ecuador  | 🇵🇪 Peru | 🇨🇱 Chile | 🇵🇫 French Polynesia | 🇹🇴 Tonga  | 🇫🇯 Fiji | 🇳🇿 New Zealand | 🇦🇺 Australia | 🇮🇩 Indonesia | 🇸🇬 Singapore | 🇲🇾 Malaysia | 🇹🇭 Thailand | 🇱🇰 Sri Lanka | 🇲🇻 Maldives | 🇲🇺 Mauritius | 🇷🇪 Réunion</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1343727462"><groundspeak:date>2025-12-31T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="25348741">SilentWolfík</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Visited during a holiday in Reunion. Beautiful place,incredible experience. TFTC from Slovakia.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1343716029"><groundspeak:date>2025-12-31T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="7327898">Silent-Wolf</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Visited during a holiday in Reunion. Beautiful place,incredible experience. TFTC from Slovakia and FP.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1338923159"><groundspeak:date>2025-11-25T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6089366">Divemann</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Heute um ca. 14:21 Uhr gefunden.

Die diesjährige Fernreise geht zum wandern nach La Reunion und zum entspannen nach Mauritius. Es stehen drei aufregende Wochen vor mir, wo das Geocachen auch nicht zu kurz kommen darf.
Am neunten Tag ging es zum Piton de la Fournaise. Es waren 13 km in einer schönen Natur.

raus: nichts
rein: Favoritenpunkt

Danke an broiler für den Earth Geocache und meinen 6386. Fund, sagt Divemann.

- Die wirkliche Entdeckungsreise besteht nicht darin neue Landschaften zu erforschen, sondern darin, altes mit neuen Augen zu sehen! (Marcel Proust)
- Nur wo du zu Fuß warst, bist du auch wirklich gewesen. (Johann Wolfgang von Goethe)
- Man reist nicht nur um anzukommen, sondern vor allem, um unterwegs zu sein. (Johann Wolfgang von Goethe)

--------------------------------------------------------------------

Trouvée aujourd'hui vers 14h21.

Ce voyage au long cours me mène à La Réunion pour la randonnée et à l'île Maurice pour la détente. Trois semaines passionnantes m'attendent, et le géocaching sera assurément au programme.

Le neuvième jour, j'ai randonné jusqu'au Piton de la Fournaise. Une randonnée de 13 km à travers de magnifiques paysages.

Sortie : rien
Entrée : mon emplacement préféré

Merci à broiler pour la géocache Earth et ma 6386e trouvaille, dit Divemann.

- Le véritable voyage de découverte ne consiste pas à chercher de nouveaux paysages, mais à avoir de nouveaux yeux ! (Marcel Proust)
- On n'est vraiment allé que là où l'on a marché. (Johann Wolfgang von Goethe)
- On ne voyage pas seulement pour arriver, mais surtout pour être en chemin. (Johann Wolfgang von Goethe)</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="45.513267" lon="25.369367"><time>2001-04-01T00:00:00</time><name>GC5D8</name><desc>Dracula's Castle by Team Romania</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC5D8</url><urlname>Dracula's Castle</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="1496" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Dracula's Castle</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Team Romania</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="6783">Team Romania</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="40" inc="0">Stealth required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="38" inc="0">Campfires</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="0">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>3</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Romania</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Romania's first cache!! Drive to within 200 meters, but those last 200 meters are not for smokers.
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>Located near Bran Castle, legendary lair of Vlad Tepes, otherwise known as Dracula. Excellent views of the Carpathian Mountains and Romanian countryside can also be seen. This cache consists mainly of toys and games, but also includes a few essential vampire deterrents, including a mirror, a Croatian pre-paid phone card with a photo of the Pope on it, and a large pencil that could be used as a wooden stake in an emergency. The cache container is a rectangular plastic tupperware-like thing with a green lid. Access information: - best way: from the castle's courtyard N 45° 30.890 E 25° 22.050, follow the path uphill. Visiting fee required, accessible only during the castle's opening hours. Recommended for those who also want to visit the castle. Estimated hiking time: 10 minutes. - 2nd best way: go to N 45° 30.860 E 25° 22.400, follow Festung street until you reach the ridge, walk on the ridge to the cache location. The road passes next to unfenced properties and barking dogs, not recommended during the night. Estimated hiking time: 30 minutes. - mad way: go to N 45° 30.740 E 25° 21.920, walk along the riverbed until you find a suitable trail going uphill, then walk on the ridge to the cache location. Difficult climbing. Accessible 24/7. Estimated hiking time: 40 minutes
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Upon reaching the top, go to the first large tree in the clearing and then walk 15 paces to the NE.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1362210189"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-18T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="45478239">AnnaMarente</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">After visiting Bran castle we coudn't leave Bran without looking for this cache. We took a bit of a scenic route to the cache (which we enjoyed very much). At GZ we first looked into the wrong direction but when we found the right direction the cache was in a logical place. Thanks for many years of maintaining this cache! </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362210183"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-18T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="43418177">LupusPrimus</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Today AnnaMarente and I decided to go to Bran castle and also look for some caches. Ofcource the oldest and most liked cache of Romania was on our list. We didn't take the shortest path to the cache, but it was definitely worthwhile with the nice views we got to see. At ground zero we were able to find and log the cache after looking around for a bit. Thanks for hiding and maintaining this cache for 25 years! A favo from me!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364274445"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-14T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6790648">Team Hvisthule</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found it on our visit to Draculas castle. 
Thanks for the hide :D</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1361835126"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-14T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="14540664">laonda2</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">After visiting the castle, I walked up the steep path to the oldest geocache in Romania.


</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360556811"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-12T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="9515096">ffiligirl</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">A long hard walk up hill not helped by the rain</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="52.54775" lon="158.1991"><time>2001-08-12T00:00:00</time><name>GC162E</name><desc>Mutnovsky:1 (Nikolay-Kam:2) by Nikolay-Kam</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC162E</url><urlname>Mutnovsky:1 (Nikolay-Kam:2)</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="5678" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Mutnovsky:1 (Nikolay-Kam:2)</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Nikolay-Kam</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="17944">____Nikolay-Kam</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>2.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Russia</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>The most fissile volcano and beautiful place. The cache with a surprise. </groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>The cache with a surprise! Around very beautiful places. The mining landscapes of a Mutnovsky volcano will not keep you indifferent. Here most fissile geothermal developments, set of hot sources and most famous electricity generating plant working on underground energy. Near there is a fissile volcano. The route is serviced by many Kamchatka travel agencies.&lt;BR&gt;
The most beautiful place on earth!!!</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Kurgan on entry in a settlement of the geologists. Height of 10 meters. The cache to find is foolproof.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1303142777"><groundspeak:date>2025-06-07T06:13:19</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="12592304">SKF5</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found and entered in the logbook</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1283241247"><groundspeak:date>2025-03-02T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="7531818">18Tom60</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Unterwegs mit Freunden in dieser trostlosen Gegend. 
Dose konnte gut gefunden und erfolgreich geloggt werden 
