</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1334925300"><groundspeak:date>2025-11-16T08:06:10</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6535652">SteLaSyXL</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Heute morgen ging es schon früh los auf Dosensuche. Weil viele der Dosen schon bald seit einem Jahr und mehr nicht mehr gefunden wurden, hatten wir nich all zu viel Hoffnung. Wir wurden aber eines besseren belehrt und fanden hier alles so vor wie es muss.
***
This morning we started early on a can search. Because many of the cans have not been found for a year and more, we did not have too much hope. But we were taught better and found everything here as it has to be.
***

Hier waren wir bei 'Jacob's Ladder' mit der grösse Klein von Shamcock den wir suchen und finden durften.

Vielen Dank und 
Grüsse vom Baselbieter🇨🇭 aus dem Fricktal
Sagt SteLaSyXL

</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1334979720"><groundspeak:date>2025-11-16T08:05:13</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8506681">Riba14</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Finally it’s time today and we cache on St Helena. What a cool experience. We explored the island and stopped at selected places. This task was also included and we successfully register.
What a steep staircase. Very impressive. We were able to find the box well and we donated a small new logbook.
Thank you for bringing me here

Says Riba14 🙋‍♀️</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1207523970"><groundspeak:date>2023-12-01T00:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="727354">qrang</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Collected the numbers then puffed our way up the steps - took us about 20-25 minutes - once at the top we caught our breathe then the cache wasn't far away and soon spotted. We left trackable and have a favourite point many many thanks</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1136475197"><groundspeak:date>2022-11-05T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2125672">Proton26</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Unfortunately the ladder is under construction. So I took the road up and could finally find the box. Thanks for the cache!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="17.122967" lon="-62.59555"><time>2002-08-01T00:00:00</time><name>GC7C85</name><desc>The Botanical Garden Cache, Nevis by crr003</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC7C85</url><urlname>The Botanical Garden Cache, Nevis</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Virtual Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="31877" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>The Botanical Garden Cache, Nevis</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>crr003</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="41116">crr003</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Virtual Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Virtual</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Saint Kitts and Nevis</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>If you are visiting Nevis, West Indies, you'll probably visit this site anyway.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>The Botanical Garden is one of the sites on a visitors' list to Nevis.  It costs $17 or 45EC (updated March 2023, thanks "Found it") to enter, but the gardens are well worth the trip.  There is a rainforest conservatory, loads of orchids, and tropical fruit plants/trees. 

The virtual cache location is in the Orchid Terraces.  There is a date at the location - email me the date to confirm the find.
UPDATE: March 2015.  The date was carved on a tree, but the tree is not there any more.  A photo of a mammalian feature close by will confirm the visit..........</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Date was carved on a Palm Tree near to a Dolphin water feature.
</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1351237917"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-26T07:30:44</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="783756">SSSharkie1</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Spent the morning at the botanical gardens. Nice spot! Thanks for bringing me here and love seeing this is an old virtual cache. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1349756530"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-17T12:14:44</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2376893">Tacozelf</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">What a beautiful garden to visit, especially enjoyed the parrots! Thanks for maintaining this old virtual!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1348764683"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-12T12:58:44</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="357101">JimHoney</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This was one of the highlights of the trip. Beautiful gardens and so well maintained. We met the owner. A favorite place. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1348769140"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-12T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="164839">Rinkey</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This is a beautiful garden, well maintained and one of the best I’ve seen in the world.  Maintained by the owner Christi, a lovely person and her staff of 6 volunteers it’s a wonderful part of Nevis. A nice walk from the Montpelier Plantation. Favorite point to you crr003. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1347440571"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-04T19:03:40</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="7339274">Famass</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Hi 
 we visited the beautiful botanical garden and went to a equally beautiful beach in Nevis! 🤩

We were very warmly welcomed and the great plants were explained to us thoroughly and professionally! I took a picture at dolphins 😁
I like it ❤️
TftC Famass</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="-13.864617" lon="-171.770667"><time>2002-08-11T00:00:00</time><name>GC7E06</name><desc>Ala o le alofa by Vailima</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC7E06</url><urlname>Ala o le alofa</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Virtual Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="32262" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Ala o le alofa</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Vailima</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="64506">Vailima</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Virtual Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Virtual</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="33" inc="0">Motorcycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="34" inc="0">Quads</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="35" inc="0">Off-road vehicles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="37" inc="0">Horses</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="38" inc="0">Campfires</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="36" inc="0">Snowmobiles</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Samoa</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>A virtual cache at the tomb of Robert Louis Stevenson in Samoa
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>At the end of the Ala o le alofa atop Mount Vaea is the final resting place of Robert Louis Stevenson (Tusitala). His grave bears the following poem.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;center&gt;&lt;b&gt;Robert Louis Stevenson, 1850-1894&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
UNDER the wide and starry sky&lt;br /&gt;
Dig the grave and let me lie:&lt;br /&gt;
Glad did I live and gladly die,&lt;br /&gt;
And I laid me down with a will.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
This be the verse you grave for me:&lt;br /&gt;
Here he lies were he long'd to be;&lt;br /&gt;
Home is the sailor, home form the sea,&lt;br /&gt;
And the hunter home from the hill.&lt;/center&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Because of the puaa ai vao, moa ai vao, ma le tagata ai vao a cache here would become malepelepe. Because of this we had to make this cache a virtual one. The tomb of RLS has two quotations on it, one is his requiem listed above, the other, on the north side, is less widely known. To log this cache post a photo of your GPS receiver and the north side of the RLS tomb.&lt;br /&gt;
The best way to get to the cache is to go up the cross island road and park at the trailhead near Stevensons former home in Vailima, now the official head of State residence, follow the trail, not your GPS .&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Manuia le caching!
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>E mafai ona e faitau le tusi paia?</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1357176383"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-26T10:35:03</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Didn't find it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="917962">Search 4</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I intend to find this virtual as a perfect start to my Sunday morning in Samoa.  Unfortunately, both the museum and botanical gardens are close on Sunday and other trailheads were blocked by fences.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1355508538"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-17T15:15:42</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="9686815">kjtorres13</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Pretty intense hike up to the tomb but quite satisfied to make it to the top!  Glad to have a spot to rest before descending. Thanks!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1355508417"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-17T15:09:32</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8743405">41VINCE</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">With kjt13, on Celebrity Solstice. Cab from shuttle stop. Beautiful botanical garden and very difficult climb to GZ. SHOULD be a D5. IMHO.  THANKS FOR establishing and maintaining this virtual. 

Fav from me. Find 5,100 and the only cache we found accessible to the port!!!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1355506744"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-17T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="333655">Aloha! &amp; Wahine Eye Spy</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Aloha! On island thanks to the Celebrity Solstice. Been on since Hong Kong and headed home to Hawaii. Love stopping at other islands along the way. You either love or hate island living. We happen to love it! This island was no exception!

What was an exception was the cache. Dang! Sure wish we had done a bit more research. We paid a taxi driver to take us to the spot indicated in the write up. He did. We were a bit surprised that people were pushing us to pay the fee, reasonable, to go in the museum. Once we got our driver to understand what we were actually looking for, he talked to another local who sent us to a trail entrance. Great! Wait! What? - 45 min to 1hr trip, same back? We didn't have that kind of time remaining! Had we known we would have gotten up and out much earlier than we did! Argh! We had him verify that there was not a closer trailhead. Nope, this was it. So disappointed! Who doesn't love Treasure Island, Kidnapped, The Strange Case of Dr, Jekyll and Mr. Hyde, and more? Such a writer! Oh well. Luckily, we had completed the Ad Lab so we will be able to show a cache on the island/country, but no virtual cache for us today. It is what it is though. Maybe one day we'll be back. Fingers crossed. Argh! Aloha!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1352770344"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-25T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5231988">Tooltime_2011</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Meine liebe Cuxine und ich sind für einige Zeit auf einer Reise um die Welt und inzwischen sind wir auf Samoa angekommen. Heute haben wir einen Ausflug mit dem Mietwagen um den westlichen Teil von Upolu gemacht. Unser erster Stopp war hier an Stevensons Grab - ein ziemlich anstrengender Aufstieg für uns. Was für eine wunderschöne Insel und das wird hier mit diesem Ausblick nochmals bestätigt. Wir haben die benötigten Fotos gemacht und sind dann wieder herunter gewandert. Vielen Dank für diesen Cache und schöne Grüße aus Wünsdorf bei Berlin.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="43.930117" lon="12.452583"><time>2005-05-06T00:00:00</time><name>GCNTKF</name><desc>[BAU] San Marino #1 by the_bau_team</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCNTKF</url><urlname>[BAU] San Marino #1</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="239120" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>[BAU] San Marino #1</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>the_bau_team</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="25650607">the_bau_team</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>San Marino</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>La 1^ Cache nella Repubblica di San Marino - The 1st Cache in San Marino Republic
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Adottata da Barafonda Team - Adopted from Barafonda Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt src="https://thebauteamhome.files.wordpress.com/2020/01/bandiera-italiana.png?w=64" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;Questa è la prima cache piazzata nella Repubblica di San Marino!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Da questo punto potete ammirare il panorama su tutta la riviera romagnola e nelle giornate più terse potete arrivare a vedere la costa della Croazia e le saline di Cervia.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt src="https://thebauteamhome.files.wordpress.com/2020/01/bandiera-inglese-1.png?w=64" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;This is the first cache placed in the Republic of San Marino!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;From this point you can admire the panorama of the entire Riviera Romagnola. On clear days you can get to see the coast of Croatia and the salt pans of Cervia.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt src="https://thebauteamhome.files.wordpress.com/2020/06/tedesca.png?w=64" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Das ist der erste Cache in der Republik San Marino&lt;/strong&gt;!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Von hier aus können Sie die Aussicht auf die ganze Riviera Romagnola sehen. An kühleren Tagen können Sie die Küste Kroatiens und die Salinen von Cervia sehen.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Chiedete della 3^ torre, la Montale...
Arrivati alla Montale, cercate una grande roccia a punta appena dietro alla staccionata...

Find the 3th tower, la Montale...
Find a big stone behind the fence...</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1365011239"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-02T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="10422130">Zosia C.</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Piękne miejsce ☺️</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364997043"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-02T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5531340">Die Breakers</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">In San Marino war heute sehr viel los, aber wir haben einen sehr guten Parkplatz im P9 erhalten. 

Die Polizei regelt den kompletten Verkehr.

Wir gingen nicht immer den Massen hinterher, eher den Cachespuren. Kreuz und quer ging es durch San Marino um Fragen zu beantworten, Bilder zu machen und Caches zu suchen.

Bei unserem Event haben wir viele Cacher getroffen und uns gut unterhalten. 
Danke für die Essensempfehlung Bar Guaita, es war echt gut.

Am Nachmittag ging es zum ältesten Cache von San Marino.
Bei einem schönen Spaziergang konnten wir tolle Ausblicke über die Region genießen. 

Ziemlich happy, hielten wir die Dose in den Händen und konnten uns im Logbuch eintragen. 

Wir hängen eine blaue Schleife dran.

Danke an the_bau_team für den Cache [BAU] San Marino #1
Die Breakers

IN: FP
Out: -

Schwierigkeit: 1.5
Gelände: 2.5
Größe: Small
Typ: Traditional-Cache</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364982684"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-02T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="609550">rocketman_diver</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found it. TFTC.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364957887"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-02T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="12623132">Vorzimmerdrache</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Gemeinsam mit Brösel1 heute dieses Doserl besucht. Danke fürs Auslegen sagt Vorzimmerdrache</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364965878"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-02T11:33:27</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="277031">Aeon</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found this old cache during my visit in San Marino! Thanks to the owner to keep this old cache alive!

Aeon</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="-0.003417" lon="6.521533"><time>2009-06-09T00:00:00</time><name>GC1NEP4</name><desc>Equator's Line by geobike16</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC1NEP4</url><urlname>Equator's Line</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="1152152" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Equator's Line</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>geobike16</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="1846209">geobike16</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="42" inc="1">Needs maintenance</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Sao Tome and Principe</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;div class="Section1"&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal"
style='margin-bottom:7.5pt;text-align:justify;line-height: normal'&gt;
&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Arial","sans-serif"; mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";color:black;mso-fareast-language: PT'&gt;
Esta cache está situada perto do marco da linha do Equador em
homenagem a Gago Coutinho, situada no ilhéu das Rolas, São Tomé e
Príncipe.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal"
style='margin-bottom:7.5pt;text-align:justify;line-height: normal'&gt;
&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Arial","sans-serif"; mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";color:black;mso-fareast-language: PT'&gt;
Equador&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;
&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Arial","sans-serif"; mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";color:black;mso-fareast-language: PT'&gt;
é a linha imaginária que resulta da intersecção da superfície da
Terra com o plano que contém o seu centro e é perpendicular ao eixo
de rotação. Devido à oscilação do eixo de rotação, a posição do
equador não é rigorosamente constante, razão pela qual é adoptada,
para efeitos geodésicos, uma posição média. O equador divide a
superfície da Terra em dois hemisférios: o &lt;b&gt;Hemisfério Norte&lt;/b&gt;,
ou Setentrional, que contém o Pólo Norte; e o &lt;b&gt;Hemisfério
Sul&lt;/b&gt;, ou Meridional, que contém o
&lt;a href="http://topazio1950.blogs.sapo.pt/32255.html"&gt;&lt;span style='color:black; text-decoration:none;text-underline:none'&gt;
Pólo Sul&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. O raio do equador é cerca de 6 378 km, a que
corresponde um perímetro de 40 075 km.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;center&gt;
&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/36cf929d-d623-460f-a86c-10a760474dd8.jpg" /&gt;
&lt;/center&gt;
&lt;p style='margin:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify'&gt;
&lt;span style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif"'&gt;A Linha do Equador
atravessa o Ilhéu das Rolas, dando a possibilidade ao
visitante&amp;nbsp;estar nos dois hemisférios na mesma altura no mesmo
instante.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;center&gt;
&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/cc4cc5f0-e7ae-443b-b57a-68957860dae8.jpg" /&gt;
&lt;/center&gt;
&lt;p style='text-align:justify'&gt;
&lt;span style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif"'&gt;O
&lt;b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'&gt;Ilhéu das Rolas&lt;/b&gt; é uma
pequena ilha no arquipélago de São Tomé e Príncipe situado no Golfo
da Guiné, a sul da ilha de São Tomé, à qual a ligação é feita
unicamente por barco. Tem a particularidade de se situar na linha
do Equador. A principal (e quase única) actividade económica é o
turismo, depois da construção de uma estância de luxo. Uma
população permanente de cerca de 200 habitantes tem a sua
sobrevivência directamente ligada à actividade
turística.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;center&gt;
&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/d1e02ed1-f531-4a7c-876e-86b73e6cd9fe.jpg" /&gt;
&lt;/center&gt;
&lt;p style='text-align:justify'&gt;
&lt;span style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif"'&gt;O Oficial de Armada,
navegador e historiador &lt;b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'&gt;Gago
Coutinho&lt;/b&gt; chefiou a missão geodésica em São Tomé entre 1915 e
1918, período em que implantou marcos para o estabelecimento de uma
rede geodésica na ilha, após o que fez observações de triangulação,
medição de precisão de duas bases e numerosas observações
astronómicas. Durante suas medições, comprovou a passagem da Linha
do Equador pelo Ilhéu das Rolas. A Carta resultante dessas
observações foi entregue em 1919, em conjunto com o Relatório da
Missão Geodésica da Ilha de São Tomé 1915-1918, que foi considerado
oficialmente o primeiro trabalho de geodesia completo referente a
uma das colónias portuguesas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;center&gt;
&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/b6afd031-9da5-4170-8848-8e9663b32e22.jpg" /&gt;
&lt;/center&gt;
&lt;p style='margin:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify'&gt;
&lt;span style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif"'&gt;As coordenadas da
cache não estão exactas, porque no momento em que foi colocada o
GPS decidiu não colaborar. Agradece-se a quem der uma localização
mais exacta. Penso que com as indicações e as fotos
&lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;spoilers&lt;/span&gt; não será difícil
encontrá-la.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal"&gt;
&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family: "Arial","sans-serif";mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";color:black; mso-fareast-language:PT'&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>No muro, na parte de trás das escadas...</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1363940085"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-27T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="35836465">MarDi21</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">With Schmarcy at the Equators line. Cool place, TFTC!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363930999"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-27T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="35730801">Schmarcy</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We had a great boat trip today. Stop at Praia S. Miguel and Pipi - and than at Equator's line. Thanks for the quick find.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1345362032"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-17T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1591002">Armor-Reisen</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This was easy, I just missed my pen.
Tftc Armor-Reisen</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1344312071"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-08T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1045736">Mondlinger</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Three days ago, I couldn't find this cache, because the coordinates point somewhere into the dense forest. After automatically translating the cache description back in the hotel, everything was clear. And because we went snorkelling to Rolas today, I took the chance to sign. The paper in the cache is quite wet. I measured the cache coordinates and will send them to the owner. 
They are S 00° 00.043' E 006° 31.321'</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1343114872"><groundspeak:date>2026-01-26T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4879812">Taipina</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Easy one ! De saude a cache</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="22.902633333333334" lon="41.147733333333335"><time>2001-03-04T00:00:00</time><name>GC4B0</name><desc>CRATERCACHE by the Cange family</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC4B0</url><urlname>CRATERCACHE</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="1200" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>CRATERCACHE</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>the Cange family</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="2622">jeffcange</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Not chosen</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="42" inc="1">Needs maintenance</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>4</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>4</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Saudi Arabia</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>WARNING when approaching the crater DO NOT drive over any rises without knowing what is on the other side, it is possible to drive over the side !!!!!!!
&lt;p&gt;
Difficulty rating:  4, you've got to look.&lt;br&gt;
Terrain rating: 4, you must climb, it is a fairly difficult climb no gear required (other than good boots and gloves).</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>The second cache in Saudi Arabia was placed on 4 Mar 2001. The Cange family; Jeff, Pam, Rachel (9), Robert (8), and Mike Sciocchetti planted a cache in the Wahba Crater.  This two km diameter, 700 ft deep crater is located 180 km north east of Taif and 75 km north of the of the Jeddah-Riyadh road.  
&lt;p&gt;
CRATERCACHE is located at the bottom of Wahba Crater enter the crater just above the Oasis, the trail is fairly easy to follow. Wear gloves and good climbing boots and take your time, (I took a tumble on the way down, luckily the only damage was a thorn in the heel of my hand, and constant ribbing from my companions) it took us about two hours to make it to the bottom. 
&lt;p&gt;
Follow your GPS to the coordinates and look for a tall stack of rocks, climb to the first large horizontal crevice (salt pan side) and look in the crevice beneath a few smaller stones.  The cache is in a green wooden decorated box.  
&lt;p&gt;
Inventory:
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt; logbook
&lt;li&gt; pen
&lt;li&gt; Lighter from South Africa
&lt;li&gt; 1 Saudi Riyal, signed by the "crew"
&lt;li&gt; 1 US dollar signed by the "crew"
&lt;li&gt; 102 Dalmatian pup from McDonalds
&lt;/ul&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1288551055"><groundspeak:date>2025-03-30T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6730399">woy23</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">A month ago (specifically on February 20, 2025), I attempted to find this cache, but unfortunately, I was unsuccessful - mainly because I couldn't find a suitable way down in time. Instead, I walked around the entire crater and enjoyed the views from all sides.
Since the listing does not include waypoints, I would like to share some up-to-date information I discovered for other cachers:

1) The information about a ban on entering the bottom of the crater and guards enforcing it is no longer valid. Upon my arrival at the crater, I saw two people walking around the white-colored center of the crater. I later met them; they were local tourists who said they had no issues with any poisonous gases.

2) There is a footpath leading down to the bottom of the crater. The approximate coordinates where the descent begins are: N 22° 54.314 E 041° 07.870. If you have a 4x4 vehicle, you can drive along a dirt road almost to the trail. Access is free of charge, but you should plan for at least four hours for the descent and ascent.

3) The visitor center at the parking lot is not operational. You can't buy anything here, so I recommend bringing your own water supplies.

4) If you have time and are here with an off-road vehicle, I also recommend the nearby cache: [GC9BRYQ](https://coord.info/GC9BRYQ). I drove to N 22° 54.131 E 041° 09.467, and from there, it was less than a kilometer of hopping over the lava field. :-)

Enjoy your trip - it's worth it!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1173325943"><groundspeak:date>2023-02-19T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="18030217">JellyCZ</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">oh boy... that was epic! one of the best experiences in geocaching and our lives in general! descending into a volcano crater in Saudi Arabia, that's as crazy as it gets. :))
it was a long drive even from the main road (40) and when we arrived, the parking was empty, visitors centre closed but surprisingly, a guard was sitting there alone in the shadows. he told us in simple English to walk a short distance round the crater but that it is no longer permitted to go down as there is gas leaking out and the police are patrolling the area. damn... so we walked to the edge and had the first look on the crater. I almost fainted. :) I underestimated its dimensions, steep 200 meters rocky sides, it looked impossible to go down without an equipment. we had to discuss it with my muggle friend but I didn't want to give up that easily so I insisted on walking to the other side where this so-called Oasis is and see what happens. he was not happy of course but it made no sense for him to wait (a few hours) in the car for my return. so he joined me. it took one hour to reach the opposite side. we then wandered around and in a few minutes we spotted the green path down. without further negotiation, my friend said "let's go!" :) so we did. the terrain was wild but it could be done pretty easily if you are very careful. we were down in about 30 minutes. no sign of gas so far. we started to search for the cache and found it soon. what a moment! we both were happy. the box is in good condition and thanks to NltRO I could sign the logbook. after that my friend wanted to continue to the crater centre but I stopped him, what if there really is some gas leaking out. and it was getting dark anyways. the ascent took another 30 minutes and once back at the top, we felt euphoric of what just happened. then I spotted a police car blinking, luckily on the other side of the crater. we didn't wait for anything and slowly returned to our car in complete darkness. there were no police waiting for us there so in the end, all went well. what an adventure! along with visiting Medina and Mecca this was the highlight of our KSA visit, we will never forget it. thousand thanks for placing the cache here and greetings from the Czech Republic!
+ 1000 FP</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1093002002"><groundspeak:date>2022-04-28T18:26:44</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6206534">Team Mortel</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Deze gevonden op een mooie plek na wat zoeken. 
TFTC. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="904922414"><groundspeak:date>2020-01-24T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="12951342">shibuneelambra</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thank you for the cache.It was our first cache. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="904852799"><groundspeak:date>2020-01-24T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="22084747">NltRO</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Came here with my bunch of Indian friends from Kerala</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="-4.650133" lon="55.45825"><time>2001-11-04T00:00:00</time><name>GC278A</name><desc>SeyCache by Anja &amp; Michael</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC278A</url><urlname>SeyCache</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="10122" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>SeyCache</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Anja &amp; Michael</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="19883">Anja&amp;Mike</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="42" inc="1">Needs maintenance</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="0">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="26" inc="1">Public transportation nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Seychelles</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>The cache is located near the end of the hiking trail to mount
Copolia some kilometers south of Victoria.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>S 04°39.008'&lt;br /&gt;
E 55°27.495' [WGS84]&lt;br /&gt;
walking distance from the road: 1.2 km&lt;br /&gt;
Satellite reception is not optimal at the place of the cache due to
rocks and heavy tree coverage.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The entry point of the trail is 6 km from Victoria on the left side
of the Sans Souci Road (it is marked by a conspicious sign) [S
04°38.831 / E 55°27.169] The total length of the trail to the top
is about 1.5 km. 150 m before the top a wooden sign indicates the
distance and direction to the top. The cache is hidden under a
couple of stones.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
We put a small Swiss army knive and a sewing kit from the Berjaya
Hotel into the cache.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Since we are from Germany we cannot take care of the cache. Still-
it was too challenging to hide the first cache on the Seychelles.
We thank you for leaving it in good condition!</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>The cache is situated about 1.5 meters on the right of the wooden sign under a couple of stones with a concrete plate.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1289008678"><groundspeak:date>2025-04-03T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="23840425">Peeruleek</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found it.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1134754811"><groundspeak:date>2022-10-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4808129">Murphy-09</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Well, even it was an archived one, which I didn't know at the moment I logged it, it is alive again. Thanks to Carangue for continuing this angient cache legend.
Greetings from Germany
TFTC
Murphy-09</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1101684691"><groundspeak:date>2022-06-05T13:55:59</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="19883">Anja&amp;Mike</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">no longer available</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1102278694"><groundspeak:date>2022-06-05T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Didn't find it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2295959">Carangue</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Here I will log a DNF because of some unforeseen circumstances…
Today 05.06.2022 we hiked up the Copolia Nature Trail and I was looking forward to find this old cache from 2001: SeyCache GC278A
I had downloaded the cache details well in advance before our trip and it is only back in our self-catering apartment that I noticed the cache had been suddenly archived on the very same day 😟
I had brought a replacement container for some kind maintenance cooperation among geocachers and placed it exactly as per the cache hint. I wrote to the owners to let them know but it was seemingly too late.
Unfortunately the oldest cache of the Seychelles 🇸🇨 has now gone to heaven 😢 🪦
Well even if I understand the reasons, I feel it is pretty sad to abandon such an old cache, which could have lived many more years with the help of the geocaching community and perhaps a relocation with a new hiding spot.
Anyway thanks for the beautiful scenery and enjoyable trail. 
I took several pictures of animals and plants we met along the way.
RIP 1st Seycache</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1100814691"><groundspeak:date>2022-06-01T10:04:27</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Didn't find it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="9565921">michmuche la capuche</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Tout retourné mais rien trouvé. Mplc. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="7.9657" lon="-11.740167"><time>2003-04-10T00:00:00</time><name>GCF7D9</name><desc>Number One in Sierra Leone by Nebola (adopted from cwsprenkle)</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCF7D9</url><urlname>Number One in Sierra Leone</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Virtual Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="63449" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Number One in Sierra Leone</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Nebola (adopted from cwsprenkle)</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="2242071">Nebola</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Virtual Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Virtual</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Sierra Leone</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Located in the city of Bo, Sierra Leone, on the premises of a public establishment, it is easily viewed from the street. Difficulty rating is due to the journey from Lungi Airport to Bo. Be advised to sit on a cushion for the long, dusty, rough, rough, ride.
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;This virtual cache is the bust of a man on a pedestal.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;To validate your find :&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You need to post in your log a picture of the Memorial &lt;u&gt;WITH YOUR USERNAME VISIBLE, CLEAR AND READABLE&lt;/u&gt; written on the medium of your choice (paper, hand, phone, t-shirt, etc...).&lt;br /&gt;
Pictures taken with only yourself, your GPS or your Logo/Avatar are not accepted as well as photoshopped/edited pictures with your username inserted afterward.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You also need to send me the answers to these questions :&lt;br /&gt;
1. What is the man&amp;#39;s name ?&lt;br /&gt;
2. His claim to fame ?&lt;br /&gt;
3. Date of death ?&lt;br /&gt;
4. Who placed this marker ?&lt;br /&gt;
5. What the H*** were you doing in Bo, Sierra Leone anyway ?&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
DO NOT POST THE ANSWERS IN YOUR LOG AND MAKE SURE THE ANSWERS CAN&amp;#39;T BE SEEN IN YOUR PHOTO !!!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;Failure to follow these instructions will lead to your log deleted.&lt;/u&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;em&gt;Thanks to cwsprenkle for letting me adopt this virtual cache.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>No hints, but while you are there, sit down and have a cold drink. You probably need one !</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1344966721"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-11T14:45:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1351184">SeekerSupreme</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I had a hard time with this one, but after contacting the CO I was allowed to log as a find. I got to GZ, the exact GZ marking zero on my GPS, and there was no man to be found. The buildings to the right and the left of GZ were both under construction. I showed the picture to people on the street to see if they knew where it was and some people didn’t  know, but finally I found one who did know and pointed me to the building on the left. However, that building was fenced all around and padlocked. People claimed to know who the guard was and we looked around for him and we even went to his home to try to find him  but no luck.  So I was on site but unable to see the matter answer the questions at this point it’s not even known if the bar still exist. It’s inside the construction site. Future visitors please try to ascertain that if you could get through the fence.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1276806378"><groundspeak:date>2025-01-03T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6697438">ToKaPet</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Teil II

Endlich in Bo. Entgegen der City of Freetown gibt es hier keine Straßenschilder, der Handyempfang ist eh schlecht. Aber gefunden haben wir den Virtual trotzdem. Ja okay wir hatten plötzlich Hilfe von dem Bruder des Taxifahrers ... Ihr merkt sicherlich, typisch Afrika. Nachdem ich und die gesuchte Person / Statue -besser Blechschild ein schönes Bild gemacht hatten ging es an das Studium der erforderlichen Tafel. Jupp, das ist wirklich einen Cache und Ehrung wert. Jetzt aber ab in die die nächste Kneipe! Knapp 5 Stunden unterwegs und das für "nur" einen Cache ... crazy white man ! 6 echte und 2 Malzbier (für den Preis von 2 im Hotel) später ging es dann auf die Rückreise. Jetzt waren die checkpoints nicht alle besetzt, war der Verkehr aus Richtung Freetown doch deutlich mehr. Nebenbei habe ich außerhalb der größeren Ortschaften mehr Fußgänger als Autos, LKW oder Busse gesehen. Viele große, schwarze und ohne Kennzeichen fahrende Fahrzeuge kamen uns entgegen (Government) , ab und zu mal große schwarze Fahrzeuge mit Kennzeichen (Militär) und große schwarze mit grüner Kennzeichenaufschrift (NGO) - auf jeden Fall alle groß und meist mit Warnblinklicht. Nebenbei gibt es 12 Stämme in Sierra Leone, wobei die Mandys, Kindo und Limbas die größten sind... Ein Besuch des Wasserfalls oder Schimpansenparks war aufgrund der einbrechenden Dunkelheit oder Öffnungszeiten nicht mehr möglich, aber wer will denn sowas auch sehen, wenn er/sie die "Number One in Sierra Leone" -einen der ältesten Caches in Afrika, zudem einen "echten" Virtual gefunden hat ? ! ? !!

In diesem Sinne macht Euch auf den abenteuerlichen Weg !
Ob es sich lohnt, entscheidet bitte selbst [:D]

P.S.
Aus den 250 $ sind letztendlich dann 260€ geworden ... Tja so ist das mit Mittelsmännern.
"Meinen" Michael habe ich aber echt schätzen gelernt. Ein afrikanischer Taxifahrer, der sich anschnallt obwohl er nicht hupt und rast, vorausschauend fährt, keinen Alkohol trinkt und auch so "ein feiner Kerl" ist - ja den mag ich wohl gern weiter empfehlen! Blickig wie er ist -und nicht auf Abzocke aus- ist die Personenanzahl nicht entscheidend. Nebenbei war dann später die Fahrt vom Hotel zum Hafen um die Hälfte billiger als mit dem anderen Touri-Abzocker vom Hafen zum Hotel. 

Jetzt traue ich mich aber nicht hier seine Nummer zu posten, denn Werbung ist ja nach guidelines von GC.com nicht erlaubt. Feel free to contact me !

Fazit:
Zeit &gt; Obwohl die Straße(n) viel besser waren als erwartet, dauert die Anfahrt von Freetown länger als z.B. Google sagt! Straßenkontrollen und Check-Points brauchen auch ihre Zeit und vor Allem: G... - G wie z.B. Geduld [;)] Einen ganzen Tag einzuplanen ist unumgänglich. 
Kosten &gt; Durch eine Preiserhöhung sind die im Internet zu findenden 40-60 $ (einfache Fahrt) nicht mehr aktuell. 250 $ sind für "Weiße" oder Touristen schon gut. Nehmt US-Dollar mit, Euros sind nicht gern gesehen...
Cache &gt; ziemlich einfach, den Reiz macht das Publish Datum und die Historie

Vielen Dank, Merci Nebola ! [:)]

FP in</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1276806607"><groundspeak:date>2025-01-03T00:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6697438">ToKaPet</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">First i apologize that the following log is maybe a bit longer... 
and this requires a log in the mother language [:D]

Also dann los geht`s...
Bereits im Vorfeld war klar, alle Caches in Sierra Leone sind nicht zu schaffen. Das waren zum 
Zeitpunkt meines Besuches zwar nur 6, aber eben auch einer (dieser), welcher für jeden Geocacher 
an erster Stelle steht bzw. stehen sollte. 260 Kilometer, 3,5 Stunden von Freetown weg ... ja da muss
man(n) schon nen ganzen Tag einplanen. Gebraucht habe ich nebenbei ganze 11 Stunden - hin und zurück. Der erste mögliche Fahrer (vom Hafen zum Hotel) verlangte satte 400 Dollar für die Tour ... ein weiterer (vorm Hotel 350 $) - ja eigentlich war da die Nummer schon erledigt, denn die eben genannten Preise waren schon die runter gehandelten! Eigentlich nur zufällig ergab sich eine dritte Möglichkeit.
Nein nicht der "State-Bus" (Abfahrt morgens um 06:00 und den wir mittags überholten) sondern über einen Hotelangestellten, der einen kennt, der ein Auto hat ... usw....
Es dauerte fast eine Stunde (entgegen dem "soon" or in ten minutes), dass Michael persönlich erschien und wir in die Preisverhandlungen einsteigen konnten. Twofifty ... inclusive the toll, fees and gas (wichtig falls jemand diese Tour auch mal versuchen sollte). Shit, mein Maximum waren doch 150... Ach was ! Wenn verrückt, dann richtig! Handschlag und Abfahrtszeit ausgemacht... 
Zur Abfahrtszeit stand dann überpünktlich ein Nissan Micra vor dem Hotel und los ging es in das afrikanische Hinterland. Die 3 Mautstellen (jeweils 5 Leons) und tanken von "Desiel" ca. 1,10€/L) waren ja überschaubar, aber die 7 Checkpoints machten "meinem Michael" dann doch zu schaffen. "Give them what they want" sagte er und nun weiß ich auch warum ein Handschlag bei uns dem Afrikanischem nicht ähnlich ist (die Ghettofaust im Anschluss bedeutet nämlich "Danke"). Wer jetzt meint das ihn eine Sandpiste erwartet, dem sei gesagt, er liegt vollkommen falsch! Zwar war es "nur" ein einspuriger Highway mit schmalem Seitenstreifen, aber dafür durchgängig asphaltiert und in gutem Zustand. Ja die Chinesen haben die Straße gebaut und betreiben auch die Sea Bird Fährverbindung (die Türken betreiben den Airport und versorgen ganz Freetown mit einem Schweröl-Generatorenschiff (125 MW)) und wir Deutschen? - wir bauen Radwege in Peru... aber ich schweife ab... Nach etwas mehr als 3 Stunden erreichten wir (immer mit afrikanischem Reggae aus dem Radio) den District of Bo und natürlich eine Polizeikontrolle. Hier war aber plötzlich auch ein Immigration Officer dabei. Zivil und an seiner Garage oder Lehmhütte stand : Immigration Post. Schien aber "echt" zu sein, denn Michael verhielt sich so wie jedes Mal. Verrückt, manche tragen Uniform oder eine Weste - da rauscht man trotz Anhaltesignal vorbei und dann steht da mal ein Ziviler und es wird angehalten. Tja meinen Pass hatte ich natürlich nicht dabei konnte aber meinen Führerschein (sind ja auch alle Daten drauf, plus Photo) aushändigen. War natürlich auch nicht richtig (I am an immigration officer not a travel police man). Aber auch ein Photo auf dem Handy von Paß und Visum/Stempel dürfte nicht genügt haben, denn wie sagte Mike so schön? - Give them what they want). Als sich der Officer mal kurz abwandte gab ich meinem Fahrer ein paar viele Scheine von Leons und nachdem sich die beiden dann mit einer Ghettofaust verabschiedeten waren gleich zwei der größten Scheine der Landeswährung "away" (40SLL), aber die Reise konnte weiter gehen. Wie auch schon die vielen Stunden und Kilometer zuvor - alle paar Kilometer eine kleine Siedlung mit vielleicht 10-20 Häusern/Hütten und einer Kirche oder Moschee. Davor die Bewohner, absolut entspannt und scheinbar in den Tag lebend. Nebenbei soll es eine Auszeichnung sein oder gute Lage hier so direkt an der Straße zu wohnen. Ab und zu standen sogar mal ein paar Händler an der Straße/Highway, welche durch hochheben ihrer Ware den Durchgangsverkehr zum anhalten bewegen wollten. In der Provinz am häufigsten Brennholz und Holzkohle in den größeren Orten hatte ich den Eindruck direkt durch einen Wochenmarkt gefahren zu werden. Da gibt es offenbar alles, alte Matratzen, Möbel von der Kippe, ausgeblichene Spiegel usw. - Aufgepasst! alles eine Frage der Perspektive! Außer einem großen Träger Mineralwasser und einer Tüte Ingwer kaufte ich insgesamt nichts, erst recht nicht die toten Ratten.
Erwähnte ich schon, dass Afrika brennt? Von den 260km waren vielleicht 50km Stadt, Dorf, Checkpoint auch da loderten die Feuer, die anderen Kilometer waren aber ebenfalls zu 2/3 von schwarzer Brandasche oder mit nach verbranntem Plastik riechendem Qualm und Flammen bestückt. Gewollt oder nicht, hier kamen mir die Worte wieder in den Sinn: "Who cares?" - Wen kümmerts? Tja diese Grundeinstellung erklärt natürlich auch die mit Plastikmüll verseuchten Strände und die vielen vielen schwimmenden Dinge in der Flussmündung vom Airport in die Stadt. 

Ende Teil I</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1214252889"><groundspeak:date>2024-01-30T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Unknown</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2242071">Nebola</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">From now on, please follow new requirements to validate this virtual.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1214156082"><groundspeak:date>2024-01-29T20:44:55</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="41563308">AGP313</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thank you for this cache! Our first and only one in Sierra Leone!!! </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="1.264533" lon="103.804383"><time>2001-12-30T00:00:00</time><name>GC2EE7</name><desc>Hidden beauty spot by gafs adopted by colincorgi</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC2EE7</url><urlname>Hidden beauty spot</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="12007" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Hidden beauty spot</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>gafs adopted by colincorgi</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="8404199">colincorgi</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Other</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Singapore</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Quite easy terrain, and beautiful, you can spend some time there.... after you find the cache.
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>New CO note: Welcome to Singapore's oldest active geocache! For an Asian country, we're proud to have a hide that's survived from 2001, and it's a privilege to have become its official caretakers in 2020. The old listing is attached below for posterity, and the location really hasn't changed much since the cache was placed 2 decades ago. If you're a visitor who hunts for old geocaches, tell us a bit about some of your other memorable finds in your log, and enjoy your walk in the rest of this beautiful park.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
When you reach the point you see two brick walls. If you pass by them you see a tree on the right side, when you are coming from below. Behind the big tree is and old bottle and beside it is the cache.
&lt;p&gt;It is filled with some memorabilia, nothing of worth really, it is more the honor and the nice surroundings. I was working in Singapore for IKEA in 2001, and spend a lot of time doing caches. First I did Singapore's first, but unfortunately it disappeared, so now this is the oldest. It is a fun sport and I am happy so many people still find this cache. I check on it sometimes, but not really any need, it is well kept by fellow cache'ists. Thanks. Anders&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;BR from gafs&lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Big tree nearer the brick wall</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364983874"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-02T23:02:16</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="47965833">invent1ng</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thanks for my first find! And a special one 😃</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1359077185"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-04T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5609949">Puimannetjes</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">For sure we had to visit this classic cache. The actual eldest one from Singapore. It was a nice walk through the park with a lot of history. Thanks for showing this location, and maintaining this old one.

We add a favo point, as this is a memorial cache!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1359320586"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-03T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4389352">Take &amp; Ilona</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We were in Singapore for a couple of nights and explored the sights while also looking for a few geocaches. Thank you very much for the cache 🥰</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1358144828"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-01T12:00:01</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="54906234">Bigyellowdot</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">🙏🏻</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363638411"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-25T10:51:09</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3019624">no1gardengirl</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Took a bit of looking to find. Here as the lone American caching with a group of Aussie friends. Thanks for keeping this oldie going. Signed as the ROOS </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="45.502269" lon="13.590617"><time>2001-06-29T00:00:00</time><name>GC103E</name><desc>Prvi Geocache v Sloveniji by Team Humuhumunukunukuapuaa</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC103E</url><urlname>Prvi Geocache v Sloveniji</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="4158" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Prvi Geocache v Sloveniji</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Team Humuhumunukunukuapuaa</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="8977">Team Humuhumunukunukuapuaa</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="1">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="1">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Slovenia</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Enjoy a scenic sculptural walk on the way to the cache. There is nearby parking and the walk is over a gravel road and usually cut grass.
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>Make sure to continue out to the end of the point to see the other sculptures and enjoy the great view from the end of the point. Since it is a relatively open location, please be discrete when finding this cache.
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>If this cache is too hard sit down under an olive tree and look underneath.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364863208"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T19:50:58</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1139926">Beetstar</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Hallo Team Humuhumunukunukuapuaa. Auf meiner heutigen Cachetour (01.06.2026) habe ich Deinen Prvi Geocache v Sloveniji bei bestem Cacherwetter - (gibt es anderes?) relativ fix gefunden. Nur durch dieses, unseres Hobbys, bin ich immer wieder an der frischen Luft, und bewege mich etwas mehr als sonst. Zum Cache: Zuerst mal nachgesehen, ob Muggel im Zielgebiet sind, dann im richtigen Moment der Zugriff. Jetzt ist Dein Logbuch um meinen Eintrag reicher. Der Dose geht es gut; damit ist alles in Ordnung. Erneut eine location, wo ich ohne Geocaching nie hin gekommen wäre. Hier erinnert nun seit dem  ein gelber Smiley an das Cacheerlebnis. Vielen lieben Dank  für Deinen Cache  GC103E, fürs ausarbeiten, legen und pflegen.

Un grand merci à Team Humuhumunukunukuapuaa pour la création, la pose et la maintenance, grâce à vous (entre autres) le geocaching est mon occupation favorite

Noch ein Hinweis: Um Platz in den Logbüchern zu sparen, nutze ich freie Plätze zwischendurch. Ich fülle gerne die Lücken, schon alleine aus Rücksicht dem Owner gegenüber, um sinnlose Wartungsarbeiten zu vermeiden.

Herzliche Grüße aus Bernkastel-Kues im schönen Moseltal.

Thank you for your nice cache. Merci pour ta cache. Bedankt voor je cache.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364863717"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="32013014">GCSalsa</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Auf unserer heutigen Cachetour kamen wir auch an diese alte Cache vorbei. Schnell fanden wir einen Parkplatz und das Objekt der Begierde war schnell gefunden und wir konnten uns ins saubere Logbuch eintragen. Nun ziert ein neues Smiley meine Karte. Ich bedanke mich bei dem Owner für seinen Cache und grüße herzlich aus dem höchsten Dorf der Pfalz in Deutschland 🇩🇪</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364533659"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-31T11:26:42</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="25822479">AnjaOlive</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found these caches a few days ago and forgot to log, finally got to it now!
TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364520902"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-31T10:21:59</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="19240089">findnx</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Wir sind auf dem Weg nach Kroatien und mussten diesen Oldie einsammeln.
Während mein Anhang eine Cappuccino schlürfte, spazierte ich den Berg rauf zum Cache.
Die Dose konnte ich schnell finden.

Danke fürs zeigen!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364303590"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T11:48:50</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="55006018">2zaaster</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Nice</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="-34.059583" lon="18.381383"><time>2001-01-18T00:00:00</time><name>GC185</name><desc>Sentinel View by Prof Charles Merry</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC185</url><urlname>Sentinel View</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="389" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Sentinel View</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Prof Charles Merry</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="9271">cmerry</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Large</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="0">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="0">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="2" inc="1">Access/parking fee</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="27" inc="0">Drinking water nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="38" inc="0">Campfires</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="10" inc="0">Difficult climb</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="21" inc="1">Cliff/falling rocks</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>South Africa</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Western Cape</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>In the Silvermine section of the Cape Peninsula National Park, with
a spectacular view over Hout Bay of the Sentinel. A pleasant
morning or afternoon's hike, but check the mountain cloud cover if
you wish to appreciate the view.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>The cache is located in the Silvermine section of the Cape
Peninsula National Park. From the Silvermine parking lot it is
about 40 minutes along tracks and footpaths to within 50m of the
cache. The cache is located on a shoulder overlooking Hout bay and
the Sentinel. On a fine day it is a magnificent site. On the day
the cache was stashed, the area was covered in cloud, with
visibility about ten metres. The cache is under a triangular
boulder about 1m by 1m in size, with a few smaller rocks packed
against it to keep out foraging baboons and porcupines. [Update
16/7/2001] redid the terrain/difficulty ratings using the
Geocaching Cache Rating System
(http://www.cordianet.com/snd/GCRS.zip) made by Scott Thomason.</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1363925966"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-20T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4041141">derStern</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Was für ein Erlebnis! Schön, dass es geklappt hat und wir zum ältesten Geocache Südafrikas gekommen sind. Falls es nachfolgende Geocacher interessiert: Wir haben von Camps Bay morgens den ersten Hop-On-Hop-Off Bus der roten Linie genommen und sind bis zur Waterfront gefahren. Dort haben wir uns dann ein Uber zum Silvermine Dam bestellt. Vom Parkplatz aus waren es dann gemütlich ca. 1h hin zum Geocache und somit grob 2h gesamt. Der Weg war angenehm zu gehen und der Cache war schnell gefunden. Die Aussicht vom Geocache aus war grandios. Der Sentinel und Hout Bay waren es. Hat wirklich Spaß gemacht. Glückwunsch zum 25. nachträglich! Übrigens, man hat in dem Gebiet kaum Handyempfang. Wir haben deswegen auch schon vorher den Uber-Fahrer für hinterher bestellt. Das hat prima geklappt. Der Park kostete Eintritt in bar.

Danke für das schöne Erlebnis!

**LEBE LIEBE LACHE LOGGE**

What an experience! I’m so glad it all worked out and we managed to find South Africa’s oldest geocache. In case any fellow geocachers are interested: We took the first red-line hop-on-hop-off bus from Camps Bay in the morning and travelled to the Waterfront. From there, we booked an Uber to Silvermine Dam. From the car park, it was a leisurely walk of about an hour to the geocache, making it roughly two hours in total. The path was pleasant to walk along and the cache was found quickly. The view from the geocache was magnificent – The Sentinel and Hout Bay were in full view. It was really good fun. Belated congratulations on your 25th! By the way, there’s hardly any mobile reception in the area. That’s why we’d already booked the Uber driver for the return journey in advance. That worked out perfectly. The park charged an entrance fee in cash.

Thanks for the lovely experience!

Translated with DeepL.com (free version)

Best regards &amp; 💚

Team derStern from Germany 

#16308</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1358013865"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-30T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="31926985">FFWLUKAS</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">sorry fürs nach Loggen

ich war Mitte März im Südafrika Urlaub (es war einfach ein Traumurlaub) und habe hier einige Geocaches gemacht und alle super gefunden. den einen oder anderen nicht sofort aber dennoch gefunden.
Danke für den Spaß :)</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1349949868"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-18T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5797611">agility22</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">It was a foggy morning when we started, but at the time we got near the cache site, the sky opened up and the sun came out and we had a beautiful sight over Hout Bay. Thank you for showing us Silbermine national park with this cache! Greetings from Austria.       </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1342489658"><groundspeak:date>2026-01-18T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="25908785">Thunder_Boy</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found it!
How cool is this… finding South Africa’s oldest active cache and being the one to spot it! Epic walk, epic view, and an epic piece of geocaching history. Reading the original logbook was next level. This one will stick with me for a long time. Legend cache!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1342488605"><groundspeak:date>2026-01-18T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="25908881">MissXG</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found it!

What a special moment finding SA’s oldest active cache with an amazing group, incredible views, and the legends themselves. Paging through the original logbook was pure magic, and sharing it with my son made it even better. History, heart, and a very happy smile all round. 

Thank you for this classic!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="-54.285667" lon="-36.508333"><time>2006-01-12T00:00:00</time><name>GCZ8ZK</name><desc>Shackleton's Rest by Scootman</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCZ8ZK</url><urlname>Shackleton's Rest</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="491247" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Shackleton's Rest</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Scootman</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="317749">scootman</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="42" inc="1">Needs maintenance</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="0">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="4" inc="1">Boat required</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>South Georgia and the South Sandwich Islands</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Located in a spot overlooking Grytviken and Shackleton's last resting place on South Georgia.
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;This cache has been placed in a somewhat unremarkable spot in an undeniably remarkable part of the world. This should be an easy cache to find once you get to Grytviken, and if there is little or no snow about. It could however be regarded as an extremely difficult cache if you happen to start your journey from the Weddell Sea and your ship's name is ‘Endurance’. Otherwise it has been placed a sufficient distance away from the local inhabitants, removing the only significant modern day obstacle to reaching it (excluding the Southern Ocean of course!).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;My first cache. Planned and researched for a very long time. Thanks to Kate and Mark for assistance in finding a suitable spot, Chris for the clip-on Koala, and to Jenny for getting us all there. Thanks also to Annetta for allowing me to take so many weeks to ‘chase the chickens’ in the Southern Ocean.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;FTF credit goes to &lt;a href="http://www.geocaching.com/profile/?guid=df829259-d326-481e-8171-5139ddeff0e9"&gt;Bouton&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Cache maintenance provided by &lt;a href="http://www.geocaching.com/profile/?guid=3a58fb4b-681e-4169-bb14-1ba6552b9b76"&gt;plexy&lt;/a&gt; + &lt;a href="http://www.geocaching.com/profile/?guid=cf47ad48-9740-4036-9f52-88abdc898ca8"&gt;fimbulisen&lt;/a&gt; (Thank you!)&lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1346810774"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-01T04:58:24</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Didn't find it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="54695324">Kr0913</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Across the world DNF</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1346137276"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-23T20:47:05</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8495494">Alba gu bràth</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We visited this historic and important site today.
Thank you for placing the cache but we were unable to scurry round due to some seals.

I hope the pictures suffice :)

Thank you so much for placing. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1346134916"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-23T20:21:58</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="988771">DOBRODRUH.cz</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We came to Grytviken today on a Hondius ship. Since there were people visiting a nearby grave that is not in the graveyard, but up in the hill we had the chance to visit actual cache. Cache is in a good condition. Only the red logbook is wet so it is not possible to write in with a regular pen. We toasted to Mr. Shackelton with the whiskey of the same name. Lovely weather today. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1346135193"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-23T16:51:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5683651">tuxici</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Nice place. Thank you for the cache. Greetings from Czech Republic </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1343828668"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-03T18:08:54</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1224738">leeroyboy</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Today it was guarded by several seals.  Paid my tribute. TFTC @</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="37.479517" lon="127.196483"><time>2003-05-03T00:00:00</time><name>GCG1V7</name><desc>NamHanSanSeong 🧱 by Crazyussoldier  Adopted by ROK Geocachers</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCG1V7</url><urlname>NamHanSanSeong 🧱</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="67310" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>NamHanSanSeong 🧱</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Crazyussoldier  Adopted by ROK Geocachers</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="5310757">wonkoo1</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="56" inc="1">Medium hike (1 km–10 km)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="40" inc="1">Stealth required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="26" inc="1">Public transportation nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>3</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>South Korea</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Gyeonggido</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>The cache is located at the Namhansanseong Fortress.  It's quite a workout getting to the top, but well worth the trip to see the spectacular views of Seoul.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size="7" color="#008080"&gt;NamHanSanSeong&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size="7" color="#0000FF"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;font color="#0000FF" size="5"&gt;(South Korea's Oldest Cache)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you're US military, show the gate guard your ID and you'll get in for free.  There's plenty of parking and buses run to the site.  Namhanseong is a hill-top fortress that was originally built around 50 BC and remodeled in 1624.  It was designed to protect the city of Seoul from invaders and a lot of the original wall is still visible throughout the park.  Temples and gates are abundant in the park and well worth some picture-taking.  For those of us who don't understand Hangul, the signs are translated into English.
Inside the fortress walls, are lots of restaurants, and a few small gift shops.  I ate at one located on a creek and paid 6,000 won ($5) for a more than generous meal.
The cache is more or less a "starter cache."  With the Garmin GPS 1 had an EPE of 25 feet when placing it.  It's about 2" x 4" x 8"  Tupperware dish with a RED lid.  It's slightly buried under some Rocks and dead leaves, but is recognizable.  I did put the required notepad and pen in it.  Also inside are a few military items from the US Army.  If you do go looking for the cache, I ask that you would add an item to it.  There's no travel bug in it yet..... we'll see how long it takes for someone to go find it then we may but some desired goodies on our next visit if there's some in it by then.  

Look at the photos before you go .....if you take something from the Cache...Please Leave Something&lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>There is a Buddhist Temple 400-500 feet south (below) the Cache location which is near Giant Boulders on the South side of the Hill. Great location to park your car and hike up from. There is a Trail behind one of the buddhist  shrines (tiger I think)that comes up almost directly to the cache point.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1360668174"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-13T00:44:31</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="42965057">TøTim</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thank you so much! Greetings from germany :) </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360725585"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-08T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="13846061">emfaza</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">#14264. Such an adventure! It checks out again that the oldest caches make the greatest adventures - not by their age, but their locations 😊 I'm sure that Namhansanseong rarely makes it to foreign tourists' to-do lists, and it definitely should! I haven't yet been to Great Wall of China, but from now I will imagine it like Namhansanseong 🥰 Great place and great cache, FP granted - thank you for taking us here!

It's our last day in Seoul and we haven't yet visited Namhansanseong - we weren't sure of this decision, since it's so far from the city, but it was a great decision - beautiful place with such an incredible skyline 🌇 And the oldest cache in the country was a nice addition 😊 Thanks!

I found this cache with NoffAnn during our wonderful 2-weeks trip to Korea 🇰🇷 We spent a week in Busan, with two daytrips to Gyeongju and also to Geoje Island (beautiful place, but sadly no caches there 😶), and our second week we spent in Seoul. Two weeks sound like a lot of time, but it wasn't nearly enough to see and experience all that we would like to, so I hope to come back here someday. 감사합니다 for all the caches, says 엠파자! 🫰</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1356792625"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-24T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="7944223">Kupfergraf</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Taking a few days off and then to visit the oldest geocache in whichever country we’re visiting has become a tradition. This time, too, I had a travelling companion (not my chief of staff and love of my life), which meant we paid a bit more attention to art, culture, food and shrines. After a long stopover in Hongkong, including a day trip to Macau, we travelled via Okinawa and Yakushima, then on to the main Japanese islands from west to east. On the way back, we chose Seoul as our pre-final stop. 

It was exhausting, hot, chaotic, wet, sandy, windy, steep, exciting, salty, breathtaking, surprising, delicious, … basically everything a geocaching trip can offer. Many thanks to all the cache owners who, with their time and effort, laid a very solid foundation for this tour. Brilliant! Greetings from Saxony! 

Bus 52 wasn’t running, so we took the 9 to the start. Following the wall anti-clockwise, after a bit of an up-and-down walk, we reached South Korea’s oldest geocache. The location and the container are more than fitting. Many thanks for maintaining it for such a long time. Of course, I’m leaving a favourite here.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1351940092"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-30T12:15:14</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="25072669">Sveinbor</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I’m in South-Korea for the first time, and this one was my main goal for today. 

Easily found. Both the log and the container are in good condition.

I grabbed a TB from the container.

Thanks a lot for the cache!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1351216606"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-26T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="95447">Norshley</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">The Crafty Canadians team of cc Cache!, brennanT, MuskieMouse, and myself are on an epic tour of the Pacific Rim, visiting 14 countries over 3 weeks and are having a blast.  South Korea and Japan are the last Asian stops on the tour.

Found this oldie cache on Mar 26, 2026 at 10:28. Signed the log as the Crafty team, and claimed the find. 
Thanks to wonkoo1 for the oldie cache hide.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="9.518317" lon="31.659333"><time>2006-06-15T00:00:00</time><name>GCXYV5</name><desc>YED Malakal by trasah</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCXYV5</url><urlname>YED Malakal</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="451708" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>YED Malakal</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>trasah</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="649241">trasah</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="1">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="33" inc="1">Motorcycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="34" inc="1">Quads</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="35" inc="1">Off-road vehicles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="37" inc="1">Horses</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="38" inc="0">Campfires</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="36" inc="1">Snowmobiles</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>South Sudan</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Malakal is a nice town at the border of the Nile in Upper Nile State in Southern Sudan. A Vocational Training Centre is supported by UNIDO in its restucturing and development for education to Youth. 
Public Internet Access in not yet available, but awareness is created for the possibilities of being in a global system.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>I did work at regular intervals in Malakal as ICT, Information and Communication Expert for UNIDO at the Malakal Vocational Training Centre.
Placing this cashe was of course one of the actions to bring information about the possibilities of Internet and Satellite Communications.

The Cache itself is a plastic transparent box of 35x20x20 cm, containing:
1. A logbook
2. Introduction to geocaching
3. To whom it concerns
4. Some pencils for entering data in logbook
5. Pencil sharpeners
6. Electricity socket adapter
7. Six alcaline batteries for GPS
8. Sunglass cleaner cloths
9. Some other ginmmicks

The plastic box and content were brought along from the Netherlands to Malakal.
Internet awareness, awareness of the possibilities of being member of a virtual group, like geocachers, still is in development at the Malakal Vocational Training Centre.
As for this moment is in the town no public Internet Access possible. The International Aid organisations possess VSATs and other means for communication with the Internet. The learning process of Internet possibilities by local public is still in its very initial stage. This cache is intended to contribute to awareness of the Internet and GPS possibilities by bringing  geocachers in contact with teachers and instructors of professional youth. 
Placing the cache in the open is difficult, so now the box is under good guardance of the UNIDO Local Project Leader.
People are friendly, eager to talk to you and to learn from you. It is very much expected that you give some more details about the hobby, your own professional activities and if you can; teach a few things. English conversation is wanted.</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Enter Malakal Vocational Training Centre. The box is in the desk of the MVTC deputy director.
MVTC Director's name is: Mr. Abdul Rachman, and he will always be delighted to assist.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1328742614"><groundspeak:date>2025-10-09T18:36:30</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="18990911">Knagur Green</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Due to no response from the CO after the request to maintain or replace the cache, I am archiving it to, stop it showing on the listings  and/or to create place for the geocaching community.

The [Geocache Maintenance guideline](http://www.geocaching.com/about/guidelines.aspx#cachemaintenance) explains a CO's responsibility towards checking and maintaining the cache when problems are reported. 

Please note that if geocaches are archived by a reviewer or Geocaching HQ for lack of maintenance, they are not eligible for unarchival. This is explained in the [Help Center](http://support.groundspeak.com//index.php?pg=kb.page&amp;id=70)

If the CO feels that this cache has been archived in error please feel free to contact me within 30 days,  via email or message via my profile ,quoting the GC number concerned

Thank you for understanding

Knagur Green
Groundspeak Volunteer Reviewer</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1319330241"><groundspeak:date>2025-08-21T23:27:25</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Unknown</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="18990911">Knagur Green</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">There have been numerous fake logs over the years and the CO has not addressed the matter . The cache seems to be missing or unobtainable as no one has posted a genuine find for the last few years, I am disabling the cache and request that the CO remove every fake log from the page and check the container is still in place. Once it is confirmed the container is in place, please enable the cache listing again and also post an owners maintenance log. 
 I will check back in 30 days and if the cache is not enabled and on line maintenance carried out, it will be at risk of archiving. 
 Thank you for understanding</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1314880893"><groundspeak:date>2025-08-03T13:17:16</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Needs Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5529931">Babashanti</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This cache is a farce. What needs to happen to stop these fake logs? It's a shame no reviewer is intervening. Or is this the kind of behavior Groundspeak tolerates and approves of?
THIS GEOCACHE IS A SHAME!!! </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1314700247"><groundspeak:date>2025-08-02T18:41:54</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="50321743">geowoo78</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Stop posting fake logs. It goes against geocaching etiquette and rules. It doesn't help anyone </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1308248241"><groundspeak:date>2025-07-02T18:29:46</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="33249185">Fkvtshfjk</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">fun cache TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="41.610317" lon="1.786483"><time>2001-02-18T00:00:00</time><name>GC2D4</name><desc>Montserrat by Francesc-Coral-Brian-Carles</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC2D4</url><urlname>Montserrat</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="724" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Montserrat</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Francesc-Coral-Brian-Carles</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="4339">comellas</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="56" inc="1">Medium hike (1 km–10 km)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="21" inc="1">Cliff/falling rocks</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>3</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Spain</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Catalunya</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>10 m from a red marked path (1075 m altitude) The path is a used by
climbers to reach the spikes and by hikers (passages require to use
hands) for its fantastic views. One of the finest in the region. We
recomend making the excursion from "Can Massana" (leave the car
there) to La Portella and Coll d'Agulles, then down the N gulley
and back to the car (2-3 h) or the reverse way. under a rock at the
foot of a big spike</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>The small white plastic container (19x11x5 cm) has been replaced in
its 5th aniversary (Feb 18, 2006) by an ammo box (thanks amon,
joanmire, vicam, garri, andreu, mr donut, effour &amp;amp; tecnics).</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Going  E the container is about 10 m N before a narrowing of the path between two spikes.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364191824"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T15:41:32</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="27080905">MATTGEO_O</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Log follow 

Favo 

M P L C </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1359408752"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-05T13:47:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4708467">lsk</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">6-day trip to Spain/Andorra with biffsjef. Caches mostly signed as BILS. The plan includes, among other things, Spain's and Andorra's oldest caches and a mega event. And much more.

Day 1: Barcelona-Andorra. Changing weather, some rain, and occasionally heavy showers. But also some sun. Fresh snow on the mountain peaks around Andorra. No wind and temperatures between 9-20 degrees. Covered some vertical meters on foot, including the trek to Spain's oldest cache, which was a spectacular trip. Otherwise, virtuals, earthcaches, mysteries, and traditionals. Favorite points awarded here and there.

TFTC

</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360501105"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-05T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6802272">biffsjef</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Then Biffsjef and Lsk were on a trip again, this time in Spain and Andorra. Big plans were made, and as usual a little bigger than we were able to achieve. But we managed all important goals and had a fantastic trip with many great cache visits. Many earthcaches, solved mysteries and challenges. Mountain hike in the Pyrenees at well over 2000 m above sea level with snow, and caching on the beach in bright sunshine. Great contrasts and lots of fun. All logs were signed with the common nickname Bils.
Many kilometers and a couple of rainy days, but that made the trip even better in great hiking company.

Big thanks to all the co's,
and greetings from Norway.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1358410833"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="16881799">Casvell</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Un dia molt feliç!!! Amb l'Oriol ens vam posar el repte de trobar el primer catxé de Catalunya i Espanya i ho hem aconseguit!!! Hem estat apunt d,abandonar i al final BINGO!! Catxé especial 1111. 
Gràcies per amagar i mantenir!!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1354791007"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-09T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4825283">Pakasch</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">#14'857 - Master of Mystery in Barcelona - dies lockte uns in diese Gegend. Bei der Vorbereitung schaute mich in der Gegend rum - hier liegt ja der älteste Cache von Spanien. Also mal begonnen zu studieren. Meine Frau - das heutige Geburtstagskind - klinkte sich ein und begann eine gute Route zu studieren. Sie zeichnete alles auf und so waren wir vorbereitet. Das Wetter war auch auf unserer Seite und so kamen wir mit dem Fröschli von unserem Camping her auf dem Parkplatz an. Es war warm, jedoch nicht heiss. Wir wechselten die Schuhe und zottelten los. Es ging gerade ein wenig hoch, doch der Weg war breit und staubig. Bald einmal zweigten wir auf einen Fusspfad ab und im Schatten von Bäumen ging es weiter in die Höhe. Bald einmal kam eine kleine Passage mit hohen Tritten, die ein klein bisschen zum Klettern einluden. Also nicht wirklich klettern, doch die Hände mussten wir zu Hilfe nehmen. Oben ging es wieder flach zum geschlossenen Refugio. Ein kurzer Rast und weiter geht es. Es wurde wieder steiler und bald waren es nur noch wenig 100 Meter zum Cache. Wir kamen an eine sehr ausgesetzte Passage - hier macht man besser keinen Fehltritt. Und nochmals wurde es steil und dann waren es noch wenige Meter bis zum Cache. Doch ein Engis, mit einigen Höhenmetern hielt uns ein bisschen auf. Wie kommen wir hier runter und vor allem wieder rauf? Zum Glück hatte ich die Bandschlingen dabei und so konnte ich meiner Frau helfen das Hindernis zu bewältigen. Schnell fand sie dann den Cache. Wir fühlten uns stolz und hatten Freude, diesen Cache gefunden zu haben. 
Doch es endet nicht damit - wir mussten ja auch wieder zurück.  Bald einmal stand meine Frau wieder bei mir und wir gingen noch auf den Feld und genossen die Aussicht. Wir haben schon zu Hause entschieden, dass wir den selben Weg zurückgehen werden und nicht die Schlaufe machen. Wir haben nun ja gesehen, was da noch alles auf einem zukommen könnte. Dann ging es zu euphorisch in den Abstieg und prompt verpassten wir den Weg. Doch nicht lange und wir waren wieder auf dem Weg. Da der Untergrund rutschig war, mussten wir konzentriert gehen. Beim Refugio assen wir dann etwas und wanderten dann weiter zurück zum Fröschli. Nach gut vier Stunden konnten wir wieder die Wanderschuhe ausziehen und den Weg zurück zum Camping unter die Räder nehmen. Für das tolle Erlebnis lassen wir einen Favoritenpunkt zurück. TFTC

Fund um 13:44

-------------------------------------------------

#14'857 - Maestro del Misterio en Barcelona - esto fue lo que nos atrajo a esta zona. Mientras nos preparábamos, eché un vistazo a los alrededores; al fin y al cabo, aquí se encuentra el geocaché más antiguo de España. Así que empecé a estudiarlo. Mi esposa, que hoy cumple años, se unió y empezó a buscar una buena ruta. Lo trazó todo, así que estábamos preparados. El tiempo también nos acompañó, así que llegamos al aparcamiento desde nuestro camping en nuestra autocaravana. Hacía calor, pero no un calor sofocante. Nos cambiamos de zapatos y nos pusimos en marcha. El camino ascendía ligeramente, pero era ancho y polvoriento. Pronto giramos hacia un sendero y continuamos subiendo a la sombra de los árboles. Pronto llegamos a un pequeño tramo con escalones altos que parecían invitar a trepar un poco. Bueno, no exactamente a escalar, pero sí tuvimos que usar las manos. En la cima, el camino se niveló de nuevo hasta el refugio cerrado. Un breve descanso y luego continuamos. El camino se volvió más empinado de nuevo, y pronto estábamos a solo unos cientos de metros del caché. Llegamos a un tramo muy expuesto; definitivamente no queríamos cometer ningún error. La pendiente se volvió pronunciada de nuevo, y entonces estábamos a solo unos metros del tesoro. Pero un pasaje estrecho, con un desnivel considerable, nos ralentizó un poco. ¿Cómo bajaríamos de allí y, lo que es más importante, cómo volveríamos a subir? Por suerte, llevaba las eslingas, así que pude ayudar a mi esposa a superar el obstáculo. Ella encontró el tesoro rápidamente. Nos sentimos orgullosos y felices de haberlo encontrado.

Pero la aventura no terminó ahí; aún teníamos que regresar. Pronto mi esposa se reunió conmigo, y salimos al campo a disfrutar de las vistas. Ya habíamos decidido en casa que volveríamos por el mismo camino y no haríamos el desvío. Ahora ya sabíamos qué más nos esperaba. Entonces, nos emocionamos demasiado en el descenso y enseguida perdimos el sendero. Pero no tardamos en retomar el camino correcto. Como el suelo estaba resbaladizo, tuvimos que caminar con cuidado. En el refugio comimos algo y luego regresamos caminando a Fröschli. Después de cuatro horas, pudimos quitarnos las botas de montaña y volver al camping. Guardamos este recuerdo como uno de nuestros favoritos. ¡Gracias por el geocaché!

Encontrado a las 13:44</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="7.957667" lon="80.76005"><time>2003-08-29T00:00:00</time><name>GCGRR6</name><desc>On Sigiriya rock by mhfares</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCGRR6</url><urlname>On Sigiriya rock</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Virtual Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="89350" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>On Sigiriya rock</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>mhfares</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="3884">mhfares</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Virtual Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Virtual</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>4</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Sri Lanka</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>Sigiriya rock is a site of considerable natural beauty and historic interest. It is only few miles north of Dambula city, famous for its cave temples. The site represents a unique concentration of fifth-century urban planning, architecture, gardening, engineering, hydraulic technology and art. 


You will have to do considerable climbing to reach the top of the rock (200m from surrounding plains), hence the rating 4. Almost half way to the top is a terrace housing the ruins of a large-scale animal that in effect was gatehouse to the palace at the summit.  


In order to claim this cache, you need to email me answers to the following two questions:

	What is the animal seen at the coordinate location?
	What is the remaining part of it that can still be seen today ?


Happy caching.
 
	
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1363676360"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-26T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="34450819">vega78220</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Très belle visite merci !</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362578319"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-22T12:56:10</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="426665">The Sundowners</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Had a wonderful time visiting this wonder of the world. Everyone sends to say the same thing. HOW!!! Getting to the top was a tad strenuous I must say but the effort was definitely worth it. Building all of the stairs that we used to climb was a feat in itself. I cannot imagine the difficulty reaching the top to build everything that is there. 

Thanks for the cache. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360560768"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-12T18:47:59</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="52000500">olgamazevedo</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">What a beautiful place! Greetings from Portugal!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1359674994"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-08T06:59:04</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="23945341">Hadrian13</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Bien atteint. La montée a été difficile notamment à la descente. Déconseillé aux personnes ayant des vertiges ! Merci pour cette cache virtuelle. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1356784219"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-24T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="11235740">dscatarino</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Amazing place! 🤩 TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="17.957667" lon="-62.8997"><time>2011-08-11T00:00:00</time><name>GC329FP</name><desc>Oyster Crew Cache by jamfan2</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC329FP</url><urlname>Oyster Crew Cache</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="2428161" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Oyster Crew Cache</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>jamfan2</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="435952">jamfan2</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="42" inc="1">Needs maintenance</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="55" inc="1">Short hike (&lt;1 km)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="11" inc="1">May require wading</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="4" inc="1">Boat required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="21" inc="1">Cliff/falling rocks</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="39" inc="1">Thorns</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>3</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Saint Barthélemy</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>The Oyster Crew Cache was placed while we were sailing in the area.
A beautiful hike to a beautiful sea lookout spot</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>Have fun hiking around Il Forche as you search the rocks for this
cache. It's in a glass peanut jar, and contains some fun items.
&lt;center&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size="1"&gt;Small note on cache maintenance: There is a local
cache guardian. Name and contact info on file with
geocaching.com.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/center&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>The cache is in a space underneath some larger rocks in the large rock outcropping. It's buried under a small pile of softball-sized rocks, to keep it anchored and protected. If you happen to have a strong plastic container, feel free to switch the cache container.




</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1350132019"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-20T10:01:07</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="30558201">Axhuti</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">A lovely lookout, thank you for the cache!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1276477020"><groundspeak:date>2025-01-05T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="10018518">str8upcacher</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">My trackable called "On the way to OZ!" is listed as being in this cache. Can anyone confirm this, please? Thanks! </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1275208033"><groundspeak:date>2024-12-29T10:20:04</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="267662">cryptoron</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Tftc</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1244837572"><groundspeak:date>2024-07-07T16:21:03</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3551734">sinxtreme</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Yes !
Out TB : the lost treasure of mary Jude</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1241898624"><groundspeak:date>2024-06-23T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="44013945">carmonunes</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I’m here with Broadreach, a sailing camp for teenagers. One of out students, Sarah found it unintentionally…and I got service to log it. Great spot for sunrise. They didn’t know about it and found it very cool. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="46.771567" lon="-56.2036"><time>2004-05-22T00:00:00</time><name>GCJGVZ</name><desc>St. Pierre 2004 cache by 48degrees</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCJGVZ</url><urlname>St. Pierre 2004 cache</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="141330" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>St. Pierre 2004 cache</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>48degrees</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="73567">48degrees</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="42" inc="1">Needs maintenance</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Saint Pierre and Miquelon</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>This cache was replaced in July 2018. It is located one kilometre outside the municipal limits of the town of St. Pierre, south of Newfoundland. The road is separated by a stone monument and when you start to see mega-houses on your right, you’re getting close.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>The small plastic container, covered in yellow Paris duck tape, was placed here to commemorate 500 years of French presence in St. Pierre in 2004 and also to remember the former site of Cutty Sark House, constructed of whiskey crates procured during prohibition years when the likes of Al Capone frequented St. Pierre to purchase liquor for resale on the black market in the United States.  Unfortunately the house has been razed. 
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints> On the north side of the road behind the electrical box. Cache has moved to the left of the nasty brambles in a tree.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="964539805"><groundspeak:date>2020-09-17T05:45:42</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1905804">Vandergore</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Bonjour,

Puisqu'il n'y a pas eu de maintenance dans un laps de temps raisonnable, j'archive cette cache définitivement.

voir aussi : http://www.geocaching.com/about/guidelines.aspx#cachemaintenance

Comme cet archivage a eu lieu à cause d'un manque de maintenance, il m'est impossible de la réactiver. 

Si vous voulez refaire une cache ici ... s.v.pl. soumettez un nouveau listing.

Cordialement,

Vandergore / Geocaching HQ - Volunteer Reviewer</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="955551591"><groundspeak:date>2020-08-17T03:53:17</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Unknown</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1905804">Vandergore</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Bonjour,

Pour garder tout son intérêt au jeu, il est souhaitable que les caches soient opérationnelles. En effet, quelle déception de ne pas trouver une boîte, car elle a disparu ou est en très mauvais état.
Le propriétaire d'une cache a la possibilité de désactiver une cache lorsqu'elle rencontre un problème et il peut lui même la réactiver lorsqu'il en a fait la maintenance.

Les derniers logs sur votre cache semblent indiquer qu'il y a un problème. Il serait souhaitable d'y faire une visite de maintenance. J'ai donc procédé à sa désactivation temporaire.
Lorsque vous aurez réalisé la visite de maintenance ou si vous estimez qu'elle n'est pas nécessaire (cache très difficile à trouver, autre…) n'hésitez pas à la réactiver vous-même en sélectionnant "Activer la cache" sur la page de la cache.

Sans action de votre part, cette cache sera archivée d'ici 30 jours.

Merci de votre compréhension.

Cordialement,
Vandergore / Geocaching HQ - Volunteer Reviewer</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="955208220"><groundspeak:date>2020-08-16T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Didn't find it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="14252004">Sacamomi</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Cette cache se trouve sur un terrain privé.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="955208231"><groundspeak:date>2020-08-16T10:39:08</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Needs Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="14252004">Sacamomi</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Ce géocacheur a signalé que cette cache devrait être archivée. Un reviewer de la communauté de bénévoles en a été informé.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="889456663"><groundspeak:date>2019-10-19T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5905341">marlown76</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Attention pas de logbook ni de stylo. Mplc</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="13.011333" lon="-61.246383"><time>2008-02-20T00:00:00</time><name>GC19HB0</name><desc>Bequia, Eh? by BequiaGeo</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC19HB0</url><urlname>Bequia, Eh?</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="797198" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Bequia, Eh?</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>BequiaGeo</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="1268874">BequiaGeo</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Other</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="0">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="52" inc="0">Night cache</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="14" inc="0">Recommended at night</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="40" inc="1">Stealth required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="30" inc="0">Picnic tables nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="0">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="59" inc="1">Food nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="27" inc="0">Drinking water nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="58" inc="0">Fuel nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="31" inc="0">Camping nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="29" inc="0">Telephone nearby</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>4</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Saint Vincent and the Grenadines</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>terrain is flat until the final hike up the hill to the cache. Please be mindful of your footing as you retrieve the cache and kindly replace in its original location.
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>Bequia is a lovely little island lying nine miles south of St. Vincent, in the Grenadines. It appears to have been inhabited from about 200AD and today it's rich heritage continues with centuries-old traditions of boat building, fishing and aboriginal whaling. Cache is a micro. Please bring your own writing stick.
&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size="1"&gt;Small note on cache maintenance: I visit this island annually. Contact info on file with geocaching.com&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1352441192"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Didn't find it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="12598799">Rose Limelight</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">With Taxi1729 sadly can't find</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1352312392"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Didn't find it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="9275665">Taxi1729</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Had a 10-minute stop here as part of an island tour. No luck with this one, I'm afraid. Had a good search. A vendor offered to help if I bought something from his store, but I had only brought $2 with me and he wouldn't accept that. I do wonder if the vendors have moved it in order to make money, but I really hope this isn't the case. Oh well, it was a lovely view anyway - many thanks for placing a cache here. (It would have earned a favourite point if I had found it.) Sadly, this was my only chance of finding a cache on this island, but it was still a wonderful visit.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1349912987"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-18T15:16:29</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="30059281">KWP</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">T-Shirt kostet mittlerweile 20 US-Dollar! 😄😉
Tftc</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1353075622"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-22T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="12545512">ericp212</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Direction les Caraïbes pour une dizaine de jours de vacances « d’hiver » au soleil. Et cela fait du bien de sentir notre astre nous éclairer et nous réchauffer 😉, de pouvoir profiter de l’eau de mer à 28°C, de la vie un peu plus tranquille, ... 
Après quelques jours de ballade (géocaching of course) et de repos à la Martinique, nous partons pour une semaines en catamaran à l’assaut de quelques îles plus au Sud. Bien entendu nous en profiterons pour trouver quelques caches lorsque le hasard des mouillages nous amènera à proximité relative d’une cache. 
Merci pour l’invitation à la ballade et pour toutes les caches. 
Pour cette première escale nous ferons le tour complet de la baie et nous trouverons cette cache après une interruption de moldus à quelques mètres du point zéro mais à un endroit presque logique une fois que l’on a vérifié les autres possibilités 😉. 


Un TB out en route pour de nouvelles aventures</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1345776685"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-21T10:43:53</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1444865">David F Green</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Long unsuccessful search, then the scarf man came to our rescue. First Caribbean cache, so a favourite point !</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="18.09065" lon="-63.010183"><time>2003-08-08T00:00:00</time><name>GCGM9P</name><desc>Green Key / Caye Verte by Fred Langa adopted by RetiredGuy</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCGM9P</url><urlname>Green Key / Caye Verte</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Virtual Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="85057" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Green Key / Caye Verte</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Fred Langa adopted by RetiredGuy</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="2758778">RetiredGuy</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Virtual Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Virtual</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="12" inc="1">May require swimming</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="4" inc="1">Boat required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="54" inc="1">Abandoned structure</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Saint Martin</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;Welcome to the oldest geocache in St. Martin placed by Fred Langa in 2003. Note that this geocache is a &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Terrain 5&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; as you must find a way to get to Green Key. Cachers have gotten to the island by boat, jetski, and swimming. All logs that do not have proof that you went to the island will be deleted. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;The original requirements were to land on the island and then “Find the foundation ruins of a stone building and post a photo of yourself standing on the stonework.&amp;quot; This is still the preferred method.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;More recently, the St. Martin Nature Reserve has started putting up “No Trespassing” signs on the beach during the nesting season of certain shorebirds. In the event that the “No Trespassing” signs are up when you visit, do not land on the island. Instead, you may submit a picture of yourself or your geocaching name from your boat with the stone ruins in the background BUT the picture must be taken close to the island (within 300 meters or 1000 feet). Pictures taken from Orient Beach will not be accepted and the log will be deleted.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/2bbd0cf6-b4c0-44b8-bc08-3fe09c257311.jpg" /&gt;  &lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/86905f03-f4e3-4b25-8c9f-51439f3097a5.jpg" /&gt;  &lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/0f5c8cc5-3728-4da0-a020-5f54add4c662.jpg" /&gt;  &lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/8216cd20-ce77-4f90-a541-6165ed7808e7.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1354577079"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-11T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1091791">LeGrandChrist</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Quand je visite un nouveau pays/nouvelle région, j'essaie de visiter la plus vieille cache.  La semaine derniere, j'ai visité la plus vieille de Sint Maarten et c'était le tour de celle-ci aujourdhui, la plus vielle de Saint-Martin. 

J'ai fait un beau tour de jetski avec mon pilote Fernando. L'aller a été bien tranquille et je ne voulais pas le brusquer. On a commencé à la earthcache pour quelques photos. puis on est allé à la virtuelle.  Pour le retour, je lui ai dit qu'il pouvait aller plus vite mais sans se faire peur.  Il a pris le temps de passer la sangle de son chapeau sous son menton et on est revenu beaucoup plus vite.

Belle promenade, 2 belles caches de plus à mon actif.

MPLC RetiredGuy</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1345392172"><groundspeak:date>2026-01-27T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="24073912">kulona</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Eine Hälfte vom Team ist wieder einmal unterwegs im Urlaub. Dieses Mal ging es über den Atlantik in die Karibik. Gemeinsam mit **6Bonnie und Clyde6** und **Olkavido65** wollten wir die Inselwelt durchstreifen und kennenlernen. Dabei können wir auch dem heimischen Winter den Rücken kehren. Hauptsächlich sollten einige gemeinsame Erlebnisse im Vordergrund der Reise stehen. Dessen ungeachtet werden sicher trotzdem ein paar Cache gesucht. 

Nach unsrigem gestrigen Besuch auf Tortola auf den British Virgins Islands brachte uns unser Schiff heute nach Philipsburg auf Sint Maarten. Wir unternahmen gemeinsam einen ausgiebigen Ausflug über die Insel. Highlights waren unter anderem der Besuch von Orient Beach, Fort Louis, Trou David und nicht zuletzt Maho Beach. Es war für uns eine neue und beeindruckende Erfahrung in anderer Natur, als wir sie kennen und gewöhnt sind. 

Auch dieser Cache war Teil unserer heutigen Aktivitäten. Hier hatten wir Spaß. Das Foto vom Jet-Ski aus war ne ziemliche wacklige Angelegenheit. Hier hinterlassen wir gern ein blaues 💙.

Wir danken **RetiredGuy** für diesen heute von uns besuchten Cache. Viele Grüße aus der Oberlausitz von kulona.
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1345317914"><groundspeak:date>2026-01-27T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="21667592">Olkavido65</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Gemeinsame Kreuzfahrt 🛳 in der Karibik 🏝 mit guten Cacherfreunden.
Der Kälte entflohen und die warmen Temperaturen genossen.
Unser heutiger Zwischenstopp war heute Sint Maarten. Heute ging es mit 6Bonnie und Clyde6 und Kulona über die Insel.
Dieser Urlaub wird uns noch lange in Erinnerung bleiben.
Dabei besuchten wir auch GCGM9P Green Key.
Leider dürfen wir die Insel nicht betreten, aber mit dem Jet-Ski kamen wir in die Nähe.

Gerne könnt ihr unseren 🐸 TB JDKXWY 🐸 loggen
Hier noch ein Hinweis für den Owner: Ich logge nicht unbedingt am Ende der Logeinträge, sondern auch gerne mal an irgendeiner freien Stelle mitten im Logbuch, die sehr oft anzutreffen sind, weil offensichtlich einige Cacher nicht ordentlich loggen wollen oder können. Ich nutze auch gerne mal eine Rückseite des Logbuches.

Danke an df8an für das Legen und Pflegen sagt Olkavido65 aus Deutschland 🍀</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1345243954"><groundspeak:date>2026-01-27T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4270457">6Bonnie und Clyde6</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Ein Traum wird war. Dem kalten Deutschland entfliehen und ab ins Warme. So ging es mit lieben Cacherfreunden Kulona und Olkavido65 aufs Schiff.
Hier war unsere nächste Station.
Der Mietwagen war gebucht und so ging es kreuz und quer über die Insel.
Hat uns super viel Spaß gemacht.
Es ist wunderschön hier. Die Einwohner alle freundlich und hilfsbereit.
Wir werden die schöne Zeit in Erinnerung behalten.
Die Insel konnten wir leider nicht betreten, kamen aber mit dem Jet-Ski in die Nähe.

Vielen Dank an RetiredGuy für die Arbeit mit dem Cache Green Key / Caye Verte und natürlich fürs Herführen und Verstecken.

Happy hunting und bis bald im Wald, sagen [6Bonnie und Clyde6](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SyhKBz9XzGM).</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1341060845"><groundspeak:date>2026-01-04T18:40:38</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2758778">RetiredGuy</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Green Key was transferred from flanga to user RetiredGuy</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="18.537766666666666" lon="31.826999999999998"><time>2008-03-19T00:00:00</time><name>GC1ABPR</name><desc>Jabal Barkkal by elmoro</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC1ABPR</url><urlname>Jabal Barkkal</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="821588" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Jabal Barkkal</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>elmoro</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="236805">elmoro</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Sudan</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Jabal Barkkal is very close to Karima, if you are going to visit the pyramids there ir the Temple of Mut, then you will be close...very close to this cache</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>A lovely spot by sunset, don't miss the awesome view</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>It is not on top of the mountain</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1128254273"><groundspeak:date>2022-09-27T11:05:14</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5721053">geo alex</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">On our way to Abou Simbel, we made a few stops.  We didn’t find the boxe🕵🏻‍♂️ TFTC and hello 🤗from Montréal Québec ✌️🇨🇦</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="992653403"><groundspeak:date>2021-02-06T06:41:04</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="330527">JBinthe615</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Being on a post in Khartoum, gives me very few opportunity to find Geocaches, this one is the only one I know of in the country. Well we went on a weekend trip to the Merowe Dam and the Barkal Mountain. The sunrise morning walk to the mountain was the perfect opportunity to find the geocache. Made the little detour and I was at GZ. A quick search, and the cache was in my hand. Picture taken, and I proceed to rejoin my group to climb that mountain and e joy a sunrise.

TFTC

Find #3769, Sudan #1</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="907357489"><groundspeak:date>2020-02-09T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="28438900">bubacek14</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Nice</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="903956631"><groundspeak:date>2020-01-17T19:16:15</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4582886">MSqwared</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">What an adventure we are having in Sudan. This cache hadn’t been logged in over a year, so I had my doubts it would still be around (also given the number of “Found It” logs that also clearly stating they did not actually find the cache itself, but simply stood at GZ. More to explain later, but I was also not able to find the cache, not the rocks in the foreground of the spoiler photo (although I was able to determine the exact correct spot where those rocks had been). The spoiler spot still had me 40ft off though, so after a thorough search there (and elsewhere) I concluded the cache was missing and went back to where my GPS zeroed out to find a fitting spot to hide a replacement container. Signed a new log in a new bottle and nestled it in among some rocks in a place that seemed safe for the moment. New spoiler photos to follow soon once I return to proper internet. First physical cache in Sudan! </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="812907959"><groundspeak:date>2018-09-26T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8819069">Maťka19</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">dokonaly vylet v dokonalej krajine.. dnes dokonale miesto na vyhlad a zapad slnka v pozadi s pyramidami .. dakujem :)</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="5.525717" lon="-55.0519"><time>2007-09-23T00:00:00</time><name>GC167VT</name><desc>Overbridge - Bridge Over Water by Witboi</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC167VT</url><urlname>Overbridge - Bridge Over Water</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Multi-cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="698705" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Overbridge - Bridge Over Water</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Witboi</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="3193265">Snabelabe</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Multi-cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="12" inc="1">May require swimming</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="4" inc="1">Boat required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="10" inc="1">Difficult climb</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="23" inc="1">Dangerous area</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="21" inc="1">Cliff/falling rocks</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="18" inc="1">Dangerous animals</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="19" inc="1">Ticks</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="17" inc="1">Poisonous plants</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="39" inc="1">Thorns</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>3.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Suriname</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Comic Sans MS;"&gt;
&lt;big&gt;&lt;span id="ShortDescription"&gt;In the middle of the jungle of
Suriname, South America on the edge of the Suriname river lies a
very&amp;nbsp;nice&amp;nbsp;River Resort. It is a&amp;nbsp;combination of a
living&amp;nbsp;and&amp;nbsp;recreation area that resembles a Caribean
beach resort except for the jungle surrounding it.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span style="font-family: Comic Sans MS; color: rgb(2, 0, 2);"&gt;The
drive from the city of Paramaribo to this River Resort takes about
one hour. From the city you have to take the "M.L. Kingweg" (
Highway) which just after passing Paranam&amp;nbsp;transforms into a
bauxite road to Afobaka. On this road the junction to this River
Resort is clearly indicated. Click
&lt;a href="http://home.tiscali.nl/witboi/View_Savannas_Suriname.pdf"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;
to get a general overview of the main roads and
savanna's.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br style="font-family: Comic Sans MS; color: rgb(2, 0, 2);" /&gt;

&lt;span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);" id="ShortDescription"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style="font-family: Comic Sans MS;"&gt;At the above position you
will find the N and W coordinates of the cache separately. Have a
good look, they are there!!!&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/big&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Comic Sans MS;"&gt;
&lt;big&gt;&lt;img style="width: 260px; height: 214px;" alt=""
src="http://sites.google.com/site/rwynhoven/bridge-over-wa/normal_LUCHTFOTO_6.jpg" /&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;img style="width: 260px; height: 214px;" alt=""
src="http://sites.google.com/site/rwynhoven/bridge-over-wa/normal_P1010043A.jpg" /&gt;
 &amp;nbsp;&lt;/big&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Comic Sans MS;"&gt;
&lt;big&gt;&lt;img style="width: 260px; height: 214px;" alt=""
src="http://sites.google.com/site/rwynhoven/bridge-over-wa/normal_P1010058.jpg" /&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;img style="width: 260px; height: 214px;" alt=""
src="http://sites.google.com/site/rwynhoven/bridge-over-wa/normal_PIER.jpg" /&gt;
 &lt;span id="ShortDescription"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/big&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Comic Sans MS;"&gt;
&lt;big&gt;&lt;span id="ShortDescription"&gt;The cache can best be reached when
the sand beaches are&amp;nbsp;at their smallest.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span id="ShortDescription"&gt;Special equipment is needed and may
sometimes be obtained at N05.31.510 W055.03.151 Please take all
safety precautions and be very carefull of (brazilian) bees and
wasps.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/big&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Comic Sans MS;"&gt;
&lt;big&gt;&lt;span id="ShortDescription"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="LongDescription"&gt;The
cache consists of a middle size plastic container wrapped in a red
plastic bag. It contains a note book, a pencil and a
goodie.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/big&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Comic Sans MS;"&gt;
&lt;big&gt;&lt;span id="LongDescription"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/big&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>A combination of words gives you the name of the River Resort. Also some words, or even the whole sentence, can have more than one meaning.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="861151055"><groundspeak:date>2019-07-02T11:09:37</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1778438">GeoCrater</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I am regretfully archiving this cache since there's been no response from nor action by the cache owner within the time frame requested in the last reviewer note.

GeoCrater
Geocaching.com Community Volunteer Reviewer</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="854171377"><groundspeak:date>2019-06-02T12:31:13</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Unknown</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1778438">GeoCrater</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Good Day,

This geocache was brought to my attention as being in need of an owner maintenance visit. The cache owner needs to check on this cache ASAP and either replace it or archive it, after picking up any geo-litter. See the [maintenance section of the Geocache Listing Requirements/Guidelines](http://www.geocaching.com/about/guidelines.aspx#listingmaintenance).

I've added this cache to my watchlist, and I will check back in four weeks to be sure that the maintenance has been done. In the meantime, I have temporarily disabled this listing. When the maintenance is completed, the owner can enable the listing by clicking on the link below the cache name to return it to active status.

Whatever your intentions, please **post a note** here on the cache page (not email) to let us know that you are still active and maintaining the cache. If a month passes without seeing a response, then I'll assume that this listing should be archived.

Looking forward to hearing from you,

GeoCrater
Geocaching.com Community Volunteer Reviewer

{#32c07fddbffc656188a2a46d72ee582a}</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="847001013"><groundspeak:date>2019-05-04T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Didn't find it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="55052">Bosscout</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">The bridge is gone. Unable to reach anymore.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="847048149"><groundspeak:date>2019-05-04T10:09:05</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Unknown</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1778438">GeoCrater</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">It appears your cache may be missing.  May I ask you (the cache owner) confirm this cache remains in place and available to be found?  Please **post a note** here on the cache page (not email) to let us know that you are still active and maintaining the cache.

GeoCrater
Geocaching.com Community Volunteer Reviewer</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="847001030"><groundspeak:date>2019-05-04T06:42:59</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Needs Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="55052">Bosscout</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Deze geocacher heeft gemeld dat deze geocache zou moeten worden gearchiveerd. Een reviewer is hiervan op de hoogte gesteld.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="78.187433" lon="15.55825"><time>2002-08-12T00:00:00</time><name>GC8287</name><desc>78°N  - Svalbard by Laila, Steffen, Alwin, Marieke</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC8287</url><urlname>78°N  - Svalbard</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="33415" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>78°N  - Svalbard</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Laila, Steffen, Alwin, Marieke</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="24793">laila</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="42" inc="1">Needs maintenance</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>3</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>4</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Svalbard and Jan Mayen Islands</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>This is one of the worlds northernmost caches! 
It is hidden at 78°N and 515 m above sea level in beautiful arctic surroundings close to the city of Longyearbyen at Svalbard/Spitsbergen. Although the terrain is steep with loose rocks at some parts, a visit is highly recommended!
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>During a summer course at Svalbard I decided to place a GPS cache hoping for it to be the worlds northernmost! 
Through brief search at the geocaching.com pages I realized that there are people hiding caches everywhere, even at 
82°N in Nunavut, Canada ("As North As It Gets!" by Iceshelf 2002 Research Team, May 2002)!!!! (https://coord.info/GC5803) 

Impressive!!!

My cache is placed at the mountain Sarkofagen at "only" 
78°N and can be reached by foot from Nybyen (totally 3h).

The cache is hidden in the lowest (of 2, so far...) pile of rocks at the very top with a fabulous view over Longyearbyen and the many surrounding glaciers, mountain peaks and valleys!


So people, go and get it!!
Or enjoy the pictures from the hiding!!







</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>If you get to the top you cant miss the cache unless it is removed by Mother Nature...</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="953786527"><groundspeak:date>2020-08-12T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1339495">kakatt</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Jeg fant den fordi guiden vår, Peter, visste hvor den lå. Jeg kjenner ikke til at det er andre cacher like ved. Tusen takk for cachen og for en fabelaktiv tur til fantasiske Svalbard :-) 

I found it because our guide knew of it. To my knowledge, there are no other caches in the vicinitiy. Thank you for the cache and our marvellous trip to Svalbard :-)</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1038165290"><groundspeak:date>2018-07-02T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="11901045">Guru kLuk</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Visited with my lovely ZOSK during our geology expedition on Svalbard :-) Thank you for this cache.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="792107280"><groundspeak:date>2018-07-02T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2708189">ZOSK</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Visited with my lovely Guru kLuk during our geology expedition on Svalbard :-) We found the cache in a good condition at the updatet coordinates in one of the log. It was a stunning place and an awesome trip with a beutiful and nice guide Hilde :-) Thank you for the cache.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="777233101"><groundspeak:date>2018-06-23T13:07:06</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1778258">Makuta Teridax</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">The coordinates are wrong by hundreds of metres, and the cache owner is no longer active.

Currently, there seems to be more than one cache at the location. It would be nice if some could remove them so they don't end up as litter.

If someone else wants to maintain a cache at Sarkofagen, please submit a new cache listing.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="780277648"><groundspeak:date>2018-06-22T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="18030217">JellyCZ</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">what? I'm back home from Svalbard and this cache is archived? this was one of the highlights of our Svalbard adventure. we went from our apartment in Longyearbyen with plan to go through Longyearbreen valley to Longyearpasset and then via Trollsteinen back (http://toposvalbard.npolar.no/). after we examined the fossils at the bottom of Longyearbreen, we continued to Longyearpasset. but this was too much for us as the snow cover was still deep in places and the walk was very difficult. at about 3/4 of the valley we gave up, turned over and went back, then turned up right to Sarkofagen. the top was snowless and we have really enjoyed the views. it was spectacular! as a bonus I found the cache there, with no problems. the location is N 78° 11.396 E 015° 33.745, it's about 20 meters back from the top pile of rocks with tourist signbook. only 1 container was there and it's a real pity to see this archived. the cache is there and in good condition. tftc and greetings from Zlín!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="-26.903933" lon="31.045917"><time>2002-04-07T00:00:00</time><name>GC4AA9</name><desc>Bushman paintings by hosta</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC4AA9</url><urlname>Bushman paintings</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Virtual Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="19113" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Bushman paintings</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>hosta</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="16574">hosta</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Virtual Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Virtual</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>4</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>4</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Eswatini</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Bushman paintings in series of overhangs</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>Here is your chance to visit this cut-off area and see something
nobody has ever seen before. I discovered these paintings myself
only a few months back. Now geocachers on this site can visit it. 
&lt;p&gt;The Bushman painting site is in fact in Swaziland, but only 35
km from Piet Retief. Even so, you will have to set aside at least
one whole day to make sure of your success. Passport is required to
enter Swaziland. Nearest border post to paintings opens at 08h00
and closes at 16h00. Mahamba border post closes at 22h00 and it
takes over one hour to drive there.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Go by mountain bicycle, 4x4 vehicle or hiking. Transport can be
arranged. To get to the paintings with passenger car is possible
only if road is not washed away. It involves long detour and
approach from other side of the mountains. Contact me for
description and road condition.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bushmen were the original inhabitants of Southern Africa. They
lived in the valleys and in the caves of the cliffs for centuries
before the arrival of present inhabitants. Their paintings in rock
shelters made them famous.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are quite a few Bushman paintings of good quality. It is
possible you will discover more of them. This is just beginning of
a gorge through which the river flows for another 12 km. This is
also beginning of an exciting three day hiking and kloofing trail
to Hlatikulu. Area is sparsely populated. A few mud houses can be
seen along the way, inhabited only by women and children. Local
inhabitants do not know about the paintings. If you don't want to
get lost don't ask them for any directions. Relay on your GPS. Be
self-sufficient. Stock up in Piet Retief.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Coordinates given are in the middle of Ka-Dinga bridge. GPS
doesn't work well in deep kloof where overhangs with paintings are
located. From the bridge walk downstream, the river on your right.
Soon your progress is stopped by rock face. Do your best to cross
the river, but do not attempt crossing if it is in flood. Mind the
rocks, they are very slippery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Once safely on the other side, you find yourself in thick and
thorny vegetation. There is no path. Remember, you are in fact the
first person to visit this area. Make your way to the rock face and
the first overhang. It is large, but there are no paintings there.
Follow the rock band and series of smaller overhangs till you reach
a larger overhang where painting are located. Explore and
admire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;But that's not the end. To claim the cache you must go on and
crawl some distance through thick and springy vegetation until you
reach an overhang where there is a small stone altar. You will
discover more animal paintings, one of which is rendered in a
different "style" to all the others. Tell me what style and you
logged this cache.&lt;/p&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="660719852"><groundspeak:date>2017-01-16T13:47:10</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="41118">Geocaching HQ</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Unfortunately, as there has been no response to the disablement of this cache, it must now be archived.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="655928395"><groundspeak:date>2016-12-17T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="481249">Fish Eagle</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">The co-ords aren't quite right.  Follow your nose.  Stop at the bridge, go a short distance along the left bank of the river, then wade through to the right bank.  Be alert, there's a very small chance there could be a croc, but highly unlikely.  Then continue a way along the right shore and climb up to the bottom of the cliff.  Move along the cliff base and look carefully for the rock paintings, sort of under the overhang, and you should see them.   Not easy terrain, expect thorns and scratches.  Good luck!! [:D]</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="655919249"><groundspeak:date>2016-12-12T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="13381949">BoazRuthFields</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Would please very much like to help with this cache. Please dont archive. We are in serious need of these caches in the Region. Thanks very much</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="298886635"><groundspeak:date>2013-03-16T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="803745">DamhuisClan</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Such a pity that it is disabled.

A small piece of Southern African history is about to go missing!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="288613456"><groundspeak:date>2013-01-09T01:09:52</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Unknown</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="41118">Geocaching HQ</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This is an automated message. This cache owner is currently inactive. This cache has been Temporarily Disabled by Groundspeak.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="59.292583" lon="17.901883"><time>2000-08-11T00:00:00</time><name>GC4D</name><desc>Match Stash by Tobias Radeskog</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC4D</url><urlname>Match Stash</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="77" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Match Stash</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Tobias Radeskog</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="390">tr_s</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="0">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="0">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="1">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="26" inc="1">Public transportation nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="19" inc="1">Ticks</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Sweden</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Stockholm</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>GC4D The Match Stash. Oldest active geocache in Sweden. Second oldest in all of Europe.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Easy find as long as there is little or no snow on the ground. Brief steep walking off path required.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
In the Stockholm-Sätra district close to the water and a network of nice walking trails. Stockholm's widest beach is a few hundred meters to the west.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
There is often fika and simple lunch possibilities during daytime at the horse riding school nearby.
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GC4D - THE MATCH STASH&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is, by registration date, &lt;strong&gt;the oldest currently active geocache in Sweden and the second oldest in Europe&lt;/strong&gt;. It is still being maintained by its original owner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
The cache was however dormant from 2003-2010, and restarted in time to the ten-year worldwide geocaching jubilaeum.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Cache code GC4D, means Geocache #4D in hexadecimal notation, that is, the 77th geocache worldwide.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Match Stash &lt;strong&gt;existed before Geocaching.com even existed&lt;/strong&gt;, a rough manual cache listing was maintained by Mike Teague, the world's first &lt;em&gt;geocache finder&lt;/em&gt;, before this.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
The name comes from that the cache originally contained a lot of safety matches.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Link to original historic cache listing: &lt;a href="http://web.archive.org/web/20010430201715/http://www.triax.com/~yngwie/sweden.html"&gt;http://web.archive.org/web/20010430201715/http://www.triax.com/~yngwie/sweden.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the woods of Sätra close to some trails. Brief off-path steep walking required but should be a very easy find as long as there is little or no snow on the ground.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
During daytime, consider supporting the nearby café in the horse farm by having a &lt;em&gt;fika&lt;/em&gt; (sw: coffee break with buns etc) or soup lunch.&lt;br /&gt;
It is just a hundred meters south of the little hill the cache is located on.&lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Under some rocks just beside tree.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364821246"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T15:53:23</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2180934">Threefoot</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Vi gjorde en minisemesterresa till Stockholm och som bieffekt fick vi bocka av två cachingrelaterade angelägenheter. Dels att slutföra den virtuella GC9P6A9 Sveriges Domkyrkor med Storkyrkan som den sista och så denna. Det är nästan lite vördnadsfullt att få logga denna cache som är nära nog samtida med Hedenhös. Inga svårigheter att finna denna, bara att följa den vältrampade geostigen. 
Trevligt att hitta denna cache. Jag gjorde det tillsammans med LBTW. I det fall vi signerade så för att spara tid, plats och bläck loggade vi som team LT eller bara LT. Stort tack till alla CO som lägger ut och underhåller cacher till vårt nöje att leta upp och signera. TFC.
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364820317"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T15:52:34</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4468068">LBTW</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Vi har tagit oss till Stockholm ett par dagar för att lösa två viktiga uppgifter. Den första löstes igår när vi besökte Storkyrkan och gick i mål med att få logga den virtuella cachen Sveriges Domkyrkor (där man ska fota sig vid landets alla 15 domkyrkor). Den andra tog vi tag i idag. Tunnelbanan ut och en promenad i det fina vädret. Så roligt att kunna logga Sveriges äldsta nu levande gömma. 

Hittad tillsammans med Threefoot, vi loggar som Team LT för att spara plats i loggboken. Tusen tack till CO för planering och underhåll under alla dessa år. Hatten av och en favoritpoäng för det! TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364773970"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="27856066">st_ranger</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Das Ziel war Schweden. Und da natürlich vor allem der älteste Cache, der legendäre Match Stash. 
Aber es gibt auch noch andere Caches in diesem schönen Land. So versuche ich auch eine Reihe von anderen Caches zu besuchen, um eine möglichst große Vielfalt zu bekommen. So kam ich zum eigentlichen Ziel der Reise, dem Cache GC4D Match Stash und konnte die Aufgabe erledigen. Vielen Dank an tr_s für dieses Versteck.

Målet var Sverige. Och där var det förstås framför allt den äldsta cachen, den legendariska Match Stash. 
Men det finns också andra cacher i detta vackra land. Därför försöker jag besöka en rad andra cacher för att få så stor variation som möjligt. Så hamnade jag också vid denna cache GC4D Match Stash och kunde klara uppgiften. Tack så mycket till tr_s för denna gömma.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364773433"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-31T14:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4001017">regenbogen_69</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Roadtripp
Mit dem WoMo reise ich derzeit bei sommerlichen Temperaturen und nutze es, wenn sich die Gelegenheit ergibt, zu halten und Orte oder Sehenswürdigkeiten zu bestaunen. Wenn es möglich ist, Cache ich natürlich auch gerne. 
Ich bedanke mich für das legen und Pflegen des Caches


I am currently traveling in my motorhome amidst summery temperatures, taking the opportunity—whenever it arises—to stop and marvel at various places or sights. Whenever possible, I also enjoy doing some geocaching, of course.
Thank you for placing and maintaining this cache.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364534334"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-31T11:30:34</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="19448223">Leixoni</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">On a road trip from 🇫🇮 to 🇸🇪 🇩🇰 🇩🇪 🇳🇱 🇧🇪 🇱🇺
Seeing history, scenery and meeting cool people, and of course caching too. This fossil of a cache was not too difficult with all the paths leading to it for obvious reasons. Thank you for maintaining this historical cache and greetings from Finland!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="46.427583" lon="7.29845"><time>2001-01-27T00:00:00</time><name>GC2A5</name><desc>Gstaash by Jesse Grimes</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC2A5</url><urlname>Gstaash</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="677" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Gstaash</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Jesse Grimes</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="1769">jessepg</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Switzerland</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Bern</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Terrain is a 3. This is because in winter the mile long hike can be tiring in snow, although it's on a maintained path. In summer the path is easy to follow.
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>This stash is located near the summit of Wispile, a mountain overlooking the Swiss Alpine town of Gstaad. The location is easily accessible year-round; a short walk from the town of Gstaad and a two-stage gondola ride to the top. Once at the top, it's a mile-long walk to the far end of a marked and maintained loop hiking path, to just where the winter sledding run continues steeply downhill. After admiring the stunning views and the summit lodge, the gondola can be taken to the base, or the sledding run can be taken to a neighboring town.
&lt;p&gt;When there's snow on the ground the path is groomed for walking and sledding and is therefore packed reasonably well. Although it's still below the treeline, it's exposed enough to mean that it can get windy and very cold. However, when I placed the cache in late January it was sunny and mild. Some people had snowshoes on but they're not necessary. During the summer there is no snow and the walk would be easy for anyone.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The cache itself is a very short distance off the path, on the down-hill side of a pine tree. See the pictures to easily orient yourself. It's a dark green ammo box.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Update in April 2005 - Sadly I've never been back to visit my cache, although I've visited Switzerland several times since. I'm always happy to check this page every six months and find more people have visited it and enjoyed the views! If the next person to visit it could take a picture of it and post it, I'd like to see what it looks like now. Thanks! Jesse&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Update in June 2008 - I'm thrilled to see Gstaash is still safely tucked away, and continues to be regularly found, more than seven years since I first placed it there! If someone could post what's inside the box when it's next found, I would be happy to hear it! Jesse&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Update in December 2010 - It's almost a decade since I placed this cache and I'm even more proud than ever that it's still going well and getting visits! Thanks to everyone that visits it for leaving some more information and adding to the history :-)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Update in March 2015 - With more than 200 successful visits to this cache (and more than 15 years after I first placed it), I'm still very pleased each time I hear of a new discovery. Congratulations to all who found this cache, and I wish success to all those who set out to search for it!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Update in August 2015 - Happy to find my historical cache in good shape! Hidden just where I left it in 2001. I'm sure many treasures have come and gone in that time. Congratulations to the many people who found it in the past years, and good luck to those who find it in the coming years!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A tip to save money on the gondola: For those visiting the area between 1st May to 31st October and staying in a hotel, a Gstaad Easy Access card (http://www.gstaad.ch/en/gstaad/tourist-office/easyaccess-card/gstaad-easyaccess-card.html) gives you three days of unlimited local transport, including the Wispile gondola, for CHF39 per person. In summer, the normal return price for this gondola is CHF45. It's one of the very rare bargains in this part of Switzerland :-)&lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>The cache is a few steps downhill from the path, behind and at the base of the pair of pine trees. It is under many low branches and partially covered by pine needles. </groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1365041922"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-02T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4982610">GeoGrillen</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Nun haben wir endlich diesen 2001er Cache besucht und das LB signiert. Die Seilbahn hat noch Pause und somit wurde der Anmarsch schon etwas weit und 50m vor der Dose ging auch noch ein Gewitter los.
Aber was tut man nicht alles für so einen gut erhalteten Oldy.
Danke fürs Legen und Pflegen sagen die GeoGrillen</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364670957"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-27T14:18:58</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="16561728">CathV</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Une semaine de vacances, il faut bien ça pour aller au 1er Méga in Italy ??. Bien entendu, le voyage se fait avec des détours en Suisse pour des webcams et des SI entre autres.

Aujourd’hui, l’objectif GC est la plus vieille cache de Suisse. Cette oldest se mérite, surtout lorsque le téléphérique est à l’arrêt et qu’il faut tout monter à pied. Nous y consacrons une grande partie de la journée mais elle est trouvée ??

Les logbooks sont signés de nos pseudos ou du nom de notre équipe : DTX.

Merci pour la pose et l’entretien de ces caches !
Merci Jesse Grimes pour la cache [:D]

Google traduction
Eine Woche Urlaub ist genau das Richtige, um am ersten Mega in Italien teilzunehmen ??. Natürlich beinhaltet die Reise auch Abstecher in die Schweiz für Webcams und SIs und vieles mehr.

Heute suchen wir den ältesten Cache der Schweiz. Diesen ältesten Cache haben wir uns redlich verdient, besonders wenn die Seilbahn außer Betrieb ist und man den ganzen Weg zu Fuß zurücklegen muss. Wir haben einen Großteil des Tages dafür geopfert, aber wir haben ihn gefunden ??

Die Logbücher sind mit unseren Benutzernamen oder unserem Teamnamen DTX signiert.

Vielen Dank fürs Platzieren und Pflegen dieser Caches!

Vielen Dank an Jesse Grimes für den Cache [:D]








</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363999322"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-25T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="128689">tecnics</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">One of the goals of our trip to Switzerland was to come and find the country’s very first cache. We really enjoyed the hike, and the scenery is truly incredible. We had a fantastic time along the trail and taking in the spectacular Swiss Alpine views.
The chairlift was not operating, so we had to switch to plan B and do the hike on foot, but it was absolutely worth it. An amazing experience in a wonderful setting.
We are also taking home a great collection of photos that we have already set as our computer wallpapers, so that from time to time we can “teleport” ourselves from Barcelona, our hometown, back to these breathtaking Swiss landscapes. Many thanks for the cache! </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363152945"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-24T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="21302979">Zuiderkruis63</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">******** Mei 2026 ********

Wat een dag… vandaag eindelijk de oudste cache van Switzerland mogen doen, en wat voor één. De bedoeling was om met de skylift omhoog te gaan, maar juist vandaag werkte die niet. Even slikken dus… maar opgeven? Geen moment aan gedacht. Auto geparkeerd op de coördinaten uit de listing en dan gewoon beginnen aan de klim omhoog.

Het was warm, héél warm zelfs, en de zon maakte het soms behoorlijk pittig. Maar stap voor stap werd de tocht alleen maar mooier. De paden waren verrassend goed en deden me denken aan mijn avontuur bij Scotland First, al waren de routes hier nog aangenamer om te lopen.

Onderweg kwam ik meerdere koeien tegen met die enorme typisch Zwitserse bellen om hun nek. Het geluid galmde prachtig door de bergen en gaf de tocht echt dat authentieke Zwitserse gevoel. Samen met de frisse berglucht, de groene hellingen en de indrukwekkende omgeving maakte dat het plaatje compleet.

En dan die uitzichten… werkelijk adembenemend. Hoe hoger ik kwam, hoe indrukwekkender het landschap werd. Bergen, natuur en stilte om je heen — momenten waarop je automatisch even stopt om alles in je op te nemen. Daar doe je het uiteindelijk voor.

De laatste meters voelden zwaar door de warmte, maar tegelijk gaf het enorm veel voldoening om door te zetten. En dan eindelijk aankomen bij deze historische cache… wat een prachtig gevoel om hier mijn naam in het logboekje achter te mogen laten. Dat moment maakte alle inspanning meer dan waard.

Een uitdagende, warme maar vooral onvergetelijke dag waar ik met enorm veel plezier op terugkijk. En natuurlijk een FAVO in 🌻</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363198967"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-23T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="13743385">danjoa</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Vom Übernachtungsplatz ging es zum Parkplatz an der Gondel 
Diese fuhr jedoch nicht, also müssten wir laufen, gut das die Bergschuhe dabei waren. 


Danke für diesen altehrwürdigen Cache, gerne lasse ich eine blaue Schleife zurück.



Einen Gruss 

**danjoa**


aus Ahlem (Hannover, Germany 🇩🇪)</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="34.5618" lon="38.2593"><time>2007-08-29T00:00:00</time><name>GC15MTE</name><desc>Zenobia's Reward by Camel Master</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC15MTE</url><urlname>Zenobia's Reward</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="681365" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Zenobia's Reward</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Camel Master</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="1210477">Camel Master</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="56" inc="0">Medium hike (1 km–10 km)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="40" inc="1">Stealth required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="33" inc="1">Motorcycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="35" inc="1">Off-road vehicles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="10" inc="0">Difficult climb</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="18" inc="1">Dangerous animals</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Syria</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>A traditional cache near to the ruins of Palmyra.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>Palmyra, or Tadmor in Arabic, is in the heart of the Syrian desert.
It is often described as the Bride of the Desert. It boasts
magnificent ruins from the time of the reign of Queen Zenobia who
ruled over a Kingdom on the edge of the Roman empire. Overseeing
the 1800 year old ruins is a 6th Century Arab citadel built on a
mountain. Several paths lead up from the ruins to the citadel and
along one of them the cache has been hidden. The cache consists of
a lunchbox camouflaged by being wrapped in a grey sock. Next to a
notebook and pencil, it initially contained:
&lt;div style="margin-left: 2em"&gt;• A small booklet on “Good luck”&lt;br&gt;
• A miniature utility tool&lt;br&gt;
• A camel fridge magnet&lt;br&gt;
• A miniature “karma” bowl woven by Bedouin women in Oman&lt;/div&gt;
The location of the cache provides a great overview over the old
and the modern city of Palmyra. Sitting on the nearby rocks during
sunset is an experience never to be forgotten. This also provides
the opportunity to search for the cache without being observed.
Many local geomuggles are convinced that untold riches are still to
be found in the ruins. If anyone suspects that something is hidden
at the cache site, the cache is certain to be raided. Therefore
please do not take any local drivers or guides along while
searching for the cache; this will certainly help its longevity!
&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size="1"&gt;Small note on cache maintenance: Although we live
in Dubai, we regularly visit Syria. We have also taken into
confidence a very good friend of ours who lives in Palmyra very
close to the cache site, He will be able to check on the cache on a
moment’s notice if any difficulties are reported.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Hidden between two rocks. Visible while walking up the hill.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1114824874"><groundspeak:date>2022-07-31T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4457351">Feluko</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Sad to see that the cache was archived. I believe, there's a chance it's still there. In April this year, I managed to find the nearby geocache "Bel Shamin" (GC20797) as the first cacher in over 10 years that had survived without a scratch here in Palmyra! Sadly, we did not have a lot of time when we were here, so I couldn't attempt this one. Maybe another cacher can try finding it in some time. I have also placed 3 new caches in Syria (GC9R30Q, GC9RNEA, GC9RNDA), but it would be good if some of the older caches would survive too.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1092729559"><groundspeak:date>2022-04-27T06:35:02</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1210477">Camel Master</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">It is with great sadness that I have to archive this cache. One day, hopefully soon, it will be possible to hide and search for geocaches in this beautiful country.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1087981489"><groundspeak:date>2022-04-10T21:10:34</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Unknown</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="18990911">Knagur Green</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Due to the length of time the caches in Syria have been unavailable and what has happened in the country , it is expected that most/all of the caches will have gone missing . The caches will be unlocked once the CO has provided information that the cache has been replaced and is ready to be found again</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="199877818"><groundspeak:date>2011-11-20T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="249784">Torgut</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I arrived yesterday and still had time for a short stroll in the site but for some reason I couldn't open the listing in my mobile phone (corrupted data I guess) so I had to check it out in the evening. Today it was easy. One of two caches I found in Palmyra and the only ones in Syria. I was probably the only foreigner in Palmyra, and I don't mean the site but the city. Thanks for the cache and greetings from Portugal.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="158821563"><groundspeak:date>2011-05-02T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2973606">napjunkie</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Our last cache in Syria!  Missed trying for this at sunset, so at 5:45 am I made the trek from the Zenobia Cham.  Logged it at 6:30.  Be careful how to approach this -- the city wall can be a problem.  Unfortunately the view this morning wasn't good because of haze and dust in the air.  Took a heart inscribed in Arabic, left a Guardians of the Wild pin.  TFTC!!!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="24.345317" lon="120.6233"><time>2002-03-28T00:00:00</time><name>GC469A</name><desc>Mom by rjt</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC469A</url><urlname>Mom</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Virtual Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="18074" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Mom</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>rjt</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="39727">rjt</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Virtual Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Virtual</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="0">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="2" inc="1">Access/parking fee</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="26" inc="1">Public transportation nearby</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Taiwan</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>It's Chinese Holy Mom's Home.
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>You can take a train then walk here. Go inside the Temple. To verify your find, please post photos of anywhere of the temple (including your GPSr) you took.&lt;br /&gt;
In center lunar March ,this town is crowded. You can see how super Mom's attraction.&lt;br /&gt;
If you visit here, don't forget to visit the golden Mom statue in the bottom floor. The entrance is situated at the side of the square.
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1358276926"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1456004">trappersduo</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We reizen per fiets door Taiwan en belandden op 1 mei in Dajia. Het jaarfeest van de zeegodin Mazu. Prachtige tempel! En wat een gezellige drukte. Een bezoek meer dan waard. En dan ook nog deze virtuele kunnen loggen! 🥳</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1357048392"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-25T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="26940951">Le20</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Vandaag vanuit Taipei de HSR gepakt richting Taichung om vervolgens een andere trein te pakken naar Dajia. Het doel is natuurlijk deze oude cache in Taiwan. Na een korte wandeling kom ik bij de virtual aan. Het is behoorlijk druk en er is van alles te zien. Na even rond te hebben gekeken natuurlijk ook de benodigde foto's gemaakt. Bedankt voor het laten zien van deze plek!

Today I took the HSR from Taipei to Taichung and then caught another train to Dajia. The goal, of course, is this old cache in Taiwan. After a short walk, I arrived at the virtual cache. It was pretty crowded and there was plenty to see. After looking around for a bit, I took the required photos, of course. Thanks for showing me this place!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1356237590"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-20T18:26:47</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1547165">tbly</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Amazing temple with many visitors. Took an unobtrusive photo inside, including todays signed TR ticket. Thank you for bringing me here to the oldest active geocache in Taiwan.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1350960605"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-24T12:50:52</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3499017">BrennanT</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Out on a crazy trip with Norshley, MuskieMouse, cc cache! and myself BrennanT. I think we are going to 15 different countries grabbing caches along the way. Hoping to grab as many webcams as we can. Thanks to all the CO’s for placing and maintaining these caches. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1350996446"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-24T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="95447">Norshley</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">The Crafty Canadians team of cc Cache!, brennanT, MuskieMouse, and myself are on an epic tour of the Pacific Rim, visiting 14 countries over 3 weeks and are having a blast. The Chinese leg of our trip includes Hong Kong, China, Macau, and Taiwan, with a brief stopover in Philippines. 

Found the oldie cache on Mar 24, 2026 at 12:46. Visited the temple and took our photo there. 
Thanks to rjt for the cache hide.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="38.847167" lon="73.41145"><time>2007-10-05T00:00:00</time><name>GC169JR</name><desc>Lake Kara Kul,Tajikistan by Hedenhös and Fnöske</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC169JR</url><urlname>Lake Kara Kul,Tajikistan</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="700378" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Lake Kara Kul,Tajikistan</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Hedenhös and Fnöske</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="925882">Hedenhös</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="10" inc="1">Difficult climb</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="23" inc="1">Dangerous area</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="21" inc="1">Cliff/falling rocks</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>3</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Tajikistan</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;font color="#0000FF" size="4"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Lake Kara Kul&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face="Verdana"&gt;&lt;img height="80" alt="" src=
"http://img.geocaching.com/cache/a1dd945a-c97b-499c-929b-c6cfb614be03.jpg"
width="160" border="1" /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face="Verdana"&gt;This cache is one of the first in
Tajikistan.&lt;br /&gt;
The box is hidden at an altitude of 4890 meters (16300 feet) (MSL),
southeast of Lake Kara-Kul, on the mountain Ortobos as belongs to
Pamir Mountains.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face="Verdana"&gt;&lt;img height="335" alt="" src=
"http://img.geocaching.com/cache/bfc50d20-5cee-449e-8ff7-4fc2d9ce1513.jpg"
width="500" border="1" /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;font size="2"&gt;View over Lake Kara-Kul&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face="Verdana"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Kara-Kul&lt;/strong&gt; is a 25-kilometer
(16-mile) diameter lake, which lies at an altitude of 3,900
meters.&lt;br /&gt;
The lake lies within a circular depression interpreted as a
metiorite impact with a rim diameter of 45 kilometers (28 miles).
The impact event ocurred less than 5 million years ago. The
Kara-Kul impact structure remained unidentified until it was
discovered though studies of imagery taken from space.&lt;br /&gt;
Kara-Kul is almost 20 meters deep on the east side and 230 meter
deep on west side. It has no drainage outlet.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img height="323" alt="" src=
"http://img.geocaching.com/cache/7bf969d0-4c1b-4d00-b724-b69c17f26a11.jpg"
width="500" border="1" /&gt;&lt;font face="Verdana"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;font size="2"&gt;Settlement near mountain Ortobos&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The cache includes notebook, pencil, geocacheinformation in english
and russian and some things to change.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;a href="http://s02.flagcounter.com/more/CXpU"&gt;&lt;img src=
"http://s02.flagcounter.com/count/CXpU/bg=FFFFFF/txt=000000/border=CCCCCC/columns=4/maxflags=248/viewers=0/labels=1/pageviews=1/"
alt="free counters" border="0" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Under the biggest stone.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1238306167"><groundspeak:date>2024-06-04T07:19:24</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="49861788">PJohnson1982</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">As a tourist, this was super cool!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1237634264"><groundspeak:date>2024-06-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="15727338">Gillou78150</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thanks for the good idea</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1125504727"><groundspeak:date>2022-09-12T21:06:37</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="39537860">Alex_pro2010</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">H</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1083569011"><groundspeak:date>2022-03-19T23:04:45</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="39580582">troutquest</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Very nice</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="880906018"><groundspeak:date>2019-09-08T16:35:17</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="22508249">neijah</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found that cache „by accident“ on our hike to Peak Urtabuz. What a surprise to find a geocache on my first 5000m peak. It was an amazing feeling to reach the top and enjoy the view on Lake Karakol. Thank you very much for the cache! </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="-3.09948333333333" lon="37.378"><time>2002-08-21T00:00:00</time><name>GC8752</name><desc>Above the Clouds by Poohbear</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC8752</url><urlname>Above the Clouds</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="34642" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Above the Clouds</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Poohbear</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="22941">poohbear</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="42" inc="1">Needs maintenance</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>4.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Tanzania</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>On Mt. Kilimanjaro in Tanzania, Africa. This Geocache is near the Barafu Camsite on the way to the summit</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>Container is a small 1/2 liter jar with a few items.</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Just north of the highest campsite. Located on the western edge of the cliff. If you have come this far, there should be no problem finding the cache.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1345441542"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-18T16:52:30</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="27075419">Guggäli</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Wow… Das war ein Abenteuer! Auf der Lemosho-Route gestern den Gipfel „the roof of africa“ erreicht! Ein tolles Abenteuer mit unvergesslichen Erlebnissen. Natürlich hier den „Stein“ gemäss Hint des Vorloggers besucht und eingeschrieben. Vielen Dank!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1346094039"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-02T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6586096">Moppihundwow</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">For many years I dreamed of climbing this magnificent mountain. Now my wife and I have finally done it. I thank all the guides and porters who helped us reach this goal. Thank you for the cache.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1349939023"><groundspeak:date>2026-01-30T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2377218">Cycle73</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">After I reached the Barafu camp on 4673m and took the photo at the sign, I looked for the container as shown in the maintenance log 11.10.2025 but didn’t find it. The next day after I came back to the camp from the final hike to the Uhuru Peak, I looked again with one of the guides, but still nothing.
So, I decided to log this cache as a found for the moment, with a photo from the sign as proof that I was really there. Leaving back a favorit point to honor this cache.
TFTC!
Cycle73
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1356608839"><groundspeak:date>2026-01-03T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4167442">Snoopy.go</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">From December 30, 2025, to January 5, 2026, I climbed Kilimanjaro via the Machame Route.
On the fifth day, we are arrived Barafu Camp.... the Base Camp!

Thanks for this cache.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1330054683"><groundspeak:date>2025-10-11T14:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="7384186">wayn0</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">After reading in previous logs that the container recently lived 135m away from the listed coordinates and is currently rather feral, I decided to add a container AT the listed coordinates which is near the camp sign. The container will handle any weather. See spoiler image. Now it’s time for a sleep before heading up to the summit! Thanks for the cache. 
Cheers 
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="18.588683" lon="98.487367"><time>2002-09-24T00:00:00</time><name>GC932A</name><desc>Thailand's Highest Point by Steve (Licorice)</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC932A</url><urlname>Thailand's Highest Point</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Virtual Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="37674" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Thailand's Highest Point</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Steve (Licorice)</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="28262">Licorice</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Virtual Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Virtual</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="30" inc="1">Picnic tables nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="26" inc="1">Public transportation nearby</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Thailand</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>This virtual cache is located in Thailand's Doi Inthanon National Park, southwest of Chiang Mai and is the highest point in Thailand.
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;img src="http://www.geckobeach.com/GPS/licorice20.jpg" width="180" height="240" hspace="5" align="right" /&gt;To log a find for this virtual cache, locate the sign that is labelled "The Highest Spot in Thailand", which can be found using the coordinates above. Have someone take a picture of you holding your GPS infront of the sign with both the coordinates and elevation showing on the sign behind you and then upload the picture with your cache log. The picture to the right shows myself and my GPS taking a reading at the sign.
&lt;p&gt;The coordinates on the sign were determined prior to the removal of selective availability, so they are slightly off. Also take note of the elevation shown on the sign and the precision used and compare it to your altitude reading on your GPS! For those that are interested, there is an official geological survey maker about 30 m up the trail behind the sign that is the "real" highest point.&lt;br clear="all" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>To visit this park without a tour group, hire a red tuk-tuk from Chaing Mai and make sure to visit some of the other sights in this fantasic park.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1359613681"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-07T22:32:05</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="19713411">stellabb77</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1356218406"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-20T14:28:17</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8677911">rubiezone</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">TFTC!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1356010410"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-19T19:21:17</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2470128">jogi01</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Wir hatten heute eine geführte Tour hierher. 
Wunderschön hier und nebenbei noch diesen Cache besucht.
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1355112205"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-14T12:12:23</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="13258707">Ida 2015</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thank you for the cache </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1355109977"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-14T10:59:48</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3006333">Arthur 2010</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thanks for the nice geocache </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="6.976483" lon="0.570133"><time>2012-07-15T00:00:00</time><name>GC3QHE2</name><desc>Kpalimé Cascade by meljean</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC3QHE2</url><urlname>Kpalimé Cascade</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="3061409" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Kpalimé Cascade</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>meljean</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="268559">meljean</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="9" inc="1">Significant hike</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Togo</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>This cache is at the top of a beautiful mountain waterfall. From Kpalime, head west past the Village de la Lumiere Blind Center (stop on your way if you like shopping; there's a lovely botique inside), and continue on up the mountain and through a small mountain village to the trailhead. The ten minute hike is moderately steep in places, and you'll be climbing to the top of the waterfall.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>Ce cache est au sommet d'une cascade magnifique dans les montagnes. Conduisez à l'ouest de Kpalimé, passez le Village de la Lumière Centre des Aveugles  (arrêtez sur votre chemin si vous aimez le shopping, il ya une belle boutique dedans), et continuez sur la route au montagne et au travers d'un petit village de montagne. L'excursion de dix minutes est peu raide, et vous allez grimper vers le sommet de la cascade.</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Look closer at the rock wall</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1335933477"><groundspeak:date>2025-11-25T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2892866">Lustiger Koala</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false"> Today I went north (a bit) for some caches. Turned out to take far longer than expected. And to include quite a bit hiking at high temperatures. So I ended up around 6pm in my hotel to finish the day with my first beer on my Westarfrica-trip: I started in Ghana and will continue tomorrow direction Benin.
After the first cache (cascade de Wome) I continued to the Missahöhe... Liked the place a lot. The Kpalime Cascade was until today not known by my driver: So we were gently 'forced' at the checkpoint to hire a guide. 5000 CFA including entrance seems to be a bit much for local prices. But still ok... Loved the many butterflies at this cascade. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1334642641"><groundspeak:date>2025-11-15T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Unknown</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="268559">meljean</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Cache replaced. Enjoy! </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1263456863"><groundspeak:date>2024-10-03T07:58:22</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2858393">msi999</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">My first in Togo! Amazing place..😎
TFTC

PS Cache box is broken, logbook eaten by someone, needs maintenance!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1212859038"><groundspeak:date>2024-01-18T17:36:07</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5847639">madcow2</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Two nights at campement de kloto and a walk round the village learning about lots of plants, buying a batik, and a visit to the waterfall. Very happy to get a Togo cache on my tour of west Africa.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1152020503"><groundspeak:date>2023-03-05T12:10:02</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Unknown</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="25137651">LLcoolF</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Dieser Geocacher hat gemeldet, dass der Behälter beschädigt ist.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="-23.627116666666666" lon="-178.89683333333335"><time>2001-10-12T00:00:00</time><name>GC2EA3</name><desc>North Minerva Reef by Klaymen</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC2EA3</url><urlname>North Minerva Reef</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Virtual Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="11939" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>North Minerva Reef</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Klaymen</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="32975">klaymen</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Virtual Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Virtual</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="4" inc="1">Boat required</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Tonga</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Ship wreck to discover. Between Tonga and New Zealand.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>Your mission is to name the wreck, 50 mtrs to the north of this safe anchourage point of North Minerva. 
When you find this name, dont mention it in the log, send klaymen an e-mail.
The wreck lies on the lagoon side of the reef with the bow section remaining intact. The name is easy to read at low tide. This reef dries to only .9 of a metre at low tide.</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1343178557"><groundspeak:date>2026-01-28T08:17:57</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="21231650">CollectorOfThings</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We are on route to New Zealand from Tonga. 
So close to the GZ
Answer sent to the CO</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1292384983"><groundspeak:date>2025-04-04T00:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="46295391">Superflymarco</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Answers sent some time ago but no response as to being the correct ones yet so fingers crossed 🤞🏼

TFTVC ✌🏼😉💙🏴󠁧󠁢󠁳󠁣󠁴󠁿

When I went in the water I nearly died (dramatic much !) 🤣

Water went into my breathing pipe/tube and I swallowed it and I went into panic mode and that was it for me …. 

Anyway this one was very very creative and possibly one of the best virtual caches I’ve came across out there so far 👏🏼👏🏼👏🏼
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1082632122"><groundspeak:date>2022-03-14T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="13949349">kribnkrew</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Greetings traveling cachers,
Working with a team on a Global Geocache Challenge, GC8J6GM. It requires you or team to get 200 geocache passport photos from around the world. These passport pics were created by the CO specifically for this challenge. Best solved with help from other cachers. Tonga is one of the countries still needed.
Would appreciate if a fellow geocacher would please go onto the cache page for GC8J6GM and send me a photo of the passport and the number below it? The passport photo displays automatically for the country you are logging in from. Or drop the photo with a note in the challenge cache logs.
If you are interested in solving or following, I can share a Google doc.
Thanks in advance COs and cachers
Kribnkrew</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1063592390"><groundspeak:date>2021-10-21T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4616025">bella at waggy</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">An amazing spot that one of the team managed to see.  At high tide its nowhere to be seen but at low tide its there and protection and rest provided. TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1060416648"><groundspeak:date>2021-10-21T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="29718081">WingsToSoar</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Great spot to anchor overnight and explore.
Introduced to this via friend and looks like fun.
Thanks</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="37.138317" lon="9.686167"><time>2002-07-26T00:00:00</time><name>GC75FA</name><desc>ICHKEUL by Franck, then Landy-Team, now adopted by TeamTunis</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC75FA</url><urlname>ICHKEUL</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="30202" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>ICHKEUL</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Franck, then Landy-Team, now adopted by TeamTunis</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="914016">TeamTunis</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="1">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="40" inc="1">Stealth required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="37" inc="1">Horses</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="21" inc="1">Cliff/falling rocks</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="18" inc="1">Dangerous animals</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Tunisia</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Ichkeul lake is located near Binzerte belonging to the Ichkeul National Park, a magical sanctuary for birds, and also Tunisia's only water buffalo herd.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>The cache is inside the National Park ( entrance is free but closing time is 6 PM).  It is half way to the Ichkeul Summi, and the cache hiding place is visible from the track.

You will have a beautiful view on the lake (this lake is unusual in that it's salinity (saltiness) changes during the year as water flows in and out).</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>behind a stone in a triangular hole / small cave.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1365025241"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-21T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="7311477">Sternenstaub29</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Für eine Woche ging es für uns, meinen Dima 11 und mich, nach Tunesien. Zwar waren wir beide schonmal vor etwa 30 Jahren hier, aber die Erinnerungen waren verblasst und Geocaching gab es damals auch noch nicht. An allen Tagen der Woche haben wir interessante Touren unternommen: nach Tunis, Carthago, Sidi Bou Said, Cap Bon, El Jem usw.. Unsere Highlights waren der Besuch am nördlichsten Punkt Afrikas und die zweitägige Wüstentour in die Sahara mit Übernachtung im Berbercamp. So haben wir viele schöne Orte im Land entdecken können. Neben den Sehenswürdigkeiten interessieren und auch immer das Leben der Menschen und die lokale Küche. Schade, dass die oft sehr schöne Natur durch den vielen umherliegenden Müll geschädigt wird. Da wäre mehr Bewusstsein der Bevölkerung für ihr Land wünschenswert. Unterwegs konnten wir auch einige Caches suchen und finden. Dieser war einer davon. 🙂

**Danke** fürs Verstecken und Erstellen der Caches und viele Grüße aus Deutschland von Sternenstaub29!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364000492"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-21T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4258256">Dima 11</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">.
**gefunden**

Es ging für mich und meiner Sternenstaub29 endlich mal wieder auf Urlaus - Reise.
Es geht nach Tunesien und wir besuchten vieles im ganzen Land.
Heute sind wir hier auf Tour und konnten den ein oder anderen Cache 
noch besuchen und sigieren und auch so einige schöne Bilder aufnehmen.
So war auch dieser Cache mit dabei, den wir gut finden konnten.


**D** a n k e an die **O** wner für die **C** aches und das **H** erlocken,
denn ohne **S** ie wäre es nicht so ein toller **T** ag geworden, 
**A** lso achtet ihre **A** rbeit , denn ohne **O** wner keine **C** aches, und ohne **C** aches kein **G** eocaching
sagt mit **G** rüßen aus **S** chwedt, der
