</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1350984425"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-21T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1185829">kosovaci</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Zajímavé a moc pěkné místo. Děkuji za kešulku</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1350979248"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-21T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="46381717">Kosovák99</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Během krátkého prodlouženého víkendu v Tunisku jsme se, kromě několika výletů, snažili odlovit i pár kesek. Tato byla jednou z nich. Díky 😊</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1341510722"><groundspeak:date>2026-01-03T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="868022">tmob</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We visited this cache during our trip to Tunisia.
Eight amazing days during which we visited many interesting locations and found a bunch of caches!

**Day #8 - Tunis -&gt; Ichkeul National Park -&gt; Cap Angela -&gt; Bizerta -&gt; Tunis**

Today was our last day in Tunisia! We left Tunis in the morning, drove towards Ichkeul National Park, and later to Cap Angela, the northernmost point of Africa! We enjoyed a walk around Bizerte in the late afternoon, and later we drove back to Tunis, where we took a late-night flight back home!

When we arrived at the park gate, we were greeted by the guard who told us that we had to have authorization to visit the park. I asked if it was possible to buy the authorization there and the gate magically opened! [:D]. We paid 10 dinars per adult (20 dinars total); kids were free. We spoke with him in French, which I think helped us to pay only 10 dinars.

We enjoyed the park, the walk, and the views! Just like us, several other (Tunisian) families were there enjoying the park!

Thanks for this one...
Greetings from Portugal.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="40.186483333333335" lon="29.05755"><time>2002-08-22T00:00:00</time><name>GC8323</name><desc>The Ottoman by gpsturk</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC8323</url><urlname>The Ottoman</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Virtual Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="33571" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>The Ottoman</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>gpsturk</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="68829">gpsturk</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Virtual Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Virtual</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Türkiye</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>A historical place, have car-park and easy to reach.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>Sultan Orhan
Sultan Orhan was a great organizer and the second ruler of the Ottoman Empire. During his reign, Bursa was captured from Byzantines. Few years later Ottomans crossed into Europe and the first Ottoman silver coin minted. He died in Bursa. Near his tomb, there is another tomb which belongs to Sultan Orhans' father (Founder of The Ottoman Empire). The virtual cache is to find the info tab which has the name, birth and death dates of the owner of the tomb. E-mail the answers to me (no Internet "finds") You can also visit the historical clock-tower and ballistas at the back of the tombs. There are cafes and a restaurant next to them. Join the great view of Bursa from there.</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Take a photo of Bursa from there. Beacuse it lays under your feet.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364828130"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2696865">kennyovi</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">[CZ] Behem meho erasmu v Bulharsku jsme si s kamarady udelali vylet do Turecka a dnes navstivili Burgu. Diky za virtualku.

[EN] During my Erasmus exchange in Bulgaria, my friends and I took a trip to Turkey and visited Bursa today. Thanks for the virtual cache.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1361638367"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-17T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3731622">MAXZ1309</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Visited Bursa today and of course we completed this cache. Thanks for the cache and greetings from Spain</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1361838757"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-15T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="16134194">Carp92</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Wir schauen uns hier einiges an und werden den ein oder anderen Geocache auch besuchen. 

Sorry für den kurzen Log, aber meine Freizeit is sehr rar. So nutze ich die Zeit viel zuerleben😎

Danke an gpsturk fürs Legen und Pflegen der Dose.
15. Mai 2026

DfdC mit TKD25 und fifi09 

🇩🇪🇨🇿🇦🇹🇮🇹🇵🇱🇱🇹🇱🇻🇪🇪🇫🇮🇷🇺🇦🇽🇸🇪🇩🇰🇸🇮🇭🇷🇱🇺🇳🇱🇧🇪🇸🇰🇸🇳🇬🇲🇵🇹🇲🇪🇦🇱🇬🇷🇭🇺🇫🇷🇨🇭🇱🇮🇲🇰🇧🇦🇷🇸🇲🇹🇨🇾🇮🇱🇵🇸🇪🇦🇬🇮🇲🇦🇪🇭🇬🇧🇮🇸</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360809390"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-14T11:38:40</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="55342136">gkhnlhn</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Nice place 😊 </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360450828"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-11T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="55224771">Karakedi_1404</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Verilen bir ödev için gelmiştim ve gelişken bunu da yapayım dedim, aynı zamanda restoran da çok lezzetliydi! Türbe ise büyüleyiciydi!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="40.252633" lon="58.439433"><time>2010-02-01T00:00:00</time><name>GC23HNZ</name><desc>The Door to Hell by Mioritics</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC23HNZ</url><urlname>The Door to Hell</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Earthcache</type><groundspeak:cache id="1542313" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>The Door to Hell</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Mioritics</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="266274">Mioritics</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Earthcache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Not chosen</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="27" inc="0">Drinking water nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="33" inc="1">Motorcycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="21" inc="1">Cliff/falling rocks</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Turkmenistan</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>A burning crater near Darvaza, Turkmenistan, is called "The Door to
Hell" by the locals.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>Darvaza and the burning gas crater are located in the central area
of Turkmenistan, about 260 km north of Turkmenistan&amp;rsquo;s capital
city Ashgabat.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;img src=
"http://img.geocaching.com/cache/f1dbe938-8d33-4c74-ad12-a5e0177b9b99.jpg" /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
It was during rule of Soviet Russia, back in 1971 when geologists
were conducting gas drilling in Kara-Kum desert and discovered an
underground chamber close to the village of Darvaza. The discovery
of the chamber was accidental and resulted in drilling rig
collapsing, leaving giant gas crater filled with poisonous gases
exposed to the world outside. The concentration of gases within the
crater was high so nobody dared to go down there. It was then when
someone came with an idea to light the gas in the crater on fire so
as to burn it before the poisonous fumes engulf the nearby town of
Darvaza.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The geologists thought the idea of burning the gas was smart and
went ahead with lighting the crater on fire. As it turns out, the
supply of quality natural gas below the crater is near infinite as
the crater&amp;rsquo;s been burning since. The gas crater in Darvaza is
still burning and has been since 1971 without interruption. No one
can even imagine how much quality natural gas was burnt throughout
the 38 years of the crater being on fire. No one can estimate how
much more gas there still is. When they first lit the gas crater on
fire, they thought the fire would go out after a few days.
It&amp;rsquo;s been decades and the gas crater is burning just as it
did the day it was first lit.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;img src=
"http://img.geocaching.com/cache/db2a6ebb-bc82-4ae4-9465-ed97fec56e6a.jpg" /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
WARNING! Don't go to close and don't stay to much near the crater
because of the almost unbreakable temperature&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
To log this Earth Cache&lt;br /&gt;
1. Take a photo of yourself and your GPS near to the crater.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Answer by email the following questions&lt;br /&gt;
2. What is the approximate diameter and the depth of the
crater?&lt;br /&gt;
3. How meters long is the biggest flame you can see?&lt;br /&gt;
4. How big is the area around the crater without vegetation?</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1360090612"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-04T08:51:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="988771">DOBRODRUH.cz</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">#46382, 2026-05-04 at 06:51, Thanks fór the earthcache. We have spent the night by the crater in a yurt. What an experience!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360406473"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-03T18:20:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="453038">dbox</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Before dinner, we took a walk to the nearby caches and the crater. Very interesting area, especially at night...[:D]!

Thanks to Mioritics for cache #16605 (8/8)
dbox.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360558162"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-03T16:13:50</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1511682">Pädeldreter</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Here we are. At one of the main reasons for our tour. Amazing.
Our first attempt fell through because of COVID. Then we had other plans. But now it’s finally worked out. 

It feels great, even though all we did was come here.

Thanks and regards
**die Pädeldreter**</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360735290"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-03T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2599829">Schlurie</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">The Trip to Turkmenistan was planed about 7 years ago. But different reasons maked it Not possible. 
Now together with dBox and Pädeltreter it hapend.
What a Great Place </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1359004725"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-03T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2993392">pinya3</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We found it during our trip across Turkmenistan, Uzbekistan, and Tajikistan.  We arrived in Turkmenistan five days ago and visited Ashgabat, the Yangikala Canyon, Nohur, and then returned to the city.
Today we slept in Darvaza. What a strange and awesome place!! 

By now we are very satisfied with the trip, but we can not help but be very upset with the authorities of this country because of how poorly maintained the roads outside the capital are and how poor the villages are! This is a clear example of the mismanagement of a tyrannical dictatorship. 
TFTC. 
Greetings from Barcelona.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="0.436967" lon="30.395067"><time>2005-02-07T00:00:00</time><name>GCMTCR</name><desc>Kibale National Park, Uganda by markmacallister</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCMTCR</url><urlname>Kibale National Park, Uganda</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="209121" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Kibale National Park, Uganda</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>markmacallister</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="294092">markmacallister</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="31" inc="1">Camping nearby</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Uganda</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>This cache is placed in the Kibale National Park in western Uganda. It is not in the Park proper--as geocachers might inadvertently interfere with chimp populations in the forest--but it instead in a popular part of that area.
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>Once you arrive at the cache coordinates, simply climb the stairs and proceed indoors. The cache is a basic RubberMaid container, and holds a logbook, some small toys, and photos of my children. If you have trouble locating the cache, please ask one of the other rangers for assistance.
&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size="1"&gt;Small note on cache maintenance: I have made arrangements with the wildlife rangers at Kibale NP to maintain this cache. Also, I and/or colleagues of mine, will return to Kibale National Park at least once a year to maintain the cache.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Watch the hatches!</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1216248069"><groundspeak:date>2024-02-15T14:39:38</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="294092">markmacallister</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Cache has been reported missing in last couple log entries and thus may have (inadvertently?) been removed from its placement.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1216201210"><groundspeak:date>2024-02-13T00:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="23019896">PiratenLP</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Chimpanzee Tracking was one of the most interesting things we have done in Uganda so far 😊
Following them around in the forest, seeing them feeding, resting, communicating - an experience we will never forget. Thanks to the rangers! 😊
Photolog as physical cache could not be found. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1217396671"><groundspeak:date>2024-02-11T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="38178217">Ceci9</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Heute war ich hier und bin total begeistert. Ich erlaube mir wie die Vorgänger zu loggen, da trotz Hilfeanfrage nichts gefunden wurde. 
Danke und Gruss aus der Schweiz</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1213953642"><groundspeak:date>2024-01-28T19:23:34</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5575412">Fiez</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Offensichtlich sind die Caches hier mehrheitlich nicht vorhanden und die „Finder“ logen per Foto.
Auch wir haben hier nichts gefunden und erlauben uns einen Foto-Log.
TFTC!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1213815243"><groundspeak:date>2024-01-28T12:49:38</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="27752668">Ramsinchen</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Nicht gefunden, aber ich erlaube mir trotzdem mich ins Logbuch zu verewigen.
TFTC </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="50.429433333333336" lon="30.5614"><time>2002-02-02T00:00:00</time><name>GC36C6</name><desc>WWII by mmacro</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC36C6</url><urlname>WWII</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Virtual Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="14022" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>WWII</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>mmacro</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="39053">mmacro</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Virtual Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Virtual</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Ukraine</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
Very easy cache to find. A wonderful place to spend a half day or a day, but it will have a great impact on you.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>To claim the find please attach a photo of the location or e-mail me what is on the ceiling of the top dome of the exhibit.
&lt;P&gt;
This is a site shown to me by my wife. Her grandfather died during WWII fighting the Germans and this is a place dedicated to all those who have fought in defense of their country.&lt;br&gt;
I would really recommend having a translator for here. There is so much to understand, or the impact and importance of some of the details will be lost on you.
&lt;P&gt;
After seeing this place I had to spend some time digesting what I saw and what it means. The Ukrainians don't sugar coat or romanticize their history. It's rather brutal and up front.&lt;br&gt;
I plan on adding some real caches as soon as I can get back.
&lt;P&gt;
We have discovered some wonderful spots that a tourist would not know about (my wife is from Kiev).
&lt;P&gt;
BTY I was worried about GPS in the country. But friends of mine who are in the police and military have assured me it's OK. And I did take it once and declaired it to their customs and there was no problem.</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>It looks similar to our Statue of Liberty. You can't miss it. As your guide for the WWII museum.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1362765795"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-23T08:38:02</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="18555596">antischaar77</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">great views and very informative exhibition. tftc</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362526479"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-25T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="548391">G &amp; E</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This park was the main objective today and it was a good visit, especially with the context of the current war. I didn't go inside any museums today but I did spent plenty of time in the free area. Picture is taken from exactly on the posted coordinates.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1330529820"><groundspeak:date>2025-10-18T12:02:04</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="14450722">Stuiterkuiken</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Long walk through the Dnipro parks today, visiting musea, churches and caches.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1320799361"><groundspeak:date>2025-08-28T13:42:10</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="30510424">olegoff</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Goff was here tftc 😁👍👍</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1296571183"><groundspeak:date>2025-05-05T11:49:57</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="7917391">pperen</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">It is nice to go outside and do some activities in Kyiv and scoring an cache at the same time. Nice weather to be outside. Co thanks for making this nice hobby possible. Tftc</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="24.075617" lon="55.772683"><time>2002-11-03T00:00:00</time><name>GCA3E8</name><desc>Jebel Hafit by Lunchbox</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCA3E8</url><urlname>Jebel Hafit</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="41960" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Jebel Hafit</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Lunchbox</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="18672">lunchbox</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="42" inc="1">Needs maintenance</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United Arab Emirates</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Jebel Hafit is a 1km high lump of limestone 20km to the south of Al Ain on the UAE - Oman border. A winding road that is a wonder of planning and engineering provides easy accesses to the mountain. If you fancy a real challenge then try biking up or you can join the annual run to the top. The exposure of the mountain makes for great GPS reception. Please be careful of your footing when looking for the cache, particularly the loose gravel.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>The cache is the usual 'Lunchbox' Tupperware affair and contains a variety off goddies of all shapes and sizes including the 'Where's George Bill' we brought out from the UK. As the driving in the UAE is (ahh hem) 'interesting' we made sure that the cache could be reached from one of the well maintained car parks and there is definitely no need to walk on the road. To really make the most of Jebel Hafit we recommend that you time to be on the top of the mountain for sunset when you can see the sun setting over the sea of dunes. A fantastic sight.</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>The cache is about 15m walk from the car park below the telecom sand radar station. It is hidden within a small hollow to the left.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1363034589"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-24T06:52:26</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1193235">arunns</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">amazing  hide out, TFC found on our way to jebel hafeet with friends</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1348273478"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-05T13:50:09</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="39929232">Randulinas59</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">🐘🦓🦒🦁🦏🐪🌸
Thank you! Merci! Grazie! Grazia fich! Obrigada! ¡Gracias! Efcharisto! Danke! Asante! Shukran! شكرًا لك
 🐘🦓🦒🦁🦏🐪🌸

In February 2023 we started our long-term travel through Southern and Eastern Africa then we shipped the LandRover to Oman to explore the Arabic Peninsula.
Sometimes we do Geocaching.
Thank you ALL for hiding caches and taking care of it. You ALL showed us interesting places and facts which makes travelling more interesting as we see and know things now not even mentioned in travelguidebooks.

Greetings from 🇨🇭 Switzerland 

www.randulinas.ch

</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1346809146"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-27T17:09:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5332608">JaSaHram</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I found this cache during my business trip to Abu Dhabi. Thanks for the hide.
Quite windy here.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1350148760"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-24T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="11272430">Koumes11</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found within my short visit of Emirates :)</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1345557259"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-14T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="11053053">penalty96</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Finally, vacation time! 🎉 Together with Alixander77 and Walli14, we planned our three-country trip to the United Arab Emirates, India, and Sri Lanka 🇻🇺 🇮🇳 🇱🇰.
Our first stop was Dubai for two exciting days full of contrasts and overwhelming impressions. We spent the first day exploring the city, and the second day took us inland near the Omani border to Jebel Hafit National Park.
On the second day, we drove our rental car to the oldest geocache in the UAE. The really old ones are always a must-see. When planning our trip, we were initially skeptical about doing the tour during our short stay in the country, but it was the best decision to do it 👌🏼. It allowed us to experience another facet of the country.
The 15 meters to the hiding place were manageable, even though I'm a bit more cautious now after my fall last year, especially since I was wearing sandals 😅. Bad idea! But I had to hold that oldie in my own hands. It's always a great feeling to find such an old cache and sign the logbook. Of course, I'll leave a blue bookmark between the pages.
Thanks for laying &amp; maintaining  [:)]


Endlich Urlaub 🎉! Gemeinsam mit Alixander77 und Walli14 planten wir unseren Drei-Länder-Trip in die Vereinigten Arabischen Emirate, Indien und Sri Lanka 🇻🇺 🇮🇳 🇱🇰.
Unser erster Stopp war in Dubai für zwei spannende Tage voller Kontraste und überwältigenden Eindrücke. Den ersten Tag nutzten wir zur Erkundung der Stadt, der zweite führte uns in das Hinterland nahe der omanischen Grenze in den Nationalpark Jebel Hafit.
Am zweiten Tag sind wir mit dem Mietwagen zum ältesten Cache UAE gefahren. Die ganz Alten sind immer ein Ziel. Bei der Planung unserer Reise waren wir erst skeptisch, ob wir bei unserem kurzen Aufenthalt im Land die Tour machen sollten, aber es war die beste Entscheidung es zu machen 👌🏼. Dadurch haben wir eine weitere Facette des Landes kennengelernt. 
Die 15 m zum Versteck waren gut machbar, auch wenn ich durch meinen Sturz im letzten Jahr jetzt etwas vorsichtiger bin, besonders weil ich Sandalen hatte 😅. Blöde Idee! Aber den Oldie muss ich in meinen eigenen Händen halten. Es ist immer wieder ein gutes Gefühl einen so alten Cache zu finden und das Logbuch zu signieren. Natürlich bleibt hier ein blaues Lesezeichen zwischen den Seiten. 
Danke für das Legen &amp; Pflegen [:)].</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="56.38715" lon="-4.550817"><time>2000-12-15T00:00:00</time><name>GCF0</name><desc>Scotland's First by Jock Scott</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCF0</url><urlname>Scotland's First</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="240" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Scotland's First</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Jock Scott</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="753">jock</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Not chosen</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United Kingdom</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Northern Scotland</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>A couple of points to make:
&lt;p&gt;1. It's impossible to place the cache on public lands because no such land exists! Every square inch of these islands is owned by someone - there is no such thing as "Public Land". Even National Parks are merely administrative areas - the government only owns military land through the MOD.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;2. Here, everyone sets their GPS units to OS Grid. Ordnanacy Survey is the government department which has mapped the British Isles. Everyone I know sets their units to OS and leaves them unless going overseas. So I've given the cache these co-ordinates.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NN42606 / 24542&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is level 5 difficulty. This is the hint: drive and hour and a quarter North of Glasgow, and then hike up a steep hill for another hour and a half. Follow a series of stream into a shallow corrie, and as the ground steepens, look to the right (South) for a large rock marked by a small piles of stones placed ontop. The cache is underneath the large rock.&lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364925779"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-02T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="18363360">OndrTera</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">TB in</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364795030"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="19060373">krpi11cz</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">IN: 2x TB</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364792797"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T11:35:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="12072028">ELmonday</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Woensdag 04 Mei 2011

Yeah! I found it

Thanks for the cache

ELmonday

7478</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364724879"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-31T21:32:15</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3693409">jankaja</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Sieltähän se kätkö löytyi
Melkoinen nousu...
Kiitos kätköstä</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364726029"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-31T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3468617">matkaja</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Finally, the long-planned trip to Scotland came true. First we spent a couple of days in sunny Edinburgh, then we got in the car and drove around the country along the coast. The weather has been kind to us and we have seen many great places, green and yellow nature and old castles. Along the way we searched for caches that were conveniently located. Jankaja and Eiwi1501 were with us on the trip. Thanks to all the owners of the caches we found.
This was one of the most important destinations of this trip. It was a pretty tough trip, it was raining and windy on the way up, but when we came down the sun was already shining.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="5.88648333333333" lon="-162.085616666667"><time>2005-03-02T00:00:00</time><name>GCNCQW</name><desc>Palmyra: No worries atoll by credenza</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCNCQW</url><urlname>Palmyra: No worries atoll</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="226763" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Palmyra: No worries atoll</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>credenza</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="94701">credenza</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Large</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>2.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>US Minor Outlying Islands</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>A must see location if you find yourself on Palmyra Atoll.  Please note difficulty doesn't include getting to Palmyra.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>One of my favorites spots on all of Palmyra.  Located on Cooper Island, not far from the airstrip.  Be sure to bring a swim suit, a camera, and some nerve.
&lt;P&gt;
Cache is five gallon bucket painted green.  Contents were a little on the cheapo side, and for this I apologize.  Hopefully further visitors will expand contents, because there is nothing but space in there.
&lt;P&gt;
Finding cache requires little to no off trail tromping, so please respect the local flora.  Depending upon how overgrown cache location gets, the last 15 feet might be a bit of a tromp.&lt;P&gt;

&lt;font size=1&gt;
Small note on cache maintenance:  While I don't reside on Palmyra, I am often in contact with friends that do and are willing to look after my cache. The property is technically owned by the Nature Conservancy, I think, and I got the permission of the manager to place this cache. I think this will be great fun for any cruisers or visiting scientist geocachers. &lt;/font&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>View in front: Rope swing and South Island framed in window.  View in back: cache framed in window.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1263617220"><groundspeak:date>2024-10-05T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="24387384">AEYL</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">depots tb</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1245034381"><groundspeak:date>2024-07-08T09:09:29</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="48190471">Jakemccartney1</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Cache has been repaired! Fixed up a new bucket with a lid that will keep the water out. New log book added as well :)</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1238764651"><groundspeak:date>2024-06-06T16:29:08</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="48190471">Jakemccartney1</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Cache is still here! Unfortunately it is in terrible condition. No log book, destroyed pen, empty, waterlogged, and guarded by a coconut crab. I will be here for 3 more months so I will try to get around to fixing it up. Will post an update when cache is nursed back to health 👍</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1084255530"><groundspeak:date>2022-02-23T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="39809881">BFDI2006</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I traveled just to this Atoll just to find this GeoCache</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1045112931"><groundspeak:date>2021-08-24T10:55:08</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="11778903">badgerboy1969</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">My nephew who works for the Nature Conservacy is on Palmyra and looked for the cache. No luck. Said he searched in a  30 meter square. Wants to know if it is dead south of the solar panels?</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="18.337133" lon="-64.786933"><time>2002-02-03T00:00:00</time><name>GC372F</name><desc>CANEEL HILL  by KO_DAT_VEY</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC372F</url><urlname>CANEEL HILL </urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Virtual Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="14127" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>CANEEL HILL </groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>KO_DAT_VEY</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="18610">KO_DAT_VEY</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Virtual Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Virtual</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>3</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>US Virgin Islands</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>LOCATED ON ST.JOHN IN THE US VIRGIN ISLANDS. JUST A SHORT HIKE FROM CRUZ BAY
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>THIS CACHE IS JUST A SHORT HIKE UP THE HILL FROM CRUZ BAY ON THE ISLAND OF ST.JOHN. GETTING TO ST.JOHN CAN BE AN ADVENTURE IN ITSELF. A LOT OF THE CRUISES THAT GO TO THE AREA DONT STOP AT ST.JOHN. THE ONLY WAY TO GET THERE WOULD BE TO BUY A SHORE EXCURSION OR TAKE THE FERRY. WE TOOK THE FERRY BECAUSE IT WAS MUCH CHEAPER. THIS IS THE ROUTE WE TOOK. WE GOT OFF THE SHIP IN ST.THOMAS AND GOT A CAB TO THE DOWN TOWN SHOPPING AREA , 3 BUCKS PER PERSON. THE FERRY DOCK IS ACROSS THE STREET FROM THE TAXI STAND IN CHARLOTTE AMALIE. JUST ASK THE DRIVER HE WILL POINT IT OUT. THE FERRYS RUN APPROX EVERY 2 HOURS AND ROUND TRIP TO ST JOHN WILL COST ABOUT $14 PER PERSON.WATCH FOR DOLPHINS ON THE WAY. WHEN YOU GET OFF THE FERRY GO STRAIGHT OFF THE DOCK AND TAKE A LEFT WHEN YOU GET TO THE STREET. THE TRAIL HEAD IS JUST A FEW BLOCKS AWAY AT (N 18- 20.007/ W 064-47-500). YOU CANT MISS IT. THERE IS A SIGN RIGHT THERE AND A ROCK WALL. THIS IS A NARROW TRAIL THAT GOES UP FROM A FEW FEET ABOVE SEA LEVEL TO 746 FEET ABOVE SEA LEVEL, BE SURE TO BRING DRINKING WATER .THE VIEW IS INCREDIBLE. TO PROVE THAT YOU ARRIVED AT THE WAYPOINT SEND ME AN EMAIL DESCRIBING THE RUIN THAT IS THERE , GOOD LUCK! (One additional note, This is a virtual cache. Someone has left a container there but it has nothing to do with this cache.)
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1361162575"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-15T12:33:35</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="30508455">taffysails</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Fun  walk to celebrate a day off work. Yay it’s good to be alive in nature. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1357263679"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-22T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2485123">jimandjoanne</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false"> Headed up early this morning before the temperature got much higher, we had nice breeze in the more open areas with a view. Once at the top we collected the information needed. And while there enjoyed the views and all the new plants to us, Joanne was looking forward to seeing all of the different varieties compared to what we have at home. 
Thanks for showing us around. 
    
TFTC--j&amp;j </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1356496800"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-21T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4543306">PghPowers</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I appreciate these virtuals especially while traveling on the Caribbean Princess. Message sent with the requested information. Photo attached. Thanks for the cache from Pennsylvania USA. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1353969407"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-08T10:46:58</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="45199418">Yetter951</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Nice view. Thanks. Answer sent. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1352173214"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-31T14:03:41</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="25709372">NatsGeo6</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We walked to this one from the parking lot and took the Tamarind Trail up. It was a lot of elevation but worth it for the view! Thanks for the virtual! </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="39.27795" lon="-100.943683"><time>2000-05-11T00:00:00</time><name>GC30</name><desc>Mingo by The Kansas Stasher</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC30</url><urlname>Mingo</urlname><sym>Geocache Found</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="48" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Mingo</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>The Kansas Stasher</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="20">Kansas Stasher</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="1">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="40" inc="1">Stealth required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="33" inc="1">Motorcycles</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Kansas</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Quick stop for a long trip.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>A 6" round container buried in the ground.  Only the lid is exposed.

Added August 29, 2004:
Over the last couple of years people have been saying that this is the oldest still active cache. (see http://forums.groundspeak.com/GC/index.php?showtopic=48657 for more discussion.) I know for sure that it was the 7th ever created and the 1st in Kansas.  I would like to thank everyone who has stopped and visited so far.  And let's keep it going for a long, long time.</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364997659"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-02T11:35:01</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="16648325">____Juliacartwr</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This is my first real Geocaching trip since I started the game in August! My main destinations are Branson and GeoWoodstock XXII in Hutchinson but I will stop at other places beforehand and afterwards. I will be hitting as many counties as I can and getting old caches when I’m able to do so. I will also be going to various iconic sites and National Parks as I travel through nine states. Cache is in good condition unless otherwise noted. If answers are needed for earth caches or virtuals, I’ve sent them. Happy caching! Can’t wait to meet everyone at GeoWoodstock! </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364890581"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T15:14:46</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="55535592">kristintowns</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Kid loved it! First one </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364868291"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T13:18:42</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="12100188">GeoNinja54</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Randomly saw this on the map as I was driving by.  What a find. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364917211"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="387551">Hummingbird &amp; Blue Jay</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Easy PNG. cache in great shape. FP for diligently preserving this piece of geocaching lore. Great container too ! We have been looking forward to logging this one for quite a while.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364844524"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T11:21:33</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4276827">Dylan Bruney</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">So glad it's still here 26 years later! Awesome road trip stop.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363361865"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-24T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2089726">travelingGeek</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">What an amazing trip this has been!
I've been going to woodstocks for over a decade but this was the first Geo road trip my wife joined me on!   It's been a treat sharing the fun with her and her sister.
To also manage to finally get to Mingo was icing on top!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="41.900883" lon="12.447717"><time>2006-08-31T00:00:00</time><name>GCY25A</name><desc>SPQR - IL VATICANO by by Radio Alfa + SPQR Team [nascosto: bluemarlin]</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCY25A</url><urlname>SPQR - IL VATICANO</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="454906" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>SPQR - IL VATICANO</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>by Radio Alfa + SPQR Team [nascosto: bluemarlin]</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="8533590">RADIO ALFA</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Micro</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="42" inc="1">Needs maintenance</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Vatican City State</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>ATTENZIONE!!! I LOG DOVREBBERO ESSERE SCRITTI IN ITALIANO O IN INGLESE AL FINE DI CONSENTIRE DI COMPRENDERE A TUTTI IL SIGNIFICATO. THE LOGS SHOULD BE WRITTEN IN ENGLISH OR ITALIAN TO ALLOW UNDERSTAND ALL MEANING.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>ROMA Viale Vaticano. 
Cache posta nelle vecchie mura che delimitano lo stato della Città del Vaticano.  
Cache placed in the old wall bordering the Vatican City State. 
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>In un foro, nascosta da una pietra. In a hole hidden by a stone.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="825594724"><groundspeak:date>2019-01-19T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1116471">bajassli</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Zusammen mit Eltitas geniesse ich heute den 2.Tag in Rom. 
Unglaublich was diese Stadt an Kultur zu bieten hat. 
Viele Sehenswürdigkeiten haben wir heute besucht und dabei auch einige Cache. 
Eltitas hat den Cache gut gefunden. 
Danke.
Bajasslis Frau [:P][:P][:P]</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="823340393"><groundspeak:date>2018-12-30T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4990130">bandita007</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">**#6138± | 6100+ range | 15/51**
**Trip to Rome – Day 2 of 5**

**Day: 30/12/2018**
**Time: --:--**

Visited with: Thomastt and Jirkas25

----------

**Overall statistics:**

* Finds: 52 (logged 51)
* DNF: 4
* Time: 5 days
* Walked: -- km ±
* By bus: 2500 km ±

Day 1 (29/12/2018) – First day of our trip we moved to Brno (CZ) to board a bus. In Brno we found 4 geocaches (3 for me) before departure. Then we traveled all day and all night to Italy.

Day 2 (30/12/2018) – Early in the morning we arrived in Rome. Today's main goal was the Vatican. Wonderful experiences. We had a lot of time left in the afternoon so we were looking for some geocaches around. (21 geocaches found)

Day 3 (31/12/2018) – Today's goal was to visit ancient Rome and, of course, enjoy the New Year's Eve in Rome! We have visited amazing places and have taken a lot of great experiences. The fireworks were nice and the celebrations were impressive. We've enjoyed it all. (14 geocaches found)

Day 4 (01/01/2019) – Happy New Year! Today we visited other places in Rome that we missed yesterday. In the evening, unfortunately, we had to go to bus to go home. (11 geocaches found)

Day 5 (02/01/2019) – Last day. On our way to the Czech Republic we found one cache in Austria. In the morning we arrived back to Brno and then to home.

Rome is a wonderful city. Lots of beautiful sights. I really enjoyed it here. I thank all the owners for nice caches here and colleagues for working on this great trip. Thank you!

----------

**Geocache:**

I did not want to miss the oldest Vatican cache. We tried it and the cache was still on place. We were so happy. Thank you!

----------

*IN: --*
*OUT: --*


Thank you for a nice cache and wish a lot of satisfied finders.
Greetings from Olomouc, Czech Republic.

Track this log at geocaching.com: 
## HOMTFM ##

bandita007
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="823338526"><groundspeak:date>2018-12-30T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6427756">jirkas25</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">**#1913 16/52**

