Thanks for this nice archive cache</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="818849551"><groundspeak:date>2018-12-06T10:04:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="730154">Eagle1977</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found this after a rather strenuous hike. Who would have thought Rome or the Vatican would actually build on a hill? I thought that phrase was just a tourist ploy. Signed and replaced as intended. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="818177630"><groundspeak:date>2018-11-29T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="11489287">Guri2</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This cache was quikly found after a nice event near the St. Peter church.
Thanks for the cache!!

Greetings from Norway!🤸‍♀️</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="6.4840333333333335" lon="-62.899316666666664"><time>2001-06-20T00:00:00</time><name>GCE64</name><desc>Arekuna  by Scott Seegmiller</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCE64</url><urlname>Arekuna </urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="3684" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Arekuna </groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Scott Seegmiller</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="1192">Seegmiller</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>3.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Venezuela</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Stay at the Arekuna Camp, get great accomodations, hearty food portions, and find a geocache.  Near Angel Falls and Canaima National Park.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>Arekuna Camp is a rustic ecotourism village in the Canaima National Park.  Take the Aerotuy flight to Canaima and fly over Angel Falls en route.  Spend the night in the delightful cabins, with hammocks, or beds.  All your food and drinks are included in the price, which should be about $280 per person.  The geocache is located at the foot of the hill, down a short road, at the base of a lone tree.
It contains malaria pills (not needed), lip balm, advil, chinese finger trick, and the cache log.  If you are going to Venezuela, do not miss Canaima National Park, or Arekuna Camp.  Just 7 minutes by plane from Canaima, it will find a spot in your log book for a long time.</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>[ http://www.canaimasoft.com/AboutCanaima.htm ]</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1138105969"><groundspeak:date>2022-11-18T00:45:52</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="34671723">BMACDC145</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">TFTC </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1118754269"><groundspeak:date>2022-08-15T12:43:56</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="41661169">petetubixd</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Grax</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1048968074"><groundspeak:date>2019-12-22T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="9320764">FMB243</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Gefunden TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="776491003"><groundspeak:date>2018-06-18T20:32:08</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="23521101">ghendriksen</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Bru</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="386066247"><groundspeak:date>2014-02-12T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3040744">ETURAC</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">On our trip through Venezuela - a scenic impressive country - we also came to Arekuna with a cessna. A great adventure. Arekuna is a very nice place. Unfortunately, we found only remnants of the cache. The next cacher should have a new box in the luggage. [:)] Many greetings to the Owner. TFTC

This entry was edited by ETURAC on Tuesday, 04 March 2014 at 19:00:44 UTC.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="16.469667" lon="107.577617"><time>2002-10-13T00:00:00</time><name>GCADD4</name><desc>Can Chanh Palace by kablooey</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCADD4</url><urlname>Can Chanh Palace</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Virtual Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="44500" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Can Chanh Palace</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>kablooey</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="18898">kablooey</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Virtual Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Virtual</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>2.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Vietnam</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Ruins at Can Chanh Palace
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;Your guidebook probably says that this site was destroyed by Americans during the Vietnam-American War. Originally, there was a plaque here that indicated that the site was destroyed earlier. Now that the plaque has been removed, find the top name on the wall at the given coordinates. It should appear just above "TAY NIM".&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;TuuronTour noted that an entrance fee of 50.000 Dong was required when he visited in October 2007. The price seems to be 105.000 Dong as of July 2013. As of July 2022, the adult price is 200.000 Dong and the child price is 40.000 Dong. I encourage you to note in your log whether a fee applied during your visit. As of July 2022, Father Monk was able to provide a new verification for this cache after the plaque disappeared. It does seem that some cachers are having trouble finding the wall or finding the carvings/engravings on the wall; so I am upping the difficulty to 2.5. You may have to get fairly close to the wall to see the names, and if it has rained a lot recently, the area near the wall may be flooded. You might consider bringing binoculars or a camera with a good zoom lens.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;!--Phizer Park--&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;NOTE: This is NOT an armchair virtual cache.&lt;/b&gt; You are EXPECTED to visit the site PERSONALLY to obtain the information requested. Please do NOT just send a photo. You are expected to make your best effort to send me a text version of what you find. Please email or message your answer to the cache owner BEFORE logging this cache as Found. Failure to follow this requirement can result in your log being deleted without any notice or me leaving a "shame" note in the cache logs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;!--
List of Shame. The following cachers are among those who have logged this cache as Found, but have not sent me the required answers:
Sushkin 21Nov2014
SNKR2006 22Oct2013
sinoshrek Jul2012
Spiraea 4Apr2012
FaIIen 1Apr2012
-StyrianBushHuschers- 7Nov2009
--&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364499486"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-31T12:00:22</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1476343">Bristows</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">tftc! impressive place.
attached is todays price list
Greetings from Switzerland
Bristows &amp; Floria</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1359105491"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-04T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="15275471">mimishu</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">#6658 - 15:20 TFTC
Today I took the train and arrived at Hue. Paid 200k to visit this famous palace. Found the name on the wall easily.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1357722466"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-28T14:49:05</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="16009949">TryMe13</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Vielen Dank für den Cache und die wunderschöne Idee, etwas entziffern zu dürfen. Habe die Mauer sehr schnell gefunden und auch das Wort.

</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1357745322"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-28T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8578155">gunsight_butte</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I was here with Babashanti, thank you for showing us this  wonderful place!

Thank you kablooey for the the Cache.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1357715154"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-28T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5529931">Babashanti</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Hi,
together with gunsight_butte I visit the Can Chanh Palace. It is a very nice place to go.
Thank you so much for the lovely virtuel cache, we enjoyed it very much!
Big greetings, all the best and see you soon
Babashanti
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="15.270617" lon="44.200233"><time>2005-01-25T00:00:00</time><name>GCMME1</name><desc>I like to be thrown by a dog ? ( 1st in Yemen) by Cyprus15 </desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCMME1</url><urlname>I like to be thrown by a dog ? ( 1st in Yemen)</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="204355" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>I like to be thrown by a dog ? ( 1st in Yemen)</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Cyprus15 </groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="24094833">Cyprus15</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Yemen</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>The cache has been moved! (a little bit :) ) This cache is located just out side Sanaa, UNDER the hill that overlooks the old village of Bayt Baws (see page 139 in the Lonely Planet guide book for Yemen) . The cache is placed under a large boulder (see spoiler photo) and covered with small rocks. / Keška je nad Sanaá, pod kopcem nad Bayt Baws (Židovským mestem, viz spoiler photo). Keška je pod velkym kamenem, zatizena mensimi.
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:72px;"&gt;update the cache as is now in Cyprus new corods&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:72px;"&gt;(35.0535368, 33.9943684)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:24px;"&gt;**Yemen is Currently having a Cvil war**&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Most governments including the British and Usa advice against all travel to Yemen .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;the difficulty is 5 due to the challenge of most people getting the visa and then entering Yemen .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Anything can change with saftey so we will try to keep the description updated.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;if the Uk foreign office changes there Yemen travel advice advice against all but essential travel we will move the difficulty to 4&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;and when it is a fine to travel we difficulty rating we only relate to finding the cache . &lt;br /&gt;
 &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;***&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
The cache is a small (6 inch diameter) tupperware type container and contains a logbook, pen, and a Czech coin. / Keška je malý plastikový boxík do mikrovlnky, obsahuje logbook, propisku a ceskou korunu.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;**Find the cache at your own risk Yemen is currently having a Cvil War** &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;most governments advice against All Travel to Yemen .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;you have been warned . &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>I am picked up by a dog when my owner throws it to me?</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1143933830"><groundspeak:date>2023-01-06T20:25:17</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="18990911">Knagur Green</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Due to this cache not being available for years, the new CO trying to illegally change its location to another country as well as no chance that it will be available soon, I am now archiving it. This will give the opportunity for a new cacher to once again place first cache in Yemen when/if the country opens up again.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1015780145"><groundspeak:date>2021-05-06T20:37:36</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Unknown</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="18990911">Knagur Green</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I have changed the listing back to Yeman and due to illegal activity taking place I have now locked it.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1015779557"><groundspeak:date>2021-05-06T20:34:51</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Unknown</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="18990911">Knagur Green</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">A cache cannot be moved to a different country. If the cache is unavailable for an extended period of time it needs to be archived. By moving the country every person who has found the cache will lose the country icon which is not acceptable .

When a cache is moved it needs to still give the same caching experience to the finder as previous finders have had. If this cannot be done it needs to be archived. 

 The way you are trying to move coordinates is also not acceptable , and it seems that you are trying to by pass the reviewer by posting coordinates on the  listing rather than doing it correctly and asking the reviewer if it is allowed . It is also not possible to move it to an existing cache in Cyprus ( GC8H1XD) to by pass the reviewers.

The cache listing should have been archived years ago for lack of maintenance but as reviewers we have left it due to its age and  as it was the only traditional cache left  in the country.

 A cache owner should also live within a reasonable travelling distance to maintain the cache which was the case when the cache was published . As you live 5,784.9 km,away from the cache it cannot be maintained and it will most likely be archived.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1015650068"><groundspeak:date>2021-05-05T23:10:39</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="24094833">Cyprus15</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We have decided to move the cache as the Cvil war in Yemen is to dangerous and we do not wish a cacher going there and us owning the cache etc so the cache will be moved 1500miles to the Republic of Cyprus until a ceasefire in Yemen .

The cords are -  (35.0535368, 33.9943684)

And the hint is - I like to be picked up by a dog 

We hope people can find the cache at its temporary new home .

( Message to Geocaching HQ

This cache is being moved temporarily due to safety concerns when the safety in the Region gets better we will travel to Yemen and replace the cache ) 

Thank you and we hope you find the cache in Kapparis , Cyprus 

Regards, Cyprus15 🇨🇾</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="973001448"><groundspeak:date>2020-10-22T00:49:17</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="24094833">Cyprus15</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">— PLEASE READ —

We would like all geocacher to know that the location of the cache is not safe . 

— UK foreign office advice — 

We advice AGAINST all travel to Yemen due to the ongoing Cvil war . 

— USA Travel advice — 
 
Level 4 travel advice , Do not travel to Yemen due to Terrorism , cvil unrest , Kidnapping, armed Conflicts and landmines . 

They also state on the Usa travel advice -

Draft a will and power of attorney etc .

————————— |

We strongly advice you do not to travel to Yemen we will not be until the foreign office states it is safe .
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="-17.926" lon="25.859483"><time>2003-10-01T00:00:00</time><name>GCGZZ6</name><desc>Victoria Falls, Zambia by Steve (Licorice)</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCGZZ6</url><urlname>Victoria Falls, Zambia</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Virtual Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="95302" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Victoria Falls, Zambia</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Steve (Licorice)</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="28262">Licorice</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Virtual Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Virtual</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="0">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="2" inc="1">Access/parking fee</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="30" inc="1">Picnic tables nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Zambia</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>At Victoria Falls on the Zambia side
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;img src="http://www.geckobeach.com/GPS/licorice47.jpg" width="240" height="180" align="right" /&gt;To visit the falls on the Zambia side will cost you US$10, unless of course you are a resident of Zambia in which case you'll pay just US$0.50! A fee is required to visit the falls and score a find for this cache.
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Find the co-ordinates listed above near the end of the walk and have someone take a picture of yourself and your GPS clearly visible infront of the gorge (picture, right) where the majority of the water falls. Upload the picture with your log to score a find.&lt;br clear="all" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1361822667"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-17T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="10420067">Alixander77</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Had visited the Niagara falls and Iguazu, now here the Victoria falls. Such great and impressive places and wonders of the earth.
After the rainy seasons lots of water is coming down actually, good to get wet😂.

Thanks Licorice for hiding and best regards from Germany.

This stash was visited and found by Vollseiler and me during a trip in Zimbabwe, Zambia and Botswana.
Independently by ourself through various Nationalparks and of course the mighty falls of Victoria. With lots of sun, wild animals and great vast landscapes.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1361628344"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-17T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="14218081">Vollseiler</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Our second visit at this extraordinary location.
And btw here is to find the oldest cache in Zambia.
Thank you for the nice VC and greetings from Team Vollseiler</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360757826"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-13T21:23:15</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="23074259">homegeo27</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Am Ende unserer Reise hier an diesem tollen Ort vorbeigekommen.  TFTC </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1359331106"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-05T16:22:12</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="20575286">Divicus8405</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Totally wet we logged this great viurtual! </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1353144236"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-05T14:43:40</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="36390594">u115</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Danke für diesen imposanten Kulisse.
Spektakulären  Blick in riesige Wassermassen. Danke Regen für  diese Flut.
Gischt weit über alles hinaus.
Danke fürs Ausarbeiten und Zeigen. 
Grüße aus dem Salzkammergut, Austria. 
Tftc </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="-18.3739" lon="32.63755"><time>2003-07-22T00:00:00</time><name>GCGH61</name><desc>Susurumba Mountain by Kulwinder</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCGH61</url><urlname>Susurumba Mountain</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="82060" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Susurumba Mountain</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Kulwinder</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="87523">Kulwinder</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="9" inc="1">Significant hike</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="38" inc="0">Campfires</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="10" inc="1">Difficult climb</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="54" inc="1">Abandoned structure</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="19" inc="1">Ticks</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="39" inc="1">Thorns</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>3</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Zimbabwe</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font face="Tahoma" size="2"&gt;&lt;span&gt;The first and oldest Geocache in Zimbabwe. Placed in a scenic location on the summit of Susurumba mountain just outside the Rhodes Nyanga National Park, in the beautiful Eastern Highlands area of the country. The hike up to the cache is excellent for bird watching and maybe you might also see some other animals like monkeys or baboons. There isn’t anything dangerous to be afraid of though.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ACCESS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Driving from Rusape take the turn off to the &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/Hotel_Review-g1747536-d2136609-Reviews-Pine_Tree_Inn-Nyanga_Manicaland_Province.html"&gt;PINE TREE INN&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; before Juliasdale. Park at the Inn car park and then walk across the little dam wall just below the Inn and pick up the trail on the opposite bank. The climb is steep in places, but any fit person will manage and the trail is marked all the way to the summit. Do not attempt the climb after 4:00pm or in very bad weather.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;APPROACH&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
It takes about 90 minutes round-trip to reach the top and return. Follow the trail and climb to the top of the mountain. At the summit find the rocky beacon and stand by it. Now move to your east, cross over the gulley and stand near the edge of the rock face looking in the direction of the Inn below (bearing 050 degrees). You will find the cache buried in a crevice nearby.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;NOTE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
The cache is located on private property belonging to the hotel, but the manager is aware of it and has been told to expect cache seekers in the future. Do let them know if you find it.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
There are also some ruins at the summit which provide archaeological interest.&lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Three small rocks cover the crevice</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1320350942"><groundspeak:date>2025-08-25T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="14521620">FvS1968</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Fick idag logga den äldsta cachen i Zimbabwe! Det var en trevligt tur med  en del klättring innan man kunde logga den fina cachen på 2050m höjd. Cachen loggad senast 2021! Vi njöt i fulla drag! TFTC </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1054485152"><groundspeak:date>2021-10-03T09:16:09</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="33530046">Froggyfarmzim</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Amazing </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1046016537"><groundspeak:date>2021-08-28T19:57:28</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="27873101">rogandclarebarry</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">What an lovely spot! We so enjoyed our climb up &amp; the kids found the cache easily. Highly recommend a stop at Froggy Farm Cafe 🍕🤗</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="923788807"><groundspeak:date>2020-05-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="29569670">McKramblers</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Got to the summit at the second attempt and found the cache fairly easily.  The start of the path is overgrown and hard to find but once found the route to the top is clear.  Great views from the top.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="886912445"><groundspeak:date>2019-10-06T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4740686">greenmealie</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">At last I have now been able to log this cache.  Thank for the cache being replaced. It's the oldest cache in Zimbabwe.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="18.203367" lon="-63.0938"><time>2008-10-05T00:00:00</time><name>GC1GXR0</name><desc>Pyrates of the Caribbean by A &amp; I (WiAnVaPaLeMa)</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC1GXR0</url><urlname>Pyrates of the Caribbean</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="1016709" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Pyrates of the Caribbean</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>A &amp; I (WiAnVaPaLeMa)</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="1795079">Wianvapalema</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="42" inc="1">Needs maintenance</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="0">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="0">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="11" inc="1">May require wading</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>3</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Anguilla</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>PYRATES OF THE CARIBBEAN
&lt;p&gt;349 years ago 45 Pirates left Spain on a hunt to find a
treasure. They follow the stars and landed on an island named
Anguilla. Their transportation was a pirate ship called The Black
Pearl.They sailed through thick and thin for four long month. When
they found the treasure, they didn&amp;rsquo;t find a way to share it
equaly among the pirates. It came up to a fight, where all died.
The Captain was Arthur John Mc Phee. He was the last to die, sadly
he blead to death, with one stab in his heart. During that long,
painful death he wrote down the coordinates of the treasure and hid
it. Many hundreds of years later we found it,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;AND THE COORDINATES ARE: N 18° 12.202&amp;rsquo;; W 063°
05.628&amp;rsquo;&lt;br /&gt;
Have fun on your adventure to find our treasure from&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;THE PYRATES OF THE CARIBBEAN&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &amp;amp; I&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
German&lt;br /&gt;
Vor 349 Jahren brachen Piraten in Spanien auf, um einem Schatz nach
zu jagen. Sie folgten den Sternen und kamen schließlich auf einer
Insel namens Anguilla an Land. Ihr Schiff war die Black Pearl. Sie
waren vier lange Monate mit einander durch dick und dünn gesegelt,
aber als sie den Schatz dann gefunden hatten, konnten sie sich
nicht einigen, wie er gerecht untereinander aufgeteilt werden soll.
Es kam zu einem heftigen Kampf, bei dem alle ums Leben kamen. Der
Kapitän Arthur John Mc Phee war der letzte, der qualvoll durch
einen Stich ins Herz verblutete. Während seines langen,
schmerzhaften Todes schrieb er die Koordinaten des Schatzes nieder
und versteckte sie. Viele hundert Jahre später fanden wir die
Schatzkarte.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;UND DIE KOORDINTEN SIND: N 18° 12.202&amp;rsquo;; W 063°
05.628&amp;rsquo;&lt;br /&gt;
Viel Spaß bei Eurer Schatzsuche!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &amp;amp; I&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size="1"&gt;Small note on cache maintenance: There is a local
"cache guardian". Name and contact info on file with
geocaching.com. Enjoy!&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>The writing way of "pyrate" gives you a hint of which village it lies in. A rum with same name was selled there. You´ll find it beheind a rock in about two metres high.

Die Schreibweise "Pyrate" gibt einen Hinweis auf den Ort, in dem der Cache versteckt ist. Bis vor kurzem wurde Rum mit dem selben Namen dort verkauft.
Hinter einem Felsen in ca. 2m Höhe.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="981579333"><groundspeak:date>2020-12-02T15:44:45</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="115500">Crow T Robot</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Archived.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="981306999"><groundspeak:date>2020-11-29T22:45:12</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Needs Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="19252633">IMGOIN2</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This geocacher reported that this geocache should be archived. A community volunteer reviewer has been notified.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="981306998"><groundspeak:date>2020-11-29T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="19252633">IMGOIN2</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">CO has not visited geocaching.com for more than 4 years, and I received no response from CO after waiting  for a response.  Not likely this one is still there..</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="968598573"><groundspeak:date>2020-10-03T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="19252633">IMGOIN2</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This one has not been found in many months, and has several DNF's.  The CO has not logged on to geocaching.com in four years, and did not answer my message sent two years ago when I volunteered to replace the container because of a DNF prior to that.  It seems doubtful that anyone has permission to replace the container.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="911661451"><groundspeak:date>2020-02-19T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Didn't find it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="14366752">Heyke</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Unfortunately dnf 😭</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="-19.545083" lon="169.4588"><time>2008-11-04T00:00:00</time><name>GC1HW2K</name><desc>Vanuatu's Volcano by fizbot</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC1HW2K</url><urlname>Vanuatu's Volcano</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Earthcache</type><groundspeak:cache id="1044876" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Vanuatu's Volcano</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>fizbot</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="88478">fizbot</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Earthcache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Not chosen</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="14" inc="1">Recommended at night</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="23" inc="1">Dangerous area</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="21" inc="1">Cliff/falling rocks</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Vanuatu</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Visits should be undertaken only with a local tour operator who can keep you safe.  Sturdy shoes and long pants should be worn because of the sharp volcanic rocks and a flashlight should be brought if you are viewing after dusk.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>Vanuatu is located in the south west Pacific. It is part of the Pacific Ring of Fire. The 83 islands were formed by volcanic activity over millions of years. Flights to Vanuatu operate from Australia, New Zealand, Fiji, New Caledonia, and Solomon Islands.

Yasur is one of the world's most active volcanoes. It is known as the Lighthouse of the Pacific because of its regular eruptions for hundreds of years. The volcano is located on Tanna Island in southern Vanuatu. It lies on a subduction zone at the boundary of the Indo-Australia and Pacific tectonic plates.

Yasur is a potentially hazardous volcano. Approaching the crater is dangerous at any time. Often quoted activity levels are for general scientific classification only, and do not relate to visitor safety. During periods of low activity, there can still be a large eruption without warning.
A volcano is an opening, or rupture, in a planet's surface or crust, which allows hot, molten rock, ash, and gases to escape from below the surface. Volcanic activity involving the extrusion of rock tends to form mountains or features like mountains over a period of time.
Volcanoes are generally found where tectonic plates are diverging or converging. A mid-oceanic ridge, for example the Mid-Atlantic Ridge, has examples of volcanoes caused by "divergent tectonic plates" pulling apart; the Pacific Ring of Fire has examples of volcanoes caused by "convergent tectonic plates" coming together. By contrast, volcanoes are usually not created where two tectonic plates slide past one another. Volcanoes can also form where there is stretching and thinning of the Earth's crust (called "non-hotspot intraplate volcanism"), such as in the African Rift Valley, the Wells Gray-Clearwater volcanic field and the Rio Grande Rift in North America and the European Rhine Graben with its Eifel volcanoes.
Volcanoes can be caused by "mantle plumes". These so-called "hotspots" , for example at Hawaii, can occur far from plate boundaries. Hotspot volcanoes are also found elsewhere in the solar system, especially on rocky planets and moons.
Stratovolcanoes (composite volcano)
Stratovolcanoes are tall conical mountains composed of lava flows and other ejecta in alternate layers, the strata that give rise to the name. Stratovolcanoes are also known as composite volcanoes, created from several structures during different kinds of eruptions. Strato/composite volcanoes are made of cinders, ash and lava. Cinders and ash pile on top of each other, then lava flows on top and dries and then the process begins again. Classic examples include Mt. Fuji in Japan, Mount Mayon in the Philippines, and Mount Vesuvius and Stromboli in Italy. In recorded history, explosive eruptions by stratovolcanoes have posed the greatest hazard to civilizations.  Mount Yasur is a Stratovolcano. 
An aspect of stratovolcanic eruptions are the creation of Volcanic Bombs
A volcanic bomb is a globe of molten rock (tephra) larger than 65 mm (2.5 inches) in diameter, formed when a volcano ejects viscous fragments of lava during an eruption. They cool into solid fragments before they reach the ground. Lava bombs can be thrown many kilometres from an erupting vent, and often acquire aerodynamic shapes during their flight. Bombs can be extremely large; the 1935 eruption of Asama in Japan expelled bombs measuring 5-6 m in diameter up to distances of 600 m from the vent.
Volcanic bombs are a significant volcanic hazard, and can cause severe injuries and death to people in an eruption zone. One such incident occurred at Galeras volcano in Colombia in 1993; six people near the summit were killed and several seriously injured by lava bombs when the volcano erupted unexpectedly.
Types of Bombs
Bombs are named according to their shape, which is determined by the fluidity of the magma from which they are formed.
1. Ribbon or cylindrical bombs
These bombs form from highly to moderately fluid magma, ejected as irregular strings and blobs. The strings break up into small segments which fall to the ground intact and look like ribbons. Hence, the name- ribbon bombs. These bombs are circular or flattened in cross section, are fluted along their length, and have tabular vesicles.
2. Spherical bombs
These bombs also form from high to moderately fluid magma. In the case of spherical bombs, surface tension plays a major role in pulling the ejecta into spheres.
3. Spindle, fusiform, or almond/rotational bombs
These bombs are formed by the same processes as spherical bombs, though the major difference being the partial nature of the spherical shape. Spinning during flight leaves these bombs looking elongated or almond shape, the spinning theory behind these bombs' development has also given them the name 'fusiform bombs'. Spindle bombs are characterised by longitudinal fluting, one side slightly smoother and broader than the other. This smooth side represents the underside of the bomb as it fell through the air.
4. Cow-dung bombs
These are formed when highly fluid magma falls from moderate height (so the bomb does not solidify before impact) which are still liquid when they strike the ground. They consequently flatten or splash and form irregular roundish disks which resemble cow-dung.
5. Bread-crust bombs
If the outside of a lava bomb solidifies during its flight, it may develop a cracked outer surface as the interior continues to expand. This type of lava bomb is known as a bread-crust bomb.
6. Cored bombs
Cored bombs are bombs that have rinds of lava enclosing a core of previously consolidated lava. The core consists of accessory fragments of an earlier eruption, accidental fragments of country rock or in rare cases bits of lava formed earlier during the same eruption.


Yasur, the best-known and most frequently visited of the Vanuatu volcanoes, has been in more-or-less continuous strombolian and vulcanian activity since Captain Cook observed ash eruptions in 1774. This style of activity may have continued for the past 800 years. Yasur is a mostly unvegetated 361-m-high pyroclastic cone with a nearly circular, 400-m-wide summit crater. Yasur is largely contained within the small Yenkahe caldera and is the youngest of a group of Holocene volcanic centers constructed over the down-dropped NE flank of the Pleistocene Tukosmeru volcano. The Yenkahe horst is located within the Siwi ring fracture, a 4-km-wide, horseshoe-shaped caldera associated with eruption of the andesitic Siwi pyroclastic sequence. Active tectonism along the Yenkahe horst accompanying eruptions of Yasur has raised Port Resolution harbor more than 20 m during the past century.

To gain credit for this earth cache, you must measure the average height of the Pyroclastic eruptions during your visit, record the types of the Pyroclastic rocks (bombs) found on the crater rim and record the duration between events and email the results to the cache owner for verification.  Pictures should be posted showing yourself at the volcano with a pyroclastic eruption in the background or with examples of volcanic bombs.  Please do not post the answers in your log.  Any answers/spoilers will be deleted.</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>The volcano crater is approximately four hundred meters across as a reference</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1363679510"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-26T21:09:14</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4387387">acbnyc</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">What an amazing place! Mesmerizing and terrifying all at once. Quite a journey to get here but the payoff was well worth it. 

This is also the first earth cache I’ve logged, seemed like a good time for it!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1353087492"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-05T21:06:27</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5679606">team-trudi</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found it together with TDrex. A real Adventure, we love it. Please refer to his log for more information. Answers were also sent by him. TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1353085455"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-05T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5166490">tdrex166</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We're on a cruise with Hapag Lloyd cruises, starting off from Noumea, visiting various islands of Vanuatu, Solomon Islands and finally disembarking after 18 days on board in Fiji. 

Today we visited the island of Tanna. Due to heavy winds from the east (there is a cyclone over Fiji) we had to anchor on the west coast near the small town of Lenakel. From there we drove 1.5 hours with jeeps on a very very bumpy road to Mount Yasur. It was fantastic, the volcano is super active, we heard a lot of eruptions, unfortunately didn't see any lava. Next time we have to come at night. Nevertheless this was a real highlight of our cruise so far. Answers will be sent in a couple of minutes.

Thanks for this wonderful earth cache - tdrex and team-trudi</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1332753038"><groundspeak:date>2025-11-02T19:24:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3230010">Lulu147</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We arrived on the Scenic Eclipse II and had a lovely presentation of local talent in The morning.  In the afternoon we ventured in the back of the pickup trucks up to the volcano.  Certainly a highlight!  Lots of rumbling and smoke.  A few good explosions!  </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1311370035"><groundspeak:date>2025-05-04T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="16942864">justforjoys</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">One of our most amazing experience! Not many chance to stand right up to a mouth of an active volcano. While didn't see much of the lava activity, but the rumble and deafening explosions were mindblowing! Mt Yasar did eventually give us a beautiful lava fountain right before we leave. Cool!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="5.082541" lon="-8.537922"><time>2014-01-19T00:00:00</time><name>GC4X70E</name><desc>Dugbe by samueljameshandley</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC4X70E</url><urlname>Dugbe</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="4123853" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Dugbe</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>samueljameshandley</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="8508174">samueljameshandley</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Micro</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="30" inc="1">Picnic tables nearby</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Liberia</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;Enjoy the views of the river and the beer. Say hi to the boys&lt;/p&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1350266483"><groundspeak:date>2025-12-31T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="42639719">Seattlehunter</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found this container on a world tour from 2022 to 2025. I think it was the best experience of my life doing this trip. Could see a lot.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1332686041"><groundspeak:date>2025-11-01T19:03:22</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="52295742">majosika</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">🤑</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1310520545"><groundspeak:date>2025-07-14T12:07:37</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="40139640">pauline43770</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">GG fryhvuhbjnwjirjcjxfjjsidjxj jjcneiejcjc</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1273602335"><groundspeak:date>2024-12-15T17:46:27</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="51751539">o70</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">N</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1272150519"><groundspeak:date>2024-11-30T03:29:01</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="50440433">wildidoitonlose</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thank you </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="-25.0685" lon="-130.113"><time>2014-01-12T00:00:00</time><name>GC4WX78</name><desc>Highest Point by scotnor adopted by SteLaSyXL</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC4WX78</url><urlname>Highest Point</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="4114454" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Highest Point</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>scotnor adopted by SteLaSyXL</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="6535652">SteLaSyXL</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Pitcairn</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Visiting this cache will reward you with spectacular views over Pitcairn Island and the Pacific Ocean.
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>The highest point is at 347 meters (1138 feet) and is a steep climb, nothing dangerous, there are good dirt roads, but quite hard going and in rainy weather some bits can be muddy and slippery. From the square, walk along towards the school until you see the sign pointing up to the left, and then just go on up. At the highest point there is a signpost to far-off places, a concrete block which marks the site of an old US satellite tracking station, a bench and a shelter. You can cool down with water from the tank behind the shelter, but it is not good drinking water. The geocache is a plastic box with some Pitcairn treasures. Depending on your fitness and how often you stop, it will take 40-60 minutes to walk up and a bit less to come down. If you have time and want a longer walk through the island, take the first path on the right after you leave the highest point and walk along the ridge to Taro Ground where you will see the old radio station, then go on down to Adamstown. Have a great walk! If you do not have time or good enough legs for this climb, ask a Pitcairner to drive you up on a four wheeler bike (for a small fee).
&lt;center&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size="1"&gt;Small note on cache maintenance: Shawn Christian, the mayor of Pitcairn, will maintain the cache. Thanks!&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/center&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Look up</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1355370602"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-15T15:18:51</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="10435116">cweissman</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thank you for encouraging us to hike up to the amazing look out. I especially loved the part of the path going through lush green </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1343523232"><groundspeak:date>2026-01-31T17:11:41</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="17466518">vlk22</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">One of the most beautiful days of my life! When we received the newsletter from Cacher-Reisen, it was clear that we had to take advantage of the opportunity. The last 3 days was strong wind and rough sea, but today was optimal weather and in the morning was hardly afraid that it would not work out.

The island is a dream. First we are up to the highest point, then to Ships Landing. Finally, we even went to the pool because ship guests told us that we had to see this...

Our Hometown is 16301km away 🤣

🇦🇹 Danke SteLaSyXL für das Erstellen des Geocache, Auslegen und Warten der Dose!  - 🇬🇧 Thanks for the cache (English) - 🇭🇺 Köszönöm a geoládát (Magyar) - 🇸🇰 Ďakujem za kešku (Slovensky) - 🇨🇿 Díky za keš (Čeština) - 🇮🇹 Grazie per questo cache (Italiano) - 🇭🇷 Hvala cache (Hrvatski) - 🇫🇷 Merci pour la cache (Français) - 🇵🇱 Dzięki za kesza (Polski) - 🇪🇸 Gracias por el cache (Español) – 🇵🇹 Obrigado por esta cache (Português) – 🇳🇱 Bedankt voor de cache (Nederlands) - 🇸🇪 Tack för cachen (Svenska) – 🇳🇴 Takk for cachen (Norsk) - 🇮🇸 Takk fyrir skyndiminnið (Íslenska) - 🇬🇷 ευχαριστώ για την κρυφή μνήμη (Greek)

&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Discover my Log-TB: GS8BH2 &lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1343517767"><groundspeak:date>2026-01-31T15:40:14</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="23008648">PersephoneOla</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">What a wonderful day! We did it! My first on Pitcairn! The dream came true!

Danke für das Erstellen des Geocache, Auslegen und Warten der Dose! - Thanks for the cache! Dzięki za kesza! Gracias por el cache! Grazie per questo cache! Obrigado por isso cache! Díky za keš! Merci pour la cache! Ďakujem za kešku! Hvala cache! Tack för att cache! Takk for at cache! Bedankt voor de cache!

Und natürlich für das Zeigen der Location!

Seit 21.04.2018 Geocacherin. Im Cachingalter von 4766 volle Jasmermatrix fertig geschafft. PL in AT. Zu meinen Lieblingscaches zählen die Tradis, Virtus und Mysterys, die einen nicht sekkieren. Meistens in Wien und im Burgenland unterwegs. In der Coronazeit leider viel nur in Österreich unterwegs gewesen, aber doch mit kleinen Abstechern. Nächste mögliche Ziele: Kanada, Svalbard, Griechenland, Montenegro, Polen. Lieblingsländer auf der Geocachingkarte bis jetzt: Färöer, Irland, Belgien, Luxemburg, Finnland, Åland Island. WICHTIG: MEGA 2026 in Łódź, Polen.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1343685713"><groundspeak:date>2026-01-31T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2237420">Brummelbären</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Unser erstes Ziel nach einem Erleichterungsseufzer auf der Insel führte uns zum Highest Point. Wir haben bequem ein typisches Inselgefährt genutzt, das uns zumindest recht bequem nach oben brachte. Beweisfoto für den Earthcache gemacht und dann erst mal die einzigartige Aussicht genossen. Anschließend das Logbuch mit unserem Nicknamen verziert und dann begann der Abstieg. Hätten nicht so viele tolle Punkte auf der Insel gelockt, hätten wir hier noch viel mehr Zeit verbringen können. 
Toll, dass hier eine "richtige Dose" vor Ort liegt.
Danke für das Legen und Pflegen dieses Geocaches sagen die Brummelbären aus Worms/Deutschland</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1343683799"><groundspeak:date>2026-01-31T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="43458938">Tarzanujane</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">mit Cacher-Reisen unterwegs von Lima nach Tahiti, heute diesen Schatz entdeckt und als CR-O-P-F-26 geloggt um Platz im Logbuch zu sparen
Traveling with Cacher-Reisen from Lima to Tahiti, discovered this treasure today and logged it as CR-O-P-F-26 to save space in the logbook.
CR-O-P-F-26 are Tumlehdo, Brummelbären, vlk22, Darmstädter, Ci_Ti, nocybe1810, 
PersephoneOla , Cacher-Reisen and Tarzanujane</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="49.107133" lon="20.2473"><time>2001-09-01T00:00:00</time><name>GC22DF</name><desc>HRADISKO by MILAN VDOVJAK A JOZEF MIKO</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC22DF</url><urlname>HRADISKO</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="8927" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>HRADISKO</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>MILAN VDOVJAK A JOZEF MIKO</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="141612">Igi</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Slovakia</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Prešovský kraj</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>difficulty: light&lt;br /&gt;
cache type: plastic pail/bucket&lt;br /&gt;
content: CD, knife, book, copy-book, medal
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>100 SPETS AYWA MORF SETNO,
AT EHT BKRNI FO GEOGR,
BNEETEW 2 MDAERK SEERT,
GSUDAR A SLKLU DEIRUB TERREUAS.
[in slovak language:] 100, ZKPNÝAOA, DALKOP, EIMDZ, AKLEB, KROKOV, IŽÁRTS, DVAOM,
IMAMORTS, AN, ÒAEAKM, OD, POZMINAÈÝNE, IJARK, ZRÁZU</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1360774238"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-10T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="49078361">zvolensk</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Dve tretiny nášho tímu mali počas tohto predĺženého víkendu program v Novej Lesnej a ja som to využil a tiež som si naplánoval nejaké aktivity. Len som si zvolil inú lokalitu, aj keď neďaleko. A tak som piatkové popoludnie po tom, čo som sa z Lesnej presunul do Tatranskej Lomnice a celú sobotu strávil v nej a v blízkom okolí. V nedeľu ráno som vyrazil smer Smokovce a následne do Novej Lesnej, kde sme sa opäť stretli a odfrčali sme domov.
Tretí deň, záverečný, som si dal skorý budík a už o šiestej som vyštartoval. Presunul som sa postupne do Starého Smokovca, vybehol som si na Hrebienok, po návrate som prešiel Starý, Nový, Horný aj Dolný Smokovec až som dorazil v dohodnutom čase do Novej Lesnej. Tentokrát počasie vyšlo na jednotku, modré nebo, krásne výhľady, nádherná rozlúčka s Tatrami.
Keď už bola hlavná myšlienka môjho výletu pod Tatry odloviť najstaršiu slovenskú kešku, nemohol som odísť bez toho, aby sme  odlovili kešku s najstarším GC kódom. Nech je to akokoľvek. A tak sme autom z Novej Lesnej zamierili do Veľkého Slavkova a odtiaľ po nie práve ideálnej ceste smerom ku keške. Dostali sme sa celkom ďaleko, odparkovali sme, preskákali potok a vyšli hore. Hľadali sme asi desať minút, napokon bola presne na tú vzdialenosť od toho objektu, ako som si to vylúštil. Takže ďalší vzácny kúsok máme za sebou a nechávame favoritný bod.

Ďakujeme za kešku.
(Peter&amp;Lenka&amp;Milan)

**#3497** (vrátane 807 labiek)</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360449562"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-10T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2255228">Any_cz</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Na prodloužený víkend jsme společně s KaMo_cz a Pendolino001 naplánovali výlet za keškami na Slovensko a do Maďarska. Bylo krásné počasí a krásně jsme si to užili. Splnili jsme většinu toho, co jsme měli v plánu a přidali jsme i něco navíc.
Za všechny keše ownerům děkuji :-)
Posílám srdíčko.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360371217"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-10T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8312550">Pendolino001</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">#18735

Together with Kamo and Any we went to Slovakia and Hungary this time. In three days we saw a lot of interesting places and found many caches. It was a great trip. Thank you to all the owners, and I apologize, but from now on in Czech.
Pohodový nález i odlov. Kouzelné místo.

Díky
+FP</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360521343"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-10T08:41:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2165368">KaMo_cz</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Naplánoval jsem (a odřídil si) trip po Slovensku a Maďarsku pro staré keše plus pár kousků cestou na doplnění SK okresů.
Díky všem ownerům za keše, bylo to parádní a intenzivní [:D]
Nalezeno společně s Any_cz a Pendolino001

Nejstarší keš na nejstarším místě, tak to je opravdu stylové. A nyvíc je tu opravdu nádherně.
+1</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1358650291"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-02T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3427117">AuntPolly</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">On our trip to Slovakia, we made a detour to visit this old cache. First, a refreshing wade across the stream, and the rest of the way through springtime meadows. Thanks for the cache!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="-37.79818" lon="77.57296"><time>2014-04-01T00:00:00</time><name>GC51G4H</name><desc>L'une des caches les plus isolées du monde by Rïon</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC51G4H</url><urlname>L'une des caches les plus isolées du monde</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="4251793" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>L'une des caches les plus isolées du monde</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Rïon</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="3051105">Rïon</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Micro</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>French Southern and Antarctic Territories</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>&lt;div&gt;[FR] L'une des caches les plus isolées du monde se trouve dans les Terres Australes et Antarctiques Françaises (TAAF), sur l'île d'Amsterdam.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;[EN] One of the most isolated cache in the world is on the French Southern and Antarctic Lands, on Amsterdam Island.&lt;/div&gt;</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;div style="text-align:center;"&gt;[FR]&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;A 2 880 km des côtes de la Réunion, au sein des Terres Australes et Antarctiques Françaises (TAAF) se trouve l’île d’Amsterdam. Etant l’une des îles les plus isolées du monde, la plus grande difficulté de cette cache sera déjà de se rendre sur Ams’ ! Attention donc à ne pas rater l’un des 4 départs annuels du Marion Dusfrene…&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;La cache se situe non loin de la chapelle Notre-Dame de l’Ocean et est accessible facilement sans sortir de la base. Inutile de prévoir une expédition sur 4 jours, vous devriez pouvoir vous en sortir seul. Attention en revanche aux éléphants de mer qui pourraient vous barrer la route.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cette cache a été posée par l’Adjudant Chef Stéphane CANO, chef garage de la 64&lt;sup&gt;ème&lt;/sup&gt; mission (2012-2013) et descendant de Juan Sebastian El Cano, l’explorateur ayant découvert l’île en 1522.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Vous cherchez une boîte à pellicule. Merci de bien remettre la cache en place, une maintenance étant difficilement envisageable, ou en tout cas, pas tout de suite…&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Si l’envie vous prend de continuer à geocacher, la cache la plus proche se trouve à 1560km de là, direction nord-ouest.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;[EN]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;2 880 km away from the french Reunion Island, within the French Southern and Antarctic Lands, is Amsterdam Island. Being one of the most isolated island in the world, the biggest difficultie for this cache will be to get to Ams' ! Therefore, be careful not to miss one of the Marion Dusfrene's 4 annual departures...&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The cache is located not far from the chapel Notre-Dame de l'Ocean and can easily be reached without getting out of the base. No need then to plan a 4-days trip, you should be able to get there on your own. Watch out for any sea elephant that may stand in your way though.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This cache was hidden by Adjudant-chef (chief warrant officer) Stéphane Cano, garage's chief during the 64th mission (2012-2013) and descendant of Juan Sebastian El Cano, the explorer who first discovered the island in 1522.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You're looking for a film canister. Please, put the cache back where it belongs, as a maintenance would be hard to make, or at least, not for now...&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you feel like geocaching some more, the nearest cache is 1560 km away from there. &lt;/p&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>[FR] Dans un trou de la borne IGN
[EN] In a hole in the Ordnance Survey marker / post.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1342034397"><groundspeak:date>2026-01-17T17:11:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="17964838">BOB1091A</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Même en mission dabs les TAAF on peut continuer a faire du geocaching.
La cache est superbe, elle a survécu a l'incendie de janvier 2025.
 Trouver le 17/01/2026 par le chef centrale de la mission 77</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1338237526"><groundspeak:date>2025-12-18T16:49:34</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="48374973">Cache_kingz</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Essenary, that’s so cap</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1281773428"><groundspeak:date>2025-02-19T19:34:48</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3051105">Rïon</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">L'île d'Amsterdam est malheureusement la proie des flammes depuis quelques semaines, sans qu'aucune intervention humaine ne soit possible. Les scientifiques et militaires sur place ont été évacués et j'ignore si des missions pourront reprendre sur place. Surtout, j'ignore si la cache aura survécu à l'incendie. 

J'attends un peu avant d'archiver cette cache, qui était si particulière et chère à mon coeur. 

Si un Geocacheur remet les pieds sur l'île, je serai ravie d'avoir des nouvelles ❤️</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1281829210"><groundspeak:date>2025-02-19T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="589255">TeamNineLives</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Je suis vraiment désolé d'apprendre la nouvelle de l'incendie.  J'espère le meilleur pour cet endroit même si j'aurai des attentes réalistes.  C'est la géocache la plus éloignée de la planète sur la planète, c'est pourquoi je l'ai considérée comme spéciale.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1193752840"><groundspeak:date>2023-09-09T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="47335086">chach9</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">J'ai eu l'occasion de visiter cette cache lors de mon hivernage en tant qu'agent flore de la réserve naturelle en 2023 lors de la mission 75.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="11.797617" lon="-13.850567"><time>2014-06-22T00:00:00</time><name>GC57XD4</name><desc>Lugajole by eshuishenk</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC57XD4</url><urlname>Lugajole</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="4442337" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Lugajole</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>eshuishenk</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="2672888">eshuishenk</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="42" inc="1">Needs maintenance</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="56" inc="1">Medium hike (1 km–10 km)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="18" inc="1">Dangerous animals</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="43" inc="1">Livestock nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="19" inc="1">Ticks</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Guinea-Bissau</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;div style="background:#eee;border:1px solid #ccc;padding:5px 10px;"&gt;Lugajole, The first geocache of Guinea-Bissau.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;img src="http://imgcdn.geocaching.com/cache/a0a9f4b9-acaa-4ff1-9760-f5dc93052d49.jpg?rnd=0.6930898" alt="House on the hill" /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The indepence of Guinea-Bissau has been signed here on top of the hill next to Lugajole on 24 september 1973. From the village you have a nice view on the small house on the top and once on the top you have a nice view over the Boé area. Despite the significance for the history of Guinea-Bissau this place is barely visited. Nearby you have the chance to see wild animals, including chimpanzees, which nests can be found close to the cache.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can get to the village of Lugajole by car, motorbike or bicycle from Beli. From the village there is a path that leads up the hill, on top go to the left following the ridge. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div style="background:#eee;border:1px solid #ccc;padding:5px 10px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:13px;line-height:1.6;"&gt;Lugajole, A primeira geocache da Guiné-Bissau.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;O indepence da Guiné-Bissau tem perna assinado aqui no topo da colina ao lado de Lugajole em 24 de setembro de 1973. Da aldeia você tem uma bela vista sobre a pequena casa na parte superior e uma vez no topo você tem uma bela vista sobre o área Boe. Apesar da importância para a história da Guiné-Bissau este lugar é pouco visitado. Perto você tem a chance de ver animais selvagens,-incluindo chimpanzés, Tudo que ninhos podem ser encontrados perto do cache.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Você pode chegar à aldeia ou Lugajole de carro, moto ou bicicleta de Beli. A partir da aldeia, há um caminho que leva até o morro, em cima vá para a esquerda seguindo o ridge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div style="background:#eee;border:1px solid #ccc;padding:5px 10px;"&gt;Lugajole, La première géocache de la Guinée-Bissau. &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Le indepence de la Guinée-Bissau a jambe signé ici au sommet de la colline à côté de Lugajole le 24 Septembre 1973. Du village vous avez une belle vue sur la petite maison sur le dessus et une fois en haut vous avez une belle vue sur la zone Boe. Malgré l'importance de l'histoire de la Guinée-Bissau cet endroit est à peine visité. À proximité, vous avez la chance de voir des animaux sauvages, y compris les chimpanzés,-Tout qui nids peuvent être trouvés à proximité de la cache. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Vous pouvez rejoindre le village ou Lugajole en voiture, moto ou vélo de Beli. Depuis le village, il ya un chemin qui mène à la colline, au-dessus aller à gauche en suivant la crête.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Parkia biglobosa</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1156993441"><groundspeak:date>2023-04-05T06:16:16</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="7846286">Dirk De Baene</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Fantastische cache. Grote wandeling naar de top van deze berg ! Favo voor het uitzicht !</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1155764987"><groundspeak:date>2023-03-28T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="28682723">UžMusímeNajítPoklad</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">
I pray for children from Guinea-Bissau</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1153781843"><groundspeak:date>2023-03-17T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="44755140">deanerboy</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">easy find 
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1122041279"><groundspeak:date>2022-08-28T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6288403">soLuna the secret</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Infelizmente não consegui chegar a visitar o local... Mas a ideia é voltar ☺️</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="475273708"><groundspeak:date>2015-01-18T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Unknown</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2672888">eshuishenk</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">After half a year got back to the place for another visit. Hannah and Brecht found the cache after some time looking in a lot of holes and other possible hiding places. The cache endured the whole rainy season without a problem so this one will last for a while! The only thing is that it needs more finds :)

Close to the monument we found some relatively fresh chimpanzee nests and while walking down even heard them in the valley west of the monument!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="2.013217" lon="45.3111"><time>2014-08-08T00:00:00</time><name>GC5AHCX</name><desc>Mogadischu's First by JoeHMontana</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC5AHCX</url><urlname>Mogadischu's First</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="4521132" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Mogadischu's First</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>JoeHMontana</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="5254492">JoeHMontana</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="40" inc="1">Stealth required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Somalia</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;h1 style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Somalia's First!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 style="text-align:center;"&gt;Since Somalia is such a pleasant country I thought it deserves a Geocache. Due to the fact that there was none so far I had to take the initiative.&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2 style="text-align:center;"&gt;The Cache itself is a simple Traditional close to the Airport next to the Indian Ocean.&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2 style="text-align:center;"&gt;Have fun with it....&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;JoeHMontana &lt;img alt="smiley" src="http://www.geocaching.com/static/js/CKEditor/4.4.0/plugins/smiley/images/regular_smile.png" title="smiley" style="height:23px;width:23px;" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="702829060"><groundspeak:date>2017-07-18T20:06:31</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="18990911">Knagur Green</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Due to no response from the CO after the request to maintain or replace the cache, I am archiving it to, stop it showing on the listings  and/or to create place for the geocaching community.

The [Geocache Maintenance guideline](http://www.geocaching.com/about/guidelines.aspx#cachemaintenance) explains a CO's responsibility towards checking and maintaining the cache when problems are reported. Caches that have been archived for lack of maintenance will not be unarchived. This is explained in the [Help Center](http://support.groundspeak.com//index.php?pg=kb.page&amp;id=70)

**If the CO feels that this cache has been archived in error please feel free to contact me  via email quoting the GC number concerned**

Thank you for understanding

Knagur Green
Groundspeak Volunteer Reviewer</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="687874772"><groundspeak:date>2017-05-22T11:54:47</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Unknown</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="18990911">Knagur Green</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">The cache appears to be in need of owner intervention. I'm temporarily disabling it, to give the owner an opportunity to check on the cache, and take whatever action is necessary.  

While I am reluctant to archive the only cache in the country, it does not seem to be available either.

The cache seems to be in a military area, according to the N/A note. If this is so, please note that there are certain criteria that need to be met for military base caches and this are does not full-fill them.

The [Geocache Maintenance guideline](http://www.geocaching.com/about/guidelines.aspx#cachemaintenance) explains a CO's responsibility towards checking and maintaining the cache when problems are reported. Caches that have been archived for lack of maintenance will not be unarchived. This is explained in the [Help Center](http://support.groundspeak.com//index.php?pg=kb.page&amp;id=70)

**Please respond to this situation in a timely manner (i.e., within 30 days) to prevent the cache from being archived for non-responsiveness. If you plan on repairing this cache,but cannot get to it within 30 days, please log a note to the cache page (not email) to let the community know**

Knagur Green
Groundspeak Volunteer Reviewer</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="674794330"><groundspeak:date>2017-04-03T21:27:40</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Didn't find it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="12980193">StuckUSAF</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">6 mile walk around the whole airfield. Looked and looked! I hope it's still there! Cheers. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="671225021"><groundspeak:date>2017-03-19T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Didn't find it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="15637500">Keystone_Arsenal</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I've looked twice for this cache, but have yet to find it.  I wish there were a few more clues.  There is a lot of construction in the area, so maybe it's no longer there.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="661828749"><groundspeak:date>2017-01-22T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1753867">blazek</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Sometimes you can have "bad luck" but sometimes you can also have not "bad luck"... due to the delay of our plane going back to Germany we where so early at the airport that we made it to GZ... 
unfortunatelly not the best area to take a photo ;-) 
Nevertheless some photos of Mogadishu are attached to proove our visit....

TFTC
blazek</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="22.551817" lon="-14.3346"><time>2014-03-25T00:00:00</time><name>GC512KH</name><desc>Awsard by damjanja</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC512KH</url><urlname>Awsard</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="4238804" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Awsard</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>damjanja</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="3036558">damjanja</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="1">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="53" inc="1">Park and grab</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Western Sahara</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>&lt;p&gt;The geocache in the centre of the main village in the middle of the most picturesque area of Western Sahara.&lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;The village of Awsard (fr: Aousserd) is a remote village in the Western Sahara, today's Morocco. The area around is a very interesting part of the desert, both regarding the desert scenery and the Saharawi culture. This makes the village of the Awsard an ideal base for making short visits to the surrounding desert. There is no hotel or camp here at the moment, but you can easilly arrange your stay here if you have your own camping equipment. Alternatively, you can talk to locals and rent a house for a week or two or even more if you want to stay for a longer period of time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For the info on where to go and what to visit, here are some pages that might help you:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;https://www.facebook.com/wsinlands&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;http://www.extrem-sud.com/guides/6-pistes-du-maroc-tome-6.html#descriptif&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;http://www.s-adventure.com/&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Of course you can also write me and ask for advice about the cache.&lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Don't be afraid to ask. Knock, knock!</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1185311629"><groundspeak:date>2023-08-03T07:45:03</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="18990911">Knagur Green</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">At CO request</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1185136813"><groundspeak:date>2023-08-02T10:46:07</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Unknown</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="18990911">Knagur Green</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Greetings

I noticed that this cache has been temporarily disabled for a period of time well in excess of "a few weeks" as contemplated by the cache guidelines. While we feel that the geocaching site should hold the location for you for a reasonable amount of time, we need to let it go at some point.

Please either repair/replace this cache within the next 30 days, or archive it (using the archive listing link in the upper right) so that it no longer shows on lists or so that someone else can place a cache in the area, and geocachers can once again enjoy visiting this location.

The [Geocache Maintenance guideline](http://www.geocaching.com/about/guidelines.aspx#cachemaintenance) explains a CO's responsibility towards checking and maintaining the cache when problems are reported.

 Caches that have been archived for lack of maintenance will not be unarchived. This is explained in the [Help Center](http://support.groundspeak.com//index.php?pg=kb.page&amp;id=70)

**If you plan on repairing this cache, within a reasonable time frame, please log a note to the cache page (not email) to let the community know and so I won't archive the listing.**


Thank you.

Knagur Green
Groundspeak Volunteer Reviewe</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1184208976"><groundspeak:date>2023-07-29T16:54:13</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Needs Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="7680062">Matisons!</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Cache is fixed? No attention from owner for a few years,...</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1099726442"><groundspeak:date>2022-05-28T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="41302891">ObamaBanana</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Oooooon</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1136917985"><groundspeak:date>2022-02-12T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="26634463">EAMteam</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Obrigado ao Owner pela partilha do local e pelo trabalho para nos proporcionar encontrar mais uma caixinha.

#Desde já peço desculpas pelo log generalista e em atraso mas o tempo passado em frente ao computador é pouco.
Mas só agora é que me está a ser possivel colocar os mesmos em dia


TFTC!!
EAM Team
###***PRACTICACITO***###</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="31.0598" lon="-7.9148499999999995"><time>2002-09-27T00:00:00</time><name>GC98C3</name><desc>Djebel Toubkal by Kwentine</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC98C3</url><urlname>Djebel Toubkal</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Virtual Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="39107" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Djebel Toubkal</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Kwentine</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="51987">Kwentine</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Virtual Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Not chosen</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>4.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Morocco</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Views from the highest summit in Western Africa (4165m)</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>To be valid, your log must contain a picture of you with the metallic structure that stands on top of Mount Toubkal.

Our team of five, with a guide, made the climb in 2h15 from the base camp before sunrise.

No climbing equipment was needed in that period of the year but make sure you wear gloves and a winter hat. A cold wind froze us up there.

The view is superb on the surrounding Atlas range, well deserved after a weeklong trek. You can go the short way from Marrakech through Imlil and straight to the base camp (2 days all-way).
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1360748962"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-13T19:22:33</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5787492">nahjo</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">@09:23

Wifey had an idea to celebrate her birthday here - because why not?

So a weeklong trip to Morocco was scheduled and plans were made to summit today. Our group of close to 20 were not as fast as CO 2h15, but let’s just say that we started from the refuge at 05:10 and got up in 4h with crampons and walking sticks (yep that was required no in may!)

Amazing view and thank you for this cache!

Trip was demanding for me since I had little experience above 3000m and we were many who felt the effects of the altitude for the last effort to get up.

Phew we made it!
Greetings from 🇳🇴 </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360746352"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-08T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="18981845">ArThiNo</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Starting off not far from Imlil, we hiked for five days through this beautiful region, with the last days leading to Toubkal (sleeping at the Refuge on the way up) and back to Imlil. The weather was magnificent (even if the wind was cold with plenty of snow still present).
The views were breathtaking, and so was the altitude:-). 
I was fortunately there with a great group supporting each other, and incredibly proud to all have reached the top!
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1355393074"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-16T09:44:09</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1802318">frede67</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Aventure incroyable vers le toit de l’Afrique du nord </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1353271326"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-29T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2302011">oscarcoky</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Espectacular i durissima pujada al cim degut a les fortes ratxes de vent que ens tiraven al terra a molts de nosaltres la darrera hora de pujada ila gran quantitat de neu verge que ens trobem.Fem nit a Mouflons dormint molt poc els dos darrers dies i un cop fet el cim baixem a dormir a Imlil.
Inoblidable aventura en familia !!!!.
El nostre primer 4000 i una sortida de sol de somni....
Tftc</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1348196143"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-08T23:52:17</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8535553">boehmi1988</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">the hardest-earned log ever 🥶</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="-4.934517" lon="11.944017"><time>2010-02-24T00:00:00</time><name>GC23NF1</name><desc>Green Lodge by therali</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC23NF1</url><urlname>Green Lodge</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="1545942" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Green Lodge</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>therali</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="2092367">therali</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="0">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="1">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="33" inc="1">Motorcycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="34" inc="1">Quads</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Congo</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;div style="text-align: center"&gt;&lt;img alt="" style=
"width: 730px; height: 334px" src=
"http://img.geocaching.com/cache/b509de96-fd99-4907-ac37-16262cd68ca6.jpg" /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;

&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;nbsp;The hotel's owner gives the authorization to create this
cache. The hotel has many bungalows in between a wonderfull
tropical greenery. There are, bar, restaurant, lodge rooms, play
area and a swimming pool. You can visit, take a drink, eat or take
a room. You have to search for the cache from monday to friday.
there' too people at the bar on saturday and sunday except 11a.m.
before I tell to the F.T.F. to write on the list book number GC
23NF1. Thank you.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>At the top of a spot</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1150481902"><groundspeak:date>2023-02-23T19:17:33</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="18990911">Knagur Green</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Due to no response from the CO after the request to maintain or replace the cache, I am archiving it to, stop it showing on the listings  and/or to create place for the geocaching community.

The [Geocache Maintenance guideline](http://www.geocaching.com/about/guidelines.aspx#cachemaintenance) explains a CO's responsibility towards checking and maintaining the cache when problems are reported. 

Please note that if geocaches are archived by a reviewer or Geocaching HQ for lack of maintenance, they are not eligible for unarchival. This is explained in the [Help Center](http://support.groundspeak.com//index.php?pg=kb.page&amp;id=70)

If the CO feels that this cache has been archived in error please feel free to contact me within 30 days,  via email or message via my profile ,quoting the GC number concerned

Thank you for understanding

Knagur Green</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1143488195"><groundspeak:date>2023-01-03T13:29:08</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Unknown</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="18990911">Knagur Green</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Greetings 

We have received a request to archive your cache page as the physical cache appears to be in need of maintenance and there has been no recent indication that timely maintenance may be forthcoming.

 I'm temporarily disabling it, to give you an opportunity to check on the cache, and take whatever action is necessary.

You are responsible for occasional visits to your cache to ensure it is in proper working order, especially when someone reports a problem with the cache (missing, damaged, wet, etc.) or posts a Needs Maintenance log. Temporarily disable your cache to let others know not to search for it until you have addressed the problem.

Please enable your cache by selecting 'enable' on the right hand side of the listing , once the cache has been replaced/repaired, or checked that it is still in situ.

The [Geocache Maintenance guideline](http://www.geocaching.com/about/guidelines.aspx#cachemaintenance) explains a CO's responsibility towards checking and maintaining the cache when problems are reported. 

Caches that have been archived for lack of maintenance will not be unarchived. This is explained in the [Help Center](http://support.groundspeak.com//index.php?pg=kb.page&amp;id=70)

If you no longer wish to maintain the cache then the listing should be archived.

**Please respond to this situation in a timely manner (i.e., within 30 days) to prevent the cache from being archived for non-responsiveness. If you plan on repairing this cache,but cannot get to it within 30 days, please log a note to the cache page (not email) to let the community know**

Thank you for understanding 

Knagur Green
Groundspeak Volunteer Reviewer</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1142554898"><groundspeak:date>2022-12-30T12:57:50</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Needs Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="11316465">azonto83</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Cache does not exist any more</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1142510121"><groundspeak:date>2022-12-30T04:17:55</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Didn't find it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="37208246">flynn12345678</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">F</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1142438843"><groundspeak:date>2022-12-29T18:41:38</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Didn't find it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="11316465">azonto83</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Following the last post from 2020 I came here for a sundowner tonight visiting from home in Brazzaville. The box no longer exists sadly</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="-13.340583" lon="-176.18725"><time>2014-09-19T00:00:00</time><name>GC5D7PY</name><desc>Uvea by guillaume.blas</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC5D7PY</url><urlname>Uvea</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="4601206" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Uvea</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>guillaume.blas</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="10577403">guillaume.blas</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="65" inc="1">Yard (private residence)</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Wallis and Futuna Islands</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>&lt;p&gt;Première cache wallisienne&lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;Cette cache est sur un terrain privé mais accueillant. Le chemin pour y accéder est en terre mais facilement accessible à pieds ou en voiture.&lt;/p&gt;
Et le propriétaire a donné son accord pour poser cette cache
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Caché dans le tron creux</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1262161696"><groundspeak:date>2024-09-27T14:45:54</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8351507">KoningMark</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Deze cache was niet op de coördinaten en ook de aanwijzing (hint) klopt niet. De cache hangt. Foto heeft ons uiteindelijk geholpen om de cache te vinden. STF</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1227479474"><groundspeak:date>2024-09-07T00:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="44691708">pacificman</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">WOW, what an unforgettable trip I was able to experience here!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1223435256"><groundspeak:date>2024-03-24T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="7680062">Matisons!</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">### My first cache in Wallis and Futuna Islands! ###

---
Stopped at this cache while visiting **Wallis and Futuna Islands**! [^]
**My #146th visited Geocaching country!**

---

Well, this was quite an adventure.  This morning I traveled to the cache location, but I was attacked by a dog from nearby house. He was only centimeters away from biting my leg. Luckily I managed to hit him with my backpack after which he backed off a bit. Sadly I needed to abort the search. 
As this was the only cache on Wallis island, It was a "must find" for me on this island. I returned to the cache site few hours later with a wooden stick and a muggler friend from the hotel.  Luckily the dog was gone and we were able to search the site. Its very overgrown now and the vegetation have taken over. After 45min search we couldnt find anything similar as mentioned in the hint. After 5 years without finds, Im pretty sure, that the cache is gone and nature has taken over. 
So I put down a new container with fresh logbook. New hiding place is ~22m away from given coords.  
**New coords: S 13° 20.434', W 176° 11.219' attached to the tree. See spoiler images.** 
It was the best option I could find to put a new cache.
One more smiley face for me in the GEO map.[;)]
Thank you for hiding this cache and showing me this place! [;)]

---

Greetings from ***Riga, Latvia***!  [^]
**Happy caching!**

----------

***For a little entertainment, here are 10 Fun Facts about Latvia!*** 

1) Latvia is among the world’s greenest countries.
2) It’s home of the first Christmas tree.
3) The Latvian flag is considered by many to be the oldest national flag in the world.
4) Country has the widest waterfall in Europe.
5) Latvia boasts the finest Art Nouveau architecture in the world.
6) Jacob W. Davis, a Latvian tailor, was an inventor of rivets on famous Jean pants.
7) The Latvian Song &amp; Dance Festival is recognised by UNESCO as the largest amateur song and dance festival in the world!
8) Alexander Laime, a famous Latvian-born explorer. He is most noted for being the first recorded human to reach Angel Falls (highest waterfall on earth), located in Venezuela, by foot.
9) Latvians love basketball and Ice Hockey.
10) Latvia is famous for being the home country of the inventor of the flavor of Pringles.


