Paldies/ Aitäh / Ačiū / Thanks / Merci / Gracias / Danke / Bedankt / ขอขอบคุณ / ধন্যবা / 謝謝 / Tak / Kiitos / ευχαριστίες / תודה / शुक्रिया / Köszönet / Grazie / 感謝 / 감사 / Whakawhetai / धन्यवाद / Dzięki / Obrigado / Mulțumiri / Cпасибо / Hvala / Díky / Teşekkürler / Ngiyabonคุณ / ধন্যবা / 謝謝 / Tak / Kiitos / ευχαριστίες / תודה / शुक्रिया / Köszönet / Grazie / 感謝 / 감사 / Whakawhetai / धन्यवाद / Dzięki / Obrigado / Mulțumiri / Cпасибо / Hvala / Díky / Teşekkürler / Ngiyabon</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="832660812"><groundspeak:date>2019-03-06T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Didn't find it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="24807156">taikawallis</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">ALORS que j'habitais Wallis ,j'ai cherché cette géocache  a plusieurs reprises mais ne l'ai jamais trouvé. l'endroit n'est plus entretenu et la nature dans ces endroits la ,repends vite ça place    je situe ma recherche vers le mois de juin 2018      </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="819023223"><groundspeak:date>2018-12-09T00:40:52</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="23471591">J2MB</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Avec la Team 199 une TTF inespérée sur une île qui ressemble à un petit caillou en plein milieu du pacifique. La population y est d'une très grande gentillesse. De supers paysages. Ca restera un excellent souvenir ! Merci à l'owner pour l'unique cache sur Wallis avec un PF.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="20.519333" lon="-13.061733"><time>2009-01-02T00:00:00</time><name>GC1KEXN</name><desc>Gateway to the Sahara by Neeltje, Jan, Martijn</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC1KEXN</url><urlname>Gateway to the Sahara</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="1092773" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Gateway to the Sahara</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Neeltje, Jan, Martijn</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="2015439">martijnlanenga</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>3</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Mauritania</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>You will find the cache inside a piece of Dutch heritage.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>Before entering the Sahara you need to be well prepared. Inside this cache you will find some of the essentials, according to us, dutchmen. 
At the same time, once you have found the cache, you will be in a place where you can get the best information imaginable for desert travel.

A local resident will assist with cache maintenance if necessary. Details are on file with geocaching.com</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>[hint 1:] Under water
[hint 2:] Made of iron
[hint 3:] Could contain camel milk</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1345755287"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-21T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5097822">didiak22</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Trouvée lors de mon séjour en Mauritanie. 
Belle découverte que c'était endroit et sa propriétaire. 
Cache trouvée avec "l'aide" de 3 allemands en séjour camion à qui j'ai expliqué le principe...</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1343817046"><groundspeak:date>2026-01-30T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="14214008">b2nuts</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">merci pour cette cache facilement trouvée dans ce lieu très reposant.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1337314093"><groundspeak:date>2025-12-08T21:36:24</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="249784">Torgut</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">So we came for the cache but the place is so lovely we decided to stay for the night instead of camping on the dunes as planned. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1337133383"><groundspeak:date>2025-12-07T13:55:30</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="26084866">vekahi</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">During our trip through Mauritanie we found this one !
TFTC 👍
Greetings from St-Job-in’t-Goor 🇧🇪</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1337133066"><groundspeak:date>2025-12-07T13:55:08</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="26524108">vekahi2</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="-77.85271666666667" lon="166.69433333333333"><time>2002-10-29T00:00:00</time><name>GCA252</name><desc>Ross Island by Transantarctic</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCA252</url><urlname>Ross Island</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="41554" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Ross Island</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Transantarctic</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="25809">Transantarctic</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Other</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>3</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Antarctica</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Terrain is volcanic rock and gravel, short steep uphill walk.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>cache is small 4" x 7" aluminum box. Contains logbook and Antarctic trinkets.  I have relocated this cache (02-12-2003) to a bit more scenic area. This is typically a windy spot, so be careful not to let contents blow away. Best to carry container to a side of the ridge with less wind to open. Please hide cache as it was found.
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Continue past historic cross and past yellow geo survey marker (about 50 to 100 ft). cache is in rock crack on right side of trail (as you face South towards White Island) and is visible from trail. For a spoiler picture, go to my webpage to Geocaching section. www.rickpierce.com</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1355114385"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-14T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="10674268">Nelsfam1512</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Learned about this "cool" geocache when earning my last Snow Globe Treasure, which had this cache number on it with an Antarctica scene. What an awesome cache for those who were able to find it! Geocaching truly is world-wide! </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1354778015"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-12T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="40934910">Ark_4_g66</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Looked up because the geocode was listed in the snowglobe treasures. Cool cache!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1340106149"><groundspeak:date>2025-12-30T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3508795">nannibella</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found this because of the treasure pointing to it.
Cool.
Lastet 20 years, which is quite amazing.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1341376895"><groundspeak:date>2025-11-16T12:38:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="27968211">gatsby1211</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I got this GC on the snow globe of the Treasures and figured I look up this cache to see where it is. Wow this is the first Antarctica geocache I know of. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1139552067"><groundspeak:date>2022-11-30T13:29:05</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="25809">Transantarctic</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">No longer able to properly maintain.  Cache removed. Thanks everyone!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="56.87345" lon="24.3018"><time>2003-06-29T00:00:00</time><name>GCGCFM</name><desc>Virtual Kurtenhof by RestonRunner</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCGCFM</url><urlname>Virtual Kurtenhof</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Virtual Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="77553" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Virtual Kurtenhof</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>RestonRunner</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="19754">RestonRunner</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Virtual Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Virtual</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="0">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="37" inc="1">Horses</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Latvia</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>This virtual cache is at the heart of an important if little known World War Two memorial site that reflects the terrible human toll the twentieth century exacted upon Latvia. Today the cache location is open to the public in a state preserved area with open fields featuring statutes, a permanent museum exhibition, and the outlines of structures.  It is about 18 kilometers southeast of Riga, Latvia.  </groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>NOTE: A "virtual cache" is a location (usually without a logbook). "Cache finders" wishing to claim this site should answer the following question: What is the aural symbol which ummistakably reminds you of what existed and was lost in this place of pain.  Extra points for reporting the "frequency" of the aural symbol.  The answer is obvious to a geocacher who successfully reaches the correct coordinates of the virtual cache. Logged entrys on the website should be accompanied by a separate email to the "cache hider", which correctly answers the question, to assure the 'cache seeker's entry is not deleted.
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>You are in center of the Kurtenhof death camp in Salaspils, a facility run by Nazi Germany in Latvia from 1941 to October 1944 where over 100,000 people perished. Standing on the cache, at the narrow north end of the black marble block, you hear in the eerie silence a sound which you must identify. Extra points if you can tell how many repetitions of the sound occur per unit of time. Post a photo of yourself at the site, if you can!</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1360104715"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-08T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="15328769">sidi.aitutaki</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Very atmospheric and peaceful place. TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1356301030"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-20T15:15:43</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="13096215">clashed mules</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">In unserem Urlaub als Geocacher im Wohnmobil durch Europa‘s Osten haben wir dieses Jahr Polen, Litauen, Lettland und Estland als Reiseziele ausgewählt. Neben der Standardausrüstung haben wir zusätzlich auch noch Fahrräder, Kanu und Angel mitgenommen. Somit waren wir für viele Herausforderungen gut gewappnet.

Beim Besuch der Gedenkstätte haben wir auch den Cache **Virtual Kurtenhof** aufgesucht. Nachdem die Frage beantwortet wurde, stehen wir nun in diesem virtuellen Logbuch und dürfen uns über ein Smiley 🙂 mehr auf der Landkarte freuen!

Viele Grüße 🙋🏼‍♂️🙋🏼‍♀️ aus Salzgitter Bad 🇩🇪 vom Team [clashed mules](https://www.geocaching.com/profile/?"u=clashed%20mules").

Vielen Dank an den Owner **RestonRunner** für das Herlocken 🙂. 

Geloggt mit Cachly und 📱
🗓 :  20.04.2026 
⏱ :  15:15 
🛢 : #16097

Zum Zeitpunkt des Logs hatte dieser Virtual die D/T Wertung von 1.0/1.0.
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1351053049"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-24T20:31:45</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="12493323">Justyui</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Place is incredible🇱🇹</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1345416050"><groundspeak:date>2026-01-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="52586031">CherryQween</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Atradu </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1338153103"><groundspeak:date>2025-12-17T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="29570504">ingo2222</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Atrasts</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="-17.3843" lon="-66.135283"><time>2003-06-04T00:00:00</time><name>GCG8Q4</name><desc>Cristo de la Concordia Cache by Team Brenkert</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCG8Q4</url><urlname>Cristo de la Concordia Cache</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Virtual Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="73941" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cristo de la Concordia Cache</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Team Brenkert</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="111517">On The Brenk</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Virtual Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Virtual</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Bolivia</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>This virtual cache is located by the Cristo de la Concordia statue on a hill overlooking Cochabamba, Bolivia.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>This is a great place to go either day or night.  You can see the statue from almost anywhere in the city.  By day, there's a great view of the valley and mountains surrounding Cochabamba.  At night, the light display from the city is breath-taking.

The terrain is rated a 1.5 simply because of the altitude (9,500').  You can take the tram to ride to the top or hire a taxi.  If your athletic, hike to the top.  Once you're on the top, the rest is easy.  

The coordinates lead you to a plaque showing different statistics for the statue.  To get credit for the cache, take a picture of yourself with your GPS from the coordinates shown, either with the plaque or witht he statue in the background.  No pictures from farther away.  Good luck and enjoy the view.</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1361531921"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-14T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="15159952">madybetune</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Petite escapade en Bolivie...merci pour cette belle découverte </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360766479"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-13T16:26:28</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="50258163">Watwulldu</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Tftc.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1344354488"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-08T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8963181">Lemonhope</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Trobat

Ens apropem a la zona aprofitant uns dies de vacances 

El cache Cristo de la Concordia Cache ha sortit ràpid i bé.

Faig fotolog 

Moltes gràcies Team Brenkert  per ensenyar el lloc.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1340527141"><groundspeak:date>2025-12-20T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5310011">valeetje</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false"> We (Valeetje and VCX1302) were fortunate enough to spend 45 days in South America. We started our trip in Brazil. From there, we headed to Paraguay, Argentina, Uruguay, Chile, and finally, Bolivia. We mostly picked the cherries off the cake, taking lots of excursions in a rental car or tour van. We were able to enjoy all that beauty thanks to geocaching. Thanks to all the contributors who are part of this. I think my buddy's log is much more comprehensive; enjoy our story there!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1331070047"><groundspeak:date>2025-10-21T11:47:42</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="111296">de trije susters</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">

Today we went up this hill more specific for the virtual cache here, the oldest cache of Bolivia. Bit of a pity this was not the best day to go here. They were working on the platform with cars and with cranes to fetch something here. So all pictures were spoiled with this material.
But besides that it was a good (geocaching) day for me. I 'found', or better in this case visited my my 84th (geocache) country  and today was the 62th time i also found the oldest cache of the country.
Thanks.
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="-12.7754" lon="45.28305"><time>2015-11-25T00:00:00</time><name>GC3V4VD</name><desc>Dziani #1 - Départ by Lefax</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC3V4VD</url><urlname>Dziani #1 - Départ</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="3138672" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Dziani #1 - Départ</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Lefax</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="9295571">cuecas83</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Micro</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="42" inc="1">Needs maintenance</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="0">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="2" inc="1">Access/parking fee</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="0">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="0">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="27" inc="0">Drinking water nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="33" inc="0">Motorcycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="34" inc="0">Quads</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="35" inc="0">Off-road vehicles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="46" inc="0">Trucks/RVs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="37" inc="0">Horses</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="38" inc="0">Campfires</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="36" inc="0">Snowmobiles</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Mayotte</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>Le site incontournable de Petite Terre est le lac Dziani. Ce lac de cratère, situé au cœur de l'île, est très facile d'accès. La route mène quasiment au bord, et il suffit de quelques minutes à pied pour dominer cette grande étendue d'eau émeraude. Résistez à la tentation de descendre au fond du cratère : l'eau est sulfureuse, donc nauséabonde, et les moucherons y pullulent. Longez plutôt le sentier qui contourne le lac, vous aurez un très beau point de vue à la fois sur le cratère et sur le lagon tout proche.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/large/4c0a0e24-a8e5-417f-88b0-105647771529.jpg" /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Cette cache est la première d'une série de 4 qui vous fera faire le tour de ce superbe lac.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Suspendue
Je n’empêche pas de passer a pied</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1243225472"><groundspeak:date>2024-06-30T09:34:20</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2469856">miguaine</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Bonjour cuecas83,

Cache archivée définitivement pour permettre éventuellement à un autre géocacheur d'en placer une dans le secteur.

Cordialement,
Miguaine - "Geocaching HQ Volunteer Reviewer"</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1237266673"><groundspeak:date>2024-05-30T09:18:02</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Unknown</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2469856">miguaine</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Bonjour,

Pour garder tout son intérêt au jeu, il est souhaitable que les caches soient opérationnelles. En effet, quelle déception de ne pas trouver une boîte, car elle a disparu ou est en très mauvais état.
Le propriétaire d'une cache a la possibilité de désactiver une cache lorsqu'elle rencontre un problème et il peut lui même la réactiver lorsqu'il en a fait la maintenance.

Les derniers logs sur votre cache semblent indiquer qu'il y a un problème. Il serait souhaitable d'y faire une visite de maintenance. J'ai donc procédé à sa désactivation temporaire.
Lorsque vous aurez réalisé la visite de maintenance ou si vous estimez qu'elle n'est pas nécessaire (cache très difficile à trouver, autre…) n'hésitez pas à la réactiver vous-même en sélectionnant "Activer" sur la page de la cache.

Sans action de votre part, cette cache sera archivée d'ici un mois.

Merci de votre compréhension.

Cordialement,
Miguaine - "Geocaching HQ Volunteer Reviewer"</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1237185610"><groundspeak:date>2024-05-29T19:21:26</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Needs Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="49842675">TimeToCleanUp</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Cache missing. Owner does not respond to multiple maintenance logs</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1233866650"><groundspeak:date>2024-05-13T18:51:50</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Unknown</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="11344369">Atomstroemchen</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This geocacher reported that the cache might be missing.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1233866639"><groundspeak:date>2024-05-12T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Didn't find it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="11344369">Atomstroemchen</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Un nouveau séjour d'aventure avec Picht. La troisième étape après Paris et La Réunion est Mayotte. Nous n'avons qu'une journée, mais avons pu faire un tour (guidé par la gendarmerie) autour du cratère. Une belle région mais le climat était très fatiguant pour nous.
A la fin du tour du cratère, nous sommes restés en arrière pour trouver aussi cette boîte. Mais comme les cachers précédents l'ont déjà écrit, il n'y a rien à trouver ni à la barrière ni à l'arbre.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="13.4228666666667" lon="-16.7040333333333"><time>2004-09-24T00:00:00</time><name>GCKMGP</name><desc>Tarima Kendolu (Good friends together) by klaproos</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCKMGP</url><urlname>Tarima Kendolu (Good friends together)</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="174647" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Tarima Kendolu (Good friends together)</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>klaproos</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="175194">klaproos</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="42" inc="1">Needs maintenance</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Gambia</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>     &lt;div align="center"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vriendschap is&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div align="center"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;een&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div align="center"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Spiegelbeeld&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div align="center"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;waarin je jezelf&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div align="center"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ontdekt&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
 
&lt;div align="center"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vriendschap is blij zijn met de
overeenkomsten en respect hebben voor de
verschillen.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div align="center"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;True friendship can be found in the
most unlikely places.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
 
&lt;div align="center"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Show me your friends and I’ll tell you
who you are.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
 
&lt;div align="center"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Friends are the family you choose
yourself.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;font color="#0000ff"&gt;In januari 2004 gingen wij (Roy, Jolanda en
Hansje) als een soort uit de hand gelopen grapje voor een lang
weekend naar Gambia, West-Afrika. Via een site boekten wij vanuit
Nederland een gids die ons zou vergezellen in Gambia. Na onze reis
hebben we zelf een site gemaakt &lt;a href=
"http://www.boyleigh.com/"&gt;boyleigh.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;font color=
"#0000ff"&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Nooit hadden wij op dat moment gedacht dat wij hiermee een ware
vriend zouden ontmoeten. Vanaf de kennismaking met Boy Leigh tot
aan ons vertrek hebben we er met z’n vieren een feest van gemaakt.
Met het prachtige landschap van Gambia als achtergronddecor
ontwikkelde zich een vriendschap die zich niet alleen tot dat ene
weekend zouden beperken. Gemeenschappelijke waarden als respect
voor jezelf en anderen, liefde voor de natuur, reizen, geocaching
en nieuwe indrukken en vooral de slappe lach vormden de basis van
een langdurige en oprechte vriendschap. Daarom was het besluit om
in juni 2004 weer terug te keren naar Gambia, en natuurlijk dus
naar Boy Leigh, niet moeilijk om te nemen. Boy Leigh, die inmiddels
bovengemiddeld enthousiast was geworden over geocaching, wilde
dolgraag nog tweede cache (eerste cache Tubaab-Moofijo) beheren en
dan ook het liefst bij hem en zijn familie op hun compound. Het
thema voor deze cache was dan ook niet moeilijk te verzinnen en
resulteerde dus in de Tarima Kendolu (Good friends together) cache.
Loop deze cache dan ook in de sfeer waarin hij gecreëerd is en denk
aan en eer je ware vrienden tijdens de speurtocht naar deze
cache.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
 
&lt;div align="center"&gt;&lt;font color="#0000ff"&gt;&lt;img width="70%"
     src="http://img.groundspeak.com/cache/b4ab93e3-129b-4784-9dcd-810511974fe5.jpg"&gt;
&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;div align="center"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Friendship is&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div align="center"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;a&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div align="center"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;mirror reflection&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div align="center"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;in which you discover&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div align="center"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;yourself.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
 
&lt;div align="center"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Friendship is to be happy with the
similarities and to have respect for the
differences.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;font color="#0000ff"&gt;In January 2004 we (Roy, Jolanda en Hansje)
went to The Gambia – West Afrika- for a weekend. due to a joke that
got out of hand. Via a website we booked from The Netherlands a
guide who would accompany us in The Gambia. After our holiday we
made a own side &lt;a href=
"http://www.boyleigh.com/"&gt;boyleigh.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;font color=
"#0000ff"&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Never in our wildest imagination would we have suspected at that
time we would meet a true friend because of this. Right form the
start when we met up with Boy Leigh until our departure the four of
us made a big party of our time there. With the beautiful scenery
of The Gambia acting as a background decorum a friendship developed
that would not only be limited to that particular weekend. Shared
values like respect for oneself and others, the love for nature,
travel, geocaching and new impressions en certainly also the
roaring with laughter formed the base of a true and long
friendship. Because of this the decision to return to The Gambia,
and of course to Boy leigh, in June 2004 was not a hard one to
make. Boy leigh, who in the meantime has become an overenthusiastic
geocacher himself, was keen on managing his own second cache,
preferably at his and his family’s compound. (first cache named
Tubaab-Moofijo) The theme for this cache was not very hard to find
and therefore resulted in this Tarima Kendolu (Good friend
together) cache. Do this cache in the spirit in which it was
created and think of and honour your true friends while you search
for the cache.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Loop door de rode poort / Walk through the red entrance porch.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="745408477"><groundspeak:date>2018-02-06T10:31:54</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="175194">klaproos</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Helaas door verhuizing is er geen cache meer aanwezig op dit compound.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="744801415"><groundspeak:date>2018-02-02T18:00:26</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Unknown</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="7855632">lunaa's beetle - LB</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Ook wij kwamen 2 x voor n gesloten rode poort waar ogenschijnlijk niemand meer woont 
De buren die wij zagen wisten van geen cache 
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="744779273"><groundspeak:date>2018-02-02T15:06:12</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="19039177">Sterre15</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Wel/niet gevonden wel gelogd... kregen hulp in de buurt. Mensen wonen er jammer genoeg niet meer </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="744357273"><groundspeak:date>2018-01-29T14:03:21</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="15826743">geertenchris</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">De ontbrekende foto.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="743946518"><groundspeak:date>2018-01-27T21:22:19</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="15826743">geertenchris</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Hier samen met onze taxichauffeur aan alle deuren liggen te roepen waar we uiteindelijk de vrouw des huizes te pakken kregen maar helaas zij wist er niets van af .
Ook zat er een zeer groot slot op de poort .hierbij een foto van de plaats en hopelijk is dat voldoende om er een smiley meer op de kaart te plaatsen </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="4.19605" lon="-52.152333"><time>2011-05-16T00:00:00</time><name>GC2WC1G</name><desc>Savane-roche Virginie by Snabelabe</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC2WC1G</url><urlname>Savane-roche Virginie</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Earthcache</type><groundspeak:cache id="2251858" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Savane-roche Virginie</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Snabelabe</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="3193265">Snabelabe</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Earthcache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Not chosen</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="56" inc="1">Medium hike (1 km–10 km)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="9" inc="1">Significant hike</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="11" inc="1">May require wading</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>French Guiana</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Fr: Earthcache près de Régina, 8km aller retour&lt;br /&gt;
Eng: Earthcache near Régina, 8km hike to go and return</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;font size="24"&gt;ENG:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
In between the vast stretches of tropical rainforest there are a
few patches of rock spread out over French Guiana, these are called
inselbergs, which is German for Island-mountains. These inselbergs
are parts where the Guiana shield sticks out through the
soil.&lt;br /&gt;
The Guiana shield is a 1.7 billion year old remnant of the South
American plate; it has survived the merging and rifting of the
tectonic plates. The Guiana shield Stretches from Colombia over
Venezuela, Guyana, Suriname, French Guiana and Brazil.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;img src=
"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fd/Guiana_shield.png/800px-Guiana_shield.png" /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Wherever the soil on top of the Guiana shield has eroded, the
granite of the shield appears as an Inselberg. These inselbergs
have allowed a very specific vegetation to develop, because they
are isolated from each other, have small surfaces, have a lack of
nutrients and experience great extremes in temperature and
humidity. Many litophytes (plants growing on rocks), orchids and
succulents grow there, adapted to the lack of nutrients and
extremes in temperature and humidity, on these bare rocks. This
type of vegetation is called savane-roche
(&amp;ldquo;rock-savanna&amp;rdquo;), many of the species in this
vegetation type are only found in a few places, due to the scarcity
and small surface of savane-roche areas.&lt;br /&gt;
An easily accessible example of such an inselberg is savane-roche
Virginie, which is located a few kilometers east of Régina. You can
park along the RN2 between Régina and St.Georges near the
trailhead. The walk is very nice and around 4km long (one way), it
took us around 2 hours to walk there, with lots of breaks and photo
shooting and 1 hour to walk back down hill, with fewer breaks. The
walk isn&amp;rsquo;t very difficult, but one has to go over a few trees
and cross some streams, so good (waterproof) shoes are recommended.
A bottle of water is really needed for this trip!&lt;br /&gt;
If you want, you can download a gpx-track of the hike &lt;a href=
"http://en.wikiloc.com/wikiloc/view.do?id=1869551"&gt;here.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
To log this earthcache, you must:&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take a picture of yourself at these coordinates with your GPS
(see example picture) and post it with your log. (optional)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Send me a message with the height in meters your GPS
indicates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Give some reason that can explain the erosion on this
inselberg, send the answer in a message to me.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Go to N04° 11.796 W052° 09.122, here you will see in intrusion
of quartz in the granite (see photo), try to explain why the quartz
sticks out from the granite? Also send me this answer in your
message.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;font size="24"&gt;FR:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
En Guyane, il y a entre la forêt tropicale quelques plaques de
roche étalé, ce qu'on appelle des inselbergs, le terme allemand
pour des « îles-montagnes ». Ces inselbergs sont des pièces où le
bouclier guyanais dépasse le sol.&lt;br /&gt;
Le bouclier guyanais est une reste, qui a 1,7 milliards années, de
la plaque sud-américaine, il a survécu à la fusion et la distension
de la tectonique des plaques. Le bouclier guyanais s'étend de la
Colombie au Venezuela, Guyana, Suriname, Guyane et le Brésil.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;img src=
"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fd/Guiana_shield.png/800px-Guiana_shield.png" /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Partout où le sol au-dessus du bouclier guyanais a érodé, le granit
du bouclier guyanais apparaît comme un Inselberg. Ces inselbergs
ont permis de développer une végétation très spécifique, parce
qu'elles sont isolées, ont de petites surfaces, l&amp;rsquo;absence
d'éléments nutritifs et des extrêmes de température et d'humidité.
Beaucoup de litophites (plantes qui poussent sur les rochers), des
orchidées et des plantes succulentes y poussent, adaptée à
l'absence d'éléments nutritifs et des températures et humidités
extrêmes, sur ces rochers nus. Ce type de végétation est appelé
savane-roche, de nombreuses espèces dans ce type de végétation ne
se trouvent que dans quelques endroits, en raison de la rareté et
lesde petites surfaces du savane-roche.&lt;br /&gt;
Savane-Roche Virginie est un inselberg facilement accessible, qui
est situé à quelques kilomètres à l'est de Régina. Vous-pouvez vous
garer le long de la RN2 entre Regina et Saint Georges, près du
début du sentier. La promenade est très agréable et environ 4km de
long (aller simple), nous avons eu besoin de 2 heures pour y aller
à pied, avec beaucoup de pauses et des photos et 1 heure pour
redescendre la colline, avec moins de pauses. La marche n'est pas
très difficile, mais il faut traverser quelques arbres et quelques
cours d'eau, donc des chaussures imperméables sont recommandées.
Une bouteille d'eau est vraiment nécessaire pour ce promenade
!&lt;br /&gt;
Vous pouvez télécharger un itinéraire gpx &lt;a href=
"http://fr.wikiloc.com/wikiloc/view.do?id=1869551"&gt;ici.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prenez une photo de vous-même à ces coordonnées avec votre GPS
(cf. photo) et le poster dans votre log. (facultatif)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Envoyez-moi un message avec la hauteur en mètres que votre GPS
indique.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Donnez quelques raisons qui peuvent expliquer l'érosion sur ce
inselberg et envoyez la réponse dans ce message.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Allez à N04 ° 11.796 W052 ° 09.122, ici vous pouvez voir une
intrusion de quartz dans le granit (cf. photo), Essayez
d&amp;rsquo;expliquer pourquoi le quartz dépasse le granit? Envoyez-moi
cette réponse dans votre message.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;a href="http://s09.flagcounter.com/more/kqLF"&gt;&lt;img src=
"http://s09.flagcounter.com/count/kqLF/bg=FFFFFF/txt=000000/border=CCCCCC/columns=8/maxflags=248/viewers=0/labels=0/pageviews=1/"
alt="free counters" border="0" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1265113931"><groundspeak:date>2024-10-13T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="32486104">asinodiburidano</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I have been on this Inselberg twice and it is still one of the most beautiful and fascinating experiences of my life. We hanged our hammocks and spent the night here, to watch the sunrise in the next morning. A night in the forest is always fascinating and scary at the same time, but it is a great experience. Pity that some people come here only to drink, and laugh loudly, which I really cannot explain (why not doing it in the city? Why not simply contemplating and respecting nature?). Anyway, after a long time since my last visit, I took the chance of the EC day to finally do my homework and complete this long overdue cache. I am very glad there is one in such a special place. Thank you!!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1254758199"><groundspeak:date>2024-08-20T02:22:36</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="50327689">LosDeQuiCau139</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Merci pour cet EarthCache.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1251121387"><groundspeak:date>2024-07-27T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="9724688">Vader&amp;zoon</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We were eager to fulfill this only Earthcache in French Guiana. We were short on time though and we doubted if we should do it or not. We decided to go for it and hiked up in 1 hour and 20 minutes. We observed everything the best we could and sent our answers to the CO.

Thanks and greetings from The Netherlands</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1247469907"><groundspeak:date>2024-07-20T17:48:57</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="32918860">TAMAMR</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Merci pour la cache, c’est notre première en Guyane ! Nous avons beaucoup apprécié la balade dans la jungle ainsi que la belle vue au niveau du cache. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1204895147"><groundspeak:date>2023-11-10T07:35:44</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="44307451">Chris_AE</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Randonnée très agréable et beau panorama une fois atteint la savane-roche</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="5.174983" lon="-59.481383"><time>2009-10-23T00:00:00</time><name>GC206AP</name><desc>Kaieteur Falls by Tequila</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC206AP</url><urlname>Kaieteur Falls</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Earthcache</type><groundspeak:cache id="1442020" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Kaieteur Falls</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Tequila</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="11556">Tequila</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Earthcache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Not chosen</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="0">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="40" inc="0">Stealth required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="21" inc="1">Cliff/falling rocks</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Guyana</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>&lt;center&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#347235"&gt;Kaieteur Falls is
located on the Guiana Shield in Guyana&amp;rsquo;s Kaieteur National
Park&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/center&gt;
.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;center&gt;&lt;img src=
"http://img.geocaching.com/cache/34efa627-1e7f-4f02-b981-c78c42840a22.jpg"
alt="Kaieteur Falls" /&gt;&lt;/center&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
At roughly two billion years old, the Guiana Shield is the
earth&amp;rsquo;s oldest surface. Covering approximately 75,000
km&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;, this area includes a large mountain plateau and
tropical rainforest that is part of a vast watershed between the
Amazon and the Orinoco rivers. One of the distinctive features of
the Guiana Shield are its distinctive plateaus or tabletop
mountains also known as tepuis &amp;ndash; remnants of sandstone
sediments that covered the metamorphic rocks.
&lt;p&gt;Kaieteur Falls first free fall drops 226 m before flowing over a
cascade of falls bringing the total fall to 251 m. Five times
higher than Niagara Falls, two times higher than Africa&amp;rsquo;s
Victoria Falls, Kaieteur Falls, with its great height and enormous
water flow at 663 meters&lt;sup&gt;3&lt;/sup&gt;/second is considered one of
the most powerful waterfalls in the world.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The surrounding area is also unique in that one can see
endangered species, some of which live in very specific
microhabitats.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;In order to log this cache, you must complete the following
tasks:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
1. Determine the answers to the following questions and submit them
to me in an email (not in the log below):&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
a) Your estimate as to how wide the falls are at their top
edge.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
b) The direction in which the Potaro River flows.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
c) Your elevation at the falls.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
d) The name of the endangered species that spends its entire life
in one plant and the name of this plant.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;When you log your visit you may optionally:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
1. Upload a photo of yourself with Kaieteur Falls in the
background,&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
and&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
2. Upload a photo of yourself with the Potaro River valley below
Kaieteur Falls in the background.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1354607612"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-06T15:28:23</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="18919286">Gabrielol</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">For many people, this was the highlight of the trip. I would say its one of the most majestic sights ive ever seen- and had been excited for months. We landed at the nearby airstrip and thankfully had sunny skies. Which was surprising since our last few days in Georgetown were quite dreary. Our indigenous guide Deandre did a good job explaining the surroundings and taking down the ancient rock face toward the three lookouts.

When we got to the first lookout, I couldnt help but exclaim wtf out loud, to no one in particular. I was floored. It wasnt just the falls, but the surprise rainbow at the bottom, the meandering river outward, the impossibly beautiful view of the landscape beyond. My brain just could not comprehend the towering cliffs to my left, and how ancient the whole view felt.

We were in a bit of a time crunch, so we hurried to the next stop. The views got better as we went on and I thankfully got my nikon d90 to start working. I took about 200 pictures but also tried to budget time to just stare longingly at the falls, lost in absorprion. On the way down to the final look out, our guide asked the group where we were all from. He only seemed to care about where I was from, as the only American. He told me he really wanted to visit, to see the “American Girls”. I chuckled.

The final lookout was sublime and I was able to get all the answers. Our local guide told us it was the most brown he had seen the water, and he comes here every few weeks. We hiked back up to the ranger station and got ready to board our plane back to civilization. This has to be one of the world’s coolest earthcache sites. thanks!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1346993501"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="14602126">Fransisquet TEAM</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Me gusta mucho las caídas de agua y me ha encantado conocer una más. Gracias por mostrarnos un nuevo rincón del planeta que sin geocaching no hubiera descubierto.  Registro tras haber enviado las respuestas al propietario. 

---
&gt;No devores caches, millor assaborix-los.

Gracies *Tequila* per amagar i mantindre este caché.
**Gracies a este Earthcaché**  *Kaieteur Falls*, D 1.0/T 5.0, **ya son 2992 anecdotes viscudes 🐺**</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1346817569"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-15T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="7680062">Matisons!</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Stopped at this cache while visiting **Guyana**! [^]
**My #168th visited Geocaching country!**

---

Place was visited, answers were collected and picture was taken.
One more smiley face for me in the GEO map.😉
I learned about this waterfall many years ago, while watching some documentaries. It was always on my "must do" list, if i ever visit Guyana. Now I was finally able to visit this remote location and see this wonder with my own eyes.
+1 FP from me.
Thank you for hiding this cache and showing me this place! 😉

---

Greetings from ***Riga, Latvia***!  [^]

----------

***For a little entertainment, here are 10 Fun Facts about Latvia!*** 

1) Latvia is among the world’s greenest countries, with over 50% of its territory covered by forests and  around 3,000 small lakes dotted around the country.
2) Latvia is home of the first Christmas tree.
3) Latvia’s flag is one of the oldest in the world. Even though the state of Latvia was only founded in 1918, its flag dates back to 1279 and is one of the three oldest in the world. 
4) Latvia is home to Europe’s widest waterfall. It is called the Ventas Rumba and it is 249 metres across.
5) Latvia boasts the finest Art Nouveau architecture in the world.
6) The world’s first spy camera was invented in Latvia in 1937. It was called the VEF Minox and it was a film camera that was only 8.73mm wide.
7) The Latvian Song &amp; Dance Festival is recognised by UNESCO as the largest amateur song and dance festival in the world with over 40,000 participants.
8) The character Crocodile Dundee is based on a Crocodile Harry, a true croc hunter from Latvia!
9) Jeans were invented by a Latvian tailor called Jākobs Jufess in 1873, who was backed by Levi Strauss.
10) The national animal of Latvia is actually an insect called the two-spotted ladybird.

----------
**Here are some words and phrases in Latvian:**

* **Hello**: Sveiki
* **How are you**: Kā tev iet?
* **What is your name**: Kā tevi sauc? 
* **My name is**…: Mani sauc...
* **Where are you from**: No kurienes Jūs esat?
* **I am from:** Es esmu no...
* **Please**: Lūdzu
* **Sorry**: Atvaino! 
* **Thank you**: Paldies
* **Yes**: Jā
* **No**: Nē
* **Goodbye:** Uz redzēšanos

