Thanks for showing this place😃.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="-18.972217" lon="-169.836283"><time>2007-10-15T00:00:00</time><name>GC16PXP</name><desc>Kapihi Water Supply Bore (Niue) by alsjfs</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC16PXP</url><urlname>Kapihi Water Supply Bore (Niue)</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Earthcache</type><groundspeak:cache id="713179" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Kapihi Water Supply Bore (Niue)</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>alsjfs</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="401694">alsjfs</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Earthcache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Other</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="1">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="14" inc="0">Recommended at night</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Niue</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>This EarthCache on the island of Niue is 220 metres from the sealed road around the island via a level dry weather bush road.
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;Niue is a large upraised coral atoll about 64km in circumference, with an area of 260 sq km. It lies in the South Pacific Ocean 560km SE of Samoa, 380km E of Tonga and 2400km NE of New Zealand. Using Google Earth is a good way to see the location of Niue, and you can zoom in right down to the enclosure around the bore at the cache site.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Niue is internally self-governing in free association with New Zealand.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is on the route of yachts that are island hopping across the Pacific, and is serviced by weekly flights from New Zealand.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Most of the island’s coastline rises steeply to a terrace at 20m above sea level, then rises again to an undulating central plateau at around 60m asl. The capital, Alofi, and villages on the western side have been established on the lower terrace, while those on the northern and eastern coasts are on the upper terrace.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Below sea level the island consists of more than 500m of limestone underlain by a caldera-shaped volcanic structure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is no public transport on the island, but bicycles, motor cycles and cars are available for hire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A third of the rain that falls on Niue percolates through the coral/limestone rock to form a fresh water lens under the island, sitting on the saline groundwater below. The size of this has been estimated at around 30 million cubic metres, or 3 months worth of recharge from rainfall.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Water is lost from the lens at the coast from seepage, and from springs in chasms and coastal caves. At low tide this flow can be observed at Matapa Chasm. Total outflow has been estimated at 4000 litres per second.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Early domestic water supplies were via rainwater collected from roofs, in some cases a village supply with a reservoir beneath a large roof. The present reticulated system comes from reservoirs supplied by 16 of the 25 bores drilled down to the fresh water lens. Total extraction from all the bores averages 26 litres per second.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For permission to claim this cache: Go to the Kapihi bore (N119B), in dry weather you can drive right to it. The land at the bore is privately owned, and there is no need to enter the fenced enclosure. Do not interfere with the pump, as this bore supplies water to the village of Mutalau. Please do not leave any rubbish here, or remove anything from the site.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Note the altitude at the site from your GPS (or just use the information above), then assuming that the lens is only a few metres thick at this bore, how far below the ground surface will the water level be?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;0-10 metres,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;10-20 metres,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;20-30 metres,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;40-50 metres,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;50-60 metres, or&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;60-70 metres.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email us the answer to the question, and explain briefly why bore water is used for the reticulated supply rather than any alternative source. If your GPS gave you an altitude reading, then include that also. You can log your find immediately, we will only reply to your answer if there is a problem.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(Technical information is from the South Pacific Applied Geoscience Commission (SOPAC) Technical Report 372, Niue Coastal Water Quality and Groundwater Resources Assessment)&lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1340093708"><groundspeak:date>2025-12-30T05:38:36</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="544348">emandel</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thank you for placing this informative Earth cache here!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1309939077"><groundspeak:date>2025-07-11T16:26:07</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1504360">gernita</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This was the last cache for us to attempt on Niue so we decided to do it today. We have had so much fun learning about the island through the earthcaches here. TFTC 😊</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1304917874"><groundspeak:date>2025-06-14T16:15:32</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="11531517">barefootguru</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Air New Zealand had an islands special on, and Niue sounded like an amazing off-the-beaten-track experience with HeiheiNZ, and an easy fun way to fulfil some country based challenges.

After the orientation tour by Keith &amp; Sue I left Heihei to further snorkeling off a boat while I circumnavigated the island gathering more caches.

The long grass tickled the bottom of the car as I drove to GZ.  Answers calculated and sent in.  Cool facts, great to get the oldest cache on Niue 💦</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1290904965"><groundspeak:date>2025-04-12T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2125672">Proton26</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This was an easy task to do for this EC. Thanks for the lecture and the cache!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1249198528"><groundspeak:date>2024-07-27T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6033905">tramyard</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Another Eartcache on Niue. Many thanks for interesting lesson about water supply on the Island.
I'm logging this hide as my 10685 find. 
Many thanks alsjfs for a placement.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="14.167567" lon="145.239333"><time>2008-07-16T00:00:00</time><name>GC1E8NW</name><desc>ROTA'S GIFTED FARMER by Ungkulu - Adopted by JIMP59</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC1E8NW</url><urlname>ROTA'S GIFTED FARMER</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="937841" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>ROTA'S GIFTED FARMER</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Ungkulu - Adopted by JIMP59</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="1297028">jimp59</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Northern Mariana Islands</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>If you’ve always wanted to take a short trip to our neighbor island “Rota” a cache awaits you there.  This beautiful Island offers so much for those who love to explore. The friendliness and greetings is one of their most unique trades.  Known to many as “The Friendly Island”.   Don’t forget to wave back. You’ll see what I mean by that.  [:D].  If you love to golf, I suggest you bring along your clubs, the resort has one heck of a awesome course. [:D]</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>Rota’s  Gifted Farmer ~San Isidro, known as the saint of farmers and the PatronSaint for the village of Sinalapo, once used as a farming area, now called home for residents of Rota.

Rota’s Gifted Farmer~San Isidro was a day laborer,  working on the farm of the wealthy 
He was steady and hard-working,  He shared what he had, even his meals, with the poor. He often gave others more than what he had for himself. 

FTF: Lincoln awaits you.
**CONGRATULATIONS TO Feisty.Butterfly FOR BEING FIRST TO FIND**</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>In a circle of beautifully maintained hedged plumeria plants, under plumeria hedged bush, behind a rock. 
</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="707676262"><groundspeak:date>2017-08-03T14:13:53</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3675695">Greatland Reviewer</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Hello:

This cache page has been archived due to the lack of response to one or more prior Reviewer Note(s) about issue(s) with the cache. If the owner would like to have the cache unarchived, please contact me through my profile as soon as possible before another cache gets placed nearby.

Please note that unarchiving a cache page requires it to go through the same review process as a newly proposed cache, using the cache placement guidelines currently in effect.

Regards,

Greatland Reviewer
Groundspeak Volunteer
My Profile: http://www.geocaching.com/profile/?guid=6354843d-6bec-4737-8db5-77907f57de8a</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="665419087"><groundspeak:date>2017-02-18T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3675695">Greatland Reviewer</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Dear Cache Owner, 

I have been going through caches that have multiple "DNF" (did not find) logs, which is often a sign that a cache is missing.   Generally cachers avoid hunting a cache with many DNF logs, so it is a good idea for the Cache Owner to check the cache and either replace it or post a log to the cache page to tell fellow geocachers that the cache is still ready to be found.   No action by the Cache Owner may result in a cache being archived to keep the cache from appearing in local Pocket Queries. 

Please contact me if you have any questions.

Regards,

Greatland Reviewer
Groundspeak Volunteer
My Profile: [http://www.geocaching.com/profile/?guid=6354843d-6bec-4737-8db5-77907f57de8a](http://www.geocaching.com/profile/?guid=6354843d-6bec-4737-8db5-77907f57de8a)</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="589326448"><groundspeak:date>2016-04-08T18:51:19</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Didn't find it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5338281">monkeysnolonger</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Did not find. I believe it was removed when the landscaping was changed as there are no longer plumeria bushes. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="584444261"><groundspeak:date>2016-03-26T15:01:14</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Didn't find it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8574660">NavyMac</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Our second look of the day. No luck w/ Leah671</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="584059977"><groundspeak:date>2016-03-22T00:22:38</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Didn't find it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5318894">Leah671</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Another no find of the day :(</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="13.8376" lon="-61.0453"><time>2009-10-29T00:00:00</time><name>GC20DP6</name><desc>Qualibou caldera - Drive-in volcano (ü99)  by unoyt</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC20DP6</url><urlname>Qualibou caldera - Drive-in volcano (ü99) </urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Earthcache</type><groundspeak:cache id="1449103" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Qualibou caldera - Drive-in volcano (ü99) </groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>unoyt</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="293134">unoyt</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Earthcache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Not chosen</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="1">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="2" inc="1">Access/parking fee</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="30" inc="1">Picnic tables nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="27" inc="1">Drinking water nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="26" inc="1">Public transportation nearby</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Saint Lucia</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;img src=
"http://img.geocaching.com/cache/bc94619c-2c86-4207-8e0d-a5a476196327.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;
________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: normal" align="center"&gt;
&lt;span style=
"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: Verdana,sans-serif; color: black"&gt;The
St Lucia volcano, also called the St Lucia sulphur springs is said
to be the only drive-in volcano in the world. The last minor
eruption occurred in the late1700&amp;rsquo;s. It was only a steam
eruption but not one with magma and ash.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: normal" align="center"&gt;
&lt;span style=
"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: Verdana,sans-serif; color: black"&gt;In
the 1830&amp;rsquo;s approximately 760 tons of sulphur was mined and
exported. Although there are signs of activity going on, for
example the boiling mud, water and steam that emerge from the
crater, the St Lucia volcano is dormant.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: normal" align="center"&gt;
&lt;span style=
"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: Verdana,sans-serif; color: black"&gt;&amp;nbsp;There
are several pots of boiling water that are above the normal boiling
point. There are also many colors at the surface as a result of
sulfur, iron, calcium oxide, copper oxide, magnesium, carbon and
other mineral deposited there.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: normal" align="center"&gt;
&lt;span style=
"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: Verdana,sans-serif; color: black"&gt;The
caldera is believed to be connected to the ocean because of
increase reaction during a full moon which causes high
tides.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: normal" align="center"&gt;
&lt;span style=
"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: Verdana,sans-serif; color: black"&gt;The
islands of the eastern Caribbean are linked via a volcanic arc, but
the St Lucia volcano is different because the water has therapeutic
qualities. You will find people who go to bath there in order to
remove blemishes on their skin.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: normal" align="center"&gt;
&lt;span style=
"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: Verdana,sans-serif; color: black"&gt;Walking
in the crater is now prohibited after one of the guides fell in a
pool of boiling water when he was jumping up and down on it.
Fortunately, it was only waist height, so he was rescued but he did
suffer from some severe burns from the waist down.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: normal" align="center"&gt;
&lt;span style=
"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: Verdana,sans-serif; color: black"&gt;There
is a very strong smell of sulfur that comes out of it. It is weak
during the day but very strong at nights. You can smell it for
miles away at nights but that is a good thing. If the smell goes
away, then that would mean that there is going to be a volcanic
eruption.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: normal" align="center"&gt;
&lt;span style=
"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: Verdana,sans-serif; color: black"&gt;The
St Lucia volcano is located in Soufriere. The people of Soufriere
pride themselves on having the only drive in volcano in the world
right at their door steps. In fact, there are people living within
the perimeter of the craters.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: normal" align="center"&gt;
&lt;font size="2"&gt;&lt;span style=
"font-family: Verdana,sans-serif"&gt;_________________________________________________________________________________________________________&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: normal" align="center"&gt;
&lt;a id="ImageUploadPanel1_ImageViewPanel1_lnkPhoto" title=
"Click for larger image" target="_blank" href=
"http://img.geocaching.com/cache/1bcfb0d3-3a05-46bb-b150-3771e6d91ac6.jpg"
name="ImageUploadPanel1_ImageViewPanel1_lnkPhoto"&gt;&lt;img style=
"BORDER-RIGHT-WIDTH: 0px; BORDER-TOP-WIDTH: 0px; BORDER-BOTTOM-WIDTH: 0px; BORDER-LEFT-WIDTH: 0px"
title="Click for larger image" alt="Inside the caldera" src=
"http://img.geocaching.com/cache/1bcfb0d3-3a05-46bb-b150-3771e6d91ac6.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: normal" align="center"&gt;
&lt;font size="2"&gt;&lt;span style=
"font-family: Verdana,sans-serif"&gt;___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: normal" align="center"&gt;
&lt;font size="2"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana,sans-serif"&gt;Be
careful on your way to the coordinates and keep your
left.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: normal" align="center"&gt;
&lt;font size="2"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana,sans-serif"&gt;The
stairs are slippery and are not calibrated.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: normal" align="center"&gt;
&lt;font size="2"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana,sans-serif"&gt;Take
note that a 8,00$US fee per person is required.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: normal" align="center"&gt;
&lt;font size="2"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana,sans-serif"&gt;In
order to log as a find, you will have to complete the tasks bellow
and send me your answers for validation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: normal" align="center"&gt;
&lt;font size="2"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana,sans-serif"&gt;What
is the type of gas coming out of the spring?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: normal" align="center"&gt;
&lt;font size="2"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana,sans-serif"&gt;Can
you see the Pitons from the above coordinates?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: normal" align="center"&gt;
&lt;font size="2"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana,sans-serif"&gt;What
does the smell remind you of?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: normal" align="center"&gt;
&lt;font size="2"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana,sans-serif"&gt;What
is the size of the caldera in square kilometers?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: normal" align="center"&gt;
&lt;font size="2"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana,sans-serif"&gt;What
is the elevation at the posted coordinates?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: normal" align="center"&gt;
&lt;font size="2"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana,sans-serif"&gt;What
is the distance from the posted coordinates and the first sulfur
spring?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: normal" align="center"&gt;
&lt;font size="2"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana,sans-serif"&gt;Post a
picture of you and your gps with the gas in the
background.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: normal" align="center"&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="949574817"><groundspeak:date>2020-07-28T22:25:22</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="293134">unoyt</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Merci pour vos visites
Thank you for your visits</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="911742850"><groundspeak:date>2020-03-04T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5720146">GeoJinx</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We had intentions of finding at least one cache while we were on the island, and that had already been done when we visited this location.  It wasn't until we were on our way home that we realized we had missed doing this earth cache while at the location.  TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="910329404"><groundspeak:date>2020-02-27T10:11:18</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="732304">Tank Hounds</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Was here on our tour of the island today. So beautiful. Answers sent. TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="910072761"><groundspeak:date>2020-02-25T07:08:26</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5721053">geo alex</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Second day in this interesting island 💝We splept in a appartement in Soufriere.  We are here for the week. Favorite point for
sure 👌TFTC 😊Merci pour la cache ;) Greetings from Montréal Québec 🇨🇦 ✌️</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="911292073"><groundspeak:date>2020-02-21T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="385852">Ramsey63</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found while on a tour of St. Lucia from the cruise ship, Crown Princess.  It was a beautiful day with only a slight breeze; thus, it was not too smelly here today.  Our guide was very nice and presented us with a lot of interesting information about the area we were in.  The bubbling mud and/or water pots reminded me of Yellowstone Park.  I really enjoyed my visit here.  TFTC.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="11.246033" lon="-60.698383"><time>2004-04-08T00:00:00</time><name>GCJ8HK</name><desc>Cuffie River Motmot by Snowy Owls </desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCJ8HK</url><urlname>Cuffie River Motmot</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="133352" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cuffie River Motmot</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Snowy Owls </groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="222303">Snowy Owls </groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="42" inc="1">Needs maintenance</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Trinidad and Tobago</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>You can drive to this Cache which is on private property. the road is unpaved and winding. The cache is in sight of the buildings.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>The cache was placed on April 8th 2004. The snowy owls put art work in the cache from the family. There are five little pictures. &lt;P&gt;

&lt;font size =1&gt;
The cache was placed with the permission of the property owner, who we are in contact with.  She will do any maintenance that might be required in our absence.&lt;/font&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Where humming birds feed up a carved set of stairs you'll find the tree that cradles our cache.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1338997188"><groundspeak:date>2025-12-17T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1161062">IndianaundJones</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We had deliberately saved this cache for the return journey from Castara to Bon Accord, and we found the location, off the main road, quite intriguing. When we arrived on site, the GPS showed a very clear spot, but it didn’t match the pictures in the hint. 
So, we expanded our search radius, and suddenly, we found ourselves in the middle of this paradisiacal estate. We quickly and safely discovered the stash where the container with the yellow screw-on lid should have been, but the cache itself was nowhere to be found. 
Disappointed, we left the area and walked back to the car. I couldn’t and didn’t want to settle for a DNF, so at the spot where the Garmin had initially shown the stash, I switched to climb mode once again—more out of sheer desperation than anything else... 
The joy was indescribable when I finally found that huge container. I quickly climbed over and peeked inside... unfortunately, there was water damage, but inside the container, I found a screwed PET container, which, though sealed, was also wet inside. 
I logged on a piece of paper I had brought. To my great joy, there were also some travel bugs in the container, so I was able to take two TBs and a coin. This cache was the last one I found out of the four active caches on Tobago at that time, and so Tobago, along with the German island of Borkum and the Greek island of Rhodes, now joins my personal "Cleared Islands" list.

TFTC by IndianaundJones</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1296597918"><groundspeak:date>2025-03-26T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1292731">TNT_Duck</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">De férias do outro lado do oceano em Trinidad e Tobago, houve tempo para encontrar alguns tesourinhos nesta fantástica ilha [:)]!
Na companhia de um grupo de amigos, a busca destes tesourinhos, permite-nos sempre encontrar recantos que de outra forma passariam despercebidos [;)]
Uma semana maravilhosa, sempre com muito sol e muito calor, com uma temperatura de água do mar sempre em volta dos 27 graus [:8D] 
A caixinha foi fácil de encontrar [:D]!
Obrigado ao owner por este geotesourinho!
On vacation across the ocean in Trinidad and Tobago, I had time to find some little treasures on this fantastic island [:)]!
In the company of a group of friends, the search for these little treasures always allows us to find corners that would otherwise go unnoticed [;)]!
A wonderful week, always very sunny and very hot, with a sea water temperature always around 27 degrees [:8D]!
The cache was easy to find[:D]! In a very nice place!
Favorite!
Thanks to the owner for this treasure!
Greetings from PORTUGAL
&gt; A cache a day keeps the Shrink away [:P]

Due to a hurricane, some trees fell. I placed a new container at the following coordinates:
N 11º 14.737
W 60º 41.904

</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1248856129"><groundspeak:date>2024-07-26T16:20:29</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1299204">jboreal</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">TFTC - both original and 2022 replacement! As previously mentioned, the log was wet so I did my best (JB) but don’t have a dry log or paper with me so couldn’t fix the issue. Used some jungle gym action to get to the cache- thanks for the adventure.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1244554940"><groundspeak:date>2024-07-06T16:13:02</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="21217503">MAGICN3</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Came to T&amp;T for a bit of relaxation and visiting old haunts. Out caching with Mauibabe1. Fun oldie. Signed as M&amp;M on wet log. Thanks to Snowy Owls  for the nice hide. TFTC. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1249624065"><groundspeak:date>2024-07-06T16:13:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="21256375">Mauibabe1</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Out caching with MAGICN3. First find in Cambodia. Signed as M&amp;M.  Thanks to Snowy Owls  for the nice hide. TFTC. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="21.776917" lon="-72.171733"><time>2009-02-23T00:00:00</time><name>GC1N0WA</name><desc>The "HOLE" by Chod</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC1N0WA</url><urlname>The "HOLE"</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Earthcache</type><groundspeak:cache id="1138859" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>The "HOLE"</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Chod</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="393487">Chod</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Earthcache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Not chosen</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="23" inc="1">Dangerous area</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="21" inc="1">Cliff/falling rocks</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Turks and Caicos Islands</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;font color="red"&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;b&gt;EXERCISE CAUTION, NO GUARD RAIL PRESENT.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/b69d1d32-be2f-45c9-9147-b89c85e14b3a.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;The “HOLE”&lt;/b&gt; is a large opening in the Earth’s surface found on Seasage Hill Drive in the vicinity of Long Bay. It has been attracting the curious for years. In the past, ropes were available for the adventurous who wanted to take a dip in its uncharted alluring waters. Unfortunately the water is now strewn with litter and those ropes are gone. &lt;b&gt;DO NOT ATTEMPT TO REACH THE WATER&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Future plans for this national landmark call for the erection of a viewing platform by &lt;b&gt;The Turks and Caicos Islands National Trust&lt;/b&gt;. A small gift shop may also be erected on the site.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;font color="red"&gt;&lt;b&gt;EXERCISE CAUTION, NO GUARD RAIL PRESENT.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To claim this &lt;b&gt;EarthCache&lt;/b&gt; answer the following questions via an E-mail to my profile &lt;b&gt;AND&lt;/b&gt; post a picture of your vsit with your log.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;#1. What type of rock is associated with this geological feature?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;#2. What is a ’hole’ like this commonly called?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;#3. What in your estimation is the average diameter of the surface opening?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;font color="blue"&gt;&lt;b&gt;AND NOW FOR THE FUN PART&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please post any one of the following three photos with your log.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;#1. Yourself or your group with a recognizable portion of the ‘HOLE’ visible in the background.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;#2. Yourself or your group at the roadside sign for the “HOLE”.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;#3. Yourself or your group at the adjoining lot’s roadside sign.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Many &lt;b&gt;"THANKS"&lt;/b&gt; to &lt;b&gt;Brengt Soderqvist&lt;/b&gt; of &lt;b&gt;Provident Limited&lt;/b&gt; for allowing this location to be listed as an &lt;b&gt;EarthCache&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;b&gt;And the&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;font color="red"&gt;"First To Find"&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;HONOR goes to&lt;/b&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color="blue"&gt;&lt;b&gt;buzio&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/614c9174-74ad-42f8-a327-e0c4b57121cd.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;font color="red"&gt;&lt;font size="5"&gt;&lt;b&gt;EXERCISE CAUTION, NO GUARD RAIL PRESENT.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;font color="red"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
.&lt;/font&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1355922524"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-19T00:54:34</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="49103451">BestieMaidATX</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Unexpected roadside attraction !</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1351365641"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-27T09:57:07</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="45694000">sillybilly42</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">very cool</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1341901118"><groundspeak:date>2026-01-15T13:53:33</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="22398282">AFamCachers</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">AFam Cachers, the family, visited this cache during our first ever trip to the Caribbean. Posting this in our family account because most of our family is here, and we found the cache in honor of the one who is not. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1341560067"><groundspeak:date>2026-01-11T06:31:06</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="84876">Buck Schwartz</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thanks for bringing us here.
Our local driver refused to go see the hole….he called it ‘creepy’
Answers sent</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1339142597"><groundspeak:date>2025-12-25T14:22:37</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="416320">ncbiscuit</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I’m visiting the Turks and Caicos with my extended family and after a lovely Christmas brunch, I drove over here to see the Hole. What a big hole it is! Email with answers sent. TFTC!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="-34.408617" lon="-57.876117"><time>2006-02-02T00:00:00</time><name>GCT9NT</name><desc>Vineyard Cache - Wood and Wine by alejolucas</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCT9NT</url><urlname>Vineyard Cache - Wood and Wine</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="342980" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Vineyard Cache - Wood and Wine</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>alejolucas</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="511529">alejolucas</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Uruguay</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Small Tupperware container at the lake!</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>I've spent some days in this resort and loved it!
We talked to the owner about geocaching, and she allowed us to place one in the resort. (She put a coupon for a free bottle of wine in the cache!)
It's near a lake, a small wooden bridge and a beatiful landscape!
You don't have to, but it's better if you go to the lobby and ask for permission to look for the cache.
Have fun!

I've noticed some people sneaking in from a hole in the fence.... 
They built a fence after I placed the cache, but it's closed most of the time.
Please enter the resort through the main entrance @ -34.406671+-57.872972 to avoid misunderstandings...
( Check this link for entrance location: http://maps.google.com/maps?q=-34.406671+-57.872972 )
The owners are very kind to let me place the cache and have no problem letting people in to look for it. Just let them know you are there for the cache.

Alejo.//

Added Oct 12, 2010: After reading finder's logs I would advise to do some research and plan ahead your stay at W&amp;W. It's not expensive, and most, if not all, of the finders would have liked to stay there for a night or two. You can call them and find about availability/rates in advance.</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>There may be some rock removal, but not too much...</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1359527354"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-06T17:23:50</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="9684855">dadid</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">What a nice place! At the reception nobody knew about the cache, not even about Geocaching.in general. The Manager was called and he was as clueless as the attendant. Anyhow, the attendant walked with us to ground zero where we found the petling with ist log stripe. There was a change of ownership one year ago, therefore no one knew about the cache. We logged and stayed for Lunch which was great. TFTC and lovely greetings from Germany.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1359502059"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-06T14:19:05</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="9684782">CaveDuRoi</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Very nice Place where we found the Cache . Thanks for showing us the Place. Favorit
 Point for this Place. Greetings from Germany </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1343456001"><groundspeak:date>2026-01-31T12:36:25</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="288856">Aix sponsa</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found this cache after taking a taxi from the ferry port. The two people showed the direction to head. It was a quick find at GZ. The first cache in Uruguay for me.
Headed south from the States a little south of Canada. Much warmer and more pleasant in Uraguay. TFTC! ⛅ Few Clouds 🌡️77°F 💧57% 🌬️12 mph</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1343454062"><groundspeak:date>2026-01-31T12:24:02</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1270379">lostcheq</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Gracias 🙂. Visiting Argentina with Aix sponsa and Mocrin   Beautiful day for caching.  Checked in at the winery first for the way to the geocache. 
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1343453750"><groundspeak:date>2026-01-31T12:21:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3848418">Mocrin</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Staying in Buenos Aires for a few days, took the ferry across to grab the oldest cache in Uruguay. Success! What a beautiful day! Hello from Minnesota, USA.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="41.6163" lon="69.9746"><time>2009-02-14T00:00:00</time><name>GC1MNKF</name><desc>My First Uzbecian by Miss Elli und Sir Molch</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC1MNKF</url><urlname>My First Uzbecian</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="1129006" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>My First Uzbecian</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Miss Elli und Sir Molch</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="823217">Miss Elli und Sir Molch</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="0">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="1">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="33" inc="1">Motorcycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="34" inc="1">Quads</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Uzbekistan</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>This is the first GEOCACHE in Tashkent region. 
It was dropped to this beautiful country site while visiting the country for business.

You will find a cachecontainer tupperwarestyle close to the main road. Parking area less than 100 m away.

If there is a need for maintenance it will be done by my local friend.

New cache location due to roadworks:
N41° 36.925 E69° 59.285
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1357724814"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-28T13:15:29</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Didn't find it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1906640">terrasax</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Leider nicht gefunden. 
Terrasax </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1330811762"><groundspeak:date>2025-10-20T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="9724688">Vader&amp;zoon</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We had to reach a bit but then we found the oldest cache of Uzbekistan.

Thanks and greetings from the Netherlands!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1324651796"><groundspeak:date>2025-09-17T18:03:57</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Didn't find it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="10702368">PilsetnieksLv</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Went to the geocaching location and there is a wall, no way to go to other side of the wall. Then went to the other location which is mentioned in the cache description, there was a lot of trash but no cache. So total DNF.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1325580214"><groundspeak:date>2025-08-29T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="9299178">reimyo</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Finnish group touring Kazakstan, Kyrgyzstan, Uzbekistan &amp; Tajikistan. TFTC.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1323152381"><groundspeak:date>2025-08-29T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3578026">geobora</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This my first Uzbekistan traditional cache and to hard one. We had watches previous logs where people beware local police and penalty. When we arrive by car there was police and walked further away. Then try to reach cache area from forest side and avoid to be seen from road by police. Luckily polices had gone away and we have change to search cache. Luckily hint photo help me and the cache was found! 

This has logged with sm07, Jynu and reimyo. Greetings from Finland, TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="4.40275" lon="18.5234"><time>2015-06-14T00:00:00</time><name>GC5XGE4</name><desc>Bangui la coquette - M'poko le foyer du soldat by anais.chris</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC5XGE4</url><urlname>Bangui la coquette - M'poko le foyer du soldat</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="5056447" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Bangui la coquette - M'poko le foyer du soldat</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>anais.chris</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="10422848">Anaïs.Chris</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Micro</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="23" inc="1">Dangerous area</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="18" inc="1">Dangerous animals</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Central African Republic</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>Bangui la coquette, surnommée depuis peu, Bangui la roquette ! Ceci est la première cache posée dans le pays. &lt;img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/48/Bangui_Shopping_District.jpg" /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;La ville a été fondée le 26 juin 1889&lt;sup&gt;[&lt;/sup&gt;dans ce qui était la colonie française du Haut-Oubangui, appelée plus tard Oubangui-Chari et qui faisait partie de l'Afrique-Équatoriale française. Nommée ainsi par le nom de ces rapides, la ville a grandi grâce à la proximité d'un poste militaire français situé sur le fleuve Oubangui. Bangui servait de centre d'administration à l'époque coloniale et continue toujours d'être le centre administratif de la République centrafricaine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;En mars 1981 ont eu lieu à Bangui des violences généralisées suite aux élections, après l'Opération Caban menée par les Français pour déposer l'empereur centrafricain Bokassa I&lt;sup&gt;er&lt;/sup&gt; et le remplacer par David Dacko. Les opposants du président mis en place par les Français se sont réunis dans la ville de Bangui et l'ont obligé à fuir le pays. Son successeur, le général André Kolingba suspend la constitution et met en place la transition avec le « Comité Militaire pour le Redressement National » mais instaure de fait une dictature militaire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;En mai 1996, environ 200 soldats de la république centrafricaine se sont mutinés dans la ville de Bangui, exigeant des arriérés de salaires et l'abdication d'Ange-Félix Patassé. Dans la foulée, les renégats ont pillé et tué plus de 50 personnes. Suite à cela, des troupes françaises stationnées dans le pays ont réprimé la rébellion et ont rétabli le pouvoir dictatorial.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Après avoir été élu, le président Patassé a annoncé un gouvernement d'union nationale au début de 1997. La même année, des troupes rebelles ont refusé de donner une base militaire à la ville de Bangui et en juin a éclaté une nouvelle révolte.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;En mars 2003, le général François Bozizé a pris le pouvoir par un coup d'État mettant fin à la présidence de Patassé. La situation dans la ville, parfois surnommée « République de Bangui » s'est depuis améliorée.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Début 2013, lors de la prise de pouvoir par Michel Djotodia, les troupes de la Seleka entrent dans Bangui en mars 2013, les affrontements font plusieurs dizaines de morts entre les troupes de sécurité sud-africaines et les miliciens. Alors que le pays s'enfonce peu à peu en 2013 dans des violences communautaires, des miliciens anti-balaka entrent dans Bangui, démarrant la bataille de Bangui. Les affrontements et représailles pendant tout le mois de décembre font plusieurs centaines de morts alors que les troupes françaises et de la MISCA tentent de ramener le calme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;De mai 2013 à janvier 2014, le maire est Catherine Samba-Panza, devenue chef de l'État de transition.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;img src="http://www.defense.gouv.fr/var/dicod/storage/images/base-de-medias/images/operations/autres-operations/republique-centrafricaine/07-09-10-visite-du-comfor-ffg-en-rca/visite-du-comfor-ffg-en-rca-3/805782-1-fre-FR/visite-du-comfor-ffg-en-rca-3.jpg" /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
Vous êtes ici dans la camp de M'poko, au foyer du soldat.
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
Cette cache est au sein d'une zone contrôlée, autorisation correcte et les informations d'authentification sont nécessaires
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
De passage seulement dans le pays, merci aux geocacheurs en transite de bien vouloir effectuer la maintenance si nécessaire.
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>La maison de Mickey</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1273929691"><groundspeak:date>2024-12-20T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5977033">olivier88200</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Mpl</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1245531544"><groundspeak:date>2024-07-11T17:49:47</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="48097734">Pawel0s</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Tftc</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1265708703"><groundspeak:date>2024-06-04T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="17109921">regis57</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Danke für den Cache ♦ Thanks for that Cache ♦ Merci pour la Cache ♦ Gracias por el Cache♦

thanksthanks for that Cache🇬🇧/🇺🇸 - Merci pour la Cache🇫🇷- Dzięki za Cache🇵🇱 - Grazie per questo Cache🇮🇹 - Takk for at Cache🇳🇴 - Obrigado por isso Cache🇵🇹 - Gracias por el Cache🇪🇸 - Díky za keš🇨🇿 - Ačiū už tą talpyklą🇱🇹 - Paldies par šo Cache🇱🇻 - Aitäh selle eest Cache🇪🇪 - Спасибо за то кэш🇷🇺 - Kiitos, että Cache🇫🇮 - Tack för att Cache🇸🇪 - Tak for denne Cache🇩🇰 - Hvala cache🇸🇮 - Ευχαριστώ για τη μνήμη cache🇬🇷 - 感謝您的高速緩存🇨🇳 - Köszönjük, hogy a cache🇭🇺 - Bedankt voor de cache🇳🇱 - Graças para o cache🇵🇹</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1228662557"><groundspeak:date>2024-04-20T17:57:05</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="28081059">Strubali</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">👍 </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1121907973"><groundspeak:date>2022-08-27T18:26:29</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="40456303">cameroonie7063</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Cool</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="-12.169466" lon="44.394926"><time>2015-04-25T00:00:00</time><name>GC5T6QB</name><desc>Le grand Escalier de Mutsamudu ! by bastoon11</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC5T6QB</url><urlname>Le grand Escalier de Mutsamudu !</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="4957750" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Le grand Escalier de Mutsamudu !</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>bastoon11</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="4224489">bastoon11</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="0">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="0">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Comoros</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;La cache se trouve à peu près au milieu entre le départ et la fin de l'escalier (environ une centaine de marches). Le départ commence au niveau de la médina, le mieux est de demander votre route aux passants (demandez "l'escalier" tout simplement) afin qu'on vous guide à travers les ruelles de la médina. Vous n'avez plus qu'à grimper les marches juqu'au niveau de la plateforme panoramique avec une superbe vue sur Mutsamudu ! &lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Dans un angle / In the corner</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1126105590"><groundspeak:date>2022-09-16T17:08:16</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4224489">bastoon11</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Cette cache n'existe plus et je suis rentré en France depuis plusieurs années maintenant ...</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="817765176"><groundspeak:date>2018-11-26T09:27:44</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Unknown</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4224489">bastoon11</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">La cache est malheureusement introuvable desormais emportée par les eaux ou bien volée :/</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="515789437"><groundspeak:date>2015-06-28T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Unknown</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4224489">bastoon11</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">La cache est toujours en place et en bon état ! On attend le premier géocacheur qui fera une découverte aux Comores !!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="508985767"><groundspeak:date>2015-06-05T08:17:42</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Unknown</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3066566">ROTSIP</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Published</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="34.944267" lon="69.257267"><time>2006-06-26T00:00:00</time><name>GCWV3K</name><desc>FLYRFN's Something to do cache by FLYRFN</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCWV3K</url><urlname>FLYRFN's Something to do cache</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="418335" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>FLYRFN's Something to do cache</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>FLYRFN</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="232152">FLYRFN</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Micro</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="0">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="40" inc="1">Stealth required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>3</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Afghanistan</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>A micro cache just for something to do!
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>A container located about 7 feet off the ground, well protected from the elements. There’s no need to go up any stairs, but a pull up may be required for the vertically challenged, please remember the Bagram caching rules; if you found it please help maintain it. Be very careful of the RLB porch muggles that are across the street 24-7. This one is the closest of the Bagram cache’s to the USO. Have fun caching and return home safe.
&lt;p&gt;FTF: K5 Flyer-Eagle River, Alaska.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.wunderground.com/global/stations/40948.html?bannertypeclick=bigwx"&gt;&lt;img src="http://banners.wunderground.com/weathersticker/bigwx_both_cond/language/www/global/stations/40948.gif" border="0" alt="Click for Kabul, Afghanistan Forecast" height="60" width="468" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>It's above your head when standing on the ground.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1124249755"><groundspeak:date>2022-09-06T17:07:01</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="18990911">Knagur Green</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">

Western Advisory Personnel have now withdrawn from the camp, and reinstated it to the local authority.Therefore permission to have a geocache placed in this area is no longer covered by the blanket agreement.

The caches in this area served their purpose and it is time to retire them .

We thank all who found them for their service</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="966687282"><groundspeak:date>2020-09-25T07:21:35</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2114388">dowjr</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Got this before the traffic gets too busy. Thanks for placing the cache, it awesome that we can cache over here. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="966508289"><groundspeak:date>2020-09-24T08:18:14</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2114388">dowjr</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Muggle factor high this morning but will try this afternoon. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="959580906"><groundspeak:date>2020-08-30T15:56:36</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4412366">kahall4860</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Nice!!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="955049016"><groundspeak:date>2020-08-16T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3101560">WorkerDrone</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Came at the right time.  No muggles in the immediate vicinity.  Had to feel quite a few places before I finally noticed the telltale sign and then found it right away.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="-38.6535" lon="-71.6453"><time>2002-02-27T00:00:00</time><name>GC3FCD</name><desc>Araucaria in Conguillio by Amaruit</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC3FCD</url><urlname>Araucaria in Conguillio</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="16333" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Araucaria in Conguillio</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Amaruit</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="27978">amaruit</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="0">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="33" inc="0">Motorcycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="34" inc="0">Quads</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="35" inc="0">Off-road vehicles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="31" inc="1">Camping nearby</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Chile</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>In the Conguillio National Park, a 15 minute walk from the Visitor Center, at the foot of a big monkey puzzle tree ( Araucaria araucana )&lt;br /&gt;
En el Parque Nacional Congillio, a 15 minutos del centro de informacion, al pie de un gran arbol de Araucaria.&lt;br /&gt;
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>From the visitor center, take the Self-guiding Educative Trail Las Araucarias. After the small bridge take to the left and follow your GPS. A 10 minute walk will take you to a large Araucaria tree ( 1.5 m diameter ). The cache is in a small 6" x 4" tupperware with a yellow lid, concealed inside a natural hole in the tree-trunk. The hole is in the east side of the tree.&lt;br /&gt;
Cheers&lt;br /&gt;
Am&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Desde el Centro de informacion tome el Sendero educativo Autoguiado Las Araucarias. Al cruzar el puente, tome hacia la izquierda siguiendo su GPS. Una caminata de 10 minutos lo llevara a un gran arbol de Araucaria ( 1.5 m de diametro ). En un hueco natural en la corteza del arbol, lado este, esta escondido un recipiente plastico de 15 cm x 8 cm con tapa amarilla.&lt;br /&gt;
Saludos&lt;br /&gt;
Am&lt;br /&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1359785570"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-08T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="10414500">damorend</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Emocionante encontrar un caché tan antiguo, y en un lugar increíble. Ojo que es crucial caminar por el escorial desde el punto mencionado en otros comentarios (S 38° 39.139' W 071° 38.966'), y evitar salirse del sendero por el bosque, para no dañar la vegetación. Ya está mal salir del sendero, al menos hagamoslo mitigando lo más posible el impacto. Mucho cuidado especialmente con los brotes de araucarias. El contenedor está dañado y rompiéndose cada vez más con cada manipulación, ojalá la próxima persona pueda traer un tupper nuevo. Gracias por el cache, le doy un punto favorito!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1344802606"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-12T16:33:29</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="50034444">bike_pato</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">excelente geocachin, debo mencionar que se encuentra en el sendero los contrabandistas, una vez avanzado los 10 min y estando a unos 200 mrs del sendero , debes buscar la araucaria</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1339308000"><groundspeak:date>2025-12-04T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1077498">Dani+Iris</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">#2161
We were puzzled by the monkey that did not climb this tree
But this was the one cache that was definitely on our wishlist for our Chile trip, not only because it is already an oldie but also because of its location in this national park we wanted to visit.

And yes, this is the perfect "traditional cache", the way we like it: 
- not an easy grab but takes some effort to get to
- takes you to a site of exceptional beauty and a place you wouldn't have experienced without the cache
- not an obvious straight line but a bit of an adventure to get to
- ...

Do not take the direct / shortest route from the path but take the route indicated in the Pacmess log: "go to the point S 38° 39.139 W 071° 38.966. There you turn right and walk ten meters through some higher plants. After that you will find the path leading you to the tree". This was a very nice track to the tree.

And yes... the tree is really worth checking out as it as really impressive.

A +1 favo point from us. Well deserved!

A little note on cache maintenance: the container is broken so take care (or replace it if possible)</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1336347496"><groundspeak:date>2025-11-29T20:58:02</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="14982450">Skyantric</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">En un recorrido por la fascinante y variada Sudamérica visitamos 🇺🇾🇦🇷🇨🇱🇧🇴&amp;🇨🇴. 
Descubrimos muchos paisajes y lugares magníficos. Por supuesto, el mapa de geocaching también nos atrajo a muchos otros lugares interesantes y nuevos puntos destacados donde había cachés como este. 
En nuestros registros siempre utilizamos espacios libres entre otros.
Gracias por diseñar el caché.
Saludos cordiales de nuestra parte, los suizos 
🇨🇭 🇨🇭 🇨🇭SKYANTRIC🇨🇭 🇨🇭 🇨🇭

El desvío hacia este escondite, un poco apartado del camino habitual, fue una delicia. Las coordenadas son exactas, pero la clasificación T1 es completamente errónea. Un favorito para esta hermosa ubicación

Auf einer Rundreise durch das faszinierende und abwechslungsreiche Südamerika besuchten wir 🇺🇾🇦🇷🇨🇱🇧🇴&amp;🇨🇴. 
Dabei entdeckten wir viele grandiose Landschaften und Sehenswürdigkeiten. Natürlich lockte uns auch die Geocaching Karte an viele weitere interessante Orte und neuen Highlights bei denen es Caches wie diesen hier gab. 
Bei unseren Logeinträgen nutzen wir immer auch freie Stellen zwischen anderen Logeinträgen.
Besten Dank fürs Auslegen des Cache.
Herzliche Grüsse von uns Schweizer 
🇨🇭 🇨🇭 🇨🇭SKYANTRIC🇨🇭 🇨🇭 🇨🇭

Etwas abseits des Weges machte der Abstecher zu diesem Cache Freude. Die Koordinaten stimmen exakt jedoch die T1 Wertung stimmt überhaupt nicht. Ein Favorit für die schöne Location. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1333281651"><groundspeak:date>2025-11-05T22:37:45</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="54187471">sephanoides_clau</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Aún se mantiene bien, pero recomiendo cambiar la caja ya que se dañó uno de los cierres. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="5.0487" lon="-74.137033"><time>2007-09-08T00:00:00</time><name>GC15VAG</name><desc>El futbolista Carrasposo / The "carrasposo" Soccer by munditruck  </desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC15VAG</url><urlname>El futbolista Carrasposo / The "carrasposo" Soccer</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="686668" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>El futbolista Carrasposo / The "carrasposo" Soccer</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>munditruck  </groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="1264325">munditruck</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="0">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="1">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="33" inc="1">Motorcycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="34" inc="1">Quads</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="35" inc="1">Off-road vehicles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="37" inc="1">Horses</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="38" inc="0">Campfires</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>4</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Colombia</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Antes de las antenas del paramo del carrasposo hay un desvio a mano izquierda, este camino lo llevara al Cache/ Before you arrive to the antennas of "el carrasposo" moor there is a detour to your left hand side, This path will drive you to the Cache.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>Pasando el municipio de Subachoque (Cundinamarca) a 10 Km, se encuentra la población de La Pradera, continuar por el camino que conduce a las verdedas de El Guamal y a la población de Pacho, antes de llegar a las antenas de el paramo de El Carrasposo, existe un desvio, es una pequeña carretera que lo llevara al Cache. / 10 km After Subachoque's village (Cundinamarca State), you will get to La Pradera, go by the path that drives to El Guamal and Pacho (wich are Small Towns), before you arrive to the antennas of "El Carrasposo", you`ll get to a detour, there is a path that will drive you to the Cache.</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Este pendiente de las piedras grandes, especialmente dos al lado izquierdo del camino / Watch out for some big rocks, specially two, on the left side of the path.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1294895682"><groundspeak:date>2022-08-22T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="12158339">Theophi1os</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">What a trip this was. I was visiting my brother in Bogotá for a few days, and at the time there were only a handful of caches in the area. I saw that this cache was the oldest in the country, and I ended up taking a day trip out here.

I neglected logging this one for so long, because I wanted my log to do it justice. Welp, it's been so long that I don't remember everything about this day.  Trying not to let perfection be the enemy of the good. 

Anyway, I was driving a rental car, and I made it through the hills out to a road near the cache.  Eventually, the road was summarily impassable, so I parked and walked the rest of the way.  My what a beautiful spot. I'll attach some pictures when I can.

On the way back, as I was driving back down the mountain, there was just a herd of cows blocking the road. For a moment I thought I was going to have to wait it out, but the folks that were grazing their cows kindly guided them off the road so I could make it by.

This ended up being a whole day trip, and it was a grand time. Favorited. Muchísimas gracias por el cache!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="830025395"><groundspeak:date>2019-02-17T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="7022711">-DOLFINANDO-</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found it! 🎉

What an adventure this one turned out to be! I'm in Bogotá visiting family, and when I told them I wanted to find a geocache in the hills, my cousin generously offered to drive me. Little did we know what we were getting into! 😅

We started off on a steep, gravel road, and her car gave it a valiant effort. But when the tires started spinning hopelessly, we knew it was game over for the vehicle. Time to switch to Plan B: our feet! 🥾

My cousins joined me for the trek and were absolute troopers. They hiked about halfway before deciding they'd had enough of the incline (and the altitude!) and cheered me on as I continued solo. The road was steep, the gravel loose, and my legs were screaming by the end, but the scenery was absolutely worth it. 🌄

When I finally reached the coordinates, I had a moment of pure triumph. The cache was tucked away safely, and the views from up there were nothing short of spectacular. The entire city spread out below me, and I felt like I was on top of the world—literally and figuratively. 🌍✨

Huge thanks to munditruck for this unforgettable experience! This cache will always hold a special place in my memory.

Find #11120</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="165468684"><groundspeak:date>2011-06-06T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1938036">pulidoscar</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Hola, encontramos el geocache pero estaba absolutamente deteriorado. El Geocoin “Help for Heroes” estaba mojado y con óxido, la he llevado a mi casa a quitarle el óxido y hacerle mantenimiento. Reemplazaremos el Geocaché “El Carrasposo” por uno nuevo y ubicaremos el Geocoin en un nuevo lugar. Informaremos oportunamente las coordenadas


Hello, We found geocache but it was absolutely deteriorated, the Geocoin “Help for Heroes” was wet and rusty, I took it home to crean it and get it back in shape. We will replace “the Carrasposo” for a new Geocaché in other place near, and will locate the Geocoin in a new interesting Geocache.

pulidoscar@gmail.com</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="97923087"><groundspeak:date>2010-02-21T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1129458">machacho</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This is a very nice notice that this cache was found and the geocoin was rescue.
Hope you could restore and will placed in other and more popular cache.
Gracias por subir al rescate de la geocoin espero que la pueda ubicar en otro lugar para que siga su camino
[:D]
Saludos
Machacho</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="97920282"><groundspeak:date>2010-02-21T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2811393">El Derrotero</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">TFTC! It needs maintenance... it's all wet. We tried to save everything, but, for example, the logbook is ruined. This place is amazing!!! We had so much fun today looking for this cache. We changed the Geocoin.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="39.483017" lon="73.87405"><time>2009-08-15T00:00:00</time><name>GC1YTDR</name><desc>A Mountaineer's Tale (~6000m) by PI thagoras</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC1YTDR</url><urlname>A Mountaineer's Tale (~6000m)</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="1400792" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>A Mountaineer's Tale (~6000m)</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>PI thagoras</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="1108892">PI thagoras</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="57" inc="1">Long hike (&gt;10 km)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="29" inc="0">Telephone nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="11" inc="1">May require wading</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="3" inc="1">Climbing gear required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="10" inc="1">Difficult climb</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="23" inc="1">Dangerous area</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="21" inc="1">Cliff/falling rocks</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Kyrgyzstan</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Very remote cache on top of an almost 6000m peak in the Pamir mountain range.
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/ddd17884-7cfe-4cac-b043-cc33e3d0d863.jpg" alt="A Mountaineer's tale" /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
In summer of 2009 a handful of people from the German Alpine Club were able to do a first ascent on this nearly 6000 meter high mountain. The cache title should remind of the adventurous days spent at the mountain and my crazy friends.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
On top of the mountain, we left a small box, which contains a log book and some pens.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
As always in life: &lt;i&gt;The first cut is the deepest!&lt;/i&gt; - also in alpinism!&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Here are the usual warnings: This cache lies in a spot that only a well-planned expedition can reach, and which is potentially dangerous - fatalities occur year after year. Only persons in perfect physical and mental shape and with appropriate climbing and mountaineering expertise may consider to find this cache! You definitely will need lots of gear! Always be self-sufficient! Be sensitive to hazards! You need really good weather! As always: EACH CACHER (for this cache: each caching climber) IS RESPONSIBLE FOR HIM/HERSELF! I do not accept any responsibility in case of accidents. Be aware that there is usually no rescue possible.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
It remains to say: take care and HAVE A LOT OF FUN!
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>On the very top of the mountain - where else?</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1058463818"><groundspeak:date>2021-10-20T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="7576543">Dunaghiri</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Previous log is obvious fake.

Still no found.
Kyrgystan is not easy accessible. We attempted Peak Lenin (7000m) in 2019. Unfortunately we did not make it, despite the good supplies at Basecamp and Camp 1

This mountain, depsite 1000m lower, is less accesible, so not a piece of cake. 
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1015475781"><groundspeak:date>2021-05-05T01:28:52</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="35759278">UsurperKing</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">that fun </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="575285189"><groundspeak:date>2016-02-21T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="281075">CrazyPeople</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Tststs, was ist denn da los?!?!? Immer noch keiner hier gewesen? Frechheit!
Liebe Grüße!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="470443793"><groundspeak:date>2015-01-05T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="281075">CrazyPeople</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Frohes Neues noch! ;-)</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="215373788"><groundspeak:date>2012-02-29T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="281075">CrazyPeople</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">In: Favoritenpunkt. [:)]</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="-8.526917" lon="179.193"><time>2014-04-22T00:00:00</time><name>GC536TT</name><desc>Tuvalu Sinking #2 by VK2RG</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC536TT</url><urlname>Tuvalu Sinking #2</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="4302424" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Tuvalu Sinking #2</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>VK2RG</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="4868997">VK2RG</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="53" inc="1">Park and grab</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="55" inc="1">Short hike (&lt;1 km)</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Tuvalu</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>&lt;p&gt;The island of Funafuti, Tuvalu, is not everyone’s cup of tea for a tourist destination, but still many make the trek by boat or plane for whatever reason. My visits here are work related on behalf of the BBC World Service. Tuvalu is in the headlines for one simple feature, its sinking as a result of global warming and sea level changes. So be quick before it disappears.&lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;Tuvalu Sinking #2&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;TO LOG THIS CACHE THE FINDER IS TO SEND A PHOTO OF THE CACHE CONTAINER TO THE OWNER vk2rg&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Tuvalu Philatelic Bureau, a government body formed in 1976, when the Gilbert and Ellice Islands colony was dissolved and Tuvalu was established as a separate British dependency. Two years later Tuvalu became fully independent within the Commonwealth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The bureau is run by a small staff, dispatching stamps to collectors worldwide, and are aware of the cache.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;center&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size="1"&gt;Small note on cache maintenance:&lt;br /&gt;
There is a local cache guardian who will assist.&lt;br /&gt;
Name and contact info on file with geocaching.com.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/center&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Base of tree</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1213451750"><groundspeak:date>2024-01-25T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Didn't find it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="10490566">KiwiAoraki</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Even though the cache is archived, I had a search after sending some postcards. As a result, it's unlikely I'll make a find in Tuvalu as I'm only here for 5 days. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1173904852"><groundspeak:date>2023-06-13T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1049026">merdian</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">It would be great, if there is a new cache at Tuvalu, as I am planing to visit Tuvalu next year.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1157066695"><groundspeak:date>2023-04-06T02:53:22</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4868997">VK2RG</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Geocachers seem to have forgotten that a cache logbook needs to be signed before claiming a find.   This cache has stood up to natures elements very well and is now retired.
I will work on a new caches for Tuvalu at a later date.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1149742172"><groundspeak:date>2023-02-20T02:30:10</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="42676317">DavidBatista09</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Easy</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1152035779"><groundspeak:date>2023-02-15T00:33:15</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6535652">SteLaSyXL</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Diesmal wollte es nicht sein. Die Zeit wird kommen… 

This time it didn't want to be. The time will come...
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="-9.4298" lon="159.9576"><time>2015-07-04T00:00:00</time><name>GC5YQ8R</name><desc>From Guadalcanal to Isarkanal by challengeservice24</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC5YQ8R</url><urlname>From Guadalcanal to Isarkanal</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Multi-cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="5092799" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>From Guadalcanal to Isarkanal</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>challengeservice24</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="7035622">challengeservice24</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Multi-cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="0">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="53" inc="0">Park and grab</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="57" inc="1">Long hike (&gt;10 km)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="66" inc="1">Teamwork cache</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="64" inc="0">Tree climbing required</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Solomon Islands</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:150%;color:red;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Please note:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style="font-size:125%;"&gt;The final is quite a distance from the cache coordinates.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;You'll need to fly by plane around the globe in order to sign the logbook.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;  &lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;img src="https://d1u1p2xjjiahg3.cloudfront.net/21e3df67-6770-4508-9987-f8ce65c24fcb_l.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On Guadalcanal, the largest of the Solomon Islands, you can find many relics, memorials and monuments, which commemorate the battles fought on the island during the Second World War. To find this geocache, you will visit four memorial sites in and around Honiara, the capital of the Solomon Islands.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Stage 1: S 09° 25.788 E 159° 57.456&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Here you'll see a nautical device.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style="color:green;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;A&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt; = ___ Number of letters of the common name of the device&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The whole object consists of three "sections". Go to the biggest.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style="color:green;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;B&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt; = ___ The number of minutes mentioned&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Now go the the middle one. Look for the date (mentioned at least twice).&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style="color:green;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;C&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt; = ___ Number of the day&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Stage 2: S 09°26.559 E 159°57.460&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Go to the star in the middle.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style="color:blue;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;D&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt; = ___ Number of letters of the next to last word on the plaque (a common three-letter abbreviation counts as one word)&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Look around and get a good overview of the area!&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style="color:blue;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;E&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt; = ___ Very last digit on the very lower right corner&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style="color:blue;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;F&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt; = ___ Number of "Tassafaronga"&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Stage 3: S 09°28.247 E 159°58.092&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
See something interesting?&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style="color:maroon;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;G&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt; = ___ Number of the first Japanese Infantry Regiment mentioned in the first paragraph&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style="color:maroon;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;H&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt; = ___ Number of the first American Infrantry Regiment mentioned in the first paragraph&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Stage 4: S 09°25.645 E 160°02.700&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style="color:red;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;J&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt; = ___ Number of long outstretched legs this object stands on&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Look for a plaque on the ground nearby. (about 15m to the north-east)&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style="color:red;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;K&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt; = ___ Number of letters of the 2nd word in the 6th line&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style="color:red;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;L&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt; = ___ Number in the middle of the last line&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style="color:red;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;M&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt; = ___ Position in the alphabet (A=1 ... Z=26) of the first letter in the 3rd line&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
Now it's time to board the plane!&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Final:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;N&lt;/b&gt; (2*(&lt;span style="color:green;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;A&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;/3)*&lt;span style="color:green;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;C&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;*(&lt;span style="color:green;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;B&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;+&lt;span style="color:green;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;C&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;)*10000 + (3*&lt;span style="color:blue;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;E&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;+2*&lt;span style="color:green;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;B&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;+&lt;span style="color:blue;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;D&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;)*1000 - &lt;span style="color:blue;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;F&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;*20 + &lt;span style="color:red;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;K&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;*(&lt;span style="color:maroon;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;G&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;+&lt;span style="color:maroon;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;H&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;) - 4*&lt;span style="color:maroon;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;G&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt; + 2*&lt;span style="color:red;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;L&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt; + 4) / 100000 °&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;E&lt;/b&gt; ((&lt;span style="color:blue;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;D&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;+&lt;span style="color:green;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;A&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;)*&lt;span style="color:green;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;C&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;*10000 + (&lt;span style="color:green;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;A&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;+&lt;span style="color:green;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;B&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;+&lt;span style="color:green;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;C&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;+&lt;span style="color:red;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;J&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;)*1000 + &lt;span style="color:maroon;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;G&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt; + &lt;span style="color:maroon;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;H&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt; - (&lt;span style="color:red;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;J&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;+&lt;span style="color:red;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;K&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;)*20 + 2*&lt;span style="color:red;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;M&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt; - 31) / 100000 °
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="696187502"><groundspeak:date>2017-06-23T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="12006214">Blue_Lion_60</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Oh no, wie ärgerlich. Vor etwa 1,5 Jahren hab ich mit diesem Cache begonnen und heute war es endlich so weit, daß ich mit nicnap1601 in die Gegend des Finals kam. Da erinnerte ich mich dran bzw das Fähnchen auf der Karte. Also marschierten wir dorthin durch Schmutz und Matsch den Hügel hinauf. Vor Ort suchten wir uns nen Wolf bis ich auf die Idee kam, die Daten zu aktualisieren und was sehe ich, der Cache wurde vor einem Monat archiviert. Grrrrr. Das darf nicht sein [:(!].</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="689322776"><groundspeak:date>2017-05-28T06:42:22</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="7035622">challengeservice24</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Dear Geocachers, dear friends of the Solomon Islands, Ladies and Gentlemen,

This cache is now history.

We, the Challengeservice24, have put all our resources into the creation of this cache. We even risked our good reputation with Groundspeak, thereby seriously endangering the foundation of our business model. Some of you wondered, why the reviewer published a listing like this. Well, actually he didn't. We first had to significantly expand our connections all across the globe. In the end, it would not have been possible without the help of Clinton1020 from Australia. Thank you very much, mate! As it were, we ended up with a cache listing, which was as controversial as it was unique among the 3 million+ caches listed on geocaching.com. A highlight in the history of the Challengeservice24, if we may say so.

At this point, we would like to sincerely thank all our finders for their logs. Many were great adventure reports, others were, well, less inspired. We hope, that you all enjoyed the experience.

Unfortunately, all good things must come to an end. As has been explained in our note on April 18th, certain necessities force us to withdraw this listing. We apologize for any inconveniences.


With best regards

Challengeservice24
Public Relations Department</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="689819756"><groundspeak:date>2017-05-27T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8682302">afrostromi</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Im digitalen Zeitalter ist das Reisen deutlich einfacher geworden. Also rein in den virtuellen Flieger und ab ging's. Mit ein bischen Unterstützung konnte ich die benötigten Daten Sammeln und schon ging's wieder zurück. Bei einem Wochenendausflug hab ich dann das Final besucht. Bei Hitze und Mückenplage kämpfte ich mich zum Döschen vor, das in einer schönen Gegend liegt. Ich konnte mich gerade noch rechtzeitig ins Logbuch eintragen, denn am nächsten Tag war der Cache leider schon im Archiv. Danke fürs legen und pflegen des etwas anderen Cache.
TFTC afrostromi</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="689302365"><groundspeak:date>2017-05-27T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="13415641">CoraTh</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Nach der Ankündigung dass dieser Cache ins Archiv wandern würde war mir klar, das muss sich noch irgendwie ausgehen. Also Airlines und Schlauchbootverleihe kontaktiert, dem Arbeitgeber eine chronische Krankheit vorgespielt, Oma um Kleingeld angebettelt und dann war es so weit, die Reise begann.

Hätte man mich vor noch wenigen Wochen gefragt wo ich eher hin käme, Salomon Inseln oder Australien, ich hätte wohl letzteres getippt, aber so kann man sich irren.

Nach der Reise erster Teil, ein Schmugglerschiff, Holzklasse (heißt in dem Fall ich musste immer neben dem Kapitän stehen und ihn mit einem Bett schlagen wenn er einschlief) kam ich nach Wochen am Ziel an. 

Im Tausch für sexuelle Dienste konnte ich vor Ort einige Transportmöglichkeiten organisieren, mal komfortabler mal weniger, aber bald waren alle Stationen abgegrast und die Werte notiert.

Der Rückweg verlief ähnlich abenteuerlich. Bis Indien kam ich am Rücken einer Meeresschildkröte, dann weiter auf einer Kuh welche ich dann gegen ein altes Kamel eintauschte und schließlich gegen einen alten Lada. So kann ich heute am Final an. 

Der Lada klapperte schon reichlich als ich ihn heute, bei reichlich Muggelaufkommen einparkte. Dann dauerte es ehrlich gesagt ziemlich lange bis ich fündig wurde, zum Teil meine Schuld, zum Teil die der "Neonradler" die unbedingt am Fuße des​ Kliffs ein LANGES Picknick einlegen mussten und mich so beim Suchen stören, denn​ ich wollte nicht unbedingt die Aufmerksamkeit auf mich lenken.

Cacher die diesen Ort vor mir besucht haben waren anscheinend nicht so vorsichtig, denn​ die scheinen vor Wut über die Steigung hier die Bäume gleich büschelweise ausgerissen zu haben. Auch auf dem alternativen Rückweg war es nicht viel besser, da gab zwar nicht die blanke Erde unter den Füßen nach, dafür das seit Jahren nicht gesammelte Laub. Der Gärtner hier muss echt mal Überstunden machen!!!

Aber ich habe es schließlich geschafft, ich stehe im Logbuch!!! 

Ich bin dann, ohne Hilfe des Hosenbodens (anders als beim Aufstieg), wieder runter und habe, am Lada angekommen, beschlossen den stehen zu lassen. Autostopp heim war definitiv schneller als diese Klapperkiste. 

Danke fürs Legen und Pflegen!!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="688696026"><groundspeak:date>2017-05-26T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="7371459">Claudius48</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Eine Reise durch Zeit und Raum wurde mir heute ermöglicht. Jules Verne geb. 8.2.1828 - gest. 24.03.1905 hätte hier seine Freude. Jetzt sind diese Reisen möglich. Durch GeoCaching sind die Raum- und Zeitgrenzen aufgehoben, bei den Zeitgrenzen war ich mir schon sicher, denn wenn ich auch nur kurz eine oder zwei Dosen suchen wollte, war es gleich immer viel später als erwartet. Bei den Raumgrenzen hatte ich bis jetzt immer gedacht, dass ich nur die Orientierung verliere und nach einem größern Cachingausflug den Weg zurück nicht mehr ohne meine mitgeführten Tools finde, aber bis zu den Solomon Inseln konnte ich das erwarten? Ja, vielen Dank für den Cache und die Mühe mit der Pflege der Dose. 

Viele Grüße aus dem Augsburger Land bitte beachte mein Event auf dem Ammersee GC73H23, ich freue mich auf viele Teilnehmer. 

Claudius48 </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="23.803067" lon="90.414117"><time>2011-01-26T00:00:00</time><name>GC2MYW8</name><desc>DUTCH POINT DHAKA by SIJUMITO</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC2MYW8</url><urlname>DUTCH POINT DHAKA</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="2060456" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>DUTCH POINT DHAKA</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>SIJUMITO</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="3679341">SIJUMITO</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="1">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="53" inc="1">Park and grab</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="1">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Bangladesh</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>DUTCH POINT DHAKA.           


If anything is not clear, please send a mail   


sijumito@gmail.com</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>Dhaka formerly known as Dacca and Jahangir Nagar, is the capital of Bangladesh.
Dhaka is a megacity and one of the major cities of South Asia. Located on the banks of the Buriganga River, has a population of over 12 million.
To find the cache, take a rickshaw or taxi and go to the district Gulshan. 
The cache-place is a meeting-place for Dutch people.
Please ask the guard for the barkeeper.
You can ask the barkeeper for the DUTCH POINT DHAKA.
If the guard / barkeeper don't understand it, ask then for the club manager.
You can come every day from 07.00 to 22.00 .


Dhaka voorheen bekend als Dacca en Jahangir Nagar, is de hoofdstad van Bangladesh.
Dhaka is een grote stad en een van de belangrijkste steden van Zuid Azië. Gevestigd aan een zijtak van de rivier Buriganga, heeft meer dan 12 miljoen inwoners.
Om de cache te vinden, neem een riksja of taxi en ga naar de wijk Gulshan.
De cache-plaats is een ontmoetingsplaats voor Nederlanders.
U kunt de bewaker vragen naar de barkeeper.
Vraag aan de barkeeper de DUTCH POINT DHAKA.
Als de bewaker / barkeeper het echt niet begrijpen, vraag dan voor de club manager.
U kunt iedere dag komen van 07.00 to 22.00. 

The starting content of the cache:
Logbook and pencils
TB-Travel Racer 3 boy’s MITOXX
Geo-bracelet
5 Smurfen</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>The cache-place is a meeting-place for Dutch people.
Please ask the guard for the barkeeper.
You can ask the barkeeper for the DUTCH POINT DHAKA.
If the guard / barkeeper don't understand it, ask then for the club manager.


De cache-plaats is een ontmoetingsplaats voor Nederlanders.
U kunt de bewaker vragen naar de barkeeper.
Vraag aan de barkeeper de DUTCH POINT  DHAKA.
Als de bewaker / barkeeper het echt niet begrijpen, vraag dan voor de club manager


</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1358019738"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-30T14:46:17</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="25092969">svente86</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Yeah das war ja mal easy und spannend</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1356645256"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-23T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="658838">tommy-online</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Next cache in Bangladesh. It was not so easy to get in although we live 50 km next to the Dutch border. But geocaching helped.
Tftc
Tommy-online &amp; Hille</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1352875376"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-04T19:47:24</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="25429000">Schiedonnetjes</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Staying here for more than one week now, and never thought about geocaching here, until my home asked if there are caches in Dhaka! I have been sleeping almost on a cache for one week! :) Thanks for placing it!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1352229024"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-01T14:13:38</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="38121966">OddlyShapedPancakes</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Very well maintained cache, thank you for hosting a cache in this lovely country! ❤️</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1352228948"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-01T14:13:15</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="41910242">teatuberculosis</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">thanks for maintaining the cache</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="0.63875" lon="11.49965"><time>2010-08-07T00:00:00</time><name>GC2D6HR</name><desc>Cookie Tin by stevestraw</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC2D6HR</url><urlname>Cookie Tin</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="1829522" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cookie Tin</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>stevestraw</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="3648121">stevestraw</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>3.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Gabon</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Just off of the route national, the cookie tin is wedged between two limbs of a bamboo tree.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>Just off of the route national, take about 15 steps down the bank toward the river.  The cookie tin is wedged between two limbs of a bamboo tree at about eye level.  It is round and brown.</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1277330261"><groundspeak:date>2025-01-13T16:25:58</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="51801630">KateWildwood</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">TFTC </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1207983095"><groundspeak:date>2023-12-08T18:38:17</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="47185858">JD2115420692137</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Pedał</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1093374377"><groundspeak:date>2022-04-30T13:31:52</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="39591456">WiltonKilroy83</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">P</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="881646643"><groundspeak:date>2019-09-11T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3975205">TDupin</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">It is hardly credible. We stopped here without much hope to find this cache after 3 years without a visit. But it is there, in good condition after the maintenance of 2016. The logbook is dry and we were able to register after a short search in this beautiful bamboo forest.
TFTC

#2843</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="584688261"><groundspeak:date>2016-02-29T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="880628">palmier</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">On our way to the village of Sam to rebuild a school built by Peace Corps Volunteers in 1965. The cache was actually found by our host from Gabon.  TFTC.
Replaced rusty and holy cookie tin with a new one. Replaced wet log with a dry one.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="42.694283" lon="20.076283"><time>2005-06-03T00:00:00</time><name>GCP7H1</name><desc>Muito Verde - Very Green by GeoSepolTeam / SousaLopes</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCP7H1</url><urlname>Muito Verde - Very Green</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="251537" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Muito Verde - Very Green</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>GeoSepolTeam / SousaLopes</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="372647">GeoSepolTeam</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Serbia</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;div class="WordSection1"&gt;
&lt;center&gt;&lt;img /&gt;&lt;/center&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal"&gt;(E)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal"&gt;&lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;Welcome&lt;/span&gt; to Kosovo!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal"&gt;&lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;This&lt;/span&gt; cache &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;is&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;located&lt;/span&gt; in &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;mountains&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;close&lt;/span&gt; to &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;the&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;city&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;of&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;Pec&lt;/span&gt;, altitude 1123m.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal"&gt;A &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;place&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;were&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="GramE"&gt;stands&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;the&lt;/span&gt; green &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;of&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;the&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;forests&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;valleys&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;were&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;the&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;rivers&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;run&lt;/span&gt; as &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;well&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;other&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;lines&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;of&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;water&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;an&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;amazing&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;place&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;were&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;you&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;also&lt;/span&gt; can admire &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;water&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;falls&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;that&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;turns&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;this&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;piece&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;of&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;land&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;into&lt;/span&gt; a &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;magnificent&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;place&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal"&gt;&lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;The&lt;/span&gt; cache &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;is&lt;/span&gt; a tupperware-&lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;style&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;small&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;plastic&lt;/span&gt; box (12 x 10x 8 cm), &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;covered&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;with&lt;/span&gt; green &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;band&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;sticker&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;see&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;photo&lt;/span&gt;), &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;with&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;the&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;following&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;initial&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;content&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;"&gt;- &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;Logbook&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;don`t&lt;/span&gt; remove)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;"&gt;- &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;Pencil&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;don`t&lt;/span&gt; remove)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;"&gt;- &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;Eraser&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;don`t&lt;/span&gt; remove)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;"&gt;-&lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;Various&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;items&lt;/span&gt; for &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;exchange&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal"&gt;&lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;Enjoy&lt;/span&gt;!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;center&gt;&lt;img /&gt;&lt;/center&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal"&gt;(P)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal"&gt;&lt;span class="GramE"&gt;Bem vindos&lt;/span&gt; ao Kosovo!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal"&gt;Esta cache localiza-se no território do Kosovo, a alguns quilómetros da cidade de &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;Pec&lt;/span&gt;, numa zona montanhosa, a uma altitude de 1123m.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal"&gt;Uma vegetação abundante, vales escarpados onde correm rios, ribeiros e outras linhas de água muito límpida, onde também é possível admirar várias quedas de água, tornam a paisagem magnífica.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal"&gt;A cache é uma pequena caixa de plástico (12 x 10 x 8 cm) tipo tupperware, revestida com fita adesiva verde (ver foto), com o seguinte conteúdo inicial:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;"&gt;- &lt;span class="SpellE"&gt;Logbook&lt;/span&gt; (não retirar)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;"&gt;- Lápis (não retirar)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;"&gt;- Borracha (não retirar)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;"&gt;- Vários itens para troca.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal"&gt;Desfrutem!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;center&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.geopt.org"&gt;&lt;img src="http://geopt.dyndns.org/GeoPT_Tools/FTF_generator.aspx?type=2&amp;amp;first1=Cannonball&amp;amp;first2=&amp;amp;first3=&amp;amp;first4=&amp;amp;second1=GerardNL&amp;amp;second2=&amp;amp;second3=&amp;amp;second4=&amp;amp;third1=Eifeltiger&amp;amp;third2=&amp;amp;third3=&amp;amp;third4=" border="0" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/center&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>(E): Under the rock!
(P): Sob a rocha!</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1357929657"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-29T17:07:59</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="26571612">MrCoxxx</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Bei einem Tagestrip durch das Rugovtal diesen Cache geloggt! 

Tftc

Falemenderit per Cache!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1353766358"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-07T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2717373">pilzmopsbande</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Am frühen Vormittag ging es ins Rugovatal. Die Straße war leidlich befahrbar und die Natur überragend. Der Cache könnte gut gefunden werden. Danke für die versteckte Dose.   FAVpunkt.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1354315531"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-05T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8237929">ballbreaker67</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Bei einem Ausflug ins Rugovatal schnell gefunden und geloggt, danke fürs Auslegen und Pflegen.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1340094887"><groundspeak:date>2025-12-30T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="12358207">NO+Tina</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Heute haben wir mit dem Leihwagen einen Abstecher ins benachbarten Ausland gemacht und dabei diesen Tradi mitgenommen. 

TftC sagen NO und Tina aus der Dübener Heide 🤗 🇩🇪</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1338800781"><groundspeak:date>2025-12-19T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="431470">Beutelteufelweibchen</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We are staying in the cabin near-by and we are looking for snow, but we are one week to early, the snow is predicted for next week  :-)
But the cache is there and easy to find.
DT 1/1 is interesting, I do not think a wheel chair can make it up that hill  :-)
TFTC, 
Beutelteufelweibchen </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="31.928833" lon="35.177833"><time>2011-04-26T00:00:00</time><name>GC2V2Q8</name><desc>Wadi Al Dilb 1st Geocache by XSDARKLORD &amp; TANUSHKA</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC2V2Q8</url><urlname>Wadi Al Dilb 1st Geocache</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="2213131" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Wadi Al Dilb 1st Geocache</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>XSDARKLORD &amp; TANUSHKA</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="4151001">XSDARKLORD</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="0">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="53" inc="0">Park and grab</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="30" inc="0">Picnic tables nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="0">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="27" inc="0">Drinking water nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="37" inc="1">Horses</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="43" inc="1">Livestock nearby</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Palestine</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>The cache lies in natural surroundings within the heart of Wadi Al-Dilb. This place, which is still a splendid work of nature, has olive trees that date back to the time of Christ and maybe before. It has many outdoor one or two story edifices which Palestinian farmers of the past used during the time of olive harvest, since this wasn't an area you'd be camping in without a protective roof over your head. The landscape is amazing, and you can see odd formations of rock, held back on their way down by ancient olive trees.</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>The container is a square transparent plastic container, not more than 14 cm in length. It contains a pencil, a pen, a notebook for Geocachers to write on, and a few trinkets</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1098310923"><groundspeak:date>2022-05-21T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1273497">Die Geokids</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">The weather was perfect to go for a short hike and explore the beautiful nature here. After climbing up from the road (quite a steep climb and crossing a nasty smelling river), I arrived at the house, which is quite off from the "new" coordinates. Better use the old ones, they actually lead you to the "house" in a cave. It was really interesting to see it. I searched for about 35 minutes because the spoiler is not so clear and I would have never assumed that the cache is where it was but oh well.. I finally could spot it. The "burial place" was even more buried now but eventually I could carefully remove all stones and found the untouched cache (has not seen any visitor ever according to the log). Great to find it.

TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="671809301"><groundspeak:date>2017-03-07T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1543658">MT-Jonea</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Visited it during 15-days geotrip to Israel, Palestine, Jordan, Egypt with Marci. Sometimes we logged as "MT". Thanks for nice caches from Brno city in Czech republic EU.
With owner accept I change my DNF log to FI and give FP. Thanks</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="582470792"><groundspeak:date>2016-03-13T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Unknown</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4151001">XSDARKLORD</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Again, I had to perform maintenance on the cache, because it was stolen. This time, I had it buried to make it more difficult to find.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="374300578"><groundspeak:date>2014-01-03T09:10:14</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3093874">Trevelyan77</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Finally success! And a FTF too!!! The photohint helped greatly, it would be very helpful by the other caches too... Short and steep climb from the road and then the pure joy from finding it :) Thanks a lot! Greetings from the Czech Republic!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="301381967"><groundspeak:date>2013-03-29T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Unknown</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4151001">XSDARKLORD</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Today, Tanushka and I visited the site, after reading from  fellow Geocacher SPEERUV, on 4 march, 2013,  that he couldn't find it. So we set out to correct the matter. It seems the place was so obvious since the box was red and not well hidden, and therefore lost to non-geocachers. We replaced the cache with a smaller one, and hid it well a few feet away from the original location, thus the update on the coordinates.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="42.1512" lon="23.3711"><time>2002-03-30T00:00:00</time><name>GC4873</name><desc>GCRILA by Mort</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC4873</url><urlname>GCRILA</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="18547" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>GCRILA</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Mort</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="71700">Mort</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="40" inc="1">Stealth required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="18" inc="1">Dangerous animals</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="19" inc="1">Ticks</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Bulgaria</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>The container is located near the Rila Monastery, hidden close to the grave of St. Ivan Rilsky.
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;h4&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;legend&gt;&lt;img alt src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0394/9549/files/greatBritainFlag.png" height="15" width="25" /&gt;ENGLISH&lt;/legend&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;fieldset&gt;
&lt;div align="center"&gt;&lt;span class="title1"&gt;&lt;b&gt;History and general information&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;hr align="justify" class="style8" /&gt;
&lt;p align="justify" class="style8"&gt;&lt;b&gt;General information&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;table width="100" border="0" align="right" cellspacing="5"&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;th scope="col"&gt;&lt;span class="Style4"&gt;&lt;a href="https://s3.amazonaws.com/gs-geo-images/4ec86717-5455-4a83-a6e0-93b33ed40dd2.jpg" rel="lightbox[roadtrip]" title="General view of Rila Monastery."&gt;&lt;img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/gs-geo-images/4ec86717-5455-4a83-a6e0-93b33ed40dd2.jpg" alt width="252" height="214" border="2" align="right" class="style_pic1" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td class="title_pic"&gt;
&lt;div align="left"&gt;General view of Rila Monastery.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;The Rila Monastery is located in 1147 meters altitude in the middle of the fragrant coniferous forests of Rila Mountain.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;The monastery is a complex of cultural, dwelling and farming buildings which take about 8800 square meters. The Rila Monastery has an unique architecture. Outside, the monastery looks like a fortress. It has 24-meter stone walls which forms irregular pentagon. That’s why when some tourist enters the monastery’s yard from some of the two iron gates he is surprised by its architecture: arches and colonnades, covered wooden stairs and carved verandas and the 300-400 monastic cells. &lt;a&gt;The Hreliov’s tower&lt;/a&gt; and the main church “The Nativity of the Virgin” cohabit at the center of the yard. This tower was created by the local feudal lord Hrelio in 1334-1335. A small church stays next to it and it is only a couple of years younger (1343). A bell-tower was added to the tower in 1844. &lt;a&gt;The main church “The Nativity of the Virgin”&lt;/a&gt; was built in these times. Its architect is a master Peter Ivanovich, who worked on it in 1834-1837. The temple has five domes, three altars and two chapels. Maybe the most important thing in the church is the iconostasis which has incredible wood-carving. The wall-paintings were completed in 1846 by many masters from Bulgaria, but only Zahary Zagraph signed his paintings. In the church there are lots of icons created in XIV-XIX.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;table width="100" border="0" align="right" cellspacing="5"&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;th scope="col"&gt;&lt;span class="Style4"&gt;&lt;a href="https://s3.amazonaws.com/gs-geo-images/18080a46-64f4-4a62-8d40-01363f715c9c.jpg" rel="lightbox[roadtrip]" title="One of the expositions of the Museum."&gt;&lt;img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/gs-geo-images/18080a46-64f4-4a62-8d40-01363f715c9c.jpg" alt width="180" height="135" border="2" align="right" class="style_pic1" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td class="title_pic"&gt;
&lt;div align="left"&gt;One of the expositions of the Museum.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;The monastery has also its own library which is very rich in literally material. There are stored lots of important Bulgarian written records – about 250 manuscript books from XI-XIX, 9000 old-printed books, manuscripts and so on. The museum, located in the monastery has a rich exposition – historical collection of 35 000 exponents, rich collections of icons, wood-carvings, cultural and ethnographical items. The museum has an unique work of art, called the Cross of Rafail. It is made of a whole piece of wood (81-43 centimeters) and it’s called to its creator. The monk used fine chisels, small knives and lentils to carve 104 religious stages and 650 small figures. It took him more than 12 years to complete his work. It’s completed in 1802 – then its creator lost his eyesight.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;In spite of the big area which the monastery has, it is not able to show its treasures at the same time – that’s why there are lots of temporary expositions in the monastery and out of it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="justify" class="style9"&gt;&lt;b&gt;History&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;table width="100" border="0" align="left" cellspacing="5"&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;th scope="col"&gt;&lt;span class="Style4"&gt;&lt;a href="https://s3.amazonaws.com/gs-geo-images/55332f62-8c6e-4657-a2fe-214cb6c6e41b.jpg" rel="lightbox[roadtrip]" title="Rila Monastery . Painter I. Petkov. Stained glass in Sofia University."&gt;&lt;img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/gs-geo-images/55332f62-8c6e-4657-a2fe-214cb6c6e41b.jpg" alt width="150" height="174" border="2" align="right" class="style_pic1" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td class="title_pic"&gt;
&lt;div align="left"&gt;Rila Monastery . Painter I. Petkov. Stained glass in Sofia University.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;The Rila Monastery was founded in the 30-th years of X century on the place of the Old Anchoress in Rila Mountain. While the monastery has been existing, it was many times rebuilt, destroyed and reconstructed. Today the Rila Monastery has had this appearance since the middle of the previous century. It is the biggest and the most respected Bulgarian monastery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;It is considered that the creator of the Rila Monastery is the first Bulgarian hermit &lt;a href="St_ivan_rilski_en.htm"&gt;Ivan Rilsky (876-946)&lt;/a&gt;, he chose to live in this way as a method of spiritual perfection and a way to express his protest against the suppression of the high moral rules of the real Christianity. The Bulgarian saint was born in the 70-th years of IX century. He was a witness of the decline of the First Bulgarian Kingdom at the time of king Peter I and Saint Ivan Rilsky became the most respected saint in the Orthodox Christianity in that time. At the time of the Byzantine slavery the established brotherhood was turned into a monastery. At the beginning of the Second Bulgarian Kingdom the relics of Saint Ivan Rilsky was displaced to the capital of the country Veliko Tarnovo as the most important relic for the Bulgarians.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;That the monastery has been existed for a millennium and that the Rila monks has been aware of the mission of books are the factors that produced the monastery library which can rival Europeans counterparts. The abundant collection comprise works that have been written in the monastery, works that have been commissioned to eminent men of letters and books and manuscripts that have been donated or bought.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;Fot centuries the Rila Monastery has been the centre of intensive literacy activities. Outstanding educators, anonymous copyists, manuscript illuminators and book-binders spent years working there. As a result of their work today the library collection is one of the richest in the Balkans.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;Among the men of letters who worked at the Rila Monastery were the grammarian Spiridon, hieromonk Anastasy, Vladislav Grammaticus, Nikifor, Yossif Bradati and the great National Revival educator and champion for secular education Neophit Rilski who brought to light all manuscripts, catalogued the library and invested a lot of effort to make it a public library which was open to the numerous pilgrims visiting the monastery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;The National Revival Period transformed the Rila Monastery into a major educational and cultural centre of the Bulgarian lands. The literary school evolved into an educational institution where some of the most prominent enlighteners of the nation received their education. The library opened its gates to inquisitive pilgrims and this is testified by the numerous marginal notes found in the old books. Thus very naturally it acquired the functions of a public library and paved the way to the community centre libraries which became very common during the National Revival.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;The Rila Monastery Library manuscript collection comprises Slavic and Greek records dating from the 11&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; to mid-19&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; century. In addition to their literary merit these records have artistic merits. Most of them have illuminations which show the Bulgarian tradition in that art. It is noteworthy that despite the large number of service books in Greek, the monastery churches and chapels never heard service in Greek although it is evident the monks had good knowledge of the language which they could speak and in which they could read and write.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;The Rila Monastery collection of printed books the earliest of which date from early 16&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; century comprises valuable items: a Tetraevangelia from 1512 that was published I Turgovishte, books that were printed in the Venice printing house which was established in 1619, many Russian old printed books, several of very rare editions that were printed in Vilno, of the Kievan-Pechora Laura, Moscow printed prologues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;The long history of the buildings in the Rila Monastery goes back to late 10&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; century when the monastic community that the Rila hermit had founded put up the first buildings not far from the cave which he occupied.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;Since the 15&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; century and particularly during the Bulgarian National Revival the numbers of pilgrims increased significantly and a large group of service buildings appeared around the monastery. The reception buildings of the metochia and the sketae along the river Rilska where there were places associated with the patron saint’s worship were renovated during the same period. In this way several architectural ensembles appeared whose purpose was to provide shelter and also to prepare worshippers mentally for their encounter with the holiest place in Bulgaria.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;The first thing that the visitors of the monastery see as they set foot on the Rila Mountain is the Orlitsa metochion which in the course of almost five centuries has been receiving pilgrims coming from the western parts of Bulgaria. In 1469 the Church of St. Peter and Paul was built to lay the relics of St. Ioan of Rila after they had been returned to the monastery. In 1491 a group of icon painters decorated the church which had been redesigned in 1478.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;The next metochion which is closer to the monastery is called Pchelino. It was here that the Church of the Dormition of the Virgin was put up in the late 18&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; century and decorated with frescoes in 1835 by Dimiter Molerov.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;The Hermitage of St. Ioan of Rila is northeast of the monastery and farthest. It stands where the cave in which the hermit lived is and where he was initially buried. For this reason the Church of the Assumption of St. Ioan of Rila was built in 1746. It is a single nave, single apse building with narthex. In 1820 it was rebuilt and became what it is today.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;A path leads from the Hermitage to the monastery. Along the path there are several picturesque buildings built down a steep slope. This is the Steke of St. Luke, also known as the New hermitage. The oldest building here is the late 17&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; century Church of St. Luke the Evangelist. It was painted in 1798-1799 when carvers from Bansko carved wooden iconostasis. The surviving frescoes are a product of the &lt;span class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;Toma Vishanov&lt;/span&gt;'s brush , called Molera from Bansko who had studied in the Central Europe and introduced baroque elements in the Bulgarian ecclesiastical art, creating expressive and ethereal paintings which were new for those times.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;The second church of the ensemble, the Shroud of the Virgin, was put up in 1805 over the holy fountain by the builders Mihail and Radoitsa from the village of Rila. It has a large semi-open exonartes with an outdoor structure whose walls were painted by Toma Vishanov in 1811.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;A small group of buildings that are enclosed by a stone wall is very near to the monastery. It includes the cemetery church and the monastery ossuary, several buildings with living premises and the monastery cemetery. The cemetery church of the Presentation of the Virgin where the brethren served their funeral service dates probably from the early 17&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; century. Like most medieval ossuaries it is on two levels and is a small lavishly decorated one-aisle church. Its frescoes from 1795 are characteristic of the style of a group of Bulgarian artists who worked on Mount Athos during the 18&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; and 19&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; centuries. Its iconostasis is noted for its elegant proportions and beautiful wood encarving.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;Between the 10&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; and 14&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; centuries the Monastery changed places several times.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;In the 14&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; century Hrelyo Dragovol, a feudal lord whose domain comprised the lands around the river Strouma, transformed the monastery into a solidly fortified and imposing architectural ensemble. This is proved by the remains of solid walls in the southwestern corner of the monastery courtyard unearthed during archeological excavations and also by the prominent tower which still stands in the courtyard and by the paintings in the monastery church built by the feudal lord and surviving until the mid-19&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; century.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;Large-scale building work began some time during mid-18&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; century and after 1816 the monastery already had high solid residential buildings which enclosed the courtyard in the shape of an irregular quadrangle.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;January 13, 1833 was one of the most tragic days in the long history of the monastery. The fire which broke out during the night destroyed almost completely the residential quarters. That was a national calamity and soon people began sending donations for the monastery’s restoration. Thousands of masons, carpenters and auxiliary workers arrived to work and did not get payment for their work. Only for a couple of years the buildings were restored.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;Three Bulgarian master builders (purvomaistori) were in charge of the construction works whose scale was unprecedented in those times. They were Alexi from the village of Rila, called Alexi Rilets, who built the northern parts of the east and the west wings, Milenko from the village of Radomir who built the south wing ‘architecton’ Pavel from the village of Krimin who built the church which at the time was the largest in the Balkans. The decoration of the main church, the chapels and the visitors’ rooms was completed by 1870. at that time the monastery looked as we know it today.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;The church of the Nativity of the Virgin is the monastery’s main church and the core of the architectural ensemble. Its construction began in 1835. That was an event of paramount importance for the entire Bulgarian nation. The innovative daring and the flexibility with which tradition has been interpreted in the architectural design of its imposing church reveals the nature of art during the National Revival Period.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;This church building is unique in the Balkans. It was built by the then widely known master builder Pavel from the village of Krimin who had worked on Mount Athos and from where he borrowed the original spatial design of the church. The compositional scheme includes medieval elements and baroque spatial principles, an approach which distinguishes Bulgarian church architecture and whose features are observed in the art of the epoch.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;The wall paintings in the Church of the Nativity of the Virgin were made by the most prominent Bulgarian painters at the time. Most of them were from Samokov where the artists of the Zograph (Painter) family, Zahari Zograph, Dimiter H. Zograph and Stanislav Dospevski, worked. In the 1840s they were joined by Ivan Obrazopissets and his son Nikola Obrazopissets. There was a group of artist of Bansko led by Dimiter Molerov, and many other unknown assistants. In the course of several years, at the cost of great effort, to quote Neophit Rilski, they completed the church interior walls, the domes, the facades hidden under the arcade and its small domes and produced 40 large icons for the iconostases and many other smaller ones.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;The central iconostasis is the work of a group of woodcarvers who worked under the supervision of Atanas Teladour. They spent three years working on it, from 1839 to 1842, investing it with experience of several generations of carvers who founded the Bulgarian school of wood carving. The size and composition of the iconostasis are unrivaled in the Balkans. Same as architecture it follows the traditions of the school combining time-honoured element of space and as a unifying element emphasizing the centre of the basilica.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;The carving which covers it from end to end is somewhat different from the carving on other iconostases. Here everything is bigger to harmonize with the large space inside the church. The carving differs from filigree miniature and is more like sculpted rather than carved.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;The colours of this huge iconostasis are in harmony with the rich colours of the interior. In the dim church space frames by the painted walls, illuminated by the hundreds of candles burning in the candleholders, the iconostases’ gilded carved surfaces glitter and reflect upon the brightly coloured icons merging with the church space forming a complete artistic whole.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;The monastery which was visited by many people had to provide accommodation and amenitites to the pilgrims. Some Bulgarian towns had their own guest rooms offering accommodation only to their notables. The Koprivshtitsa, Chirpan, Gabrovo and Teteven rooms have been presented to this day. They are in the north wing which is like an ethnographic exposition.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;The monastery kitchen is on the ground floor of the same wing. The food for pilgrims was cooked there. The kitchen is large and has an overhead opening in the shape of the huge stone chimney which goes through all the levels to take smoke from the fire to the roof and out. It is in the shape of a hollow pyramid whose walls are built by octahedrons which grow smaller. The spaces between them have been filled up by semicircular arcs. The result is an ideally balanced self-supporting 22 meter high construction whose lightness and strength have been provided in the course of more than a century.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;The prints, graphic impressions upon copper plates of wood, were of special significance for the popularization of the monastery and the history of its founder. There were two common types: St Ioan of Rila with miniature scenes from his life, and the monastery itself with the main sketae and metochia along the rive Rilska. Those prints were available even to the poorer pilgrims and thus popularized the Rila Monastery across the Balkan lands, serving as books for the illiterate who could learn from them the legends about the monastery and St Ivan of Rila. Initially the monastic community commissioned the prints in Moscow or Vienna. However, as demand for such prints was growing during the 19&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; century, a monk Kalislearn the craft of print-making and in 1856 the monastery acquired a large iron press and opened its own workshop for the production of prints. The output of the latter was large. Nevertheless the prints that it turned out were not inferior and some even could view with art primitives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;The printing press that the monastery bought the 1860s from Vienna is also on display in the monastery museum. The repositories keep most of handmade copper printing plates and prints produced with them.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;The Rila Monastery museum collections trace its history over the countries and reveal its role in Bulgaria’s cultural history. In the course of the centuries the Rila Monastery maintained lively relations with the countries of the Eastern Orthodox world; the metochia that were scattered in all Balkan Peninsula lands with Bulgarian population did educational work; the monastery repository holds records, books, church plate, icons and gifts from pilgrims.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;The Rila Monastery History Museum possesses a rich collection of extremely valuable exhibits both in the exposition halls and in the monastery vaults. The exhibits are thematically grouped and trace the evolution of the monastery and its cultural, religious and nation-consolidation role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;The exposition includes the early historical and ecclesiastical collection of the monastery, some books of the monastery library and many copies of wall paintings that have been destroyed, icons, prints, vestments and church plate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;In 1980 the International Federation of Travel Writers and Journalists (FIJEST) distinguished the Monastery with Golden Apple, the highest award for familiarization and cultural tourism. Ion 1983 the Rila Monastery was recorded on &lt;a href="http://whc.unesco.org/pg.cfm?cid=31&amp;amp;id_site=216" target="_blank"&gt;the List of World Cultural Heritage&lt;/a&gt; as a world cultural value. Again at that time it got the status of a national museum, so the government started subsiding the museum collections, conservation and restoration of the wall paintings and the architectural heritage. A decree of the Council of Ministries of the Republic of Bulgaria reinstated the monastic status of the Rila Monastery in 1991, so today it is again the largest religious centre in the Bulgarian lands.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/fieldset&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;fieldset&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;div align="left"&gt;&lt;span class="title1"&gt;&lt;b&gt;St. Ivan Rilsky&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;hr align="justify" class="style5" /&gt;
&lt;table width="100" border="0" align="right" cellspacing="5"&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;th scope="col"&gt;&lt;span class="Style4"&gt;&lt;a href="https://s3.amazonaws.com/gs-geo-images/e0eda3f4-c03f-4d9c-806d-962b5254b2f8.jpg" rel="lightbox[roadtrip]" title="St. Ivan Rilsky. Icon from Rila Monastery."&gt;&lt;img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/gs-geo-images/e0eda3f4-c03f-4d9c-806d-962b5254b2f8.jpg" alt width="170" height="252" border="2" align="right" class="style_pic1" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td class="title_pic"&gt;
&lt;div align="left"&gt;St. Ivan Rilsky. Icon from Rila Monastery.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;The greatest saint on Bulgarian land ever, revered Ivan Rilsky was born around 876 in Skrino, hidden in the Osogovska Mountain near river Struma (near Dupnitsa). He was a contemporary of kniaz Boris (852-889) and of his son Vladimir, Tsar Simeon the Great and Simeon's son Tsar Petar. Till his 25-year-age he was a shepherd. In this fragile age in the soul of Ivan began to grow and develop his religious faith. At those times there were building churches and monasteries around the whole Bulgaria.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div align="left"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;The new monasteries became not just centres of the Christianity but literary and educating centres. The desire of the young man was to devote himself to God. He wished to go a monastery and became a monk. Firstly Ivan went to the close monastery 'Saint Dimitrii' under mount Ruen. There he didn't just develop his talent in the religious meditation, but educated and studied many of sacred, liturgical and religious books. He accepted the title monk but didn't stay for too long in the monastery and devoted his life to an absolute loneliness, prayers, fasts and destitute.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;Revered Ivan Rilsky lived in many places, until at last he settled down in the gorgeous Rila Mountain, where he stayed to the end of his life. There he has founded a monastery, which has survived more than a thousand years till nowadays. He made many miracles during his lifetime and after his death: he fed shepherds, cured with his pray a madman, healed and still healing from different sicknesses many pious people and being defending the monastery with his noble power.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;table width="100" border="0" align="right" cellspacing="5"&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;th scope="col"&gt;&lt;span class="Style4"&gt;&lt;a href="https://s3.amazonaws.com/gs-geo-images/3ace5819-6e84-4c1e-ab7f-6bad04636165.jpg" rel="lightbox[roadtrip]" title="St. Ivan of Rila and king Peter I."&gt;&lt;img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/gs-geo-images/3ace5819-6e84-4c1e-ab7f-6bad04636165.jpg" alt width="250" height="167" border="2" align="right" class="style_pic1" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td class="title_pic"&gt;
&lt;div align="left"&gt;St. Ivan of Rila and king Peter I.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;The fame of the hermit spreaded soon among the Bulgarian people and reached the capital. While traveling to Sofia, Tsar Petar the I-st, made a 120 km detour to see the pious old man. Ivan Rilsky however didn't allow Tsar Petar to come close to him but just bowed to the ruler from far and so did Tsar Petar. The recluse, of course, returned the sent gold as a gift from Tsar Petar. That action increased even more Ivan Rilsky's glory and many students joined him, who built huts for them. That was the beginning of the most famous Bulgarian monastery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;Before his death revered Ivan went in full privacy and made his 'legacy'. He holidayed on 18 august 946 at almost 70-year age and was buried in the narthex of a little church in a stone tomb. The stone tomb still exists. His assumption the Church celebrates each year on the same date.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="Style4_1" style="text-align:justify;text-indent:35.4pt;"&gt;The revered Ivan Rilsky is declared for and exceptional celestial sentinel of the Bulgarian nation and is being held in respect from all Bulgarian people.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/fieldset&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>
In the hole. Under the stones.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1362796377"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-08T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1985609">Archi1</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Expedice Balkan_2026, den sedmí.
Na tento výlet jsme se vydali společně s Mikkisek, Mikrp, Nalim26 a Dandos1. Byl to náš dlouho plánovaný druhý balkánský výlet, tentokrát do severnějších států. Navštívili jsme Slovensko, Maďarsko, Rumunsko, Moldavsko, Bulharsko, Řecko, Srbsko, Maďarsko a Slovensko. Byl to úžasný výlet plný zážitků, kešek a dokonce i koupání v moři. Je to osvědčený tým z několika předchozích akcí. Je to pohodový, vyrovnaný a spolupracující tým, jak při lovu kešek, tak i při dalších aktivitách. Ráno po snídani a nákupu zásob v Karváli se vydáváme směr Sofie. Trasa je naplánovaná se zastávkou na nejstarší bulharské keši a taky prohlídkou Rilského kláštera. Dnes nám poprvé od začátku cesty, už se pohybujeme v Bulharsku prší. V podvečer přijíždíme do cíle dnešní cesty, kde už jsme očekáváni. Večer pak posedíme v místní restauraci. Cestou máme vytipované kešky, které chceme určitě najít. Nebránili jsme se, nicméně cestou ani jiným keškám, které nám přišly do cesty, no a tahle byla právě jedna z vyvolených. Na místě uložení to byl pohodový a celkem rychlý odlov. Krabičce přejeme dlouhý život, stále dobrou kondici a majiteli málo práce s údržbou. Dekuji ownerovi za zpestření trasy, zábavu, za info a za kešku i za a další bodík do sbírky a statistik. Našli jsme ji v pořádku a zůstala tak i po našem odchodu. Zdravíme z Česka,
Eng
Expedition Balkan_2026, day seven.
We went on this trip together with Mikkisek, Mikrp, Nalim26 and Dandos1. It was our long-planned second Balkan trip, this time to the northern states. We visited Slovakia, Hungary, Romania, Moldova, Bulgaria, Greece, Serbia, Hungary and Slovakia. It was an amazing trip full of experiences, caches and even swimming in the sea. It is a proven team from several previous events. It is a relaxed, balanced and cooperative team, both when hunting for caches and during other activities. In the morning, after breakfast and buying supplies in Karval, we set off towards Sofia. The route is planned with a stop at the oldest Bulgarian cache and also a tour of the Rila Monastery. Today, for the first time since the beginning of the trip, we are already moving in Bulgaria, it is raining. In the early evening we arrive at the destination of today's trip, where we are already expected. In the evening, we will sit in a local restaurant. We have selected caches along the way that we definitely want to find. However, we did not resist other caches that came our way along the way, and this one was one of the chosen ones. At the place where it was stored, it was a relaxed and fairly quick catch. We wish the box a long life, continued good condition and the owner little work with maintenance. I thank the owner for diversifying the route, entertainment, for the info and for the cache and for another point in the collection and statistics. We found it in order and it remained that way even after we left. Greetings from the Czech Republic,</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360402436"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-08T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1683344">dandos1</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Expedice Balkán 2026, den 7.
Spolu s Archi1, nalim26, Mikkisek a Mikrp.

Po ranním nákupu pečiva, oliv a olejů vyrážíme směr Sofie, se zastávkou na nejstarší  bulharské keši, při té příležitosti si prohlédnene kapli Ivana Rilského a přilehlý klášter. Dnes nám poprvé od začátku cesty prší. Děkuji za zábavu, poznání a kešku.


Балканска експедиция 2026, ден 7.
С Archi1, nalim26, Mikkisek и Mikrp.

След сутрешното пазаруване на сладкиши, маслини и олио, тръгнахме към София, със спирка при най-стария български кеш, по време на който посетихме параклиса на Иван Рилски и съседния манастир. Днес за първи път от началото на пътуването вали. Благодаря ви за забавлението, знанията и кеша.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360065691"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-08T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="22373154">mikrp</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Nalezeno v rámci geotripu s *Archi1*, *Nalim26*, *dandos1* a *Mikkisek* po Maďarsku, Rumunsku, Moldavsku, Bulharsku, Řecku a Srbsku. Díky za keš a dalšího usmívajícího smajlíka na mapě. 🇹🇯 🇦🇩 🇲🇩 🇧🇬 🇬🇷 
Found it during our geotrip with  *Archi1*, *Nalim26*, *dandos1* and *Mikkisek* throught Hungary, Romania, Moldova, Bulgaria, Greece and Serbia. Q Thank you for the cache and another happy smile on our map.  🇹🇯 🇦🇩 🇲🇩 🇧🇬 🇬🇷 
Many greetings from Czech Republic! 🇨🇿</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1358359513"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5603627">womochri</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This is the eleventh day of the Balkan caching tour for cachesurfer2011 and womochri.
We started this morning with a nice event in Sofia. Afterwards we visited the Rila Monastery and this very old cache. I enjoyed the hike to this cache and the great environment.
This cache deserves a favorite point!
2 TBs in. 0 TBs out.

Danke für das Herlocken und den Geocache! - 🇬🇧 Thanks for the cache (English) - 🇮🇹 Grazie per questo cache (say) – 🇮🇪 Go raibh maith agat as an taisce (Gaeilge) - 🇭🇺 Köszönöm a geoláda (Magyar) - 🇸🇰 Ďakujem za kešku (Slovensky) - 🇨🇿 Díky za keš Čeština) - 🇭🇷 Hvala cache (Hrvatski) - 🇫🇷 Merci pour la cache (Français) - 🇵🇱 Dzięki za kesza (Polski) - 🇪🇸 Gracias por el cache (Español) – 🇵🇹 Obrigado por isso cache (ar ) – 🇳🇱 Bedankt voor de cache (Nederlands) - 🇸🇪 Tack för att cache (Svenska) – 🇳🇴 Takk for at cache (Norsk) - 🇮🇸 Takk fyrir skyndiminnið (Íslenska) - 🇹🇷 Önbellek için teşekkürler (Türkçe) - 🇷🇺 Спасибо за кеш (рус.) - 🇨🇳 感谢您的缓存 (中文) - 🇯🇵 キャッシュありがとうございます (日本語)</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1358353982"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4516421">cachesurfer2011</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">TB in</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="-14.31963" lon="-170.71703"><time>2012-04-24T00:00:00</time><name>GC3GKDW</name><desc>On My Honor by jinkrwna</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC3GKDW</url><urlname>On My Honor</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="2854788" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>On My Honor</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>jinkrwna</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="5221672">jinkrwna</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="0">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="53" inc="1">Park and grab</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>American Samoa</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>&lt;b&gt;OFFICE IS OPEN M-F 9:00 to 3:00&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
This cache is in honor of a fantastic world-wide youth organization. The cache is a great place for Travel Bugs and to trade patches and memorabilia.
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;img alt src="http://img.geocaching.com/user/35eced4e-2ebe-43c1-9891-da45803ece3a.jpg?rnd=0.8019328" style="width:640px;height:478px;" /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
American Samoa Boy Scout Office, Aloha Council, BSA&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
As of this listing, there are four Geocaches in American Samoa... they are rarely visited and most have disappeared. This cache is in a secure location, and will be maintained regularly. It is also a great place for swapping out Travel Bugs. Most of the cachers that visit American Samoa do so on a visiting cruise ship... to all of you, this cache is simple and easy to find. Just follow the listed coordinates and you will be guaranteed a FIND in the small island country of American Samoa.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Office hours of the Scout shop is M-F 9:00 to 3:00. If you visit this cache after hours, simply upload a photo of yourself in front of the Scout Office Sign (above) and you can count this as FOUND.
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>READ THE DESCRIPTION</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1151334294"><groundspeak:date>2023-02-28T06:18:53</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="115500">Crow T Robot</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This listing was edited after publication to allow "photologging". This listing is being archived to prevent additional cheating by players logging finds on a missing container.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1150778078"><groundspeak:date>2023-02-25T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2758778">RetiredGuy</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">There hasn't been a legitimate find of the physical container since 2017. The cache description allow you to claim the cache by having your picture taken in front of the Boy Scouts sign, but that is no longer there having disappeared in 2020. I have made three unsuccessful attempts at contacting the cache owner but he has not logged in since 2018.

Since the cache was inside the American Samoa Boy Scout headquarters, I have contacted the Billy Rayl (Billy.Rayl@scouting.org), Field Director of the Aloha Council which American Samoa is part of.  He confirmed, "We no longer have a BSA office in American Samoa since the LDS departure.  It is our hope that we can one day reorganize Scouting there."

In conclusion, the physical cache, the building, the CO, and the sign are all now gone. Time to archive this one.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1150778085"><groundspeak:date>2023-02-25T06:48:38</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Needs Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2758778">RetiredGuy</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This geocacher reported that this geocache should be archived. A community volunteer reviewer has been notified.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1156392047"><groundspeak:date>2023-02-13T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8506681">Riba14</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Eigentlich schade, dass dieser so nicht mehr besucht werden kann wie angedacht. Wir haben aber unseren Aufenthalt hier genossen in der Kreuzfahrt Truppe mi bi52, Woisträßler und SteLaSyXL.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1154386608"><groundspeak:date>2023-02-13T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6535652">SteLaSyXL</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Eigentlich schade, dass dieser so nicht mehr besucht werden kann wie angedacht. Wir haben aber unseren Aufenthalt hier genossen in der Kreuzfahrt Truppe mi bi52, Woisträßler und Riba14.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="43.732533" lon="7.423367"><time>2009-08-25T00:00:00</time><name>GC1XQQ2</name><desc>Grand Prix de MONACO - La Rascasse by Juan Manuel Fang.</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC1XQQ2</url><urlname>Grand Prix de MONACO - La Rascasse</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="1369367" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Grand Prix de MONACO - La Rascasse</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Juan Manuel Fang.</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="1199579">tontonlou</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Micro</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="42" inc="1">Needs maintenance</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="1">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="14" inc="1">Recommended at night</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="40" inc="1">Stealth required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="33" inc="1">Motorcycles</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>3</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>Monaco</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>None</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;div style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:1px 10px;border-radius:15px;text-align:center;background:none 0% 50% repeat scroll rgb(255, 255, 150);box-shadow:10px 10px 10px #888822;"&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:20px;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#0000FF;"&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Depasser, encore un virage, et puis c'est l'arrivée,&lt;br /&gt;
une derniere acceleration, le drapeau s'abaisse.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color:#A9A9A9;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:10px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:12px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://d1u1p2xjjiahg3.cloudfront.net/36cc0e15-6a48-4821-8b76-729fe06b56b7.jpg" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;img alt src="https://d1u1p2xjjiahg3.cloudfront.net/36cc0e15-6a48-4821-8b76-729fe06b56b7.jpg" style="border-radius:15px;border:2px solid rgb(255, 0, 255);box-shadow:10px 10px 10px #888822;height:183px;width:550px;" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://d1u1p2xjjiahg3.cloudfront.net/36cc0e15-6a48-4821-8b76-729fe06b56b7.jpg" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#A9A9A9;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:10px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:1px 10px;border-radius:15px;text-align:center;background:none 0% 50% repeat scroll rgb(255, 255, 150);box-shadow:10px 10px 10px #888822;"&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align:justify;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://d1u1p2xjjiahg3.cloudfront.net/36cc0e15-6a48-4821-8b76-729fe06b56b7.jpg" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"&gt;Le Grand Prix de Monaco est une des plus anciennes et prestigieuses courses automobiles, disputée en Principauté de Monaco, sur un circuit urbain conçu en 1929, par Antony Noghes fils du président de l'Automobile Club de Monaco, sous les auspices du Prince Louis II de Monaco.&lt;br /&gt;
Cette création répondait au défi d'organiser une compétition sur le territoire exigu de Monaco (environ 1,5 km² à l'époque), condition requise par la Commission Sportive Internationale pour que l'Automobile Club de Monaco soit reconnu internationalement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align:justify;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://d1u1p2xjjiahg3.cloudfront.net/36cc0e15-6a48-4821-8b76-729fe06b56b7.jpg" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"&gt;En effet, l'autre grande compétition monégasque, le rallye automobile Monte-Carlo, créé dès 1911, était disputé sur les routes de nombreux pays d'Europe.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://d1u1p2xjjiahg3.cloudfront.net/36cc0e15-6a48-4821-8b76-729fe06b56b7.jpg" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#A9A9A9;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:10px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:1px 10px;border-radius:15px;text-align:center;background:none 0% 50% repeat scroll rgb(255, 255, 150);box-shadow:10px 10px 10px #888822;"&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align:justify;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://d1u1p2xjjiahg3.cloudfront.net/36cc0e15-6a48-4821-8b76-729fe06b56b7.jpg" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"&gt;Le Grand Prix de Monaco est organisé par l'Automobile Club de Monaco fondé sous le nom de Sport Vélocipédique de Monaco en 1890, qui organise également le rallye automobile Monte-Carlo.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://d1u1p2xjjiahg3.cloudfront.net/36cc0e15-6a48-4821-8b76-729fe06b56b7.jpg" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#A9A9A9;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:10px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div style="z-index:0;position:relative;left:200px;width:250px;border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:1px 10px;border-radius:15px;text-align:center;background:none 0% 50% repeat scroll rgb(255, 255, 150);box-shadow:10px 10px 10px #888822;"&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#0000FF;"&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:22px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Juan Manuel Fangio&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://d1u1p2xjjiahg3.cloudfront.net/98c6452c-b172-4921-828b-5e36dbaa371a.jpg" target="_blank" style="color:rgb(7, 130, 193);font-family:sans-serif, Arial, Verdana, 'Trebuchet MS';font-size:13px;line-height:20.8px;text-align:center;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 150);"&gt;&lt;img alt src="https://d1u1p2xjjiahg3.cloudfront.net/98c6452c-b172-4921-828b-5e36dbaa371a.jpg" style="border:none;cursor:default;height:350px;margin:1px;outline:rgb(7, 130, 193) solid 1px;padding:1px;width:233px;" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#0000FF;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:22px;"&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2 victoires à Monaco&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style="color:#0000FF;font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:22px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1950 - 1957&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#A9A9A9;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:10px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div style="border:1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);padding:1px 10px;border-radius:15px;text-align:center;background:none 0% 50% repeat scroll rgb(255, 255, 150);box-shadow:10px 10px 10px #888822;"&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:20px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="color:#FF0000;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"&gt;Vous cherchez une MicroCache.&lt;br /&gt;
Bonne Chance.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
