&lt;big style="font-family: Times New Roman;"&gt;&lt;big&gt;&lt;big&gt;&lt;big&gt;&lt;small&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;/small&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/big&gt;&lt;/big&gt;&lt;/big&gt;&lt;/big&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>No hints</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1341678268"><groundspeak:date>2026-01-12T19:57:33</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="29102498">cianfrusaglie76</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Quanto abbiamo sudato per arrivare fin qui....
Ma una rinfrescata sotto la cascata non ce l'ha tolta nessuno a me e M!!! 
Un altro posto meraviglioso in questa meravigliosa Cambogia!!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1338524699"><groundspeak:date>2025-12-21T10:22:28</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="31280778">Thelemaren</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I took a guided tour to the waterfall. It was a lovely day out.
Tftc</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1339777417"><groundspeak:date>2025-12-05T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="184678">Boa</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Today I'm going back to Kulen National Park. The waterfall I was looking for for Cambodia's oldest geocache turned out to be different from the one we visited yesterday. This time I'm going by private car. 

The waterfall I'm visiting now is much quieter. A handful of other tourists, mainly from Cambodia itself, and also the usual leaf sweepers and guards who are waiting everywhere at important sites, or in this case, in a hammock in the jungle.

It's about a kilometer and a half through the jungle, gently ascending, sometimes clambering over rocks. At the top of the walk, there are also sculptures in the river. This time, not only fertility symbols but also beautiful statues of Shiva and Vishnu.

At the waterfall, I make new friends with a Cambodian family who have come from the north and are taking a bath in the waterfall. After that, I'll go look for the crocodile I need for the geocache. This turns out to be harder to find than I thought, but with some help from the local guides, who don't speak a word of English but do understand Pictionary, I find my goal.

Thanks for showing this place
Greetings Boa</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1341637197"><groundspeak:date>2025-11-23T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="883343">p-boro</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">After a visit to Kulen waterfall, which was really busy, we decided to come to this more remote part of the National Park. The walk through the jungle was quite an experience. Hadn't expected so many reliefs in the river. A very interesting site indeed. Thanks for creating this earth cache. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1335240204"><groundspeak:date>2025-11-19T23:54:52</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6547459">UteMolly</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">With a group of geocachers we made a tour in the southeast of Asia. 
We travel in Thailand, Vietnam, Cambodia, Laos, Malaysia, Singapur and Indonesia.
A lot of interesting places and informations we got on this trip. And a lot of geocaches we done together. To protect the logbook we logged as group CR-Asia-1-25
Our group is:

btjg, cmpcrzy, Geo-Igel, Haarteppichknüpfer, HungerCat, Iliona, Jowo2003, Königsblauen , L.E.Saxon, Lichtenberger, Luna49, Marc27, mao_gc, MurmelschnK, Muschel3, Myfiorina, Nocybe1810, Schmaal166, TeamAMW, TeamMehl, TMzH,UteMolly, Viko76, Virtualboy, VoBe1994, Wühlhase, Foxi23.

Thank you for all owners for their work.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="43.91206666666667" lon="18.420416666666668"><time>2010-08-07T12:22:00</time><name>GLJVHV</name><cmt>Go left and continue up hill.</cmt><desc>Go Left</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=f4c00edd-349c-4c3d-befc-11991996cf21</url><urlname>Go Left</urlname><sym>Reference Point</sym><type>Waypoint|Reference Point</type></wpt><wpt lat="43.910617" lon="18.416333"><time>2010-08-07T12:19:04</time><name>LHJVHV</name><cmt>Go up hill; keep Loviste Hut on your left.</cmt><desc>Loviste Hut</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=4e3948e9-11f3-4ee4-ae47-40ea571b7b79</url><urlname>Loviste Hut</urlname><sym>Reference Point</sym><type>Waypoint|Reference Point</type></wpt><wpt lat="43.910333333333334" lon="18.416516666666666"><time>2010-08-07T12:17:46</time><name>RSJVHV</name><cmt>Right to Big Rock cache; left to Little Rock Rocks and Bukovoic #</cmt><desc>Route Split</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=384544ed-b4cf-4039-b1a5-a08db06e20ec</url><urlname>Route Split</urlname><sym>Reference Point</sym><type>Waypoint|Reference Point</type></wpt><wpt lat="43.91075" lon="18.417516666666668"><time>2010-08-07T12:20:54</time><name>SGJVHV</name><cmt>Bear right keeping on the main trail.</cmt><desc>Straight as You Go</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=ea8022b3-bdde-49fb-9896-fa01733ac5b3</url><urlname>Straight as You Go</urlname><sym>Reference Point</sym><type>Waypoint|Reference Point</type></wpt><wpt lat="43.91518333333333" lon="18.421566666666667"><time>2010-08-07T12:23:23</time><name>SLJVHV</name><cmt>Make a sharp left and go up hill; trail begins to fade.</cmt><desc>Sharp left</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=546530f1-56b7-4ee1-96e7-5f5bbb6efade</url><urlname>Sharp left</urlname><sym>Reference Point</sym><type>Waypoint|Reference Point</type></wpt><wpt lat="43.9103" lon="18.413383333333332"><time>2010-08-07T12:16:22</time><name>WUJVHV</name><cmt>Bear left up hill on main road.</cmt><desc>Way Up</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=720956cc-ca1a-481c-b28f-513674cf5e6b</url><urlname>Way Up</urlname><sym>Reference Point</sym><type>Waypoint|Reference Point</type></wpt><wpt lat="-24.26785" lon="-48.40958333333333"><time>2016-09-15T12:15:33</time><name>PKC67</name><cmt /><desc>GCC67 Parking</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=1681cbd6-73b6-4bf4-b240-ca075c370add</url><urlname>GCC67 Parking</urlname><sym>Parking Area</sym><type>Waypoint|Parking Area</type></wpt><wpt lat="-24.26795" lon="-48.4096"><time>2016-09-15T12:16:20</time><name>S1C67</name><cmt>This waypoint marks the beginning of Mirante Trail / APE cache Trail</cmt><desc>Trail</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=f02490b5-45b0-42b5-9322-1ac8984aea42</url><urlname>Trail</urlname><sym>Reference Point</sym><type>Waypoint|Reference Point</type></wpt><wpt lat="-24.2704" lon="-48.406133"><time>2016-09-15T12:12:30</time><name>S2C67</name><cmt>This waypoint marks the intersection at which you should leave the Mirante Trail for the APE cache Trail.</cmt><desc>Intersection of Mirante Trail and APE cache Trail</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=dade5571-6083-49e6-ae9e-d691b61d202e</url><urlname>Intersection of Mirante Trail and APE cache Trail</urlname><sym>Reference Point</sym><type>Waypoint|Reference Point</type></wpt><wpt lat="55.755417" lon="12.438"><time>2018-08-05T12:39:16</time><name>016A</name><cmt>Park here and walk the rest of the way.</cmt><desc>Parking</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=935517a2-87e6-406f-9580-c82d5cb1efa5</url><urlname>Parking</urlname><sym>Parking Area</sym><type>Waypoint|Parking Area</type></wpt><wpt lat="58.016" lon="25.880055555555558"><time>2009-02-04T00:02:26</time><name>01263</name><cmt>Parkige oma auto lihtsalt näiteks 58° 00'57.6'' ja 25° 52'48.2'', jalutage veidi kenas looduses ja peaksitegi varsti leidma.</cmt><desc>Car parking</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=cbfd7d40-39ce-4761-a8f0-4172df0e0546</url><urlname>Car parking</urlname><sym>Parking Area</sym><type>Waypoint|Parking Area</type></wpt><wpt lat="53.193033" lon="-6.087717"><time>2023-01-05T06:32:11</time><name>0143</name><cmt>Most direct route however trail may be encroached by gorse in the summer months. Left here and follow the trail until next Trailnead 2, or continue straight on the De Buitléar Way (Slí De Buitléar) up towards Bray Head and cut across to cache</cmt><desc>Trailhead 1</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=cc3902ce-b555-4025-8bf1-b21bd69c968f</url><urlname>Trailhead 1</urlname><sym>Trailhead</sym><type>Waypoint|Trailhead</type></wpt><wpt lat="53.193283" lon="-6.08705"><time>2023-07-01T14:13:17</time><name>0243</name><cmt>Follow trail uphill towards GZ</cmt><desc>Trailhead 2</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=be5c5d60-95f2-476a-84ca-22f3551a59b2</url><urlname>Trailhead 2</urlname><sym>Trailhead</sym><type>Waypoint|Trailhead</type></wpt><wpt lat="53.1919833333333" lon="-6.0843"><time>2024-10-14T02:10:29</time><name>0343</name><cmt>Near GZ, approach from here.</cmt><desc>Way In</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=919ee241-5709-4487-b2a5-9703eda1e71f</url><urlname>Way In</urlname><sym>Trailhead</sym><type>Waypoint|Trailhead</type></wpt><wpt lat="53.19128333333333" lon="-6.080066666666666"><time>2014-03-30T13:45:40</time><name>OR43</name><cmt /><desc>Original Site</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=a60f808c-ba65-46c0-8807-d0a81f0bf763</url><urlname>Original Site</urlname><sym>Reference Point</sym><type>Waypoint|Reference Point</type></wpt><wpt lat="53.195117" lon="-6.089"><time>2009-10-17T08:07:27</time><name>P143</name><cmt>Parking with 2m Height Restriction</cmt><desc>Parking (2m Height Restriction)</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=697b1cee-41be-4372-9f8d-6713fef0ae3d</url><urlname>Parking (2m Height Restriction)</urlname><sym>Parking Area</sym><type>Waypoint|Parking Area</type></wpt><wpt lat="53.1972" lon="-6.09375"><time>2016-08-23T04:51:40</time><name>P243</name><cmt>Parking with no Height Restriction</cmt><desc>Parking (No Height Restriction)</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=44ef8a67-d678-43bd-9f78-2506c735d5f2</url><urlname>Parking (No Height Restriction)</urlname><sym>Parking Area</sym><type>Waypoint|Parking Area</type></wpt><wpt lat="46.519367" lon="11.360417"><time>2023-10-29T14:32:10</time><name>0117B3</name><cmt /><desc>Parking</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=17949db5-aa6b-4cdc-8aad-ecc99e801fea</url><urlname>Parking</urlname><sym>Parking Area</sym><type>Waypoint|Parking Area</type></wpt><wpt lat="20.3253" lon="100.0979"><time>2024-01-15T10:53:40</time><name>01B8F7</name><cmt>Near this waypoint you will find at least two different vendors selling 'snake medicine".</cmt><desc>Market</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=f6b09abf-8e8a-480f-a27c-2532e5a8f832</url><urlname>Market</urlname><sym>Virtual Stage</sym><type>Waypoint|Virtual Stage</type></wpt><wpt lat="25.786083333333334" lon="10.575166666666666"><time>2008-01-14T13:52:34</time><name>0118KWH</name><cmt /><desc>Awaynat</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=9301dd4e-e525-437b-98f7-2196872b89d4</url><urlname>Awaynat</urlname><sym>Trailhead</sym><type>Waypoint|Trailhead</type></wpt><wpt lat="42.39576666666667" lon="18.763633333333335"><time>2011-06-03T09:05:39</time><name>011095F</name><cmt /><desc>Parking</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=00636dd4-60fc-415b-b719-aa67071b88d5</url><urlname>Parking</urlname><sym>Parking Area</sym><type>Waypoint|Parking Area</type></wpt><wpt lat="-29.022033333333333" lon="167.97118333333333"><time>2007-06-03T03:47:09</time><name>CPE80C</name><cmt /><desc>CASC1</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=c856bf0f-b62c-4200-9842-7a76ab8e6044</url><urlname>CASC1</urlname><sym>Parking Area</sym><type>Waypoint|Parking Area</type></wpt><wpt lat="60.3285" lon="5.292833"><time>2006-02-12T07:34:29</time><name>B1BBF</name><cmt>Get off the bus 15 at this location. Bus 15 goes via Fjøsanger or Fyllingsdalen. Both of them are well suited for this stop. If coming from Minde, bus 25 also goes here. From the bus stop, you may aim for the parking lot.</cmt><desc>Bus stop nearby</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=76bc2ec3-30fd-4dba-9f94-4621d2d2e8b4</url><urlname>Bus stop nearby</urlname><sym>Trailhead</sym><type>Waypoint|Trailhead</type></wpt><wpt lat="60.3322" lon="5.294867"><time>2008-09-03T07:23:07</time><name>CPBBF</name><cmt>This parking lot usually has some space. From the parking, go north between the buildings. Follow the northern building to the playground, and then go left. Start searching for step 1, which is the original cache position. :-)</cmt><desc>Parking</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=9182d22e-27f4-41f6-9a48-3671b38e2f67</url><urlname>Parking</urlname><sym>Parking Area</sym><type>Waypoint|Parking Area</type></wpt><wpt lat="24.595566666666667" lon="56.018433333333334"><time>2011-03-16T09:18:56</time><name>PK1B56</name><cmt>Old terraces at the start of the wadi ideal for overnight camping out of sight of the main road.</cmt><desc>Great camping spot reachable by 4x4</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=96cb3454-6734-4374-9b64-82fe1ac92ffb</url><urlname>Great camping spot reachable by 4x4</urlname><sym>Parking Area</sym><type>Waypoint|Parking Area</type></wpt><wpt lat="24.605716666666666" lon="56.029266666666665"><time>2011-03-16T09:25:00</time><name>TO1B56</name><cmt>Turn-off from the Hatta - Mahdah road onto a dirt track leading to the parking area / camping spot.</cmt><desc>Turn-off from the main road</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=c88b212